Parameter Description:
UE mobility group selection criteria.

Defines selection criteria that UE needs to fulfill to belong to UE mobility group instance.

If selection criteria evaluates to True, UE fulfills UE mobility group instance.

If selection criteria evaluates to False or Unknown, UE does not fulfill UE mobility group instance.

If selection criteria evaluates to True for more than one UE mobility group instance, UE belongs to UE mobility group instance with highest setting of ueMobilityGroupPriority.

Syntax:
======
The syntax of selection criteria is defined using Backus-Naur form.

<SelectionCriteria> ::= <ParentExpressionList> | ""
<ParentExpressionList> ::= <ParentExpressionList> <AndOr> < ParentExpressionList> | <Not>? "(" <ParentExpressionList> ")" | <ExpressionList> | <FlowExpressionList>
<FlowExpressionList> ::= <FlowExpressionList> <AndOr> <FlowExpressionList> | <Not>? <FlowExpression>
<FlowExpression> ::= "["<ExpressionList>"]"
<ExpressionList> ::= <ExpressionList> <AndOr> <ExpressionList> | <Not>? "(" <ExpressionList> ")" | <Not>? <VariableExpression>
<VariableExpression> ::= <Variable> <RelationalOperator> <Value> | <Variable> "==" "{" <ValueList> "}"
<ValueList> ::= <Value> "," <ValueList> | <Value>

<Variable> ::= "5qi" | "arp" | "cgrole" | "chipset" | "imeisv" | "imeisvn" | "imeitac" | "plmn" | "qci" | "redcapue" | "rfsp" | "rrcEstResCause" | "snssai" | "spid"

<AndOr> ::= "&&" | "||"
<Not> ::= "!"

<RelationalOperator> ::= "==" | "!=" | "<" | "<=" | ">=" | ">"

A list of possible values can be specified in the form <Variable> == {<value1>, <value2>, ... , <valueN>}. This statement is equivalent to writing (<Variable> == <value1> || <Variable> == <value2> || ... || <Variable> == <valueN>).

Up to 4 <FlowExpression> can be defined in <SelectionCriteria>.

Whitespaces are allowed in the string for improved readability and are removed prior to evaluation.

Question mark (?) means zero or one occurrence. For example, <Not>? makes <Not> optional.

Syntax is case sensitive.

Semantic:
========
Selection criteria evaluation is defined by the following semantic rules.

If empty or set to empty string "", selection criteria always evaluates to True.

Selection criteria evaluation is done per UE with the current applicable UE <Variable> values as input. List of UE <Variable> values that are applicable to NR standalone and EN-DC, respectively, is defined in Variable Definitions section below.

Selection criteria for a UE is evaluated separately for each flow using applicable flow-dependent <Variable> together with rest of applicable UE <Variable>. For UE in NR standalone flow-dependent <Variable> 5qi, arp, and snssai are applicable. For UE in EN-DC flow-dependent <Variable> qci, and arp are applicable.

Selection criteria evaluates to True if any of the flows evaluates to True. If UE does not have a flow, flow-dependent <Variable> values are evaluated as unknown variable values. If selection criteria shall match combination of flow-dependent <Variable>, then <FlowExpression> and <FlowExpressionList> must be used.
Note: An <ExpressionList> defined as <VariableExpression> && <VariableExpression>, for which both <VariableExpression> relate to flow-dependent <Variable>, needs special attention.

Example: <ExpressionList> = "5qi==5 && 5qi==9" always evaluate to False for UE in NR standalone even if UE has one flow with 5qi=5 and one flow with 5qi=9.

Example: <ExpressionList> = "5qi>=7 && 5qi<=11" will evaluate to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi between 7 and 11.

<FlowExpression> is defined as "["<ExpressionList>"]" and indicates that an <ExpressionList> is evaluated per QoS flow independent of other <ExpressionList>.

Example: <FlowExpressionList> = "[5qi==1] && [5qi==5]" evaluates to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi=1 and any flow with 5qi=5. In the example, [5qi==1] must match one flow, and [5qi==5] must match one flow.

<VariableExpression> evaluates to Unknown if <Variable> is not known or if the <Variable> value is not valid.
<VariableExpression> evaluates to True or False if <Variable> value is known and valid.

<Value> "ref" is a special <Value> of <Variable> representing <ValueList> defined via corresponding reference attribute. For <Variable> chipset, and imeisv, corresponding reference attribute is chipsetRef, and imeiSvRef respectively.

If reference attribute is empty, represented <ValueList> is empty.

The logical operators <AndOr> and <Not> apply three way logic as defined below:

F=False; T=True; U=Unknown
A=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression>
B=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression>

NOT operator:
A !A
-----------------
F T
U U
T F

AND operator:
A B A && B
-------------------
F F F
F T F
F U F
T F F
T T T
T U U
U F F
U T U
U U U

OR operator:
A B A || B
------------------
F F F
F T T
F U U
T F T
T T T
T U T
U F U
U T T
U U U

Variable Definitions:
=================

Allowed <Value> and <RelationalOperator> depend on <Variable> with limitations given below.

5qi:
5G QoS Identifier (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: Integer in range 0..255 given in decimal.

arp:
Priority Level part of the Allocation and Retention Priority (3GPP TS 38.413, 3GPP TS 36.423). Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: Integer in range 1..15 given in decimal.

cgrole:
Cell group role. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: mcg or scg, where mcg is only applicable to NR standalone.

chipset:
Chipset identifier. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: String in format "<vendor>.<variant>.<version>" matched by regular expression "(1[0-6]|[0-9])\\.(6[0-4]|[1-5]?[0-9])\\.(12[0-8]|1[01][0-9]|[1-9]?[0-9])", or a string constant "ref".

Description: Chipset identifier composed of three distinct elements:
- vendor: 1-2 digit decimal number in range 0..16
- variant: 1-2 digit decimal number in range 0..64
- version: 1-3 digit decimal number in range 0..128

UEs that do not support chipset identifier reporting are represented internally as 0.0.0.

Example values: 0.0.0, 1.1.1, 1.2.3, 16.10.100, 16.64.128, ref.

imeisv:
International Mobile Station Equipment Identity Software Version. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: String in format "<TAC><SNR><SVN>" matched by regular expression "[0-9]{10}[0-9fF]{4}[0-9]{2}", or string constant "ref".

Description: IMEISV composed of three distinct elements:
- TAC (Type Allocation Code): 8 digit decimal number
- SNR (or SN, Serial Number): 2 digit decimal number + 4 digit hexa-decimal number, last four digits are automatically masked with 0xFFFF to match with masked IMEISV
- SVN (Software Version Number): 2 digit decimal number

Example values: 1234567890123456, 1234567890FFFF12, 1234567890ffff12, ref.

imeitac:
Type Allocation Code (TAC) part of imeisv. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: 8 digit decimal number.

imeisvn:
Software Version Number (SVN) part of imeisv. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: 2 digit decimal number.

plmn:
Public Land and Mobile Network identifier. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: A string matched by regular expression "[02-79][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9][0-9]?".

Example values: 070-007, 070-07, 234-56.

qci:
QoSClass Identifier (3GPP TS 23.401). Applicable to EN-DC.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: Integer in range 0..255 given in decimal.

redcapue:
Reduced Capabilities UE indicator. Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: Boolean
Description: RedCap UE identification received via LCID in MSG3 (see 3GPP TS 38.331).

rfsp:
Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal.

rrcEstResCause:
RRC establishment cause or RRC resume cause. Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: One of emergency, highPriorityAccess, mt-Access, mo-Signaling, mo-Data, mo-VoiceCall, mo-VideoCall, mo-SMS, mps-PriorityAccess, or mcs-PriorityAccess.
Description: Establishment cause value received in RRC Setup Request message or resume cause received
in RRC Resume Request message (see 3GPP TS 38.331).
The received establishment cause or resume cause is valid in UE grouping framework when performing UE group evaluation during time specified by corresponding validity time attribute value in MO class UeGroupSelection.

snssai:
Single Network Slice Selection Assistance Information (3GPP TS 23.003). Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: input option 1: String in format "<SST><SD>" matched by regular expression [0][x][0-9a-fA-F]{8} (8 digit hexa-decimal number).
Value: input option 2: Integer in range 0x0..0xffffffff given in hexadecimal.
Description: S-NSSAI is composed of two distinct elements:
- SST (Slice/Service Type): 2 digit hexa-decimal number
- SD (Slice Differentiator): 6 digit hexa-decimal number
The SD field has a reserved value "no SD value associated with the SST" defined as hexadecimal FFFFFF/ffffff.

Example values, input option 1:
- 0x050000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE)
- 0x2effffff (SST=0x2e,SD=0xffffff // no SD associated with the SST)

Example values, input option 2:
- 0x1 (SST=0x00,SD=0x000001)
- 0x50000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE)
- 0x150000EE (SST=0x15,SD=0x0000EE)

spid:
Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency Priority (3GPP TS 36.300). Applicable to EN-DC.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal.

Operator Precedence Order:
=======================
The logical and relation operators are evaluated according to the precedence order listed below.

---------------------------------------------
1 (highest precedence)
< Less than
<= Less than or equal
> Greater than
>= Greater than or equal
== Equal
!= Not equal
-------------------------------------------
2 ! (Not)
---------------------------------------------
3 && (And)
---------------------------------------------
4 (lowest precedence)
|| (Or)
---------------------------------------------

The NOT operator "!" negates the following <ParentExpressionList>, <VariableExpression>, <FlowExpression> or an <ExpressionList> encapsulated in parenthesis.
Therefore, expression !a==b && c==d is equivalent to ((!(a==b)) && (c==d)) and different from !(a==b && c==d).
Expression !a==b and !(a==b) are equivalent.

Since AND operator "&&" has higher precedence than OR operator "||", a<b || a<c && c<d is equivalent to (a<b || (a<c && c<d)). Surround expression list including OR operator with parenthesis to force OR operator to be evaluated before AND operators outside of the expression list, for example (a<b || a<c) && c<d.

Examples:
=========

Simple one valued expressions:
plmn == 234-56
spid == 1
cgrole == mcg
arp > 3
snssai == 0xfedcba98
rrcEstResCause == mo-VoiceCall
imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12

imeisv == ref //Special <value> ref represents <ValueList> defined via imeiSvRef.
chipset == ref
chipset == 1.1.1 //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1.
chipset == 0.0.0 //Matches all UEs that do not support chipset identifier reporting.

Value list expressions:
spid == {8,9,10,1,155}
!plmn == {234-56, 434-567}
chipset == {1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.1.3, ref} //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1, 2 or 3, or the corresponding vendor, variant and version defined via chipsetRef.
imeisv == {1234567890FFFF12, ref, 1234567890FFFF13} //Matches all UEs with imeisv: TAC = 12345678, SNR = 90FFFF and SVN = 12 or 13, or the corresponding TAC, SN and SVN defined via imeiSvRef.

Equivalent expressions using ||:
(spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) //Equals to spid == {8, 9, 10, 1, 155}.
!(plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567) //Equals to !plmn == {234-56, 434-567}.

imeisv == ref || imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12|| imeisv == 1234567890FFFF13 //Equals to imeisv == {ref, 1234567890FFFF12, 1234567890FFFF13}.
chipset == 1.1.1 || chipset == ref || chipset == 1.1.2 // Equals to chipset == {1.1.1, ref, 1.1.2}.

Negative expressions:
!5qi==1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.
5qi!=1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.

Negative <FlowExpressions> that produce same result:
[!5qi==1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.
[5qi!=1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.

<FlowExpressionList> negative expressions:
!([5qi==1]) //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1.
![5qi==1] //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1.

Mixed examples:
spid == 1 && cgrole == mcg
!(spid != 1 || cgrole != mcg)
(spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) && (plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567)

Precedence given by "()" and sequence alter the evaluation order and result:
[5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5] //Equals to ([5qi==1] && chipset==ref) || (imeisv==ref && [5qi==5])
[5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5]
([5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5]
[5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5])
chipset==ref || [5qi==1] && [5qi==5] && imeisv==ref

Examples of selection criteria that shall be avoided since they will always be evaluated to False. <FlowExpression> can be used in these cases.
5qi==5 && 5qi==9
snssai==0x15000000 && snssai==0x17000000
arp==5 && arp==10
qci==5 && qci==9

Example of selection criteria for UE variable snssai:
snssai>=15000000 && snssai<=15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 regardless of value of S-NSSAI SD part.
snssai==15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 and S-NSSAI SD part value equal to FFFFFF, meaning no SD value associated with the SST.

Flow expressions combined with UE variables:
plmn == 234-56 && [5qi==1] && [5qi==9] //Matches UE which has plmn equal to 234-56, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1, and any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9.
chipset==1.5.32 && [5qi==9] && ![5qi==1] //Matches UE which has chipset identifier equal to 1.5.32, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9, and no QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1.
[5qi==1 && snssai == 0xfedcba98] || ([5qi==2] && [snssai == 0xfedcba77]) //Matches UE which has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba98, or has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 2 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba77.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
UE service group selection criteria.

Defines selection criteria that UE needs to fulfill to belong to the UE service group instance.

If selection criteria evaluates to True, UE fulfills UE service group instance.

If selection criteria evaluates to False or Unknown, UE does not fulfill UE service group instance.

If selection criteria evaluates to True for more than one UE service group instance, UE belongs to the UE service group instance with highest setting of ueServiceGroupPriority.

Syntax:
======
The syntax of selection criteria is defined using Backus-Naur form.

<SelectionCriteria> ::= <ParentExpressionList> | ""
<ParentExpressionList> ::= <ParentExpressionList> <AndOr> < ParentExpressionList> | <Not>? "(" <ParentExpressionList> ")" | <ExpressionList> | <FlowExpressionList>
<FlowExpressionList> ::= <FlowExpressionList> <AndOr> <FlowExpressionList> | <Not>? <FlowExpression>
<FlowExpression> ::= "["<ExpressionList>"]"
<ExpressionList> ::= <ExpressionList> <AndOr> <ExpressionList> | <Not>? "(" <ExpressionList> ")" | <Not>? <VariableExpression>
<VariableExpression> ::= <Variable> <RelationalOperator> <Value> | <Variable> "==" "{" <ValueList> "}"
<ValueList> ::= <Value> "," <ValueList> | <Value>

<Variable> ::= "5qi" | "arp" | "cgrole" | "chipset" | "imeisv" | "imeisvn" | "imeitac" | "plmn" | "qci" | "redcapue" | "rfsp" | "rrcEstResCause" | "snssai" | "spid"

<AndOr> ::= "&&" | "||"
<Not> ::= "!"

<RelationalOperator> ::= "==" | "!=" | "<" | "<=" | ">=" | ">"

A list of possible values can be specified in the form <Variable> == {<value1>, <value2>, ... , <valueN>}. This statement is equivalent to writing (<Variable> == <value1> || <Variable> == <value2> || ... || <Variable> == <valueN>).

Up to 4 <FlowExpression> can be defined in <SelectionCriteria>.

Whitespaces are allowed in the string for improved readability and are removed prior to evaluation.

Question mark (?) means zero or one occurrence. For example, <Not>? makes <Not> optional.

Syntax is case sensitive.

Semantic:
========
Selection criteria evaluation is defined by the following semantic rules.

If empty or set to empty string "", selection criteria always evaluates to True.

Selection criteria evaluation is done per UE with the current applicable UE <Variable> values as input. List of UE <Variable> values that are applicable to NR standalone and EN-DC, respectively, is defined in Variable Definitions section below.

Selection criteria for a UE is evaluated separately for each flow using applicable flow-dependent <Variable> together with rest of applicable UE <Variable>. For UE in NR standalone flow-dependent <Variable> 5qi, arp, and snssai are applicable. For UE in EN-DC flow-dependent <Variable> qci, and arp are applicable.

Selection criteria evaluates to True if any of the flows evaluates to True. If UE does not have a flow, flow-dependent <Variable> values are evaluated as unknown variable values. If selection criteria shall match combination of flow-dependent <Variable>, then <FlowExpression> and <FlowExpressionList> must be used.
Note: An <ExpressionList> defined as <VariableExpression> && <VariableExpression>, for which both <VariableExpression> relate to flow-dependent <Variable>, needs special attention.

Example: <ExpressionList> = "5qi==5 && 5qi==9" always evaluate to False for UE in NR standalone even if UE has one flow with 5qi=5 and one flow with 5qi=9.

Example: <ExpressionList> = "5qi>=7 && 5qi<=11" will evaluate to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi between 7 and 11.

<FlowExpression> is defined as "["<ExpressionList>"]" and indicates that an <ExpressionList> is evaluated per QoS flow independent of other <ExpressionList>.

Example: <FlowExpressionList> = "[5qi==1] && [5qi==5]" evaluates to True for UE in NR standalone if UE has any flow with 5qi=1 and any flow with 5qi=5. In the example, [5qi==1] must match one flow, and [5qi==5] must match one flow.

<VariableExpression> evaluates to Unknown if <Variable> is not known or if the <Variable> value is not valid.
<VariableExpression> evaluates to True or False if <Variable> value is known and valid.

<Value> "ref" is a special <Value> of <Variable> representing <ValueList> defined via corresponding reference attribute. For <Variable> chipset, and imeisv, corresponding reference attribute is chipsetRef, and imeiSvRef respectively.

If reference attribute is empty, represented <ValueList> is empty.

The logical operators <AndOr> and <Not> apply three way logic as defined below:

F=False; T=True; U=Unknown
A=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression>
B=Evaluation result of <ExpressionList> or <VariableExpression>

NOT operator:
A !A
-----------------
F T
U U
T F

AND operator:
A B A && B
-------------------
F F F
F T F
F U F
T F F
T T T
T U U
U F F
U T U
U U U

OR operator:
A B A || B
------------------
F F F
F T T
F U U
T F T
T T T
T U T
U F U
U T T
U U U

cgrole:
Cell group role. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.
Operator: ==, and !=.

Chipset identifier. Applicable to both NR standalone and EN-DC.

Value: Integer in range 0..255 given in decimal.

redcapue:
Reduced Capabilities UE indicator. Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: Boolean
Description: RedCap UE identification received via LCID in MSG3 (see 3GPP TS 38.331).

rfsp:
Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority (3GPP TS 23.501). Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal.

rrcEstResCause:
RRC establishment cause or RRC resume cause. Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, and !=.
Value: One of emergency, highPriorityAccess, mt-Access, mo-Signaling, mo-Data, mo-VoiceCall, mo-VideoCall, mo-SMS, mps-PriorityAccess, or mcs-PriorityAccess.
Description: Establishment cause value received in RRC Setup Request message or resume cause received
in RRC Resume Request message (see 3GPP TS 38.331).
The received establishment cause or resume cause is valid in UE grouping framework when performing UE group evaluation during time specified by corresponding validity time attribute value in MO class UeGroupSelection.

snssai:
Single Network Slice Selection Assistance Information (3GPP TS 23.003). Applicable to NR standalone.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: input option 1: String in format "<SST><SD>" matched by regular expression [0][x][0-9a-fA-F]{8} (8 digit hexa-decimal number).
Value: input option 2: Integer in range 0x0..0xffffffff given in hexadecimal.
Description: S-NSSAI is composed of two distinct elements:
- SST (Slice/Service Type): 2 digit hexa-decimal number
- SD (Slice Differentiator): 6 digit hexa-decimal number
The SD field has a reserved value "no SD value associated with the SST" defined as hexadecimal FFFFFF/ffffff.

Example values, input option 1:
- 0x050000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE)
- 0x2effffff (SST=0x2e,SD=0xffffff // no SD associated with the SST)

Example values, input option 2:
- 0x1 (SST=0x00,SD=0x000001)
- 0x50000EE (SST=0x05,SD=0x0000EE)
- 0x150000EE (SST=0x15,SD=0x0000EE)

spid:
Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency Priority (3GPP TS 36.300). Applicable to EN-DC.
Operator: ==, !=, <=, >=, <, and >.
Value: Integer in range 1..256 given in decimal.

Operator Precedence Order:
=======================
The logical and relation operators are evaluated according to the precedence order listed below.

---------------------------------------------
1 (highest precedence)
< Less than
<= Less than or equal
> Greater than
>= Greater than or equal
== Equal
!= Not equal
-------------------------------------------
2 ! (Not)
---------------------------------------------
3 && (And)
---------------------------------------------
4 (lowest precedence)
|| (Or)
---------------------------------------------

The NOT operator "!" negates the following <ParentExpressionList>, <VariableExpression>, <FlowExpression> or an <ExpressionList> encapsulated in parenthesis.
Therefore, expression !a==b && c==d is equivalent to ((!(a==b)) && (c==d)) and different from !(a==b && c==d).
Expression !a==b and !(a==b) are equivalent.

Since AND operator "&&" has higher precedence than OR operator "||", a<b || a<c && c<d is equivalent to (a<b || (a<c && c<d)). Surround expression list including OR operator with parenthesis to force OR operator to be evaluated before AND operators outside of the expression list, for example (a<b || a<c) && c<d.

Examples:
=========

Simple one valued expressions:
plmn == 234-56
spid == 1
cgrole == mcg
arp > 3
snssai == 0xfedcba98
rrcEstResCause == mo-VoiceCall
imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12

imeisv == ref //Special <value> ref represents <ValueList> defined via imeiSvRef.
chipset == ref
chipset == 1.1.1 //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1.
chipset == 0.0.0 //Matches all UEs that do not support chipset identifier reporting.

Value list expressions:
spid == {8,9,10,1,155}
!plmn == {234-56, 434-567}
chipset == {1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.1.3, ref} //Matches all UEs with chipset identifier: vendor = 1, variant = 1 and version = 1, 2 or 3, or the corresponding vendor, variant and version defined via chipsetRef.
imeisv == {1234567890FFFF12, ref, 1234567890FFFF13} //Matches all UEs with imeisv: TAC = 12345678, SNR = 90FFFF and SVN = 12 or 13, or the corresponding TAC, SN and SVN defined via imeiSvRef.

Equivalent expressions using ||:
(spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) //Equals to spid == {8, 9, 10, 1, 155}.
!(plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567) //Equals to !plmn == {234-56, 434-567}.

imeisv == ref || imeisv == 1234567890FFFF12|| imeisv == 1234567890FFFF13 //Equals to imeisv == {ref, 1234567890FFFF12, 1234567890FFFF13}.
chipset == 1.1.1 || chipset == ref || chipset == 1.1.2 // Equals to chipset == {1.1.1, ref, 1.1.2}.

Negative expressions:
!5qi==1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.
5qi!=1 //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.

Negative <FlowExpressions> that produce same result:
[!5qi==1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.
[5qi!=1] //Matches flows with 5qi not equal to 1.

<FlowExpressionList> negative expressions:
!([5qi==1]) //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1.
![5qi==1] //Matches UEs that do not have flows with 5qi 1.

Mixed examples:
spid == 1 && cgrole == mcg
!(spid != 1 || cgrole != mcg)
(spid == 8 || spid == 9 || spid == 10 || spid == 1 || spid == 155) && (plmn == 234-56 || plmn == 434-567)

Precedence given by "()" and sequence alter the evaluation order and result:
[5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5] //Equals to ([5qi==1] && chipset==ref) || (imeisv==ref && [5qi==5])
[5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5]
([5qi==1] && chipset==ref || imeisv==ref) && [5qi==5]
[5qi==1] && (chipset==ref || imeisv==ref && [5qi==5])
chipset==ref || [5qi==1] && [5qi==5] && imeisv==ref

Examples of selection criteria that shall be avoided since they will always be evaluated to False. <FlowExpression> can be used in these cases.
5qi==5 && 5qi==9
snssai==0x15000000 && snssai==0x17000000
arp==5 && arp==10
qci==5 && qci==9

Example of selection criteria for UE variable snssai:
snssai>=15000000 && snssai<=15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 regardless of value of S-NSSAI SD part.
snssai==15FFFFFF //Matches UE which has a flow with S-NSSAI SST part equal to 15 and S-NSSAI SD part value equal to FFFFFF, meaning no SD value associated with the SST.

Flow expressions combined with UE variables:
plmn == 234-56 && [5qi==1] && [5qi==9] //Matches UE which has plmn equal to 234-56, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1, and any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9.
chipset==1.5.32 && [5qi==9] && ![5qi==1] //Matches UE which has chipset identifier equal to 1.5.32, any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 9, and no QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1.
[5qi==1 && snssai == 0xfedcba98] || ([5qi==2] && [snssai == 0xfedcba77]) //Matches UE which has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 1 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba98, or has any QoS flow with 5qi equal to 2 and snssai equal to 0xfedcba77.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
In-session activity handling.

If false, DRB is labeled as bursty. Active session time is measured for each DRB after data is transferred in uplink or downlink. Session time measurement continues with added guard period of 100 ms.
Bursty DRBs are labeled as released in session if any data is transferred during last 100 ms.

If true, DRB is labeled as continuous. Active time is measured for each DRB from first uplink or downlink data transmission until 100 ms after last data transmission.
Continuous DRBs are labeled as released in session after transmission of first packet of data and afterwards.

Only applicable to standalone DRBs. Default value is false, which is applicable to all non-standalone DRBs.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect network KPI values.

Parameter Description:
Enables GTP-U supervision for S1 paths.

When true, all GTP-U S1 paths are supervised by gNodeB-CU-UP that sends Echo Request every 60 seconds. If five requests in row do not receive response, path connectivity is considered lost. If three requests in row receive response, connectivity is considered re-established.
When connectivity is lost no traffic is allocated to the path.
If a path is unused for 24h the supervision stops and connectivity is thereafter not known.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q4. Deprecated: Since 22.Q1. Replaced by GtpuSupervisionProfile::gtpuEchoEnabled. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
DSCP value used when sending GTP-U Echo Request.

Value is applicable if gtpuEchoEnabled is true.

Whether GTP-U supervision is enabled.

When enabled, path or paths with given interfaces and local IP addresses are supervised by gNodeB-CU-UP that sends echo request.
If three consecutive echo requests with 60-second period receive responses, path connectivity is considered reachable.
If five consecutive echo requests with 3-second period do not receive responses, path connectivity is considered lost.
When path connectivity is lost, no traffic is allocated to the path.

A GtpuSupervisionProfile instance defines supervision for one or several interfaces among interface names NG, S1, X2, and XN.
It can only act within its grandparent GNBCUUPFunction instance.
There are three main configuration alternatives based on interfaceList and endpointResourceRef.

Alternative 1: interfaceList is non-empty, endpointResourceRef is empty.
GtpuSupervisionProfile instance covers grandparent GNBCUUPFunction instance for interfaces in interfaceList.

Alternative 2: interfaceList is empty, endpointResourceRef is non-empty.
GtpuSupervisionProfile instance covers LocalIpEndpoint instances under referenced EndpointResource instances.
Empty interfaceList means "all interfaces NG, S1, X2, and XN" and matches any interface in LocalIpEndpoint::interfaceList.

Alternative 3: interfaceList is non-empty, endpointResourceRef is non-empty.
GtpuSupervisionProfile instance covers LocalIpEndpoint instances under referenced EndpointResource instances, for matching interfaces.
Matching means listed in both interfaceList and LocalIpEndpoint::interfaceList.

GtpuSupervisionProfile MO is not applicable to LocalIPsecEndpoint MO.
Dependencies:
If true, following dependencies apply.
Dependencies between GtpuSupervisionProfile instances apply among instances where value is true under same GNBCUUPFunction instance.

One of interfaceList and endpointResourceRef must be non-empty.

An InterfaceName in interfaceList must be unique among GtpuSupervisionProfile instances where endpointResourceRef is empty.

An InterfaceName in interfaceList cannot be used both in GtpuSupervisionProfile instance with empty endpointResourceRef and in GtpuSupervisionProfile instance with non-empty endpointResourceRef.

An EndpointResource instance referenced by endpointResourceRef must be reserved by at least ResourcePartitionMember or GNBCUUPFunction instance.

An EndpointResource instance referenced by endpointResourceRef must have at least one LocalIpEndpoint child instance that contains NG, S1, X2, or XN in its interfaceList.

An EndpointResource instance referenced by endpointResourceRef must have at least one LocalIpEndpoint child instance that has at least one InterfaceName in its interfaceList that matches an InterfaceName in interfaceList.

Only one GtpuSupervisionProfile instance can match a given InterfaceName for a given EndpointResource instance. Match means InterfaceName listed both in interfaceList and in any LocalIpEndpoint::interfaceList under an EndpointResource instance referenced by endpointResourceRef.

If interfaceList is empty, a reference to EndpointResource instance in endpointResourceRef must be unique among GtpuSupervisionProfile instances.

If interfaceList is empty, it matches all InterfaceName values used in EndpointResource instances referenced by endpointResourceRef. Used InterfaceName values are listed in LocalIpEndpoint::interfaceList under EndpointResource instances. The same InterfaceName values cannot be listed in interfaceList of other GtpuSupervisionProfile instance that has empty endpointResourceRef.

TDD cell:
For a BWP instance, placement must be at low end of band (value 0) or at position compatible with NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth configuration.

FDD cell:
For a BWP instance, that is defined less than NRSectorCarrier bandwidth, placement must be at low end of band (value 0) or at high end of the band, with value depending on the cell BW size:
* 24: BWP bandwidth is 25 MHz
* 48: BWP bandwidth is 30 MHz
* 72: BWP bandwidth is 35 MHz
* 96: BWP bandwidth is 40 MHz
* 144: BWP bandwidth is 50 MHz
For a BWP instance, that is defined equal to NRSectorCarrier bandwidth, placement must be at low end of band (value 0).

Parameter Description:
SpCell-specific buffer based SCell activation threshold value.

One or more SCells can be activated if number of downlink slots required to transmit all bits in UE queues is higher than sCellActDeactDataThres.

When deciding SCell activation, minimum number of downlink slots needed to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits that can be transmitted in one downlink slot by SpCell.

If -1, data-triggered activation condition is always satisfied even with no data in buffer, and also that data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied.
Dependencies: When greater than -1, must also be greater than or equal to sCellActDeactDataThresHyst.

Parameter Description:
SpCell-specific buffer based SCell deactivation threshold hysteresis value.

One or more SCells can be deactivated if number of downlink slots required to transmit bits in UE queues is less than or equal to
sCellActDeactDataThres minus value of this attribute.

Minimum number of downlink slots needed to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits that can be transmitted in one downlink slot by SpCell.

If sCellActDeactDataThres is -1, data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied and value of this attribute is ignored.
Dependencies: Must be less or equal to sCellActDeactDataThres when sCellActDeactDataThres is greater than -1.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for SpCell-specific buffer-based SCell activation in uplink.

If number of uplink slots needed to transmit all bits for UE is higher than sCellActDeactUlDataThresh, one or more SCells can be activated.

Number of uplink slots needed to transmit all bits is calculated as total number of bits in all priority queues divided by number of bits that can be transmitted in one uplink slot by SpCell.

If -1, data-triggered activation condition is always fulfilled, even with no data in uplink buffer. This value means that data-triggered deactivation condition is never fulfilled.
Dependencies: When greater than -1, it must also be greater than or equal to sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst.

Parameter Description:
Hysteresis of threshold for SpCell-specific buffer-based SCell deactivation in uplink.

If number of uplink slots needed to transmit all bits is less than sCellActDeactUlDataThresh minus value of this attribute, one or more SCells can be deactivated.

Number of uplink slots needed to transmit all bits is calculated as total number of bits in all priority queues divided by number of bits that can be transmitted in one uplink slot by SpCell.

If sCellActDeactUlDataThresh is -1, data-triggered deactivation condition is never fulfilled and value of this attribute is ignored.
Dependencies: Must be less than or equal to sCellActDeactUlDataThresh when sCellActDeactUlDataThresh is greater than -1.

Parameter Description:
Activation prohibit timer.

No new SCell activation is allowed while this timer is running.

SpCell specific buffer based SCell deactivation time control.

One or more SCells are deactivated if time to transmit bits in queues is less than or equal to sCellActDeactDataThres minus sCellActDeactDataThresHyst for a duration of sCellDeactDelayTimer.

Deactivation prohibit timer.

No new SCell deactivation is allowed while this timer is running.

Disturbances: Changing this attribute can result in different sector shape, therefore, UEs can be left out of coverage.
Dependencies:
Must be MACRO_1, if NRSectorCarrier::azimuthNull or NRSectorCarrier::elevationNull is non-empty or PowerBackoffDir::powerBackoffDirEnabled is true.
Must be PRODUCT_DEFAULT, HIGHRISE_1, HOTSPOT_1 or STREET_COVERAGE_1 if PowerBackoffDir::powerBackoffDirEnabled is true.
Precondition: If parent NRSectorCarrier::maxAllowedEirpPsd is not -1, then this attribute can be changed only when parent NRSectorCarrier::administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Custom beamforming weights of downlink common channels.

Only applicable if radio equipment supports AAS configuration. At least one amplitude must be non-zero for custom beamforming weights to take effect.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can result in different sector shape, therefore, UEs can be left out of coverage.
Dependencies: Must be empty, if NRSectorCarrier::azimuthNull or NRSectorCarrier::elevationNull is non-empty.
Precondition: If parent NRSectorCarrier::maxAllowedEirpPsd is not -1, then this attribute can be changed only when parent NRSectorCarrier::administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Digitally controlled pan through beamforming.

Only applicable if radio equipment supports AAS configuration. Positive value gives clockwise pan and negative value gives counterclockwise pan. If empty, usedDigitalPan shows the digital pan in use.

Select a value supported by installed radio equipment. Refer to CPI for installed radio equipment.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can result in different sector shape, therefore, UEs can be left out of coverage.
Precondition: If parent NRSectorCarrier::maxAllowedEirpPsd is not -1, then this attribute can be changed only when parent NRSectorCarrier::administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Digitally controlled tilt through beamforming.

Relative to horizontal plane, adjusted by mechanical tilt.

Only applicable if radio equipment supports AAS configuration. Positive value gives downwards tilt and negative value gives upwards tilt.
If empty or unsupported for configuration, system selects value within supported range. Attribute usedDigitalTilt shows tilt in use.

Make sure that selected value is supported by installed radio equipment. For more information, see Antenna Integrated Radio Unit Description of installed radio equipment.

If value of usedCoverageShape is HIGHRISE or HOTSPOT, a fixed digital tilt is applied.
Change Take Effect:
For Low-Band and Mid-Band sector carriers, takes effect immediately.
For High-Band sector carriers, takes effect at next NRSectorCarrier unlock.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can result in different sector shape, therefore, UEs can be left out of coverage.
Precondition: If parent NRSectorCarrier::maxAllowedEirpPsd is not -1, then this attribute can be changed only when parent NRSectorCarrier::administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Target coverage width in elevation.

Elevation is in vertical plane.

If empty or unsupported for configuration, system selects value within supported range. Attribute usedElevationCoverageWidth shows width in use.

For Low-Band and Mid-Band cells in downlink, only applicable if any of the following is true:
- customComBfwWideBeam is empty.
- customComBfwWideBeam.amplitude is set to all zeros.

Only applicable when usedCoverageShape is FLEXIBLE_COVERAGE_1.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band sector carriers.

Select a value supported by installed radio equipment. Refer to radio equipment CPI for supported values.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can result in different sector shape, therefore, UEs can be left out of coverage.
Precondition: If parent NRSectorCarrier::maxAllowedEirpPsd is not -1, then this attribute can be changed only when parent NRSectorCarrier::administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Number of SSB beams.

If PRODUCT_DEFAULT, system automatically selects number of SSB beams.

Must be set to value supported by installed radio equipment. Otherwise system overrides setting.

Attribute usedSsbBeams shows number of SSB beams in use.

Only applicable to High-Band sector carriers.
Range and Values:
PRODUCT_DEFAULT
SSB_BEAMS_12
SSB_BEAMS_24
SSB_BEAMS_4
SSB_BEAMS_6
SSB_BEAMS_8
Dependencies:
For High-Band cells, following apply:
- Must be SSB_BEAMS_12 if NRCellDU::ssbDuration is set to 3.
- Must be SSB_BEAMS_12 or SSB_BEAMS_24 if NRCellDU::ssbDuration is set to 4, 5.
- Must be SSB_BEAMS_12 or SSB_BEAMS_24 or PRODUCT_DEFAULT if NRCellDU::ssbDuration is empty.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Payload size in bytes for configured grant.

A margin is added for size of IP header, PDCP header and RLC header. Bytes for Buffer Status Report (BSR) and Power Headroom Report (PHR) are always included in configured grant and do not need to be considered when setting configuredGrantDataSize.

If 0, BSR can be reported at configured grant occasions. When receiving BSR, required data transmission can be scheduled with a dynamic scheme.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

Configured grant mode for corresponding UE.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

For FDD, following values are applicable: 5, 10, 20, 40, 80, 160, 320, 640.
For TDD, following values are applicable: 5, 10, 20, 40, 80, 160, 320, 640, 1280.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies: Cannot be 5, if tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04, or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08 in NRCellDU instance that references this ConfiguredGrantUeCfg instance. In other words: Cannot be 5, if this ConfiguredGrantUeCfg instance is referenced by UeBbProfileUeCfg::configuredGrantUeCfgRef under UeBbProfile instance that is referenced by NRCellDU::ueBbProfileRef and NRCellDU::tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04, or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08.

Parameter Description: Priority to use after priority downshift fulfills at rate.

Whether relative priority for downlink is used in demoted state.

If false, value of relative priority is 1. Otherwise, value of relative priority is SchedulingProfile::relativePriority.

Determines what happens when UE is overloaded with rate-based priority shift algorithm.

Overload means a DRB with rate tracking is attempted to be set up while UE already has two DRBs with rate tracking.

Rate tracking is activated when SchedulingProfile::schedulingAlgorithm is PRIORITIZED_RATE or SOFT_RATE_THROTTLING.
Rate to be prioritized.
The value component of the RDN.

Limit of downlink spectrum resources.

Used with elevated priority by a single DRB configured with a rate.

The lower the value, the less spectrum resources can be utilized with elevated priority by rate-controlled scheduling.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.

Whether high rate timers are used.

High rate timers tReassemblyDlHighRate and tStatusProhibitDlHighRate are used for configuring UE DRB RLC timer t-reassembly and t-statusProhibit respectively when UE DRB total throughput reaches high rate threshold.

If true, UE is reconfigured with timer value defined in tReassemblyDlHighRate and tStatusProhibitDlHighRate, when UE DRB total throughput reaches high rate threshold.
If false, no UE RLC timer reconfiguration is performed, when UE DRB total throughput reaches high rate threshold.

Parameter Description:
Radio Link Control (RLC) SN field size.

Used only if DU5qi::drbRlcInDu5qiEnabled is false.

Following values are recommended:
* 18 if profile5qi is 8 or 9.
* 12 if profile5qi is 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 65, 66, 67, 69, or 70.
* 6 if profile5qi is 79, 80, 82, 83, 84, or 85, and for voice over NR with good RF conditions.

3GPP recommends 6 when profile5qi is 1, 2, 65, 66, or 67.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute without following the dependencies can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Must be 6 or 12 if rlcMode is set to UM in corresponding CUCP5qi profile.

Must be 12 or 18 if rlcMode is set to AM in corresponding CUCP5qi profile.

Must be lower than or equal to pdcpSnSize in corresponding CUCP5qi profile.

Parameter Description:
Maximum downlink baseband capacity available on unlocked Baseband hardware.

Maximum limit of downlink capacity that can be granted by baseband HWAC. This level sets the limit at emergency unlock.

Granted downlink baseband capacity.

Available capacity of corresponding Baseband HWAC property for all enabled Baseband HW.

Required amount of Baseband HWAC throughput capacity for downlink to be allocated to NR.

The setting impacts installation and distribution of HUPs on the node.
In LTE + NR mixed mode Baseband configuration, ENodeBFunction::dlBbCapacityTarget must also be considered in following cases:

- If greater than or equal to 75 for just one RAT, the system attempts to allocate the required value to that RAT. Available excess capacity is allocated to the other RAT.
- If greater than or equal to 75 on both RATs, an attempt to fulfill both requirements is made with priority to NR. Until requirements are met, HUPs are distributed proportionally. Afterwards, HUPs are distributed equally.
- If undefined on both RATs (set to empty on NR and set to -1 on LTE), Baseband HWAC throughput capacity for downlink is equally allocated by the system to the extent allowed by HUPs, with priority to NR.

With the Instantaneous Licensing feature activated, an undefined attribute setting gives a minimum requirement of 75 Mbps.

Granted Baseband DL capacity is shown by dlBbCapacityNet.
Granted Baseband uplink capacity is half of granted downlink capacity and is shown by ulBbCapacityNet.

Information on installed Baseband HWACs and HUPs can be found in CapacityUsage::hupInfo.
Disturbances: Changing this parameter in LTE+NR mixed mode configuration can impact throughput limit on NR and LTE and can cause traffic degradation.

Can be LOW_SE_QAM64 only if linkAdaptationUeMode is CUSTOM.
Cannot be QAM256 if linkAdaptationUeMode is ROBUST_BASIC or ROBUST_HIGH.

Parameter Description:
Actual boost for PDCCH channel carrying Msg2, Msg3 retransmission, Msg4 and P2 refinement.

This value can be less than pdcchRachBoost, depending on installed radio equipment and config mode.

Only applicable to High-Band SpCells.

Actual boost for PDSCH channel carrying Msg2.

This value can be different from value of pdschRachBoost, depending on installed radio equipment and configuration mode.

Only applicable to High-Band SpCells.

Actual boost for SSB.

For Mid-Band cells, value can be less than ssbPowerBoost because of limitations of installed radio equipment.

For High-Band, value is same as ssbPowerBoost.

Empty for Low-Band cells.

Whether additional PUCCH resource is allocated in the cell for Carrier Aggregation.

Set value to true if cell is intended to be used as PCell for Carrier Aggregation.
Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
The administrative state.

While set to SHUTTINGDOWN the cell is automatically barred. Set to LOCKED when all UEs have left the cell or timer maxOffloadDurationShutDown expires.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED causes loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Attribute nRSectorCarrierRef must be set for administrativeState to change to UNLOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether Advanced Downlink Single-User MIMO Mid-Band feature is enabled in cell.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies:
If true, following conditions must be fulfilled:
- tddUlDlPattern must not be set to TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00.
- NrTransmissionBandwidthRO.subCarrierSpacing must be set to 30 (Mid-Band).
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must not be set to TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00.
- If NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is active (dlAvailableCrbs > 0 or ulAvailableCrbs > 0), downlink available bandwidth must be in range of uplink available bandwidth and srsHoppingBandwidth must be FULL.
- rdsUeAdvancedPosEnabled must be false.
Can be true if maxUeSpeed is not one of following values:
- UP_TO_200KMPH
- UP_TO_350KMPH
- UP_TO_500KMPH
Must be false if following conditions are true:
- NRSectorCarrier::nullSteeringMode is not COMMON_BEAMFORMING.
- NRSectorCarrier::azimuthNull or NRSectorCarrier::elevationNull is non-empty.
Must be true if following conditions are true:
- maxNoOfAdvancedDlMuMimoLayers is set to value higher than 0.
- aperiodicSrsEnabled is true.
- srsHoppingBandwidth is set to HALF.
- interferenceSensingEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
Whether EMF Integrator Mid-Band feature is enabled.

If true, Air Interface Load Generator (AILG) for PDSCH is beamformed according to PMIs set by ailgI11BeamDirection and ailgI12BeamDirection.

Only applicable if value of ailgDlPrbLoadLevel is greater than 0.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies: See dependencies of ailgI11BeamDirection and ailgI12BeamDirection.

Parameter Description:
Air Interface Load Generator (AILG) load level required for PDSCH.

If 0, AILG for PDSCH is disabled.

The i11 PMI component of Air Interface Load Generator beam direction for PDSCH.

Set according to highest CSI-RS configuration.
Dependencies:
If ailgBeamDirectionEnabled is true or ailgPdcchBeamDirectionEnabled is true, following dependencies apply:
- If csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports is set to FOUR_FOUR, range of attribute is 0..15.
- If csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports is set to FOUR_TWO_N1AZ or FOUR_TWO_N1EL, range of attribute is 0..15.
- If csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports is set to FOUR_ONE_N1AZ or FOUR_ONE_N1EL and csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports and csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports are set to OFF, range of attribute is 0..15.
- If csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports is set to TWO_TWO and csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports and csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports are set to OFF, range of attribute is 0..7.

Parameter Description:
The i12 PMI component of Air Interface Load Generator (AILG) beam direction for PDSCH.

Set according to highest CSI-RS configuration.
Dependencies:
If ailgBeamDirectionEnabled is true or ailgPdcchBeamDirectionEnabled is true, following dependencies apply:
- If csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports is set to EIGHT_TWO_N1AZ, range of attribute is 0..7.
- If csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports is set to FOUR_FOUR, range of attribute is 0..15.
- If csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports is set to EIGHT_ONE_N1AZ, attribute must be 0.
- If csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports is set to FOUR_TWO_N1AZ or FOUR_TWO_N1EL, range of attribute is 0..7.
- If csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports is set to FOUR_ONE_N1AZ or FOUR_ONE_N1EL and csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports and csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports are set to OFF, attribute must be 0.
- If csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports is set to TWO_TWO and csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports and csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports are set to OFF, range of attribute is 0..7.

Parameter Description: PDSCH Air Interface Load Generator (AILG) modulation type.

Whether EMF Integrator Mid-Band feature is enabled for PDCCH.

If true, Air Interface Load Generator (AILG) for PDCCH is beamformed according to PMIs set by ailgI11BeamDirection and ailgI12BeamDirection.

Only applicable if ailgPdcchLoadLevel is greater than 0.
Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies: See dependencies of ailgI11BeamDirection and ailgI12BeamDirection.

Parameter Description:
Air Interface Load Generator (AILG) load level required for PDCCH.

If 0, AILG for PDCCH is disabled.

Whether NR Aperiodic SRS Mid-Band feature is enabled.

Dependencies:
The combination of this attribute set to false and advancedDlSuMimoEnabled set to true and combination of this attribute set to true and advancedDlSuMimoEnabled set to true cannot co-exist in the instances of NRCellDU under same GNBDUFunction.

- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled must be true
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be one of following values:

- TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_04
- TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05

Parameter Description:
List of all NR bands the cells belongs to.

Calculated by the system at cell unlock.

If bandListManual is configured, it is used instead of bandList.

Configured list of bands to be used by cell.

If present, this list is used instead of bandList.

Bands specified in bandListManual must be intersection of possible bands for given cell configuration.
Possible bands are displayed in bandList.
Example, if bandList contains only bands 77 and 78, this attribute must contain 77, 78, or both.

If a band specified in bandListManual does not match cell configuration, cell fails to unlock.

Recommendation is that this list has same content as NRFrequency::bandListManual for cells with same frequency. This recommendation is for 3GPP compliance.

Order of NR bands listed in bandListManual corresponds to order of bands in frequencyBandList in SIB1.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether Beam Failure Recovery is enabled.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q1. Planned to be removed.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
References to instances of BWP MO.

If empty at cell unlock and bWPSetRef is also empty, channel bandwidth according to NRSectorCarrier instance is used in this cell.
If non-empty at cell unlock and bWPSetRef is also non-empty, channel bandwidth from referenced MO instances are used.

Only applicable if license for NR Dynamic Power Optimizer or NR Reduced UE Bandwidth Support is present and feature is active.
Dependencies:
Must have equal number of initial BWP downlink and initial BWP uplink instances (BWP::isInitialBwp=true). Only two BWP instances can be referenced. Only initial BWP instances can be referenced. Two referenced initial BWP instances must have same size.
Referenced BWP instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of BWPSet MO.

If empty at cell unlock and bWPRef is also empty, channel bandwidth according to NRSectorCarrier instance is used in this cell.
If non-empty at cell unlock and bWPRef is also non-empty, channel bandwidth from referenced MO instances are used.

Only applicable if license for NR Dynamic Power Optimizer or NR Reduced UE Bandwidth Support is present and feature is active.
Dependencies: Referenced BWP instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Size of downlink Carrier Aggregation buffer splitting threshold.

Defines whether volume of data in buffer is split into multiple activated cells.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether scheduler fairness for CA UE in each Component Carrier (CC) is enabled.

Used with Carrier Aggregation feature and set on PCell node to improve scheduler fairness for CA UE in each CC, when enabled.

If true, scheduling priority on one CC is not affected by scheduling activity on other CC.
If false, scheduling activity on one CC affects scheduling priority on all CC.

Not applicable to High-Band cells.

Whether scheduler fairness for uplink carrier aggregation UEs in each component carrier is enabled.

Used to improve uplink scheduler fairness for carrier aggregation UEs in each component carrier.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

Reference to an instance of CaSCellHandling MO.

If non-empty, attributes from referenced MO instance are used.
If empty, attribute default values according to CaSCellHandling and CaSCellHandlingUeCfg MO class definitions are used.
Dependencies: Referenced CaSCellHandling instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Preferred bandwidth for CBRS cell.

Affects CBRS Domain Coordinator policies.
Dependencies: If cell is a CBRS-managed cell, value cannot be 50 MHz or higher if cbrsCellPriority is HIGH.

Parameter Description:
CBRS cell priority.

Used together with cbrsCellPriorityRank.
Affects CBRS Domain Coordinator policies.
Dependencies: If cell is a CBRS-managed cell, value cannot be HIGH if cbrsCellBandwidthPreferred is 50 MHz or higher.

Parameter Description:
CBRS cell rank in priority group.

If 1, lowest rank is prioritized.
If 10, highest rank is prioritized.
Used together with cbrsCellPriority.
Affects CBRS Domain Coordinator policies.

Whether optimization of SSB placement for CBRS cell is allowed.

Affects CBRS Domain Coordinator policies.

Configuration for barring NR cell.

If BARRED, cell is barred.
If NOT_BARRED, cell can still be barred for other reasons. See cellBarredStatus.
Dependencies:
When BARRED in a CBRS-managed cell, cell must be configured as a CBRS SCell Only or as a CBRS Downlink Only SCell.
When NOT_BARRED in a CBRS-managed cell, cell must be configured as a CBRS PCell or SCell.

Parameter Description:
Reason why cell is barred.

Cell can be barred for following reasons:
- cellBarred is BARRED.
- administrativeState is SHUTTINGDOWN, in NR Cell Soft Lock feature.
- Barred by NR Booster Carrier Sleep feature for energy saving.

If empty, cell is not barred.

Whether cell is currently barred.

Cell can be barred for following reasons:
- cellBarred is BARRED.
- administrativeState is SHUTTINGDOWN, in NR Cell Soft Lock feature.
- Barred by NR Booster Carrier Sleep feature for energy saving.

Used together with gNodeB identifier to identify NR cell in PLMN.

Must be unique in gNodeB.
Used together with gNBId to form NCI.
Dependencies: cellLocalId < 2^(36 - gNBIdLength)
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of CellPriorityShift MO.

If empty, attribute default values according to CellPriorityShift MO class definitions are used.
If non-empty, attributes from referenced MO instance are used.
Dependencies: Referenced CellPriorityShift instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Maximum signal path distance from BS where connection to UE can be set up and maintained.

If empty, system configures 1100 m for High-Band cells and 1600 m for Low-Band or Mid-Band cells.

Value greater than 15000 m when rachPreambleFormat is RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_00 (F0) can cause random access performance degradation and interference to other channels.
Dependencies:
Must be less than or equal to 10000 m for Low-Band if rachPreambleFormat is RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4).

Must be less than or equal to 5000 m for Mid-Band if rachPreambleFormat is RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4).

Must be less than or equal to 14000 m for High-Band.
If value is less than or equal to 1100 m:
- fixWideBeamsForPeriodicSr must be FIX_WB_FOR_PERIODIC_SR_NONE.
If value is greater than 1100 m:
- rachPreambleFormat must be RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_04 (C2).
- license for Extended Propagation Delay Support High-Band must be present and activated before cell unlock.
If value is greater than 4000 m:
- fixWideBeamsForPeriodicSr must be FIX_WB_FOR_PERIODIC_SR_HIGH.
If value is greater than 4300 m:
- maxUeSpeed must be UP_TO_10KMPH.
If value is greater than 6900 m:
- rachPreambleFormat must be RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3).
If tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_05 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_06, value must be less than or equal to 1100 m.
For High-Band, all NRCellDU instances with administrativeState set to UNLOCKED mapping to same SectorEquipmentFunction instance must have same value, if any this attribute is empty, the other attribute must be empty or 1100 m.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether the cell is reserved for operator use.

Reference to an instance of CellResourceMapping MO.

Only applicable if nrRrpEnabled is true.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Referenced CellResourceMapping instance must be under ResourceAllocationPolicies instance under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Factor for estimated cell weight.

Scales cell weight contribution when selecting serving cells.

A value less than 100 reduces the cell weight compared to maximum cell weight.
Current cellState.

Whether Contention-Free Random Access (CFRA) is enabled.

If true, system allocates a portion of random access preambles for CFRA, to be used for incoming NR SA HO. If allocation fails, CBRA is performed.
Dependencies: Must be false for High-Band cells.

Parameter Description:
EPS TAC, is not broadcast and differs from 5G System (5GS) TAC.

If empty, gNodeB takes TAC from ENDCX2SetupRequest message and includes in ENDCX2SetupResponse or ENDCConfigurationTransfer message.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Periodicity in slots for configured grant.

For FDD, following values are applicable: 5, 10, 20, 40, 80, 160, 320, 640.
For TDD, following values are applicable: 5, 10, 20, 40, 80, 160, 320, 640, 1280.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies:
Value must be same for all NRCellDU instances under a GNBDUFunction instance.
If tddUlDlPattern is set to TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04, or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08, then value cannot be 5.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether Coverage-Optimized Uplink Scheduling High-Band is enabled.

Only applicable if license for Coverage-Optimized Uplink Scheduling High-Band is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.
Value must be false for Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when NRCellDU with matching cellLocalId has administrativeState LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether aperiodic CSI reports include subband or wideband feedback.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Active CSI-RS resource configuration.

The active CSI-RS resource configuration has been determined based on the preferred HW/SW configurations of gNodeB.

Settings related to 16-port CSI and associated port to antenna mapping.

Applies only to cells based on radios with at least 16 Tx branches. Otherwise, ignored.

In standalone operation on radios with 8 or more Tx branches, 8-port CSI-RS is necessary to ensure that users with minimum allowed CSI measurement capability are served by cell. 8-port CSI-RS can be configured together with 16-port or 32-port on compatible AAS.
Dependencies:
If secondaryCellOnly is false, csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports can have a value other than OFF only if csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports also has a value other than OFF and csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports is OFF.
If dlMaxMuMimoLayers is greater than 0, csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports must be EIGHT_ONE_N1AZ.
See also dependencies of ailgI11BeamDirection and ailgI12BeamDirection.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Settings related to 2-port CSI and associated port to antenna mapping.

Applies only to cells based on radios with two Tx branches or applies to cells based on radios with four TX branches if NRSectorCarrier::ueAssistedPrecodingOptEnabled is true. Otherwise, ignored.
Dependencies:
If secondaryCellOnly is false, at least one of csiRsConfig2P.csiRsControl2Ports, csiRsConfig4P.csiRsControl4Ports, and csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF.
If NRSectorCarrier::ueAssistedPrecodingOptEnabled is true, csiRsConfig2P.csiRsControl2Ports must be ON.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Settings related to 32-port CSI and associated port to antenna mapping.

Applies only to cells based on radios with at least 32 Tx branches. Otherwise, ignored.

In standalone operation on radios with 8 or more Tx branches, 8-port CSI-RS is necessary to ensure that users with minimum allowed CSI measurement capability are served by cell. 8-port CSI-RS can be configured together with 16-port or 32-port on compatible AAS.
Dependencies:
If secondaryCellOnly is false, csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports can have a value other than OFF only if csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports also has a value other than OFF and csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports is OFF.
If dlMaxMuMimoLayers is greater than 0, csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports must be EIGHT_TWO_N1AZ or FOUR_FOUR.
See also dependencies of ailgI11BeamDirection and ailgI12BeamDirection.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Settings related to 4-port CSI and associated port to antenna mapping.

Applies only to cells based on radios with four Tx branches. Otherwise, ignored.
Dependencies:
If secondaryCellOnly is false, at least one of csiRsConfig2P.csiRsControl2Ports, csiRsConfig4P.csiRsControl4Ports, and csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF.
If NRSectorCarrier::ueAssistedPrecodingOptEnabled is true, csiRsConfig4P.csiRsControl4Ports must be TWO_ONE.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Settings related to 8-port CSI and associated port to antenna mapping.

Applies only to cells based on radios with at least eight Tx branches. Otherwise, ignored.

In standalone operation on radios with 8 or more Tx branches, 8-port CSI-RS is necessary to ensure that users with minimum allowed CSI measurement capability are served by cell. 8-port CSI-RS can be configured together with 16-port or 32-port on compatible AAS.
Dependencies:
If secondaryCellOnly is false following apply:
- at least one of csiRsConfig2P.csiRsControl2Ports, csiRsConfig4P.csiRsControl4Ports, and csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF.
- csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF if csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports or csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports has a value other than OFF.
If NRSectorCarrier::nullSteeringMode is not COMMON_BEAMFORMING, and at least one of NRSectorCarrier::azimuthNull or elevationNull is non-empty, then csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF.
See also dependencies of ailgI11BeamDirection and ailgI12BeamDirection.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Periodicity of CSI-RS transmission.
Dependencies:
Must be 20 if cell uses NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId configured.

Must be greater than or equal to 40 for Mid-Band cells if ssbTimeShiftEnabled is true.

Cannot be 10 or 20 if tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether primary CSI-RS resource allocation shifting is activated.
Whether secondary CSI-RS resource allocation shifting is activated.

Whether DFT-S-OFDM waveform support for Msg3 in the RACH process is enabled.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether DFT-S-OFDM waveform support for PUSCH is enabled.
Dependencies: In High-Band cells, value can be true only if maxUeSpeed is empty or UP_TO_10KMPH.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
UE starts on DFTS-OFDM when reported RSRP is below threshold in attribute value.

RSRP is reported in 3GPP TS 38.331 CG-ConfigInfo.
Applicable at secondary cell group addition.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.

Enables 256 QAM support in downlink.

Not applicable in High-Band cells.

Total amount of CRBs available for downlink channels.

Total downlink channel bandwidth corresponds to sum of downlink available CRBs and downlink blanked CRBs.
Total downlink channel bandwidth is configured in NRSectorCarrier::bSChannelBwDL. Formula for conversion to number of CRBs is defined in 3GPP TS 38.211.

If empty, there is no bandwidth restriction and no blanking in downlink.
If 0, there is no available CRB, NR Channel Bandwidth is fixed to NRSectorCarrier::bSChannelBwDl.
Dependencies:
See dependencies for trsConfigMode.
For allowed values of this attribute and dlStartCrb, see feature description NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth and Ericsson Spectrum Sharing All-In-One User Guide.
Downlink available bandwidth [dlStartCrb, dlStartCrb + dlAvailableCrbs - 1] must be in the range of uplink available bandwidth [ulStartCrb, ulStartCrb + ulAvailableCrbs - 1] if following options apply:
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true.
- NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is used (dlAvailableCrbs > 0 or ulAvailableCrbs > 0).
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Downlink channel scrambling identity.

Scrambling identity used for downlink physical channels and reference signals.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.

SINR threshold used by gNodeB to decide multiplexing PDSCH with DMRS for given PDSCH transmission.

To avoid throughput degradation, gNodeB does not use Downlink Data and DMRS Multiplexing for a given UE when estimated UE SINR is below this threshold.

Maximum number of codebook co-scheduled downlink MU-MIMO layers at cell level.

Values greater than 8 are not supported. If value greater than 8 is configured, then maximum number of layers is 8.

If 0, downlink MU-MIMO is disabled.
Only used if Downlink Multi-User MIMO Mid-Band is present and active.
Only used if radio equipment supports AAS configuration.

Value must be 0 for Low-Band and High-Band cells.
Dependencies:
dlMaxMuMimoLayers can be greater than 0 if subCarrierSpacing is 30 (Mid-Band cell) and one of following applies:
- csiRsConfig32P.csiRsControl32Ports is EIGHT_TWO_N1AZ or FOUR_FOUR.
- csiRsConfig16P.csiRsControl16Ports is EIGHT_ONE_N1AZ.
dlMaxMuMimoLayers can be greater than 0 if maxUeSpeed value is not UP_TO_200KMPH, UP_TO_350KMPH or UP_TO_500KMPH.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Maximum modulation order supported by cell.

Value is QAM_256 if radio unit supports 256 QAM and license for NR 256-QAM Downlink High-Band is present and feature is active. Otherwise, value is QAM_64.

Only set when NRCellDU instance is unlocked.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.

Whether downlink robust link adaptation is enabled.

Only applicable if license for Critical IoT is present and the High-Band feature is active.

Must be false for Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Supported downlink subcarrier spill-over value of radio to which ESS cell pair is connected.

Spill-over means that subcarrier or subcarriers of guard band NB-IoT PRB can exceed PRB subcarrier range of ESS NR cell.
Spill-over value represents capability of radio which defines exceeding subcarrier number compared with outmost subcarrier of NR.

Robustness mode for downlink small data.

Used to configure increased robustness of downlink small data.
Not applicable to High-Band cells.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause DL MCS distribution and DL MAC cell throughput change.

Parameter Description:
Start position of CRBs available for downlink channels.

Blanked CRBs appear before start position and after the range of available CRBs.
Dependencies:
See dependencies for trsConfigMode.
For allowed values of this attribute and dlAvailableCrbs, see feature description NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth and Ericsson Spectrum Sharing All-In-One User Guide.
Downlink available bandwidth [dlStartCrb, dlStartCrb + dlAvailableCrbs - 1] must be in the range of uplink available bandwidth [ulStartCrb, ulStartCrb + ulAvailableCrbs - 1] if following options apply:
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true.
- NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is used (dlAvailableCrbs > 0 or ulAvailableCrbs > 0).
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether DrxProfile MO class is used.

If true, appropriate attributes of DrxProfileUeCfg instance under DrxProfile instance referenced by drxProfileRef are used.
