Extended DRX mode.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Only applicable to RAN Compute group 4 and higher.
Dependencies: Must be DISABLED if Paging::nS is 2 or 4 under same GNBDUFunction instance.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of CgSwitch MO.

Automatically set to CgSwitch=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.

Applicable to EN-DC.
Dependencies: Referenced CgSwitch instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description: Whether EN-DC downlink leg switching is enabled.
Dependencies: At most 48 unique combinations of endcDlLegSwitchEnabled, endcDlNrLowQualThresh, endcDlNrQualHyst, endcUlLegSwitchEnabled, endcUlNrLowQualThresh, and endcUlNrQualHyst can be used across all NRCellDU instances under same GNBDUFunction instance.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q1. Replaced by CgSwitchCfg::dlCgSwitchMode. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
NR radio quality level threshold used for SN terminated split bearer.

Common for EN-DC and NR-DC.
Below this threshold the SCG leg is not used for downlink user data transmission.

SINR is used to represent quality. Value -16 corresponds to zero throughput, and lower values have no further impact.
Dependencies: At most 48 unique combinations of endcDlLegSwitchEnabled, endcDlNrLowQualThresh, endcDlNrQualHyst, endcUlLegSwitchEnabled, endcUlNrLowQualThresh, and endcUlNrQualHyst can be used across all NRCellDU instances under same GNBDUFunction instance.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q1. Replaced by CgSwitchCfg::dlScgLowQualThresh. Planned to be removed.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
NR radio quality hysteresis used for SN terminated split bearer.

Common for EN-DC and NR-DC.
Quality needs to be hysteresis more than endcDlNrLowQualThresh to start using SCG leg for downlink user data transmission again.

SINR is used to represent quality.
Dependencies: At most 48 unique combinations of endcDlLegSwitchEnabled, endcDlNrLowQualThresh, endcDlNrQualHyst, endcUlLegSwitchEnabled, endcUlNrLowQualThresh, and endcUlNrQualHyst can be used across all NRCellDU instances under same GNBDUFunction instance.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q1. Replaced by CgSwitchCfg::dlScgLowQualHyst. Planned to be removed.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether EN-DC or NR-DC uplink leg switching is enabled.
Dependencies: At most 48 unique combinations of endcDlLegSwitchEnabled, endcDlNrLowQualThresh, endcDlNrQualHyst, endcUlLegSwitchEnabled, endcUlNrLowQualThresh, and endcUlNrQualHyst can be used across all NRCellDU instances under same GNBDUFunction instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
NR radio quality level threshold used for SN Terminated split bearer.

Below this threshold SCG is not used as primary uplink path.
SINR is used to represent quality.
Common for EN-DC and NR-DC.
Dependencies: At most 48 unique combinations of endcDlLegSwitchEnabled, endcDlNrLowQualThresh, endcDlNrQualHyst, endcUlLegSwitchEnabled, endcUlNrLowQualThresh, and endcUlNrQualHyst can be used across all NRCellDU instances under same GNBDUFunction instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
NR radio quality hysteresis used for SN Terminated split bearer.

Quality need to be hysteresis better than endcUlNrLowQualThresh to start using the SCG Radio Resources as primary uplink path again.
SINR is used to represent quality.
Common for EN-DC and NR-DC.
Dependencies: At most 48 unique combinations of endcDlLegSwitchEnabled, endcDlNrLowQualThresh, endcDlNrQualHyst, endcUlLegSwitchEnabled, endcUlNrLowQualThresh, and endcUlNrQualHyst can be used across all NRCellDU instances under same GNBDUFunction instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Decimal representation of bitmap for ESS MBSFN subframes in four consecutive radio frames.

Each bit has one of following values:
1: Corresponding MBSFN subframe is configured for ESS.
0: Corresponding MBSFN subframe is not configured for ESS.

Starting from first radio frame and from first or leftmost bit in bitmap, configuration applies to subframes #1, #2, #3, #6, #7, and #8 in sequence of four radio frames.

MBSFN subframe configuration for eNodeB using four frames.

ESS NSA:
110000 000000 100000 000000 (decimal 12584960).

ESS SA:
100100 000000 110100 000000 (decimal 9440512) or
100100 000000 111100 000000 (decimal 9441024).
Dependencies:
When cell uses NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId configured.
Must be set to 12584960 when secondaryCellOnly is true.
Must be set to 9440512 or 9441024 when secondaryCellOnly is false.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q4. Deprecated: Since 22.Q1. Replaced by NRCellDU::essMbsfnSubframeVariant. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: MBSFN subframe configuration variant for ESS enabled cell.
Range and Values:
NSA_BASIC
SA_BASIC
SA_SIB_ROBUST_15_PERCENT
NSA_25_PERCENT
SA_25_PERCENT
NSA_SA_35_PERCENT
NSA_SA_45_PERCENT
NSA_SA_55_PERCENT
Dependencies:
Applicable when cell uses NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId configured.
If secondaryCellOnly is true, it must be set to one of following values:
- NSA_BASIC
- NSA_25_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_35_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_45_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_55_PERCENT
If secondaryCellOnly is false, it must be set to one of following values:
- SA_BASIC
- SA_SIB_ROBUST_15_PERCENT
- SA_25_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_35_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_45_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_55_PERCENT

Parameter Description:
Configuration of PDSCH early start symbol for ESS enabled cell.

Defines earliest possible start symbol for PDSCH.

Only applicable if license for LTE-NR FDD Spectrum Sharing with Additional NR PDSCH Symbols is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to Low-Band, ESS cells.
Dependencies: Must be NO_PDSCH_EARLY_START in non-ESS cell, when NRSectorCarrier::essScPairId is empty in MO instance referenced from nRSectorCarrierRef.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of ExtCaPriority MO.

Automatically set to ExtCaPriority=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.
Dependencies: Referenced ExtCaPriority instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Additional round trip delay required for Indoor Connect 8855 or similar component.

Value must be taken from external connecting system.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies:
Can be different from default value if following conditions are met:
- subCarrierSpacing is set to 30, that is, Mid-Band cell.
- tddUlDlPattern is set to either TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02.
- rachPreambleFormat is set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01.
- cellRange is equal to 5000.

Parameter Description:
Number of fixed wide beams for periodic SR in PRACH slot according to SSB relation.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.
For Low-Band and Mid-Band cells, value must be FIX_WB_FOR_PERIODIC_SR_NONE.

Attribute is for 12 wide beam configuration and is scaled automatically for 24 wide beam support.
Dependencies: For High-Band cells, must be FIX_WB_FOR_PERIODIC_SR_NONE if cellRange is less than or equal to 1100 m and set to FIX_WB_FOR_PERIODIC_SR_HIGH if cellRange is greater than 4000 m.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if the administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether additional uplink scheduling occasion is used in sparse BWP.

If true, improved uplink performance is expected in sparse BWP by using more uplink scheduling occasions.

Only applicable to 4+2+4, 4+1 and 8+2 TDD pattern.
Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Only applicable if license for NR Dynamic Power Optimizer is present and feature is active.
Whether Improved Uplink Link Adaptation feature is enabled for cell.

Whether NR cell supports emergency services for UEs in limited service mode.

If true, attribute indicates by broadcasting ims-EmergencySupport in SIB1 that cell supports emergency services for UEs in limited service mode.
If false, IMS emergency call is not supported by network in cell for UEs in limited service mode.

Only applicable if license for NR Limited Service Mode Emergency Call Support is present and feature is active.

Whether Ericsson Interference Sensing feature is enabled.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Value true is only applicable to RAN Compute group 5 and higher.
Dependencies: Must be false if advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is false.

Parameter Description:
Activation mode of NR Interference Mitigation for Downlink Scheduling feature.

Only applicable to Low-Band cells.
Dependencies:
Can be PM_ONLY or ACTIVATED when following conditions are fulfilled:
- pdschStartPrbStrategy is RANDOM_START_WITHIN_BAND
- prioBoundaryCrb is non-empty
Must be DEACTIVATED otherwise.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of advanced downlink MU-MIMO Mid-Band layers at cell level that are co-scheduled.

Values higher than 8 are only applicable to RAN Compute group 5 and higher.
Dependencies:
If value is greater than 0, advancedDlSuMimoEnabled must be true.
If value is greater than 0, speedAdvMuThresh must be less than or equal to speedAdvSuThresh.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of simultaneously supported UEs in sparse BWP per cell.

If 0, DCI-based BWP switch is not allowed.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Only applicable if license for NR Dynamic Power Optimizer is present, feature is active and configured in the cell.

Maximum time administrativeState is set to SHUTTINGDOWN.

Value -1 means wait forever.

Maximum value possible for PUCCH format 3 resources to be allocated for downlink HARQs.

Actual number configured might be adjusted by algorithm.

Expected maximum speed of moving UE.

If empty, system configures a value depending on cell configuration.
For High-Band, value is UP_TO_10KMPH.
For Low-Band or Mid-Band, value is UP_TO_100KMPH.

For High-Band, one of following values is allowed:
- UP_TO_10KMPH
- UP_TO_50KMPH
- UP_TO_100KMPH
- Empty
For Low-Band and Mid-Band cells, one of following values is allowed:
- UP_TO_100KMPH
- UP_TO_200KMPH
- UP_TO_350KMPH
- UP_TO_500KMPH
- Empty
Range and Values:
UP_TO_10KMPH
UP_TO_50KMPH
UP_TO_100KMPH
UP_TO_200KMPH
UP_TO_350KMPH
UP_TO_500KMPH
Dependencies:
For Low-Band and Mid-Band cells, values UP_TO_200KMPH, UP_TO_350KMPH and UP_TO_500KMPH can only be set if following conditions are fulfilled:
- ul256QamEnabled is false.
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is false.
- ulTxSwitchingEnabled is false.
- dlMaxMuMimoLayers is 0.
- ulMaxMuMimoLayers is 0.
- pdschAllowedInDmrsSym is false.

For High-Band cells:
- Values UP_TO_50KMPH and UP_TO_100KMPH can only be set if dftSOfdmPuschEnabled is false.
- Value must be UP_TO_10KMPH if cellRange is greater than 4300 m.
- Value must be UP_TO_10KMPH if tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_05 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_06.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of connected users for scheduling PUSCH on RACH symbols.

Maximum number of connected users for each cell to allow scheduling PUSCH on symbols configured for RACH.
If 0, scheduling of PUSCH on symbols configured for RACH is not allowed.

Only applicable when this cell is configured as PSCell.

Maximum number of HARQ transmissions for Msg3.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.

Whether NB-IoT cell is deployed with LTE and NR cells.

Only applicable if license for LTE-NR FDD Spectrum Sharing with NB-IoT is present and feature is active.
NR Cell Identity.
Network signaling value to adjust UE power.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can reduce UE power.
Dependencies:
If 55, bandListManual must contain 77 only and referenced NRSectorCarrier::arfcnDL must be in range 630000..636666.
If 57, bandListManual must contain 77 only and referenced NRSectorCarrier::arfcnDL must be in range 643334..665333.

Parameter Description:
Number of Contention-Based Random Access (CBRA) preambles.

If rachRestrictedSetConfig is not UNRESTRICTED_SET, value 16 is used.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies: Must be equal to or less than totalNoOfRaPreambles.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Reference to an instance of CgSwitch MO.

Automatically set to CgSwitch=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.

Applicable to NR-DC.
Dependencies: Referenced CgSwitch instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Whether NR cell is deployed in an LTE-NR coexistence in a Low-Band or Mid-Band cell.

If true when using TDD, tddUlDlPattern settings are validated with respect to alignment to LTE TDD. Value of N_TA, offset is configured to 39936 x T_c to enable uplink frame alignment with an LTE TDD network.
If true when using FDD, value of N_TA, offset is configured to 0 x T_c to enable uplink frame alignment with an LTE FDD network.
If false, value of N_TA, offset is configured to:
- 25600 x T_c, if ulCaTimeAlignmentMode is N_TA_O_STANDARD
- 39936 x T_c, if ulCaTimeAlignmentMode is N_TA_O_39936

See 3GPP TS 38.133, 5G; NR; Requirements for support of radio resource management, chapter 7.1.2.
Dependencies:
Can be true if following apply:
- tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01 and tddSpecialSlotPattern is TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_01, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_04, or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05.
- tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04 and tddSpecialSlotPattern is TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03.
- tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08 and tddSpecialSlotPattern is TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03.
- ulCaTimeAlignmentMode is N_TA_O_STANDARD.
Must be false otherwise.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: The Physical Cell Identity (PCI) of the NR cell.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether NR radio resource partitioning is enabled.

Only applicable if license for NR Radio Resource Partitioning is present and feature is active.
Only applicable if cellResourceMappingRef is non-empty.
Not applicable to High-Band cells.

References to instances of NRSectorCarrier MO.

If empty, no SectorCarrier instance is used in this cell.
Dependencies:
Must be unique if configured, that is, two cells cannot reserve same NRSectorCarrier instance.

At most one NRCellDU instance under GNBDUFunction instance can reference more than one NRSectorCarrier instance. Configuring more than one NRSectorCarrier instance is only applicable to Mid-Band TDD cell, and all NRSectorCarrier instances referenced by this attribute must fulfill following conditions:
- arfcnDL, arfcnUL, bSChannelBwDL, bSChannelBwUL, configuredMaxTxPower, txDirection, noOfTxAntennas, noOfRxAntennas and cbrsEnabled must have same value.
- txPowerRatio must be 100.
- sectorEquipmentFunctionRef must be unique.
- maxAllowedEirpPsd must be -1.
- essScPairId must be empty.
- ueAssistedPrecodingOptEnabled must be false.
- noOfTxAntennas and noOfRxAntennas must be non-zero.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED. Value can only be changed if administrativeStates of all NRSectorCarrier instances are LOCKED, when number of NRSectorCarrier instances is greater than 1.

Parameter Description:
Data size threshold used by gNodeB to label a user session as heavy traffic.

SRS resources are only allocated to users with this label.

If 0, data size is not considered, and SRS is allocated to users in order of arrival.

Only applicable if license for Advanced Downlink Single-User MIMO Mid-Band is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.

Packet age threshold used by gNodeB to label a user session as heavy traffic.

If 0, packet age is not considered for SRS allocation. Only data size is considered if nrSrsDlBufferVolThr value is non-zero.

If values of this attribute and nrSrsDlBufferVolThr are both zero, SRS is allocated in order of arrival.

Only applicable if license for Advanced Downlink Single-User MIMO Mid-Band is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.

NR Tracking Area Code (TAC).

Values 0, 16777214, and 16777215 are not broadcast in SIB1.
Change Take Effect:
If GNBDUFunction::dynTACConfigEnabled is true, immediately.
Otherwise Next cell unlock.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute without cell lock and unlock can cause PWS service impact.
Dependencies: NRCellDU instance can have no AdditionalPLMNInfo instances with duplicable nRTAC and pLMNIdList.

Parameter Description:
Whether nRTAC can be included in SIB1.

If false, nRTAC is excluded from SIB1 and NR cell is not used as a PCell within any of the PLMNs in pLMNIdList.
If true and secondaryCellOnly is false, nRTAC is included in SIB1.
The operational state.

Whether PCell downlink data offloading is enabled.

If true, cell is offloaded to SCells with larger pipe size.

Can only be true for Low-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Fraction of beamforming gain considered by PDCCH Link Adaptation to enhance PDCCH capacity.

Decreasing from 100 to 0 shifts the emphasis of PDCCH Link Adaptation (LA) from PDCCH capacity enhancement to PDCCH robustness enhancement.

If 0, PDCCH LA does not consider beamforming gain difference between codebook-based PDCCH beamforming and common channel PDCCH beamforming. PDCCH robustness improves.

If 100, PDCCH LA fully consider beamforming gain difference between codebook-based PDCCH beamforming and common channel PDCCH beamforming.
PDCCH LA is more aggressive in aggregation level selection. PDCCH capacity improves.

If a value between 0 and 100, PDCCH LA partially considers beamforming gain difference between codebook-based PDCCH beamforming and common channel PDCCH beamforming.

Only applicable if license for Coverage- and Capacity-Optimized PDCCH Beamforming is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

SINR offset added to SINR estimated from CQI to determine PDCCH SINR.

To determine aggregation level, PDCCH LA utilizes SINR offset. SINR offset accounts for link and beamforming compensations.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies: The sum of the UE PDCCH offset (PdcchLinkAdaptation::pdcchLaSinrUeOffset) and any Cell PDCCH offset (pdcchLaSinrOffset) must not be outside of the [-30..30] range.

Parameter Description:
Determines how PDCCH outer loop adjustment is computed.

Only applicable to Low-Band, ESS cells.

Amount of power boosting to PDCCH for initial access.

This is applicable to following messages:
- Msg2
- Msg3 retransmission
- Msg4
- P2 refinement

Only applicable to High-Band SpCells.

Value must be 0 for Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

Attribute actualPdcchRachBoost shows actual boost.

Reference to an instance of PdcchReuseForPdsch MO.

Automatically set to PdcchReuseForPdsch=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies: Referenced PdcchReuseForPdsch instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Configuration for number of symbols used for PDCCH in each downlink slot.

Value must be MINIMUM in following cases:
- High-Band cells (TDD cells)
- Low-Band cells with bandwidth larger than 50 MHz
- Mid-Band cells (TDD cells) with bandwidth lower than 20 MHz or larger than 100 MHz

Value can be MINIMUM or ADAPT_MAX_2 for ESS cells.
Value can be MINIMUM, STATIC_2 or STATIC_3 for cells that are both FDD and non-ESS, with bandwidth of 5 MHz or 10 MHz when NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth in downlink is used (dlAvailableCrbs greater than 0).
Value can be MINIMUM, STATIC_2, ADAPT_MAX_2, STATIC_3 or ADAPT_MAX_3 for cells that are both FDD and non-ESS, with bandwidth of 15, 20 MHz or 10 MHz when NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth in downlink is not used (dlAvailableCrbs equal to 0 or empty).
Value can be MINIMUM, ADAPT_MAX_2 or ADAPT_MAX_3 for cells that are both FDD and non-ESS, with bandwidth of 25, 30, 35, 40 or 50 MHz.
Value can be MINIMUM or ADAPT_MAX_2 for Mid-Band cells (TDD) with a bandwidth of 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80, 90 or 100 MHz.

Not applicable to High-Band cells.

Whether DMRS symbols are allowed to be used for PDSCH data transmission.

If true, PDSCH can be present in symbols carrying DMRS. gNodeB determines number of DMRS CDM groups without data for each PDSCH transmission.
If false, PDSCH is not present in symbols carrying DMRS unless required by 3GPP TS 38.214, section 5.1.6.2.

The gNodeB signals UE according to 3GPP TS 38.212, section 7.3.1.2.

In ESS cell, only applicable if license for LTE-NR FDD Spectrum Sharing with Downlink Data and DMRS Multiplexing is present and feature is active.
In non-ESS cell, only applicable
- to FR1 frequencies
- if license for Downlink Data and DMRS Multiplexing is present and feature is active.
Dependencies: Must be false if maxUeSpeed is greater than 100 km/h.

Parameter Description:
Amount of power boosting to PDSCH channel carrying Msg2.

Only applicable to High-Band SpCells.

Value must be 0 for Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

Attribute actualPdschRachBoost shows actual boost.
Dependencies:
Must be set to one of following values:
- Less than or equal to 6 if referenced NRSectorCarrier::bSChannelBwDL is equal to 100.
- Less than or equal to 4 for 50 MHz if referenced NRSectorCarrier::bSChannelBwDL is equal to 50.

Parameter Description:
Mitigate interference strategy that chooses one of following ways to allocate PRBs to UEs for downlink.

- From lower frequency band edge, START_LOWER_EDGE.
- From higher frequency band edge, START_HIGHER_EDGE.
- Both from lower and higher frequency band edges by random for each slot, RANDOM_START_LOWER_OR_HIGHER.
- Random starting point for each slot for interference spreading over the whole band, RANDOM_START_WITHIN_BAND.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: PLMNs that can be served by NR cell.
Dependencies:
Maximum number of unique PLMN IDs in pLMNIdList across all instances of NRCellDU and AdditionalPLMNInfo is 12.
Maximum number of PLMN IDs in pLMNIdList allowed on NRCellDU instance and its AdditionalPLMNInfo instances is 12, under one cell instance.
Order of PLMN IDs must be same in identical pLMNIdList attributes with same nRTAC value when reused in other instances of NRCellDU and AdditionalPLMNInfo.
Different pLMNIdList attributes with same nRTAC value with one or more identical PLMN IDs are not allowed across all instances of NRCellDU or AdditionalPLMNInfo (3GPP 23.501).
NRCellDU instance can have no AdditionalPLMNInfo instances with duplicable nRTAC and pLMNIdList.

Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.
Changing primary PLMN ID, that is, first PLMN ID in pLMNIdList, is not allowed for already created cell.
If TheftDeterrence::thdStatus is LOCKED or LOCKED_PERMANENTLY, this value can only be changed when all modified PLMN IDs are part of Lock Token or Operator List.

Parameter Description:
Maximum UE uplink transmission power in serving cell.

Corresponds to parameter PEMAX in 3GPP TS 38.101.
All cells that belong to same frequency relation must be set to same value
If empty or 1000, maximum uplink power of UE is limited by UE capabilities.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

PointA value given by center frequency of resource element 0 in cell resource block 0 and indicated on a raster as NR-ARFCN.

Can only be 157 or 159 if tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_03 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04.

Parameter Description:

If true, PUSCH can be present in symbols carrying DMRS.

Only applicable if license for NR Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Mitigate interference strategy that chooses one of following ways to allocate PRBs to UEs for uplink.

- From higher frequency band edge, START_HIGHER_EDGE.

Power control parameter P0 nominal for SRS transmissions.

Controls received SINR target.

Only applicable if ul256QamEnabled is true.

If empty, value is not broadcast in SIB1.

Offset applied to signaled Qqualmin.

If empty, value is not broadcast in SIB1, and the UE applies default value of 0 dB for Qqualminoffset in 3GPP TS 38.304.
Required minimum received RSRP level in cell for cell selection or re-selection.

Offset applied to signaled Qrxlevmin.

If empty, value is not broadcast in SIB1, and the UE applies default value of 0 dB for Qrxlevminoffset in 3GPP TS 38.304.

Hysteresis that defines good radio quality for UE configured with DCI-based BWP switching.

Radio quality is considered good when greater than the sum of this value and threshold, where the threshold is value of poorRadioQualDciBwpSwitchThr.

SINR is used to represent radio quality.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Only applicable if license for NR Dynamic Power Optimizer is present, feature is active and configured in the cell.

Fraction applied to PRACH power level detection threshold.

Value lower than 10 decreases PRACH power level detection threshold.
Value higher than 10 increases PRACH power level detection threshold.

RACH preamble format.

If empty, system configures:
For Low-Band, RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_00 (F0)
For Mid-Band, RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4)
For High-Band, RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3).

For Low-Band cells, RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_00 (F0), RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4) and RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_02 (F1) are allowed.

For Mid-Band cells, RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_00 (F0) and RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4) are allowed.

For High-Band cells, RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3) and RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_04 (C2) are allowed.
Value RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4) is allowed for backward compatibility. System applies RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3).
Dependencies:
For Low-Band cells:
- Must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_00 (F0) or RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_02 (F1) if cellRange is greater than 10000 m.
- Must not be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4) if rachRootSequence is greater than 137.

For Mid-Band cells:
- Must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_00 (F0) if cellRange is greater than 5000 m.
- Must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4) if tddUlDlPattern is set to TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_07.
- Must not be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4) if rachRootSequence is greater than 137.

For High-Band cells:
- Must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3) if tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_05 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_06.
- Must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_04 (C2) if cellRange is greater than 1100 m.
- Must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3) if cellRange is greater than 6900 m.
- For High-Band cells with RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_04 (C2), license for Extended Propagation Delay Support High-Band must be present and feature be active. Otherwise cell cannot be unlocked and there is alarm.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Target random access preamble power level at network receiver side.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Configuration of restricted sets for random access preamble.

Configuration of unrestricted set, or one of two types of restricted sets for random access preamble.
First root sequence index for random access preamble generation.
Dependencies:
Must be less than 138 if rachPreambleFormat is RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_01 (B4).
Must be less than 138 for High-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Negative offset for uplink interference and noise PM counters in Radio Dot System.

The offset is applied in following PM counters:
- pmRadioRecInterferencePwrSumPrbDistr
- pmRadioRecInterferencePwrDistr
- pmRadioRecInterferencePowerDistr
- pmRadioRecInterferencePwrUlSlotXDistr, X=1..6
- pmRadioRecInterferencePwrSpecialSlotXDistr, X=1..4

The offset makes the PM counter represent the noise floor at one RU, consisting of IRU and connected Radio Dots (RD), instead of aggregated values from all RD connected to the IRU.

Use only for cell in RDS.

Whether Advanced RDS Location Support for Dedicated RAN is enabled in cell.

Only applicable if license for Advanced RDS Location Support for Dedicated RAN is present and feature is active.
Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Value true can only be set on RAN Compute group 4 or higher.
Dependencies:
If true, following condition must be fulfilled:
- subCarrierSpacing must be set to 30 (Mid-Band).
- tddUlDlPattern must not be set to TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00.
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must not be set to TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00.
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled must be false.

Parameter Description:
Whether Reduced Capability 1Rx UE for cell is enabled.

If true, IE cellBarredRedCap1Rx-r17 in SIB1 is set to notBarred and IE intraFreqReselectionRedCap-r17 in SIB1 is set to allowed.

If false, IE cellBarredRedCap1Rx-r17 in SIB1 is set to barred.

If both this attribute and redCap2RxEnabled are false, IE intraFreqReselectionRedCap-r17 is not transmitted in SIB1 and this disables Reduced Capability UE in cell.

If both this attribute and redCap2RxEnabled are true, cell supports both types of UE.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

Whether Reduced Capability 2Rx UE for cell is enabled.

If true, IE cellBarredRedCap2Rx-r17 in SIB1 is set to notBarred and IE intraFreqReselectionRedCap-r17 in SIB1 is set to allowed.

If false, IE cellBarredRedCap2Rx-r17 in SIB1 is set to barred.

If both this attribute and redCap1RxEnabled are false, IE intraFreqReselectionRedCap-r17 is not transmitted in SIB1 and this disables Reduced Capability UE in cell.

If both this attribute and redCap1RxEnabled are true, cell supports both types of UE.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

Number of RedCap UEs that are allowed to enter cell.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.

Reference to an instance of ResourceAllocTypeDl MO.

Automatically set to ResourceAllocTypeDl=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.
Dependencies: Referenced ResourceAllocTypeDl instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of RimRSSet MO.

If empty, no RimRSSet instances are used in this cell.
Dependencies:
Must be set when rimLocationEnabled set to true.

Attribute setId in RimRSSet instance referenced by this attribute must be same as setId in RimRSSet instance referenced by rimVictimRSSetRef.
Attribute setType in RimRSSet instance referenced by this attribute must be RS_2.

Referenced RimRSSet instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Whether high uplink interference state is detected.

Threshold for average IpN.

Threshold for triggering PDSCH special downlink slot and special slot blanking.

DISABLED
AUTO_MODE
SPECIAL_SLOT

AUTO_RS1
AUTO_RS1_PC

If 0, corresponding timer is disabled.

UEs with estimated UE SINR below this threshold are not scheduled in slots slated for power control by RIM power control.
