Dependencies: Must be greater than rimRS2TransStopThresh.

Parameter Description:
Minimal portion of RIM-RS1 with "Not enough" indication to stop RIM-RS2 transmission.

Only applicable if sequenceDomainPara.enableEnoughNotEnoughIndication under RimRSGlobal instance is ENABLED.
Dependencies: Must be less than rimRS2TransStartThresh.

Parameter Description:
Modifier for RIM-RS detection threshold.

Increasing value can lead to lower false alarm rate and raise missed detection rate.

RS detection time.

Period to detect RS reception. Attributes rimDetectedRS1State and rimDetectedRS2State are updated with this periodicity.
Periodicity to generate and report RIM-RS Detection report.
Whether RIM-RS1 sequence is transmitted.
Whether RIM-RS2 sequence is transmitted.

Reference to an instance of RimRSSet MO.

If empty, no RimRSSet instances are used in this cell.
Dependencies:
Must be set when rimLocationEnabled set to true.

Attribute setId in RimRSSet instance referenced by this attribute must be same as setId in RimRSSet instance referenced by rimAggressorRSSetRef.
Attribute setType in RimRSSet instance referenced by this attribute must be RS_1.

Referenced RimRSSet instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description: Threshold for triggering remote interference triggered offload.
Dependencies: Must be less than or equal to rimCLPCHighIpnRSThresh.

Parameter Description: Defines if cell prevents camping of UE instances on cell.
Dependencies:
When set to false in High-Band cells, NRSectorCarrier::txDirection must be DL_AND_UL.

If true and NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId is configured, essMbsfnSubframeVariant must be set to one of following values:
- NSA_BASIC
- NSA_25_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_35_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_45_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_55_PERCENT
If false and NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId is configured, essMbsfnSubframeVariant must be set to one of following values:
- SA_BASIC
- SA_SIB_ROBUST_15_PERCENT
- SA_25_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_35_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_45_PERCENT
- NSA_SA_55_PERCENT
If false in a CBRS-managed cell, cell must be configured as a CBRS PCell or SCell.
If true in a CBRS-managed cell, cell must be configured as a CBRS SCell Only or as a CBRS Downlink Only SCell.
See also dependencies of csiRsConfig2P, csiRsConfig4P, csiRsConfig8P, csiRsConfig16P, and csiRsConfig32P.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Current service state.

System Frame Number offset relative to GPS time.

1 radio frame is equal to 10 ms.
Dependencies: All NRCellDU instances under GNBDUFunction instance must have same value.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether SIB9 broadcast is scheduled.
Information needed for acquisition of System Information Block 2.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Information needed for acquisition of System Information Block 4.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Information needed for acquisition of System Information Block 5.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Information needed for acquisition of System Information Block 6 (SIB6).

Contains PWS warning message for ETWS primary notification.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Information needed for acquisition of System Information Block 7 (SIB7).

Contains PWS warning message for ETWS secondary notification.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Information needed for acquisition of System Information Block 8 (SIB8).

Contains PWS warning message for Wireless Emergency Alerts (WEA), also known as CMAS.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Information needed for acquisition of System Information Block 9 (SIB9).
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Length of SI scheduling window in slots.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
List of slot specific downlink link adaptation configurations.

Configuration of SFN and slot must be unique. Refer to NR Slot Specific Downlink Link Adaptation Feature Description for conflicting scenarios.

In NR TDD Mid-Band cell, only downlink slot and special slot can be configured, uplink slot is not allowed.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies:
Struct members sfnPeriodForLaConfig, sfnOffsetForLaConfig, and slotForLaConfig must define unique SFN and slot among configurations in list.

Struct member slotForLaConfig cannot refer to uplink slot in NR TDD Mid-Band cell. Position of uplink slot depends on value of tddUlDlPattern.

Parameter Description:
List of supported network slices.

If empty, cell can be used for all UEs regardless of their S-NSSAI.
Dependencies: The pLMNIdList and nRTAC can only associate with one unique sNSSAIList (TAC + PLMN must give unique sNSSAI list).

Parameter Description:
Effective UE speed threshold to decide if reciprocity-based MU-MIMO is used.

Reciprocity-based MU-MIMO is allowed if effective UE speed is less than or equal to this threshold.
Effective UE speed is estimated speed based on measured doppler in gNodeB.
Applicable to periodic SRS and aperiodic SRS.

Only applicable if advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true and maxNoOfAdvancedDlMuMimoLayers is greater than 0.
Values lower than 500 are only applicable to RAN Compute group 5 and higher.
Dependencies: Must be less than or equal to speedAdvSuThresh if maxNoOfAdvancedDlMuMimoLayers is greater than 0.

Parameter Description:
Effective UE speed threshold to decide if reciprocity-based SU-MIMO is used.

Reciprocity-based SU-MIMO is allowed if effective UE speed is less than or equal to this threshold.
Effective UE speed is estimated speed based on measured doppler in gNodeB.
Applicable to periodic SRS and aperiodic SRS.

Taken into consideration whether an SRS resource can be configured or released to a UE in case of periodic SRS and whether an SRS resource can be triggered to a UE in case of aperiodic SRS.

Only applicable if advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true.

Values lower than 500 are only applicable to RAN Compute group 5 and higher.
Dependencies: Must be greater than or equal to speedAdvMuThresh if maxNoOfAdvancedDlMuMimoLayers is greater than 0.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of SrPeriodicityPoolSet MO.

If empty, for Low-Band and Mid-Band cells, cell is configured with short, common, and long pools with predefined values.
If empty, for High-Band cells, cell is configured with default pool with predefined values.

Applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells if license NR Service-Adaptive SR Periodicity is present and feature is active.
Applicable to High-Band cells if license Service-Adaptive SR Periodicity High-Band for Dedicated RAN or license Service-Adaptive SR Periodicity High-Band for Public RAN is present and feature is active.
Dependencies:
SrPeriodicityPoolSet::fddTddUlDlPattern in referenced SrPeriodicityPoolSet instance must be FDD for FDD (Low-Band) cell or match tddUlDlPattern for TDD (Mid-Band or High-Band) cell.

SrPeriodicityPoolSet::subCarrierSpacing in referenced SrPeriodicityPoolSet instance must be equal to subCarrierSpacing.

Referenced SrPeriodicityPoolSet instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of SrPeriodicity MO.

Automatically set to SrPeriodicity=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.

Applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells if license NR Service-Adaptive SR Periodicity is present and feature is active.
Applicable to High-Band cells if license Service-Adaptive SR Periodicity High-Band for Dedicated RAN or license Service-Adaptive SR Periodicity High-Band for Public RAN is present and feature is active.
Dependencies: Referenced SrPeriodicity instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description: SRS frequency hopping bandwidth.
Dependencies:
Must be FULL if advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true and NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is active (dlAvailableCrbs greater than 0 or ulAvailableCrbs greater than 0).
Must be FULL if tddSpecialSlotPattern is TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02.
Must be FULL if aperiodicSrsEnabled is true.
If not FULL, advancedDlSuMimoEnabled must be true.

Parameter Description: SRS periodicity in slots in a Mid-Band cell.
Dependencies: If 5, tddUlDlPattern must equal TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02.

Parameter Description:
Controls how uplink symbols and comb offsets are selected for SRS transmissions.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Value COMMON is only applicable to RAN Compute group 5 and higher.

Duration of SSB transmission.

If empty, system selects SSB duration, which is presented in ssbDurationAutoSelected.

For Low-Band cells, value must be empty, 1, or 2.
For Mid-Band cells, value must be empty or 1.
For High-Band cells, value must be empty, 3, 4, or 5.
Dependencies:
Must be 1 for ESS Low-Band cells, if ssbOffset is 1.
For High-Band cells, following apply:
- Must be 3, 4, 5 or empty if CommonBeamforming::ssbBeams is SSB_BEAMS_12 under NRSectorCarrier instance referenced by nRSectorCarrierRef.
- Must be 4, 5 or empty if CommonBeamforming::ssbBeams is SSB_BEAMS_24 under NRSectorCarrier instance referenced by nRSectorCarrierRef.
- Must be empty if CommonBeamforming::ssbBeams is PRODUCT_DEFAULT under NRSectorCarrier instance referenced by nRSectorCarrierRef.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Automatically selected SSB Duration.

Calculated at cell unlock if ssbDuration is empty. Value is empty if ssbDuration is configured.

Frequency (NR-ARFCN) of the SSB transmission.

The frequency identifies the position of resource element RE=#0 (subcarrier #0) of resource block RB#10 of the SS block. The frequency must be positioned on the NR global frequency raster, as defined in 3GPP TS 38.101, and within bSChannelBwDL.

If 0, the system selects an SSB frequency, which is presented in ssbFrequencyAutoSelected.
Dependencies:
For cells below 3 GHz, difference between NR-ARFCN value set for arfcnDL on NRSectorCarrier instance and for this attribute must be zero or one of following:
- multiple of 3 for subCarrierSpacing 15 kHz, that is, (arfcnDL - ssbFrequency) mod 3 = 0
- multiple of 6 for subCarrierSpacing 30 kHz, that is, (arfcnDL - ssbFrequency) mod 6 = 0.

For cells above 3 GHz, difference between NR-ARFCN value set for arfcnDL on NRSectorCarrier instance and for this attribute must be zero or a multiple of two, that is, (arfcnDL - ssbFrequency) mod 2 = 0.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Automatically selected SSB frequency (NR-ARFCN).

Calculated at cell unlock if ssbFrequency is set to 0. Empty if ssbFrequency greater than 0.

GSCN of SSB.

SSB location on synchronization raster (required for primary cell in stand-alone gNodeB). If empty, SSB is not placed on synchronization raster.

Configured SSB index.

If empty, gNodeB selects SSB index value which is presented in ssbIndexAutoSelected.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Not applicable to ESS cells.
Dependencies: Must be empty if ssbTimeShiftEnabled is false.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Automatically selected SSB index.

Empty if ssbIndex is non-empty.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Not applicable to ESS cells.

Offset of SSB transmission window.

Corresponds to the SSB time domain position.
If empty, the system selects an SSB duration, which is presented in ssbOffsetAutoSelected.

For ESS Low-Band, values empty, 0 and 1 are allowed.
Otherwise, values empty and 0 are allowed.
Dependencies: Must be less than ssbPeriodicity.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Automatically selected SSB Offset.

Calculated at cell unlock if ssbOffset is empty. Value is empty if ssbOffset is configured.
Periodicity of SSB transmission.
Dependencies:
For Low-Band and Mid-Band cells:
- must be 10 or 20 ms if ssbTimeShiftEnabled is false.
- must be 20 ms if ssbTimeShiftEnabled is true.

For High-Band cells:
- must be 20 ms.

Must be 20 ms if cell uses NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId configured.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Boost value to be applied to SSB power.

Only applicable if license for SSB Power Boost is present and feature is active.

For High-Band cells, values must be as follows:
- For 100 MHz cells, less than or equal to 5.
- For 50 MHz cells, less than or equal to 2.

For Mid-Band cells, values must be as follows:
- For 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80, 90, or 100 MHz, less than or equal to 6.
- For 20 MHz, less than or equal to 4.
- For 15 MHz, less than or equal to 3.
- For 10 MHz, less than or equal to 1.
- For other bandwidth, equal to 0.
Actual boost is seen in actualSsbPowerBoost.

Value must be 0 for Low-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Boost value applied to SSB power during Massive MIMO Sleep in addition to ssbPowerBoost.

Used to compensate for SSB power lost during Massive MIMO Sleep.

If empty, value of 0 is used.

Combined value of ssbPowerBoost and this attribute must be as follows:
- For 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80, 90, or 100 MHz, less than or equal to 6.
- For 20 MHz, less than or equal to 4.
- For 15 MHz, less than or equal to 3.
- For 10 MHz, less than or equal to 1.
- For other bandwidths, equal to 0.

Actual boost is only seen in actualSsbPowerBoost when Massive MIMO Sleep feature is in a sleep state.

Only applicable if Massive MIMO Sleep Mode license is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Sub-carrier spacing of the SSB.
Dependencies: Must be equal to subCarrierSpacing.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether NR SSB Time Shift feature is enabled.

Only applicable if license for NR SSB Time Shift is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Not applicable to ESS cells.
Dependencies:
If true, following apply:
- tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01, but tddSpecialSlotPattern must not be set to TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05.
- tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_03, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08.
- ssbPeriodicity must be 20.
- trsPeriodicity must be greater than or equal to 20.
- csiRsPeriodicity must be greater than or equal to 40.
- tddBorderVersion must be DISABLED.

If false, ssbIndex must be empty.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Sub-carrier spacing for common elements at cell level.
Dependencies:
Must be 15 for Low-Band cells, 30 for Mid-Band cells, and 120 for High-Band cells.
Must be 15 if cell uses NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId configured.
Must be 30 if advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true.

Must match SrPeriodicityPoolSet::subCarrierSpacing if srPeriodicityPoolSetRef is non-empty.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
TDD border version.

TDD border version can be used in certain geographic areas in different countries to mitigate downlink to uplink interference. Unaligned TDD patterns lead to cross-link interference when tddUlDlPattern and tddSpecialSlotPattern of adjacent cells have certain values. Both patterns must be adapted to avoid downlink and uplink in the same time slot. This means that this attribute must be set in both cells.

Only applicable to Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies:
Can be VERSION_1 for Mid-Band cells in following cases:
- When tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01 and tddSpecialSlotPattern is TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03.
- When tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02 and tddSpecialSlotPattern is TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00 or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02.

Must be DISABLED if ssbTimeShiftEnabled is true.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
TDD special slot pattern.

Defines the downlink, guard, and uplink symbols of special slot or slots for NR TDD in Mid-Band or High-Band cell.

Configured special slot pattern must be applicable to Mid-Band in Mid-Band cells.
Configured special slot pattern must be applicable to High-Band in High-Band cells.

For High-Band cell, default value TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00 is overridden by the system to High-Band applicable special slot pattern TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02.
Range and Values:
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_01
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_04
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_06
TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_07
Dependencies:
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00, following dependencies apply:
- tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02, or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_03.
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled must be false.
- rdsUeAdvancedPosEnabled must be false.
- tddBorderVersion can be VERSION_1, if TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02.
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_01, following dependencies apply:
- tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02, or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_03.
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02, following dependencies apply:
- tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02, or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_03.
- tddBorderVersion can be VERSION_1, if TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02.
- srsHoppingBandwidth must be FULL.
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03, following dependencies apply:
- tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01, TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04, or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08.
- tddBorderVersion can be VERSION_1, if TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01.
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_04, tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01.
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05, following dependencies apply:
- tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04.
- rimPdschSlotBlankMode must be DISABLED.
- ssbTimeShiftEnabled must be false, if TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01.
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_06, following dependencies apply:
- tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_05 or TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_06.
- cellRange must be less than or equal to 1100 m.
- rachPreambleFormat must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3).
- maxUeSpeed must be UP_TO_10KMPH.
For TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_07, following dependencies apply:
- tddUlDlPattern must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_07.
Must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03 or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_04 or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05 if aperiodicSrsEnabled is true.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
TDD uplink-downlink pattern configuration.

Defines downlink, uplink, and special slot pattern for NR TDD in Mid-Band or High-Band cell.

Configured uplink-downlink pattern must be applicable to Mid-Band in Mid-Band cells.
Configured uplink-downlink pattern must be applicable to High-Band in High-Band cells.
Must be TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00 in Low-Band cells.

For High-Band cell, default value TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00 is overridden by the system to High-Band applicable TDD pattern TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02.
Range and Values:
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_03
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_05
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_06
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_07
TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08
Dependencies:
For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_00, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_01, or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02.
- nrLteCoexistence must be false.
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled must be false.
- rdsUeAdvancedPosEnabled must be false.
- csiRsPeriodicity cannot be 10 or 20.
- ssbTimeShiftEnabled must be false.
- prachConfigIndex cannot be 156 or 157.

For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_01, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_01, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_04, or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05.
- tddBorderVersion can be VERSION_1, if TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03.
- configuredGrantPeriodicity cannot be 5.
- ConfiguredGrantUeCfg::configuredGrantPeriodicity cannot be 5 in any ConfiguredGrantUeCfg instance referenced by UeBbProfileUeCfg::configuredGrantUeCfgRef under UeBbProfile instance referenced by ueBbProfileRef.
- ssbTimeShiftEnabled can be true, if tddSpecialSlotPattern is not TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05.
- prachConfigIndex cannot be 155, 157 or 159.

For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_02, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_01, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02.
- nrLteCoexistence must be false.
- tddBorderVersion can be VERSION_1, if TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00 or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02.
- prachConfigIndex cannot be 155, 156 or 158.

For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_03, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_00, TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_01, or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_02.
- nrLteCoexistence must be false.
- prachConfigIndex cannot be 155, 156 or 158.

For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_04, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03 or TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_05.
- configuredGrantPeriodicity cannot be 5.
- ConfiguredGrantUeCfg::configuredGrantPeriodicity cannot be 5 in any ConfiguredGrantUeCfg instance referenced by UeBbProfileUeCfg::configuredGrantUeCfgRef under UeBbProfile instance referenced by ueBbProfileRef.
- prachConfigIndex cannot be 155, 156 or 158.

For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_05 and TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_06, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_06,
- cellRange must be less than or equal to 1100 m.
- rachPreambleFormat must be set to RACH_PREAMBLE_FORMAT_03 (A3).
- maxUeSpeed must be UP_TO_10KMPH.
- ssbTimeShiftEnabled must be false.

For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_07, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_07
- nrLteCoexistence must be false.
- ssbTimeShiftEnabled must be false.

For TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08, following dependencies apply:
- tddSpecialSlotPattern must be TDD_SPECIAL_SLOT_PATTERN_03.
- trsPeriodicity must be greater than or equal to 20.
- configuredGrantPeriodicity cannot be 5.
- ConfiguredGrantUeCfg::configuredGrantPeriodicity cannot be 5 in any ConfiguredGrantUeCfg instance referenced by UeBbProfileUeCfg::configuredGrantUeCfgRef under UeBbProfile instance referenced by ueBbProfileRef.
- prachConfigIndex cannot be 155, 157 or 159.

Must match SrPeriodicityPoolSet::fddTddUlDlPattern if srPeriodicityPoolSetRef is non-empty in TDD (Mid-Band or High-Band) cell.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Total number of CBRA and CFRA preambles.

If rachRestrictedSetConfig is not UNRESTRICTED_SET, value 17 is used.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Dependencies: Must be equal to or greater than noOfCbraPreambles.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of TrafficGroup MO.

Automatically set to TrafficGroup=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Changing this attribute can prevent new traffic from being setup.
Dependencies: Referenced TrafficGroup instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description: TRS bandwidth configuration mode.
Dependencies:
Value FULL_BW_MUTE can only be set if dlAvailableCrbs is greater than 0.
Value PRB_52 can only be set if dlAvailableCrbs is greater than or equal to 52 when dlStartCrb modulo 4 is equal to 0.
Value PRB_52 can only be set if dlAvailableCrbs is greater than or equal to 53 when dlStartCrb modulo 4 is equal to 3.
Value PRB_52 can only be set if dlAvailableCrbs is greater than or equal to 54 when dlStartCrb modulo 4 is equal to 2.
Value PRB_52 can only be set if dlAvailableCrbs is greater than or equal to 55 when dlStartCrb modulo 4 is equal to 1.

Parameter Description:
Selected TRS mode.

If empty, TRS mode is not selected.
Periodicity of Channel State Information-Reference Signal (CSI-RS) used for tracking purpose.
Dependencies:
Must be greater than or equal to 20 if one of following apply:
- ssbTimeShiftEnabled is true.
- tddUlDlPattern is TDD_ULDL_PATTERN_08.

Must be 40 if cell uses NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId configured.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
TRS power boosting.

Selects different power boosting levels for CSI-RS transmission for tracking purposes.

For Low-Band and Mid-Band cells, values 0, 3, 4, and 6 are allowed.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Whether TRS resource allocation shifting is activated.
Dependencies: Must be DEACTIVATED, when cell uses NRSectorCarrier instance with essScPairId configured.

Parameter Description:
Bit mask that indicates UE-specific rank restriction for codebook of Type1 single panel.

Only applicable to Low-Band or Mid-Band cells.

Following values can be applied:
- Bitmap b00001111, no rank restriction, value 15.
- Bitmap b00000001, rank restricted to 1, UE can only report rank 1, value 1.
- Bitmap b00000010, rank restricted to 2, value is 2.
- Bitmap b00000100, rank restricted to 3, value is 4.
- Bitmap b00001000, rank restricted to 4, value is 8.
- Bitmap b00000011, rank restricted to 1, or 2, value is 3.
- Bitmap b00000101, rank restricted to 1, or 3, value is 5.
- Bitmap b00001001, rank restricted to 1, or 4, value is 9.
- Bitmap b00000110, rank restricted to 2, or 3, value is 6.
- Bitmap b00001010, rank restricted to 2, or 4, value is 10.
- Bitmap b00001100, rank restricted to 3, or 4, value is 12.
- Bitmap b00000111, rank restricted to 1, 2, or 3, value is 7.
- Bitmap b00001011, rank restricted to 1, 2, or 4, value is 11.
- Bitmap b00001101, rank restricted to 1, 3, or 4, value is 13.
- Bitmap b00001110, rank restricted to 2, 3, or 4, value is 14.

Note that this is a configuration for all UEs in cell. However, if UE capability conflicts with the value, bitmap b00000001 will be set to this UE.

Reference to an instance of UeBbProfile MO.

Automatically set to UeBbProfile=Default instance, unless manually set to refer to another MO instance.
Dependencies: Referenced UeBbProfile instance must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
Mode of UE specific DRX.

If ENABLED and a UE specific DRX cycle is provided in paging message from AMF, that is shorter than Paging::defaultPagingCycle value, then value from AMF overrides value in RBS.

Whether 256-QAM support in uplink is enabled.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
For High-Band cells, value must be false.

Only applicable if license for 256-QAM Uplink Low/Mid-Band is present and feature is active.
Dependencies: Can be true if maxUeSpeed value is not UP_TO_200KMPH, UP_TO_350KMPH or UP_TO_500KMPH.

Parameter Description:
Total amount of CRBs available for uplink channels.

Total uplink channel bandwidth corresponds to sum of uplink available CRBs and uplink blanked CRBs.
Total uplink channel bandwidth is configured in NRSectorCarrier::bSChannelBwUL. Formula for conversion to number of CRBs is defined in 3GPP TS 38.211.

If empty, there is no bandwidth restriction and no blanking in uplink.
If 0, there is no available CRB, NR Channel Bandwidth is fixed to NRSectorCarrier::bSChannelBwUL.
Dependencies:
For allowed values of this attribute and ulStartCrb, see feature description NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth and Ericsson Spectrum Sharing All-In-One User Guide.
Downlink available bandwidth [dlStartCrb, dlStartCrb + dlAvailableCrbs - 1] must be in the range of uplink available bandwidth [ulStartCrb, ulStartCrb + ulAvailableCrbs - 1] if following options apply:
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true.
- NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is used (dlAvailableCrbs > 0 or ulAvailableCrbs > 0).
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Timing advance offset configuration in Low-Band cells.

Only applicable if license for NR Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Only applicable to non-ESS Low-Band cells.
Dependencies: Can be N_TA_O_39936 only in non-ESS Low-Band cells and if nrLteCoexistence is false.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of co-scheduled uplink MU-MIMO layers at cell level.

Uplink MU-MIMO is disabled when value is 0.
Only used if Control Channel Beamforming is present and active.
Only used if radio equipment supports AAS configuration.

Value must be 0 for Low-Band and High-Band cells.
For Mid-Band cells, values 0, 2 and 4 are allowed.
Dependencies: ulMaxMuMimoLayers can be greater than 0 if maxUeSpeed value is not UP_TO_200KMPH, UP_TO_350KMPH or UP_TO_500KMPH.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether uplink robust link adaptation is enabled.

Only applicable if license for Critical IoT is present and the High-Band feature is active.

Must be false for Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Supported uplink subcarrier spill-over value of radio to which ESS cell pair is connected.

Spill-over means that subcarrier or subcarriers of guard band NB-IoT PRB can exceed PRB subcarrier range of ESS NR cell.
Spill-over value represents capability of radio which defines exceeding subcarrier number compared with outmost subcarrier of NR.

Start position of CRBs available for uplink channels.

Blanked CRBs appear before start position and after the range of available CRBs.
Dependencies:
For allowed values of this attribute and ulAvailableCrbs, see feature description NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth and Ericsson Spectrum Sharing All-In-One User Guide.
Downlink available bandwidth [dlStartCrb, dlStartCrb + dlAvailableCrbs - 1] must be in the range of uplink available bandwidth [ulStartCrb, ulStartCrb + ulAvailableCrbs - 1] if following options apply:
- advancedDlSuMimoEnabled is true.
- NR Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is used (dlAvailableCrbs > 0 or ulAvailableCrbs > 0).
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether NR Switched Uplink for Throughput Boost feature is enabled in cell.

For Mid-Band cells and High-Band cells, value must be false.

Only applicable if license for NR Switched Uplink for Throughput Boost is present and feature is active.
Only applicable to Low-Band cells.
Dependencies: Can be true if maxUeSpeed value is not UP_TO_200KMPH, UP_TO_350KMPH or UP_TO_500KMPH.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.
Whether NRPimCancellationConfig instance is created by operator or by the system.
Whether DL carriers for PIM calculation are included.
The value component of the RDN.

Reference to an instance of PimCancellationFunction MO.

Reference specifies PIM cancellation function in which NRSectorCarrier instance participates.

NRPimCancellationConfig instances belonging to same NRSectorCarrier instance cannot refer to same PimCancellationFunction instance.

PIM cancellation mode on uplink carriers.

Cannot be set to value different than EXCLUDED for more than one NRPimCancellationConfig instance under an NRSectorCarrier instance.

The administrative state.

If set to SHUTTINGDOWN, the state is immediately brought to LOCKED.

Altitude of transmitter antenna position measured in meters.

Positive value means height, negative value means depth. Altitude is in relation to WGS84 reference ellipsoid. WGS84 reference ellipsoid is based on theoretical mean sea level.

If empty, value is not defined.

NR Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number (NR-ARFCN) for downlink.

If value is less than 600000, value must be a multiple of 20, except for band n41 cells, where value must be multiple of 6.
Only even values if between 600000 and 2016666.
Only odd values supported if above 2016667.
Dependencies:
Must be equal to arfcnUL if PowerBackoffDir is created.
If txDirection is DL or DL_AND_UL, value must be non-zero.
Cannot be a High-Band ARFCN if GNBDUFunction::multiTddPatternSmEnabled is true.
Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
NR Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number (NR-ARFCN) for uplink.

If value is less than 600000, value must be a multiple of 20, except for band n41 cells, where value must be multiple of 6.
Only even values if between 600000 and 2016666.
Only odd values supported if above 2016667.
Dependencies:
Must be equal to arfcnDL if PowerBackoffDir is created.
If txDirection is DL_AND_UL, value must be non-zero.
Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
The availability status.

It contains details about operationalState.
Range and Values:
IN_TEST
FAILED
POWER_OFF
OFF_LINE
OFF_DUTY
DEPENDENCY
DEGRADED
NOT_INSTALLED
LOG_FULL
DEPENDENCY_LOCKED
DEPENDENCY_FAILED
DEPENDENCY_SHUTTINGDOWN
DEPENDENCY_RECOVERY
DEPENDENCY_HOLDING

Parameter Description:
Azimuth null characteristics.

Used for reducing interference towards target in a known direction.
Only takes effect if radio equipment that supports AAS configuration.
Two sequence elements cannot have the same value for horizontalAngle struct member.

If empty, azimuth null-steering is not applied.

Must be empty for Low-Band and High-Band cells.
Dependencies:
If non-empty, CommonBeamforming::coverageShape must be MACRO_1 and CommonBeamforming::customComBfwWideBeam must be empty.
If nullSteeringMode is not COMMON_BEAMFORMING, and at least either this attribute or elevationNull is non-empty, then NRCellDU::csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether EVM-aware power backoff is allowed when Radio Unit cannot support reporting backoff data.

Only applicable to Remote Radio Units.
BS Channel bandwidth in MHz for downlink.
Dependencies:
Must be equal to bsChannelBwUL except for bands allowing for asymmetric bandwidths (n66 in the present product release). If asymmetric channel bandwidth is configured, the configured uplink and downlink bandwidths must be part of a asymmetric bandwidth combination.

If essScPairId is configured, supported values are 10, 15, and 20.

Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Precondition:
Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.
Value cannot be changed if reservedBy contains NRCellDU MO with administrativeState UNLOCKED.

Parameter Description: BS Channel bandwidth in MHz for uplink.
Dependencies:
Must be equal to bsChannelBwDL except for bands allowing for asymmetric bandwidths (n66 in the present product release). If asymmetric channel bandwidth is configured, the configured uplink and downlink bandwidths must be part of a asymmetric bandwidth combination.

If essScPairId is configured, supported values are 10, 15, and 20.

Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Precondition:
Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.
Value cannot be changed if reservedBy contains NRCellDU MO with administrativeState UNLOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Whether sector carrier is externally supervised by authorized channel of Spectrum Access System.

For CBRS sector carrier, set to true.
Dependencies: Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
When to stop the transmission on assigned spectrum in UTC.

Sector carrier becomes disabled when it expires or is empty.

Updated by setCbrsTxExpireTime action.

String format is YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ.

Only applicable when cbrsEnabled is true.

Maximum output power to be used in an NRSectorCarrier instance.

Output power is evenly distributed over antenna connectors used for TX transmission allocated for NRSectorCarrier instance.
For High-Band and mmWave, EIRP value per cross-polarized beam pair must be used.

Value 0 must not be used.

Note: Value has an impact on maxTransmissionPower which displays the used output power.
Dependencies:
If maxRegPowerLimit is not -1, value must be less than or equal to maxRegPowerLimit.
Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Transmission point coverage.

Described by radius, bearing and opening angle.
Downlink antenna calibration information.

Whether downlink antenna calibration is enabled.

If true, Antenna Calibration DL Failure alarm is raised on AAS-capable radios.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause throughput loss.
Disabling antenna calibration can impact beamforming.
Dependencies: If false and noOfTxAntennas is 8, PowerBackoffDir::powerBackoffDirEnabled must be false.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Elevation null characteristics.

Used for reducing interference towards target in a known direction.
Only takes effect if radio equipment that supports AAS configuration.
Two sequence elements cannot have the same value for verticalAngle struct member.

If empty, elevation null-steering is not applied.

Must be empty for Low-Band and High-Band cells.
Dependencies:
If non-empty, CommonBeamforming::coverageShape must be MACRO_1 and CommonBeamforming::customComBfwWideBeam must be empty.
If nullSteeringMode is not COMMON_BEAMFORMING, and at least either this attribute or azimuthNull is non-empty, then NRCellDU::csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
The gNodeB internal ID attribute for SectorCarrier within Ericsson Shared Spectrum.

Must be unique and non-zero in gNodeB for ESS NRSectorCarrier instances.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
ID attribute that pairs SectorCarriers from gNodeB and eNodeB in Ericsson Spectrum Sharing (ESS).

Must be unique within gNodeB and eNodeB.
Dependencies:
If configured, arfcnDL must be different than arfcnUL, and bsChannelBwDL and bsChannelBwUL must be 10, 15, or 20.

If empty, DlOuterLoop::dualOuterLoopEnabled must be false and NRCellDU::essPdschEarlyStartConfig must be NO_PDSCH_EARLY_START in MO instance under NRCellDU instance with nRSectorCarrierRef referring to this NRSectorCarrier instance.
Must be empty if parent NRCellDU instance references more than one NRSectorCarrier instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Radio frame start offset of sector carrier at antenna reference point-relative GPS time.

Tc = 1 / (480 * 10e3 * 4096) seconds.
Dependencies: All NRSectorCarrier instances under GNBDUFunction instance must have same value.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: RF Reference Frequency of downlink channel.
RF Reference Frequency of uplink channel.

Latitude of transmitter antenna position.

Positive value means north, negative value means south.

Local Coordinate System (LCS) to Global Coordinate System (GCS) translation information.

If empty, this attribute is not used.

Only applicable to RAN Compute group 4 and higher.

Longitude of transmitter antenna position.

Positive value means east, negative value means west.
Whether Massive MIMO Sleep Mode feature is enabled.
Dependencies: When set to ENABLED (1) or DETECTION (2), mMimoSleepTimeGroupRef must be set.

Parameter Description: Status of feature Massive MIMO Sleep Mode.

Maximum EIRP density threshold per MHz required for EIRP restriction.

If -1, no EIRP restriction.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
If not -1, txPowerRatio must be 100.
Must be -1 if parent NRCellDU instance references more than one NRSectorCarrier instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Maximum EIRP density threshold per MHz required for EIRP restriction.

Only applicable for limiting EIRP within maximum EIRP stated by Ericsson product specifications. Only recommended for markets with restrictions on EIRP.

If empty, EIRP restriction is not employed.

If non-empty, attributes on CommonBeamforming MO cannot be updated while NRSectorCarrier::administrativeState is UNLOCKED.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
If non-empty, then txPowerRatio must be 100.
Must be empty if parent NRCellDU instance references more than one NRSectorCarrier instance.
Deprecated: Since 23.Q1. Replaced by maxAllowedEirpPsd. Planned to be removed.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Maximum downlink transmission power.

If -1, configuredMaxTxPower is unrestricted.
Dependencies: If not -1, value must be greater than or equal to configuredMaxTxPower.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Maximum possible power at antenna reference point.

Measured for all downlink channels in all TX branches used simultaneously in NRSectorCarrier instance.

Reference to an instance of MMimoSleepTimeGroup MO.

If empty, no MMimoSleepTimeGroup instance is used in this sector carrier.
Dependencies:
Must be set when massiveMimoSleepEnabled set to ENABLED or DETECTION.
Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.

Parameter Description:
A PMI distance-based threshold used for adaptive power limitation in Advanced Downlink MU-MIMO.

Used to determine if UEs must be of the same group.

Only applicable to AAS radios.

Number of antennas NRSectorCarrier MO uses for uplink transmission.

Only used for NRSectorCarrier instances on sectors with non-AAS capable radios.
If 0, NRSectorCarrier instance uses maximum number of RX antennas, else specified number is used.

For Low-Band cells, value must be less than or equal to 8.
For Mid-Band cells, value must be less than or equal to 8.
For High-Band cells, value must be less than or equal to 2.
Dependencies:
Must be equal to the size of rfBranchRxRef list if rfBranchRxRef list is non-empty.
Must be 0 if txDirection is DL only.
If cbrsEnabled is true, and this NRSectorCarrier instance is referenced by an NRCellDU instance which is configured as a CBRS PCell/SCell or as a CBRS SCell Only, value must be greater than 0.
If cbrsEnabled is true, and this NRSectorCarrier instance is referenced by an NRCellDU instance which is configured as a CBRS Downlink Only SCell, value must be 0.
Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Must be non-zero if parent NRCellDU instance references more than one NRSectorCarrier instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Number of antennas NRSectorCarrier MO uses for downlink transmission.

Only used for NRSectorCarrier instances on sectors with non-AAS capable radios.
If 0, NRSectorCarrier instance uses maximum number of TX antennas, else specified number is used.

For Low-Band cells, value must be less than or equal to 4.
For Mid-Band cells, value must be less than or equal to 8.
For High-Band cells, value must be less than or equal to 2.
Dependencies:
Must be equal to size of rfBranchTxRef list if rfBranchTxRef list is non-empty.
Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Must be non-zero if parent NRCellDU instance references more than one NRSectorCarrier instance.
If 8 and dlCalibrationEnabled is false, PowerBackoffDir::powerBackoffDirEnabled must be false.
If 2 or 4, PowerBackoffDir::powerBackoffDirEnabled must be false.
If not 0 or 4, PowerBackoff::powerBackoffEnhanced must be false.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Number of used RX antennas.

Maximum number is determined by noOfRxAntennas.
Empty means undefined.

Number of used TX antennas.

Maximum number is determined by noOfTxAntennas.
Empty means undefined.

Whether NR Micro Sleep TX feature is enabled.

If false, feature is disabled.

Not applicable to NRSectorCarrier instances that are on sectors with AAS capable radios nor RDS.

Only applicable in radio equipment supporting Micro Sleep TX. For more information on hardware support, see NR Micro Sleep TX feature description.

NRPPa Cell Portion ID.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
The value component of the RDN.

Spatial null-steering mode that determines impacted downlink channels.

Only applicable to Mid-Band.
Dependencies: If not COMMON_BEAMFORMING and at least one of azimuthNull or elevationNull is non-empty, NRCellDU::csiRsConfig8P.csiRsControl8Ports must have a value other than OFF.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: The operational state.
Minimum slot interval between two blanked slots in downlink.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause degradation of downlink throughput.

Parameter Description:
PIM Avoidance behavior level.

Only applicable to Low-Band sector carriers.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause degradation of downlink throughput.

Parameter Description:
Whether PIM Avoidance is enabled on Baseband.

True if both of following conditions apply:
- Value of pimAvoidLevel is not DISABLED.
- Value of pimDetected is true.

Whether SectorCarrier is identified as a PIM victim.

PIM Detection can identify a SectorCarrier as a PIM victim if SectorCarrier is affected by interference from passive intermodulation. Details on interference can be collected with PM events.

If empty, PIM Detection is not active for this SectorCarrier instance.

Only applicable to Low-Band NRSectorCarrier instances.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q1. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Whether PIM Detection is activated for SectorCarrier.
Dependencies:
Cannot be true while GNBDUFunction::pimAutoDetectionEnabled is true.
Can only be true for FDD (Low-Band) sector carriers.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q1. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Coverage area of transmission point as a polygon used for UE positioning.

Each polygon corner is described by latitude and longitude pair and represented with one position in the sequence. The other configured polygon corners follow in sequence. At least three configured corners required in polygon when function is active. Points must be connected in given order. Last point is connected to first point.

Backoff mode for Modulation-Aware Power Control feature.

Not applicable to radio equipment that supports AAS High-Band configuration.

Backoff offset.

Optional backoff offset for higher order modulation in addition to value calculated by Modulation-Aware Power Control feature.

A negative offset reduces backoff but never boosts power over nominal output power.

Not applicable to radio equipment that supports AAS High-Band configuration.

Power averaging time for EMF exposure power measurements in Massive MIMO AAS Systems.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.
Must be empty for Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
If empty in High-Band cell, system uses value 360.

Whether radio report is evaluated for EVM-aware power backoff.

Only applicable to Remote Radio Units.

Radio transmit operating mode.

Better performance can be achieved in downlink according to cell traffic profile when radio is configured to maximum output level.
Green modes are power saving modes, which can reduce energy consumption when radio transmits in low power modes.
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

References to instances of RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch MO.

References are used for deterministic RX carrier allocation if noOfRxAntennas is greater than 0.

If empty, carrier allocation is based on the RF Branch MOM list by default behavior.
Dependencies:
If non-empty, number of references must be equal to noOfRxAntennas.
List must contain only RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch instances, but not both.
All references in both this attribute and rfBranchTxRef must refer to either RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch instances.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
References to instances of RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch MO.

The references are used for deterministic TX carrier allocation if noOfTxAntennas is greater than 0.

If empty, carrier allocation is based on the RF Branch MOM list by default behavior.
Dependencies:
If non-empty, number of references must be equal to noOfTxAntennas.
List must contain only RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch instances, but not both.
All references in both this attribute and rfBranchRxRef must refer to either RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch instances.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Used power at antenna reference point.

Covers all downlink channels in all TX branches used simultaneously in NRSectorCarrier instance.

Represents the scaled power based on scaling factor, txPowerRatio, being applied to the allocated power at antenna reference point, maxTransmissionPower.

Value is set every time txPowerState is set to STABLE.
Reference to an instance of SectorEquipmentFunction MO.
Dependencies: Must be unique among NRSectorCarrier instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Transmission direction.

Value DL is only allowed in High-Band cells.
Dependencies:
If DL, value of noOfRxAntennas must be 0 and value of arfcnDL must be non-zero.
If DL_AND_UL, values of arfcnDL and arfcnUL must be non-zero.
Must have same value in all instances referenced by same NRCellDU instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
Change rate for downlink output power to reach txPowerRatio.

Example: If 5, a change of txPowerRatio from 100 to 80 will take 4 seconds.
Change Take Effect: In an unlocked NRSectorCarrier a change will take effect at the next change of txPowerRatio.

Parameter Description:
Whether configuredMaxTxPower is locked.

If true, configuredMaxTxPower cannot be changed and MO cannot be deleted.

Once set to true there is no possibility to change the value back to false unless a node re-integration is performed.
Precondition: Can only be changed when the value is false and administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description:
DL output power ratio.

Default value is 100 %. At unlock of NRSectorCarrier the current value will be set directly. When the value is changed on an unlocked NRSectorCarrier instance, the TX power changes with rate txPowerChangeRate.
Change Take Effect: If a previous change in txPowerRatio is currently ongoing, the latest change will be started once the previous change has completed. Otherwise the current change will be started immediately.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Must be 100 if maxAllowedEirpPsd is not -1.
Must be 100 if parent NRCellDU instance references more than one NRSectorCarrier instance.

Parameter Description: DL output power state.
Whether NR UE-Assisted Precoding Optimization feature is enabled.
Dependencies:
If true, NRCellDU::csiRsConfig2P.csiRsControl2Ports must be ON and NRCellDU::csiRsConfig4P.csiRsControl4Ports must be TWO_ONE.
Must be false if parent NRCellDU instance references more than one NRSectorCarrier instance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if administrativeState is LOCKED.

Parameter Description: Status of NR UE Assisted Precoding Optimization feature.
Time gap between two NR UE Assisted Precoding Optimization events.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause degradation of downlink throughput.
Changing this attribute can cause more frequent AC-events, during which one UE suffers performance degradation.

Parameter Description: Uplink antenna calibration information.
The value component of the RDN.

Paging cycle T.

Used by the RBS and broadcasted in SIB1.
Change Take Effect: After all cells in same gNodeB-DU have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.
Disturbances: If cell lock/unlock is not performed immediately after changing defaultPagingCycle, the number of discarded paging messages increases

Parameter Description:
Number of PFs in the DRX cycle.

For example, one T is every radio frame, half T is every second radio frame, quarter T is every fourth radio frame etc.

For High-Band cells, value T is not supported, instead value T1_2, that is, half T is used.
Change Take Effect: After all cells in same gNodeB-DU have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

Parameter Description:
Number of POs for one PF.

For ESS cells, value 4 is not allowed.
For High-Band cells, values 2 and 4 are not supported, instead value 1 is used.
Change Take Effect: After all cells in same gNodeB-DU have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

Parameter Description:
Time for which received paging is retained or queued in RBS before it is discarded.

Recommended to set to same as or lower value than T3513 in AMF. Timer T3513 is defined in 3GPP 24.501. Timer T3513 starts when AMF sends Request paging and stops when it receives SERVICE REQUEST or REGISTRATION REQUEST.
Change Take Effect: After all cells in same gNodeB-DU have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

Parameter Description:
Time for which received eDRX paging is retained or queued in RBS before it is discarded.

Recommended to set to same as or lower value than paging resend timer in AMF, to prevent RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after re-sent copy is received from AMF.

Only applicable to Low-Band and Mid-Band cells.
Only applicable to RAN Compute group 4 and higher.
Change Take Effect: After all cells in same gNodeB-DU have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Whether partition mapping is used for a resource partition for CA SCell traffic.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
If true, listResourcePartitionRef and priorityPartition5qiList must be empty.
Only one PartitionMapping instance under a CellResourceMapping instance can have value set to true.

Parameter Description: References to instances of ResourcePartition MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Referenced ResourcePartition instances must be unique among PartitionMapping instances under CellResourceMapping instance.
Referenced ResourcePartition instances must be under same GNBDUFunction instance as PartitionMapping instance.

Parameter Description:
Identity of a policy group.

If empty, partitions are not mapped to a group.
Identity for observability of resource partition.
Dependencies: Must be unique among PartitionMapping instances under a CellResourceMapping instance.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Name of a PartitionMapping.

List of 5QI values to be included in priority partition.

To be appended to 5QI values configured in parent CellResourceMapping instance.

If empty, no 5QI values shall be included in priority partition.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Must be empty if caPartition is true.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of ResourceAllocationPolicy MO.

If empty, residual partition is used.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Sum of number of ResourceAllocationPolicy instances and ServicePolicy instances referenced must be less than 25 for a CellResourceMapping instance. This shall not include resourceAllocationPolicyRef in PartitionMapping instance with caPartition set to true.
Referenced ResourceAllocationPolicy instance must be under ResourceAllocationPolicies instance under same GNBDUFunction instance as PartitionMapping instance.

Parameter Description: Reference to an instance of ResourcePartition MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Must be unique in PartitionMapping instances under a CellResourceMapping instance.
Must be empty if caPartition is true.
Referenced ResourcePartition instance must be under ResourcePartitions instance under same GNBDUFunction instance as PartitionMapping instance.
Deprecated: Since 23.Q2. Replaced by listResourcePartitionRef. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.
UE specific SINR offset added to estimated SINR.
Dependencies: The sum of the UE PDCCH offset (pdcchLaSinrUeOffset) and any Cell PDCCH offset (NRCellDU::pdcchLaSinrOffset) must not be outside of the [-30..30] range.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
The value component of the RDN.
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

UE configuration group type.

UE configuration group type that is applied in contained PdcchReuseForPdschUeCfg instances.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.

Whether PDCCH and PDSCH Frequency Division Multiplexing in UE is enabled.

Not applicable in High-Band cells.
The value component of the RDN.

Preference UE group list.

List of preference UE group identifiers.

If empty, MO instance matches preference UE group identifiers not defined in prefUeGroupList of any other MO instances under parent MO instance.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
The value component of the RDN.

UE configuration group type.

UE configuration group type that is applied in contained SrPeriodicityUeCfg instances.

Whether coverage adaptive scheduling request periodicity is enabled.

Only applicable to High-Band cells.
Change Take Effect: New connection. PSCell setup and PSCell change in the Secondary Node.

Parameter Description:
NR radio quality threshold.

Used for configuring SR periodicity on PUCCH.

Below this threshold, uplink channel quality is assumed limited hence SR Periodicity on PUCCH is configured to longer duration.

Uplink SINR is used for estimating uplink coverage.

Recommended to be set to a value 3 dB higher than endcUlNrLowQualThresh.

Only applicable if covAdaptSrPEnabled is True.
Only applicable to High-Band cells.
Change Take Effect: New connection. PSCell setup and PSCell change in the Secondary Node.

Parameter Description:
NR radio quality hysteresis.

Used for configuring SR periodicity on PUCCH.

Quality needs to be hysteresis better than covAdaptSrPNrLowQualThresh to configure SR periodicity on PUCCH back to shorter duration.

Uplink SINR is used for estimating uplink coverage.

Only applicable if covAdaptSrPEnabled is True.
Only applicable to High-Band cells.
Change Take Effect: New connection. PSCell setup and PSCell change in the Secondary Node.

Parameter Description:
RSRP threshold.

SR periodicity is configured to longer duration if reported RSRP value is below RSRP threshold.

RSRP is reported in 3GPP TS 38.331 CG-ConfigInfo.

Applicable at PSCell setup and PSCell change in the Secondary Node (for NR-DC and EN-DC).

Recommended to be set to a value 3 dB lower than dftSOfdmPuschStartRsrpThresh.

Only applicable if covAdaptSrPEnabled is True.
Only applicable to High-Band cells.
Change Take Effect: PSCell setup and PSCell change in the Secondary Node.

For all preference UE group identifiers in prefUeGroupList attributes under same parent SrPeriodicity instance, exactly one SrPeriodicityCovAdaptUeCfg instance must exist that combines given preference UE group identifier with an empty ueGroupList.

If 15 kHz, fddTddUlDlPattern must be set to FDD.

Parameter Description: Central Unit (CU) name.

IPv4 address of the gNodeB-CU-CP.

The input format is four fields of digits, separated by dots. Each field may consist of three digits. The value of each field is in the range 0..255.

IPv6 address of gNodeB-CU-CP.

Format is eight fields, separated by colons.

Each field consists of four hexadecimal characters. Value of each field is in range 0..FFFF.

Leading zeroes can be omitted in a field, and multiple groups of 16 bits of zeroes can be compressed to ::.

The :: can appear only once in an address.

Parameter Description: Power allocated for extension TRX.

References to MO RfBranch(es) instances, LDN.
MO represents RF branch that extension TRX uses for RX. 
One reference per used RX RfBranch. 
Index vise the references can be interpreted as logical antennas.

Parameter Description:
Used for identifying a Extension Antenna Site in Combined cells site statistics in BSC and OSS/ENM. Normally use the same extAntSiteIndex value for all MO ExtTrx instances on an Extension Antenna Site.
Recommended values 1..7. Value 0 is reserved for Main Antenna Site. Not recommended values 0 and 8..63 will be changed to 7, and these changes will affect PM data from BSC to OSS/ENM.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Part of the licensed capacity a baseband processing resource is allowed to use. Relevant for eNB in dual DU configuration, i.e. ENodeBFunction supported by 2 or 3 DU, each with a BbProcessingResource. Dual DU is not supported with Baseband Unit.

Default setup is ENodeBFunction::licCapDistrMethod=SYSTEM, and BbProcessingResource::licCapDistr=0. In runtime, licCapDistr then shows the distribution made automatically by the RBS.

If ENodeBFunction::licCapDistrMethod=OPERATOR, licCapDistr decides the allowed capacity for each BbProcessingResource.
Dependencies: Can only be set if ENodeBFunction::licCapDistrMethod=OPERATOR. Then the sum for all (2 or 3) BbProcessingResource instances must be 100%.

Parameter Description: Bin step size representing PRB license unit for the DL/UL distribution of PRB capacity usage.

Max UL baseband capacity available on unlocked Baseband hardware.
Maximum limit of UL capacity that can be granted by baseband HWAC. This level sets the limit at emergency unlock.

Granted UL baseband capacity.
Available capacity of corresponding Baseband HWAC property per Baseband HW.

Parameter Description:
The administrative state.
Note: If this attribute is set to SHUTTING_DOWN, it will immediately go into the state LOCKED.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED or SHUTTINGDOWN can cause loss of traffic. Loss of MBMS capability if Internal MCE is used.

Parameter Description:
The fully-qualified domain name of the MME.
A valid domain name consists of 1 or more labels separated by dots (.).
Valid characters for a label are limited to letters a - z, A - Z, digits 0 - 9, and the character - (dash). Character case is preserved. Length of a label may not exceed 255 characters.
NOTE: The first and last character in the domain name must be one of the following alphanumeric characters a - z, A - Z or digits 0 - 9. For more information refer to RFC 952, 1101 and 1123.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible loss of MBMS capability if Internal MCE is used.

Parameter Description:
The primary IP address of the MME. A unique IP address is required for each MME.
The input format is four fields of digits, separated by dots. Each field consists of three digits. The value of each field must be in the range 0-255.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

The secondary IP address of the MME. A unique IP address is required for each MME.
The input format is four fields of digits, separated by dots. Each field consists of three digits. The value of each field must be in the range 0-255.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

The primary IPv6 address of the MME.
The input format is eight fields, separated by colons. Each field consists of four hexadecimal characters. The value of each field must be in the range 0-FFFF. Leading zeroes can be omitted in a field, and multiple groups of 16 bits of zeroes can be compressed to ::. The :: can be used only once in an address.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

The secondary IPv6 address of the MME.
The input format is eight fields, separated by colons. Each field consists of four hexadecimal characters. The value of each field must be in the range 0-FFFF. Leading zeroes can be omitted in a field, and multiple groups of 16 bits of zeroes can be compressed to ::. The :: can be used only once in an address.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.
The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

The destination address used for initialization of the underlying SCTP association of the latest successful M3-Setup.

The IP address can be an IPv4 or an IPv6 address.

Note: usedIpAddress never changes during the lifetime of the SCTP association.

Defines the weight of "time since last use" when determining the relation priority. The priority is used when deciding which relation to remove, when too many relations have been added. The priority is also used when determining which UTRAN cell to perform mobility measurements for.

Specifies if detection of problematic cell is activated or not.

Threshold that controls when hoSuccLevel changes from HIGH to MEDIUM and conversely. Works together with probCellDetectMedHoSuccTime.

Note: hoSuccLevel of a cell relation is changed from HIGH to MEDIUM if handover execution success rate of this relation is less than or equal to probCellDetectMedHoSuccThres, but for at least time defined by probCellDetectMedHoSuccTime time. hoSuccLevel of a cell relation is changed from MEDIUM to HIGH if handover execution success rate of this relation is greater than probCellDetectMedHoSuccThres, but for at least time defined by probCellDetectMedHoSuccTime/2.

Only applicable when problematicCellPolicy is set to AUTO_DETECT or AUTO_DETECT_AND_BAR.
Dependencies: probCellDetectMedHoSuccThres >  probCellDetectLowHoSuccThres.

Parameter Description:
Time that controls when hoSuccLevel changes from HIGH to MEDIUM and conversely. See also description for probCellDetectMedHoSuccThres.

Only applicable when problematicCellPolicy is set to AUTO_DETECT or AUTO_DETECT_AND_BAR.

Threshold that controls when hoSuccLevel changes from MEDIUM to LOW and conversely. Works together with probCellDetectLowHoSuccTime.

Note: hoSuccLevel of a cell relation is changed from MEDIUM to LOW if handover execution success rate of this relation is less than or equal to probCellDetectLowHoSuccThres, but for at least time defined by probCellDetectLowHoSuccTime. hoSuccLevel of a cell relation is changed from LOW to MEDIUM if handover execution success rate of this relation is greater than probCellDetectLowHoSuccThres, but for at least time defined by probCellDetectLowHoSuccTime/2.

Only applicable when problematicCellPolicy is set to AUTO_DETECT or AUTO_DETECT_AND_BAR.
Dependencies: probCellDetectMedHoSuccThres > probCellDetectLowHoSuccThres.

Parameter Description:
Time that controls when hoSuccLevel changes from MEDIUM to LOW and conversely. See also description for probCellDetectLowHoSuccThreas.

Only applicable when problematicCellPolicy is set to AUTO_DETECT or AUTO_DETECT_AND_BAR.

This parameter together with b2Threshold2RscpUtra specifies "The Received Signal Code Power" (RSCP)  threshold value for reported power for a cell to be automatically added as neighbor. The equation for calculating the RSCP threshold is b2Threshold2RscpUtra + cellAddRscpThresholdUtranDelta.

This parameter together with b2Threshold2EcNoUtra specifies "Ratio of energy per modulation bit to noise spectral density"  threshold value for reported EcNo for a cell to be automatically added as neighbor. The equation for calculating the EcNo threshold is b2Threshold2EcNoUtra + cellAddEcNoThresholdUtranDelta.
