The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

The maximum target number of measurement reports per hour for each GeranFrequencyGroupRelation. The number of measurement reports may deviate from the target.
Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.
Dependencies: Must be higher than or equal to anrGeranMeasReportMin.

Parameter Description:
The minimum target number of measurement reports per hour for each GeranFrequencyGroupRelation. The number of measurement reports may deviate from the target.
Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.
Dependencies: Must be lower than or equal to anrGeranMeasReportMax.

Parameter Description:
The decrease in the target number of measurement reports per GeranFrequencyGroupRelation each time an Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) GERAN measurement report is received with only known neighbor cells.
Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

Defines the increase in the target number of measurement reports per GeranFrequencyGroupRelation each time an Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) GERAN measurement report is received with unknown neighbor GERAN cells or an unknown cell found in GERAN mobility report.
Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.
This parameter indicates if ANR should be able to modify RIM associations to GERAN cells

Defines the increase in the target number of measurement reports for each GeranFreqGroupRelation each time a PCI measurement report is received with known cell but the corresponding RAC missing.
Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.
Indicates whether more CGI measurements shall be initiated to find RAC for cells that were previously added by ANR with missing RAC.
Whether detection of problematic cell is activated for GERAN.
The value component of the RDN.
Lists all PLMN IDs that are available for outgoing handover toward EUTRAN, UTRAN or GERAN cell and X2 setup.
PLMN that plmnWhiteList is applied to.
Target RAT for CS fallback.
The value component of the RDN.
Activates or deactivates ANR function support for NR for one RBS. Value is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for Automated Neighbor Relation feature.

Length of gNodeB ID bit string representation.

gNodebIdLength is the length that ANR assumes for all newly found nodes.
gNodeBId can be 22-32 bits and localCellId can be 4-14 bits.

Whether ESS NR neighbor cell information is used for ANR.

If true, ESS NR neighbor cell information is transmitted to neighbor eNodeBs through X2. ESS NR neighbor cell information received from neighbor eNodeBs is used for ANR to supplement a measurement on ESS NR cell not transmitting SIB1.
Change Take Effect: Next X2 setup or eNB Configuration Update message transmitted for sending ESS NR neighbor cell information. Immediately when looking up ESS NR neighbor cell information.

Parameter Description:
Whether to allow other vendor MME to identify MORAN configured en-gNB.

If true, separate en-gNB instance for MORAN Cell is transferred into Connected en-gNB List over S1.
Dependencies: Only applicable when ENodeBFunction::endcX2IpAddrViaS1Active is true.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q1. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
ANR criteria to suspect if PCI conflict cell exists for each UE.

If number of NR random access failures reaches this value, NR neighbor cell is suspected as PCI conflict for the UE.
If set to 0, NR random access failure is not monitored for suspecting a PCI conflict.

ANR criteria to detect PCI conflict cell.

If number of EN-DC-capable UEs that suspect PCI conflict for cell reaches this value, ANR function is triggered to detect unknown PCI neighbor cells that have PCI conflicts.
Dependencies: Only applicable if endcRachFailThrPerUe is more than 0.

Parameter Description:
SCG session time to detect NR random access failure for EN-DC-capable UE.

NR random access failure is detected if RRC SCGFailureInformationNR message is sent with information elements randomAccessProblem or syncReconfigFailure-SCG in failureType within specified time.

If set to 0, SCG session time is not considered.

Recommended value to set is greater than Rrc::t304 defined under GNBDUFunction instance for SCG that is provided to UE by SCG radio configuration. A value shorter than Rrc::t304 can lead to missing an NR random access failure for finding PCI conflict suspect cell.
Whether ANR finds NR PCI conflict cell.

ANR-specific threshold for RSRP value for NR cell to be automatically added as neighbor.

Only used if received measurement report trigger quantity is set to SS_RSRP.

ANR-specific threshold for RSRQ value for NR cell to be automatically added as neighbor.

Only used if received measurement report trigger quantity is set to SS_RSRQ.

Whether frequency and cell relation can be changed as NR frequency change over EN-DC X2 message.

If set to ADD_FREQREL or ADD_FREQREL_IF_CELLREL_EXIST, a new GUtranFreqRelation instance can be added for a changed frequency and an existing GUtranCellRelation instance can be moved to a different GUtranFreqRelation instance for a changed frequency.
The value component of the RDN.
Time lapsed before request for new poll if no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the UL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause significantly higher drop rate.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of PDUs before polling for a STATUS report.

Special value: 0 means infinity.

Time lapsed before request for new poll.

If no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the DL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set, new poll is sent. Not applicable for Massive IoT.

Maximum number of PDUs before polling for a STATUS report.

Special value: 0 means infinity.

Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in DL.

Stopping and indicating to RRC if RLC threshold is reached. Not applicable for Massive IoT.
Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in UL before stopping and indicating to RRC that the RLC threshold is reached.
Disturbances: Lowering the value of this attribute can cause significantly higher drop rate.
Dependencies: ulMaxRetxThreshold >= ulMaxRetxThresholdLow

Parameter Description: Overrides ulMaxRetxThreshold in case of high eNodeB uplink RLC buffer utilization.
Disturbances: Lowering the value of this attribute can cause significantly higher drop rate.
Dependencies: ulMaxRetxThresholdLow <= ulMaxRetxThreshold

Parameter Description:
Timer that supervises poll for STATUS PDU.

Used for CE level 0 CAT-M equipment in uplink DRB.
AM RLC uplink transmitter waits for RLC STATUS feedback after sending poll for status before retransmitting poll.

Timer that supervises poll for STATUS PDU.

Used for CE level 0 CAT-M equipment in downlink DRB.
AM RLC downlik transmitter waits for RLC STATUS feedback after sending poll for status before retransmitting poll.
Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in DL. Values higher than 7 will be treated as 7.
Dependencies: Can be overridden by QciProfilePredefined::dlMaxHARQTxQci or QciOperatorDefined::dlMaxHARQTxQci when QCI has highest priority.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Overridden by ulTtiBundlingMaxHARQTx when UE is in TTI Bundling mode.
Can be overridden by QciProfilePredefined::ulMaxHARQTxQci or QciOperatorDefined::ulMaxHARQTxQci when QCI has highest priority.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Maximum number of HARQ transmissions for downlink COM Msg4. When set to 0, the value of the attribute dlMaxHARQTx will be used instead.

Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL when UE is in TTI Bundling mode.

In TTI bundling mode one HARQ transmission handles four consecutive repetitions.
Dependencies: Valid only when feature TTI Bundling is active. Overrides ulMaxHARQTx when UE is in TTI Bundling mode.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Reordering timer Cat-M CE Level 0.
Reordering timer Cat-M CE Level 1.
The value component of the RDN.
This timer is used by the receiving end of the Acknowledged Mode (AM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in eNB for SRB1 or SRB2, to detect loss of uplink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
Disturbances: Low values can cause high drop rate.

Parameter Description:
Time lapsed before request for new poll.

If no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the DL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set, new poll is sent. Not applicable for Massive IoT.

Maximum number of PDUs before polling for a STATUS report.

Special value: 0 means infinity.

Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in DL.

Stopping and indicating to RRC if RLC threshold is reached. Not applicable for Massive IoT.
Time lapsed before request for new poll if no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the UL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set.
Disturbances: High values can cause high drop rate.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of PDUs before polling for a STATUS report.
Special value: 0 means infinity.
Time before sending STATUS report when a Sequence Number is outstanding.
Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in UL before stopping and indicating to RRC that the RLC threshold is reached.
Disturbances: Low values can cause high drop rate.

Parameter Description:
Timer used by NB-IoT UE with twoHARQ-ProcessesConfig set to true.

Time before triggering RLC STATUS report, when DL RLC sequence number is out of sequence.

Timer used in eNodeB for NB-IoT SRB1 and SRB1bis with twoHARQ-ProcessesConfig set to true.

This timer is used by receiving end of AM RLC entity to detect loss of UL RLC protocol data units at lower layers.

Timer that supervises the poll for STATUS PDU used by NB-IoT downlink.

AM RLC DL transmitter waits for RLC STATUS feedback after sending poll for STATUS before retransmitting the poll.

Timer for the UE to supervise the poll for STATUS PDU used by NB-IoT uplink.

AM RLC UL transmitter waits for RLC STATUS feedback after sending poll for STATUS before retransmitting the poll.

Timer that supervises poll for STATUS PDU.

Used for CE level 0 CAT-M equipment in uplink SRB.
AM RLC uplink transmitter waits for RLC STATUS feedback after sending poll for status before retransmitting poll.

Timer that supervises poll for STATUS PDU.

Used for CE level 0 CAT-M equipment in downlink SRB.
AM RLC downlink transmitter waits for RLC STATUS feedback after sending poll for status before retransmitting poll.

Reordering timer Cat-M CE level 0.

RLC tReordering timer is used when RLC PDUs arrive to the receiving entity out of order. This can happen in case HARQ retransmissions for the same radio bearer overlap in time.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q4 planned to be removed

Parameter Description:
Reordering timer Cat-M CE level 1.

RLC tReordering timer is used when RLC PDUs arrive to the receiving entity out of order. This can happen in case HARQ retransmissions for the same radio bearer overlap in time.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q4 planned to be removed

Parameter Description: Maximum value to indicate the set of MPDCCH repetition numbers for CE level 0.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q4 planned to be removed

Parameter Description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN). Valid values for this MO type are: 0, 1, 2, or 3. The values correspond to logical channel group IDs in 3GPP TS 36.321.
Label for free use.
Contains a list of QciProfile instances that reserve this MO instance.

Scheduling algorithm used for a certain QCI.

Only applicable if license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and feature is active.
Range and Values:
RESOURCE_FAIR
EQUAL_RATE
PROPORTIONAL_FAIR_HIGH
PROPORTIONAL_FAIR_MEDIUM
PROPORTIONAL_FAIR_LOW
MAXIMUM_C_OVER_I
DELAY_BASED
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Value DELAY_BASED can only be used if serviceType is VOIP or PTT.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Label for free use.

Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203  (Release 8). Each instance of this MO has a unique value for the QCI.

Special value: 0 refers to a default QCI profile activated whenever a profile related to a specific QCI has not been defined.
Dependencies: Each qci must be set to a unique value.

Parameter Description:
Decimal part of QCI-related priority.
Fractional part of priority is defined by priorityFraction attribute.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: (priority + priorityFraction) > 0 AND (priority * 10 + priorityFraction) <= 140

Parameter Description: The contribution from eNodeB to the Packet Delay Budget (PDB) for a QCI. Packet delays outside eNodeB e.g. in the transport network are excluded. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and active.

Parameter Description: The Differentiated Services Code Point for a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI). This corresponds to mappings from RAN QoS to Transport Network QoS.
Dependencies: Applied if bearer has Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) value for which DSCP value is not configured in dscpArpMap attribute. Otherwise, value configured in dscpArpMap attribute is used.

Parameter Description: Refers to an instance of LogicalChannelGroup. Assigns a Logical Channel Group to a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI).
Active Queue Management (AQM) mode
An offset to the PDB used by Active Queue Management (AQM).
Dependencies: pdb + pdbOffset >= 0

Parameter Description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected. Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Radio Link Control (RLC) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.322.
Dependencies:
RLC UM must be configured (rlcMode = UM) to set this attribute to 5. RLC AM must be configured (rlcMode = AM) to set this attribute to 16. 16-bit RLC SN is only applied if:
- extendedRLC-SN-SO-Field-r13 is indicated by UE; and
- 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension license is enabled; and
- UE is capable of at least 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation.
Otherwise, default value of 10-bit RLC SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

Parameter Description: Indicates the Packet Data Convergence Protocol (PDCP) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.323.
Dependencies:
The rlcMode attribute must be set to UM to set this attribute to 7. The rlcMode attribute must be set to AM to set this attribute to 15.
15-bit PDCP SN is only applied on following conditions:
- The pdcp-SN-Extension capability is indicated by UE
- UE is category 11 or above
- UE is capable of at least 3CC carrier aggregation
- License for 3CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension is present and feature is activated
Otherwise, default value of 12-bit PDCP SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

Parameter Description: This timer is used by the receiving end of Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in UE, to detect loss of downlink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
Dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

Parameter Description: This timer is used by the receiving end of the Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in eNB, to detect loss of uplink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
Dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

Parameter Description: RLC Mode
Dependencies: Can only be set to AM if rlcSNLength is set to 10 or 16 and pdcpSNLength is set to 12 or 15. Must be set to UM if rlcSNLength is set to 5 or pdcpSNLength is set to 7.

Parameter Description: Indicates if the resource type of the Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) is Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) or non-GBR as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203.
Enables forwarding of data for this QCI. However, forwarding of DL data for SN terminated bearers in EN-DC setup is always enabled and is not controlled by this attribute.
Dependencies: The parameter is only valid if the IntraLTEHODataFwd or S1HODataFwd licence is installed and active.

Parameter Description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected.

Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Indicates if the data radio bearer is subject to Absolute Priority Override.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Defines the resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
Dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses for Uplink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and the features are active.

Parameter Description: If the parameter srsAllocationStrategy in the QoS configuration for a Data radio Bearer assigned to a UE is set to ACTIVATED, then an attempt is made to allocate sounding for a UE. If several Data Radio Bearers are setup towards the UE with different QoS configurations, and the QoS configurations has different QCI parameter, an algorithm using the priority parameter in the QoS configuration, will resolve which QoS configuration that will define sounding.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses for QoS Aware Scheduler and frequency selective scheduling are present and the features are active.

Parameter Description: Parameters for service-specific load management for a certain QCI profile.

Normalized subscription quantity associated with the specific the QCI. Specifies the subscription cost of a bearer with this predefined profile.  The subscription cost is used for traffic load balancing purposes.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Tuning factor per QCI for admission control. Only valid for QCIs with resource type GBR.
Disturbances: Setting values below one means overbooking of GBR resources and thus a risk of letting in more GBR traffic than can be supported. Setting values above one means underbooking of GBR resources and thus a risk of underutilization of the resources.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Dynamic GBR admission control is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Defines the downlink resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
Dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the licenses for Downlink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and the features are active.

Parameter Description: The relative priority associated with a QCI.

Whether ROHC is enabled.
Note: Enabling ROHC is only supported for a QCI that is intended to carry RTP/RTCP/UDP based VoIP traffic as for example the standardized QCI1 or QCI with serviceType PTT and not for any other type of traffic.
Indicates the service that the bearer is used for.
Dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
Precondition: ServiceType PTT can only be set to QciProfilePredefined=qci65 and qci66. ServiceType MC_SIGNALING can only be set to QciProfilePredefined=qci69.

Parameter Description: Points out the DRX profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the DrxProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, DRxProfile=0.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.
Dependencies: The DRX profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default DRX profile.

Parameter Description: The relative priority among the DRX profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher DRX priority than any of the existing bearers, the DRX configuration will be set to those selected by the drxProfileId for this QCI. The drxPriority has to be unique across all the configured QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined MOC instances except for instances where the drxProfileId is the same. That is, instances that share the same drxProfileId may have the same drxPriority value. Also note that larger drxPriority values indicate higher relative priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.

Parameter Description:
Defines the interpretation of active for the QCI:
FALSE (DEFAULT):
Active time is measured in the case of:
DRB: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter
UE: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter in any of the DRBs connected to the UE
The pmCounters for active E-RABs are stepped in case of data in a buffer, DL and/or UL.
TRUE:
Active time is measured in the case of:
DRB: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for that DRB
UE: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for any DRB associated with the UE
The pmCounters for active E-RABs are always stepped since the DRB is considered always active
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Points out the RLF profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the RlfProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, RlfProfile=0.
Dependencies: The RLF profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default RLF profile.

Parameter Description: The relative priority among the RLF (Radio Link Failure) profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher RLF priority than any of the existing bearers, the RLF configuration will be set to those selected by the rlfProfileId for this QCI. If more than one QCI has been configured with the same and highest value of rlfPriority the RLF configuration will be set by the lowest QCI. The instances that share the same rlfProfileId may have the same rlfPriority value. Also note that larger rlfPriority values indicate higher relative priority.
The offset time value that can be used to prolong the default inactivity timer.

The scheduler attempts to achieve dlMaxWaitingTime for DL bearers before giving any DL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
Dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: The scheduler attempts to achieve ulMaxWaitingTime for UL bearers before giving any UL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
Dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Refers to the timer profile associated with this QCI.

Relative priority among the timer profiles. TimerProfile with highest priority can be applied for a new connection in case the bearer QCI has an associated TimerProfile.
In case several bearers with different QCIs are established, the TimerProfile with highest relative priority is applied.
The TimerProfile with lowest QCI number is applied, if TimerProfiles have the same priority,
Larger timerPriority value indicates higher relative priority.
Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in DL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority. Values higher than 7 will be treated as 7.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Service-Specific HARQ is present and feature is active.
Overrides MACConfiguration::dlMaxHARQTx when QCI has highest priority.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Service-Specific HARQ is present and feature is active.
Overrides MACConfiguration::ulMaxHARQTx when QCI has highest priority.

Parameter Description: Relative HARQ priority of this QCI. If a bearer that is setup with this QCI has highest HARQ priority, HARQ transmission number is set to ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci. HARQ priority must be unique for all configured MOC instances for QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined. Does not apply when ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci are same. Note that larger harqPriority values indicate higher relative priority.

Time delay that scheduling stays on-hold for Low Energy Scheduler Solution.
If 0, Low Energy Scheduler Solution is disabled.

Reference to instance of EndcProfile or EndcProfilePredefined.
EN-DC profile associated with this QCI.

For QCI 1, 2, 3, and 4, set by system by default to ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, EndcProfilePredefined=3.

For QCI 5, set by system by default to ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, EndcProfilePredefined=2.

For QCI 6, 7, 8, and 9, set by system by default to ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, EndcProfilePredefined=1.

If not set, default value of ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, EndcProfilePredefined=1 is used.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Only applicable in Baseband Radio Node.

Parameter Description:
Adds delay for links when calculating delay of VoIP UL packets.

Primarily for use in configuration with at least one vPP.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause VoIP counters to indicate worse performance.
Following counters can be affected:
- EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::pmPdcpPktPdbUlOkVoip
- EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::pmVoipQualityRbUlOk
- EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::pmVoipQualityRbUlNok
- EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::pmVoipQualityUeUlOk
- EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::pmVoipQualityUeUlNok
Deprecated: Since 19.Q1. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Fractional part of QCI-related priority.
Decimal part of priority is defined by priority attribute.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: (priority + priorityFraction) > 0 AND (priority * 10 + priorityFraction) <= 140

Parameter Description: Enables bit rate recommendation for QCI.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for VoLTE Rate Recommendation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Enables Robust Header Compression (ROHC) for data. Focus is on UL data, TCP/IP traffic, and related QCIs.
Dependencies: Must be false if rohcEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: Defines DSCP to be used for each Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP).
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for DSCP Mapping Based on ARP and QCI is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Whether Priority Access (PA) bearers are included in partitioning.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Radio Resource Partitioning is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Whether traffic belonging to this QCI profile is supported on LAA cells. For more information about QCI characteristics that can be supported on LAA cells refer to CPI. Default value is true in MO instances 4,6,8 and 9.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Supplemental Downlink with License-Assisted Access is present and the feature is active. Value true cannot be set when serviceType is not UNDEFINED.

Parameter Description:
Whether traffic belonging to this QCI profile can be offloaded through secondary carriers.

If caOffloadingMode for PCell is set to DISABLED, this parameter does not take effect for UEs attached to this Pcell.

Operation mode for resource allocation between RATs in ESS.

If SCHED_POLICY, attribute SharingGroup::schedPolicy is used for prioritization of RAT resource needs in ESS resource allocation.

If DEMAND_WEIGHTED_RP, relativePriority and resource demand are used for prioritization of RAT resource needs in ESS resource allocation. The corresponding QCI is prioritized over SCHED_POLICY configured QCIs.
Dependencies:
Only relevant for ESS cells.
Only applicable if licenses for Relative Priority Scheduling and LTE-NR FDD Spectrum Sharing with QoS-Aware Relative Resource Allocation are present and features are active.

Parameter Description:
Relative priority associated with a QCI.

Must be applied for a QCI carrying Cat-M traffic instead of value of relativePriority attribute defined in QCI table. The override must be applied only for Cat-M bearers.

Only applicable if licenses for Category M Access and Category M Dynamic Resource Sharing with LTE are present and features are active.
Dependencies: Only applicable if ENodeBFunction::relativePriorityBrOverride is true.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Contains a list of cells that reserves this MO instance.
Indicates if the data radio bearer is subject to Absolute Priority Override.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Active Queue Management (AQM) mode
Enables forwarding of data for this QCI. However, forwarding of DL data for SN terminated bearers in EN-DC setup is always enabled and is not controlled by this attribute.
Dependencies: The parameter is only valid if the IntraLTEHODataFwd or S1HODataFwd licence is installed and active.

Parameter Description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected.

Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: The Differentiated Services Code Point for a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI). This corresponds to mappings from RAN QoS to Transport Network QoS.
Dependencies: Applied if bearer has Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) value for which DSCP value is not configured in dscpArpMap attribute. Otherwise, value configured in dscpArpMap attribute is used.

Parameter Description: Refers to an instance of LogicalChannelGroup. Assigns a Logical Channel Group to a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI).
Parameters for service-specific load management for a certain QCI profile.
The contribution from eNodeB to the Packet Delay Budget (PDB) for a QCI. Packet delays outside eNodeB e.g. in the transport network are excluded. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and active.

Parameter Description: An offset to the PDB used by Active Queue Management (AQM).
Dependencies: pdb + pdbOffset >= 0

Parameter Description: Indicates the Packet Data Convergence Protocol (PDCP) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.323.
Dependencies:
The rlcMode attribute must be set to UM to set this attribute to 7. The rlcMode attribute must be set to AM to set this attribute to 15.
15-bit PDCP SN is only applied on following conditions:
- The pdcp-SN-Extension capability is indicated by UE
- UE is category 11 or above
- UE is capable of at least 3CC carrier aggregation
- License for 3CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension is present and feature is activated
Otherwise, default value of 12-bit PDCP SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

Parameter Description:
Decimal part of QCI-related priority.
Fractional part of priority is defined by priorityFraction attribute.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: (priority + priorityFraction) > 0 AND (priority * 10 + priorityFraction) <= 140

Parameter Description: Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203 (Release 8). Each instance of this MO has a unique value for the QCI.
Dependencies: Each qci must be set to a unique value.

Parameter Description: Tuning factor per QCI for admission control. Only valid for QCIs with resource type GBR.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Dynamic GBR admission control is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Normalized subscription quantity associated with the specific the QCI. Specifies the subscription cost of a bearer with this predefined profile. The subscription cost is used for traffic load balancing purposes.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Defines the resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active

Parameter Description: Indicates if the resource type of the Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) is Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) or non-GBR as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203.
RLC Mode
Dependencies: Can only be set to AM if rlcSNLength is set to 10 or 16 and pdcpSNLength is set to 12 or 15. Must be set to UM if rlcSNLength is set to 5 or pdcpSNLength is set to 7.

Parameter Description: Radio Link Control (RLC) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.322.
Dependencies:
RLC UM must be configured (rlcMode = UM) to set this attribute to 5. RLC AM must be configured (rlcMode = AM) to set this attribute to 16. 16-bit RLC SN is only applied if:
- extendedRLC-SN-SO-Field-r13 is indicated by UE; and
- 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension license is enabled; and
- UE is capable of at least 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation.
Otherwise, default value of 10-bit RLC SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

Parameter Description: Specifies which scheduling algorithm is to be used for a certain QCI.
Range and Values:
RESOURCE_FAIR
EQUAL_RATE
PROPORTIONAL_FAIR_HIGH
PROPORTIONAL_FAIR_MEDIUM
PROPORTIONAL_FAIR_LOW
MAXIMUM_C_OVER_I
DELAY_BASED
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active. The value DELAY_BASED can only be used if the attribute serviceType has value VOIP.

Parameter Description: If the parameter srsAllocationStrategy in the QoS configuration for a Data radio Bearer assigned to a UE is set to ACTIVATED, then an attempt is made to allocate sounding for a UE. If several Data Radio Bearers are setup towards the UE with different QoS configurations, and the QoS configurations has different QCI parameter, an algorithm using the priority parameter in the QoS configuration, will resolve which QoS configuration that will define sounding

This timer is used by the receiving end of Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in UE, to detect loss of downlink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
Dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

Parameter Description: This timer is used by the receiving end of the Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in eNB, to detect loss of uplink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
Dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

Parameter Description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected.

Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.
The relative priority associated with a QCI.

Indicates the service that the bearer is used for.
ServiceType PTT and MC_SIGNALING cannot be set on QciProfileOperatorDefined MO.
Dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Points out the DRX profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the DrxProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, DRxProfile=0.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.
Dependencies: The DRX profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default DRX profile.

Parameter Description: The relative priority among the DRX profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher DRX priority than any of the existing bearers, the DRX configuration will be set to those selected by the drxProfileId for this QCI. The drxPriority has to be unique across all the configured QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined MOC instances except for instances where the drxProfileId is the same. That is, instances that share the same drxProfileId may have the same drxPriority value. Also note that larger drxPriority values indicate higher relative priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.

Parameter Description:
Defines the interpretation of active for the QCI:
FALSE (DEFAULT):
Active time is measured in the case of:
DRB: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter
UE: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter in any of the DRBs connected to the UE
The pmCounters for active E-RABs are stepped in case of data in a buffer, DL and/or UL.
TRUE:
Active time is measured in the case of:
DRB: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for that DRB
UE: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for any DRB associated with the UE
The pmCounters for active E-RABs are always stepped since the DRB is considered always active

Indicates if Robust Header Compression (ROHC) is enabled.
Note: Enabling ROHC is only supported for a QCI that is intended to carry RTP/RTCP/UDP based VoIP traffic as for example the standardized QCI1 (3GPP TS 23.203) and not for any other type of traffic.
Defines the downlink resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
Dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the licenses for Downlink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and the features are active.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Points out the RLF profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the RlfProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, RlfProfile=0.
Dependencies: The RLF profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default RLF profile.

Parameter Description: The relative priority among the RLF (Radio Link Failure) profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher RLF priority than any of the existing bearers, the RLF configuration will be set to those selected by the rlfProfileId for this QCI. If more than one QCI has been configured with the same and highest value of rlfPriority the RLF configuration will be set by the lowest QCI. The instances that share the same rlfProfileId may have the same rlfPriority value. Also note that larger rlfPriority values indicate higher relative priority.
The offset time value that can be used to prolong the default inactivity timer.

The scheduler attempts to achieve dlMaxWaitingTime for DL bearers before giving any DL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
Dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: The scheduler attempts to achieve ulMaxWaitingTime for UL bearers before giving any UL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
Dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Refers to the timer profile associated with this QCI.

Relative priority among the timer profiles. TimerProfile with highest priority can be applied for a new connection in case the bearer QCI has an associated TimerProfile.
In case several bearers with different QCIs are established, the TimerProfile with highest relative priority is applied.
The TimerProfile with lowest QCI number is applied, if TimerProfiles have the same priority,
Larger timerPriority value indicates higher relative priority.
Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in DL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority. Values higher than 7 will be treated as 7.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Service-Specific HARQ is present and feature is active.
Overrides MACConfiguration::dlMaxHARQTx when QCI has highest priority.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Service-Specific HARQ is present and feature is active.
Overrides MACConfiguration::ulMaxHARQTx when QCI has highest priority.

Parameter Description: Relative HARQ priority of this QCI. If a bearer that is setup with this QCI has highest HARQ priority, HARQ transmission number is set to ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci. HARQ priority must be unique for all configured MOC instances for QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined. Does not apply when ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci are same. Note that larger harqPriority values indicate higher relative priority.

Time delay that scheduling stays on-hold for Low Energy Scheduler Solution.
If 0, Low Energy Scheduler Solution is disabled.

Reference to an instance of EndcProfile or EndcProfilePredefined.
EN-DC profile associated with this QCI.

If not set, defaults to EndcProfilePredefined with LDN = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, EndcProfilePredefined=1.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Only applicable in Baseband Radio Node.

Parameter Description:
Fractional part of QCI-related priority.
Decimal part of priority is defined by priority attribute.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: (priority + priorityFraction) > 0 AND (priority * 10 + priorityFraction) <= 140

Parameter Description: Enables bit rate recommendation for QCI.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for VoLTE Rate Recommendation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Enables Robust Header Compression (ROHC) for data. Focus is on UL data, TCP/IP traffic, and related QCIs.
Dependencies: Must be false if rohcEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: Defines DSCP to be used for each Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP).
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for DSCP Mapping Based on ARP and QCI is present and feature is active.

Whether Priority Access (PA) bearers are included in partitioning.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Radio Resource Partitioning is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Whether traffic belonging to this QCI profile is supported on LAA cells. For more information about QCI characteristics that can be supported on LAA cells refer to CPI.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Supplemental Downlink with License-Assisted Access is present and the feature is active. Value true cannot be set when serviceType is not UNDEFINED.

Parameter Description:
Whether traffic belonging to this QCI profile can be offloaded through secondary carriers.

If caOffloadingMode for PCell is set to DISABLED, this parameter does not take effect for UEs attached to this PCell.

Operation mode for resource allocation between RATs in ESS.

If SCHED_POLICY, attribute SharingGroup::schedPolicy is used for prioritization of RAT resource needs in ESS resource allocation.

If DEMAND_WEIGHTED_RP, relativePriority and resource demand are used for prioritization of RAT resource needs in ESS resource allocation. The corresponding QCI is prioritized over SCHED_POLICY configured QCIs.
Dependencies:
Only relevant for ESS cells.
Only applicable if licenses for Relative Priority Scheduling and LTE-NR FDD Spectrum Sharing with QoS-Aware Relative Resource Allocation are present and features are active.

Parameter Description:
Relative priority associated with a QCI.

Must be applied for a QCI carrying Cat-M traffic instead of value of relativePriority attribute defined in QCI table. The override must be applied only for Cat-M bearers.

Only applicable if licenses for Category M Access and Category M Dynamic Resource Sharing with LTE are present and features are active.
Dependencies: Only applicable if ENodeBFunction::relativePriorityBrOverride is true.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of consecutive "out of sync" indications received from lower layers.
Disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of consecutive "in-sync" indications received from lower layers.
Disturbances: Increasing the value can increase drop rate.

Parameter Description: UE timer to supervise a response to RRC Connection Reestablishment Request (according to 3GPP TS 36.331), during a radio connection re-establishment procedure. The UE returns to Idle and optionally starts to reconnect over NAS when the timer expires.
Disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

Parameter Description:
Waiting time for radio link failure.
Used by the UE.
Disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

Parameter Description: UE timer triggered at radio link failure to supervise the period where the UE tries to re-establish the radio connection, either by performing RRC Connection Reestablishment (according to 3GPP TS 36.331), or by finding a suitable cell on another RAT. The UE returns to Idle and optionally starts to reconnect over NAS when the timer expires.
Disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Contains a list of QciProfile instances that reserve this MO instance.
The value component of the RDN.
Contains a list of managed object instances that reserves this managed object instance.
Dependencies: The MO cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

Parameter Description:
Waiting time for the RRC message RRC Connection Reestablishment Request upon detecting Radio Link Failure.
Used by the RBS.

Waiting time for the RRC message RRC Connection Reconfiguration Complete.
Used by the RBS.

Waiting time for the RRC message RRC Connection Reestablishment Complete.
Used by the RBS.

Supervision timer of the outgoing S1/X2/intra-eNodeB handover execution procedure according to 3GPP TS 36.413 and TS 36.423.
If the feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Re-establishment is active this timer also supervises the Context Fetch procedure.
Disturbances: Low values can stop outgoing HO.

Parameter Description: Indicates if the data radio bearer is subject to Absolute Priority Override.

Parameter Description: Scheduler attempts to achieve dlMaxWaitingTime for DL bearers before giving any DL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to similar or slightly shorter value than PDB. If value set too low, higher priority services can be affected. For more information about PDB refer to TS23.203.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers.
A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
Dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if licenses for Flexible QoS and Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduling are present and active.

Parameter Description: Scheduler attempts to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that minRate scheduler is not used.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Parameter is used only if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms is selected: "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate". Only relevant if the licenses for Flexible QoS and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and active.

Parameter Description: SCI-related bearer priority. Refer to priority defined in 3GPP TS 23.203.

Note: UE is part of subscriber group if evaluated to true in following trigger lists:
- spidTriggerList
- bearerTriggerList

If all five lists are empty, all UEs match. If no list is empty, UE must match at least one value in each list.

Parameter Description: UL MCS upper limit for UEs belonging to a subscriber group. Value -1 means ulMcsUpperLimit function is off, value in range [1-28] means ulMcsUpperLimit function is on for subscriber group.

ulMcsUpperLimit > ulMcsLowerLimit when both of ulMcsUpperLimit and ulMcsLowerLimit are set to non-default value.
Can be -1 only when volteCodecRateForUlSinrEst is set to default value.

Parameter Description: UL MCS lower limit for UEs belonging to a subscriber group. Value -1 means ulMcsLowerLimit function is off, value in range [1-28] means ulMcsLowerLimit function is on for subscriber group.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: ulMcsLowerLimit < ulMcsUpperLimit when both of ulMcsLowerLimit and ulMcsUpperLimit are set to non-default value.

dlDynBlerTargetMax must be larger than or equal to dlDynBlerTargetMin, or equal to -1.

Parameter Description:
UL SINR threshold.

If SINR is less than or equal to this threshold, a UE can be selected as candidate for UL reserved region.
Dependencies: Only applicable if ulCandidateToRegion is true.

Dependencies: Only applicable if license for ASGH-Based Spectral Efficiency Package is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Mode of optimized, PDCCH-flexible BLER for UEs belonging to a subscriber group.

Overrides attributes EUtranCellFDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled and EUtranCellTDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled.

If ENABLED, following apply:

- If EUtranCellFDD::diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled is true, EUtranCellFDD::pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow and EUtranCellFDD::pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh are used as maximum PDCCH target BLER for UEs in the subscriber group. Otherwise EUtranCellFDD::optimizedPdcchMaxTargetBler is used.

- If EUtranCellTDD::diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled is true, EUtranCellTDD::pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow and EUtranCellTDD::pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh are used as maximum PDCCH target BLER for UEs in the subscriber group. Otherwise EUtranCellTDD::optimizedPdcchMaxTargetBler is used.
Dependencies: Only applicable if licenses for Optimized PDCCH, Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation, and ASGH Performance Package are present and features are active.

Parameter Description:
List of SON-based measurement configuration features.

Measurements triggered by these features are disabled.
If empty, measurements are not affected.

Maximum limit of difference between predicted and current outer loop link adaptation adjustment.

Limit is on absolute value.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for AI Powered DL Link Adaptation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
VoLTE codec rate to estimate required SINR.

Used for uplink link adaptation when applying uplink MCS upper limit.
-1 means that the function of SINR estimation for uplink link adaptation is off.
Other values mean the configured VoLTE Codec Rate, for example, 2385 means AMR-WB 23.85 kbps.
It is recommended to configure it to the VoLTE codec rate used by all users or most users in the subscriber group.

Only applicable if license for Robust Uplink Link Adaptation for VoLTE is present and the feature is active.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Can be non-default value only when ulMcsUpperLimit is set to non-default value.

Parameter Description:
Uplink outer loop step size factor.

Used to increase adjustment step size of PUSCH HARQ NACK based gain adjustment.
10 means that function of increasing step size is off.
Other values mean a multiple of the step size increase, for example, 15 means 1.5 times the step size increase. Setting this parameter to greater than ten will lower the uplink BLER target.
If set to higher value, outer loop adjustment is more conservative when receiving PUSCH HARQ NACK, with more PRBs and lower MCS are used.

Only applicable if license for Robust Uplink Link Adaptation for VoLTE is present and the feature is active.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Whether higher priority in delay-based scheduling is enabled for UEs in this subscriber group.

- customTriggerList

- plmnTriggerList
If all five lists are empty, all UEs match. If no list is empty, UE must match at least one value in each list.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Restricts bearers with lower or equal ARP level from being configured as split bearer.

Value 0 means that bearer mapped to this profile can be set up as split bearer irrespectively of its ARP value.
Value lower than the ARP of bearer mapped to this profile, means no split restrictions for the bearer.
Value equal to or higher than ARP of a bearer mapped to this profile means the bearer is not allowed as split bearer.

Note: The split allowance for the bearer is controlled together with meNbS1TermExclArpList parameter.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for Basic Intelligent Connectivity is present and feature is active.

Value lower than ARP of this bearer means no restrictions on other bearers.
Value equal to or higher than ARP of this bearer means no bearer is allowed as split bearer.
Controls if configuration of split bearers is allowed with this bearer for a UE not capable of EN-DC dynamic power sharing.

Example: If MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.
Note: The value (MCC=001, MNC=01) indicates that the PLMN is not initiated. The value can not be used as a valid PLMN Identity.

Specifies whether the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled or disabled in the external eNB. Specifies whether it is allowed to perform mobility actions for secondary frequency bands to that eNB or not.

Configures whether uplink triggered handover is allowed to this external eNodeB or not. This parameter has only effect if no X2 interface is configured or the external node does not support the ULTRIG feature.

Set to true by the system when license for Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is installed and a X2 connection exists.

Parameter Description: VlanPort instance that can be used to set up EranInterMeLinks and BbLinks under this ExternalENodeBFunction for Elastic RAN UL CoMP. If not set, ENodeBFunction::eranUlCompVlanPortRef is used as default.

Parameter Description:
Maximum allowed delay for ERAN link, If measured delay exceeds this value, link is not used.

Since 23.Q2 this parameter does not take effect for non-TDD AAS and non-RGW configuration. Instead maximum RTT is measured automatically by system.
Change Take Effect: Change takes effect at ERAN link setup.
Disturbances: Setting this attribute to lower value than real delay causes loss of all CA ERAN traffic.
Precondition: ERAN license enabled.

Whether E-RAN CA has to be prioritized over inter-eNodeB CA.

This parameter has only effect if licenses for both inter-eNodeB CA and E-RAN CA are active on this node.
Using value false keeps legacy behavior meaning that E-RAN CA is prioritized over inter-eNodeB CA.
This parameter has to be set to true when there is no idle connection between the nodes. If set to true, E-RAN tunnel setup is omitted, and system tries to set up inter-eNodeB CA instead.

If ENodeBFunction::eranPrioritizeDefaultEnabled is false, initial value of this parameter is set to true when MO instance is created automatically by ANR or X2.
Change Take Effect: Next tunnel setup. The TermPointToENB.administrativeState attribute under ExternalENodeBFunction MO instance must be set to LOCKED and then to UNLOCKED.

VlanPort instance that can be used to set up EranInterMeLinks and Bblinks under this ExternalENodeBFunction for PIM function.
If empty, ENodeBFunction::eranPimVlanPortRef is used as default.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Immediately after the change, all EranInterMeLinks to this external eNodeB are disconnected. If child TermPointToENB MO exists, it requires lock and unlock after this parameter is changed.

Parameter Description:
Represents how suitable this external node is for multi-node PIM detection.

Actual value represents the highest PIM overlap ratio between downlink FDD frequencies served by this external node and uplink FDD frequencies served by local eNodeB.

If empty, multi-node PIM detection is not supported, for one of following reasons:
- External node is from other vendor.
- External node does not support software version used in local node.
- External node does not serve any FDD cell.
Whether external node is used for remote aggressor of PIM detection.
Dependencies: Up to two ExternalENodeBFunction and ExternalGNodeBFunction MO instances can be set to true.

Parameter Description: Whether external eNodeB is co-sited.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
User-defined alphanumeric label, maximum 128 characters including spaces.

The percentage of total cell trace storage (totalCellTraceStorageSize) reserved for high-priority scanners.

This means that no events from low-priority scanners are stored in the file when the storage limit is reached for the sum of the low-priority scanners:

totalCellTraceStorageSize - (cellTraceHighPrioReserv / 100) * totalCellTraceStorageSize.

High-priority scanner files are not limited to the reserved area for high priority scanners. These files can also be stored in the non-reserved area together with the low-priority scanner files. When the default value of zero is set, the high- and low-priority share the totalCellTraceStorageSize for storing cell trace events.
Dependencies: Only applicable in DU Radio Node.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q3. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Total available storage for the cell trace recording files. The actual limit may be slightly offset from this value due to the fact that the compressed file size is approximated by the system.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q3. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
cellTraceFileSize is calculated basing on compression factor equal to 8. In some outstanding conditions it is possible that the maximum size could exceed definition in MOM attribute, depending of content of ROP file.

If the cellTraceFileSize is reached within a specific Reporting Output Period (ROP), cell trace recording stops until the next ROP begins.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q3. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
The total storage that the observability mechanisms can use to store information about the collected event data.
This means that the total size of the cell trace and UE trace files stored should be less than the value of this attribute. The actual limit may be slightly offset from this value due to the fact that the compressed file size is approximated by the system.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q3. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
ueTraceFileSize is calculated basing on compression factor equal to 8. In some outstanding conditions it is possible that the maximum size could exceed definition in MOM attribute, depending of content of ROP file.

If ueTraceFileSize is reached during ROP, UE trace recording stops until next ROP.
The value component of the RDN.
Total available storage for UE trace recording files. Actual limit can differ slightly from value because system approximates compressed file size.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q3. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:

Provided to the UE by System Information.

Parameter Description:
Periodicity of the system information change notification sent at cell deblock.

After cell deblock a system information change notification is sent to force all UEs to read SI. First redistribution of SI occurs 15 seconds after cell deblock. Parameter controls periodicity between consecutive SI redistributions between second and last, eighth redistribution. If parameter is set to 0, only first redistribution occurs.

Dependencies: Only applicable if license for Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Enables checking the second value - RSRP or RSRQ - in an A5 Target Good Enough measurement report triggered by RSRQ or RSRP respectively.

If set to true, handover occurs only if both the RSRP_target and RSRQ_target conditions are met. This setting increases the impact of EUtranFreqRelation::qOffsetFreq, EUtranCellRelation::cellIndividualOffsetEUtran and EUtranCellRelation::cellIndividualOffsetEUtranQci1. This is because these offsets appear in both the RSRP and RSRQ equations and they do not have additional offsets to allow independent adjustment for RSRP and RSRQ. Furthermore, RSRQ has a much smaller range than RSRP, so changing these offsets has a bigger impact on RSRQ triggering than on RSRP triggering. It is therefore recommended that these offsets be changed in +/-1dB steps only, as bigger steps can have a severe impact on behavior.
Dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

Offset value above UL SINR in source cell that estimated UL SINR in target cell must reach for handover to be allowed. Used when feature UL-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled. Configured in source cell.
The length of time the eNodeB discards A3 measurement report for CSG or Hybrid CSG cells from UE. If 0, timer is not started.
