Length of time eNodeB waits for reports from A3 measurements configured in CAT-M UE for intra frequency mobility. If 0, timer is not started.
Intra-frequency measurement configuration mode for CAT-M UE which requires measurement gaps for intra-frequency measurement.
Activates A3/A5 measurements on E-UTRAN inter-frequencies for mobility purposes about CAT-M UE.
Length of time eNodeB waits for reports from A3/A5 measurements configured in CAT-M UE for mobility reasons.
Parameters for service-specific priority offset for a certain QCI profile.
Enables checking the second value - RSCP or Ecno - in a B1 measurement report.
Dependencies: Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

Parameter Description:
Enables checking the second value - RSCP or Ecno - in a B2 measurement report.

If set to true, handover occurs only if both the RSCP_target and EcNo_target conditions are met. This setting increases the impact of UtranFreqRelation::qOffsetFreq, which appears in both the RSCP and EcNo equations and impacts both conditions. Furthermore, EcNo has a much smaller range than RSCP, so changing qOffsetFreq has a bigger impact on EcNO triggering than on RSCP triggering. It is therefore recommended that qOffsetFreq be changed in +/-1dB steps only, as bigger steps can have a severe impact on behavior. qOffsetFreq also impacts idle mode triggering.
Dependencies: Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

Parameter Description: Enables checking the second value - RSRQ or RSRP - in an intra-frequency A3 measurement report.
Dependencies: Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

Parameter Description:
Enables checking the second value - RSRQ or RSRP - in an inter-frequency A3 measurement report.

If set to true, handover occurs only if both the RSRP_target and RSRQ_target conditions are met. This setting increases the impact of EUtranFreqRelation::qOffsetFreq, EUtranCellRelation::cellIndividualOffsetEUtran and EUtranCellRelation::cellIndividualOffsetEUtranQci1. This is because these offsets appear in both the RSRP and RSRQ equations and they do not have additional offsets to allow independent adjustment for RSRP and RSRQ. Furthermore, RSRQ has a much smaller range than RSRP, so changing these offsets has a bigger impact on RSRQ triggering than on RSRP triggering. It is therefore recommended that these offsets be changed in +/-1dB steps only, as bigger steps can have a severe impact on behavior.
Dependencies: Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

Parameter Description: Filtering coefficient for UTRAN using measured quantity Received Signal Code Power (RSCP). The coefficient filters measurements before event evaluation.
Filtering coefficient for UTRAN using measured quantity ratio of energy per modulation bit to noise spectral density (Ecno). The coefficient filters measurements before event evaluation.
Allow for release-with-redirect to NR.
Deprecated: Since 23.Q4. Replaced by nrB1MeasEnabled. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by UE on NR objects for mobility to NR SA.

Total number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by UE on NR measurement objects for NR SA and EN-DC is restricted by specification.
Time to wait for configuration of B1 NR measurement to start.

Time to wait for B1 NR measurement report to redirect to NR, excluding time to trigger.
Value -1 indicates to wait forever.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute for more frequent B1 NR measurement report can affect UE battery consumption and user throughput.
Deprecated: Since 19.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Time to wait for configuration of B1 NR measurement to resume.
Value -1 indicates to stop configuration of second or more NR B1 measurement.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute for more frequent B1 NR measurement report can affect UE battery consumption and user throughput.

Parameter Description: Number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by UE on E-UTRA frequencies other than serving cell frequency. UE does not support monitoring increased number of E-UTRA carriers, but supports extended number of measurement Ids as specified by 3GPP Rel-12.
Number of intra-mode (FDD - TDD) measurements that can be concurrently performed by the 3GPP Rel-12 compliant UE on E-UTRA frequencies other than the serving cell frequency.

Number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by UE on E-UTRA frequencies other than serving cell frequency. UE supports monitoring increased number of E-UTRA carriers, and supports extended number of measurement Ids as specified by 3GPP Rel-12.

Time to wait for B1 NR measurement report for mobility to NR SA, excluding time to trigger.

If set to -1, no time restriction is applied.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute for more frequent B1 NR measurement report can affect UE battery consumption and user throughput.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of B1 measurement configurations in first RRC reconfiguration message for EN-DC.

Frequency relations are selected based on endcB1MeasPriority.
If multiple frequency relations with same priority exceed available number of configurations indicated by this parameter, the frequency relations are randomly selected accordingly.

Value 0 indicates that no measurement is performed.
Deprecated: Since 19.Q4. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Sets Measurement Scaling Factor. Defines relaxation to requirements for carriers measured with normal measurement performance. Corresponds to MeasScaleFactor-r12 parameter in RRC connected mode messages.
Value -1 means Measurement Scaling Factor is not configured and not sent in RRC messages.
Value 0 means Measurement Scaling Factor is set to sf-EUTRA-cf1.
Value 1 means Measurement Scaling Factor is set to sf-EUTRA-cf2.
Applicable for UEs compliant with 3GPP release since Rel-12, and which indicate support for Increased UE Carrier Monitoring E-UTRA.

Number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by UE on NR measurement objects for EN-DC.

The total number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by UE on NR measurement objects for RwR and EN-DC is restricted by specification.

Time in which UE performs measurements requested in each RRC reconfiguration message for EN-DC.

Value -1 means infinity.
Filtering coefficient for UE UL-normalized Signal-to-Noise-Max measurements for VoLTE CS fallback in eNodeB. Coefficient filters measurements before event evaluation.
Dependencies: Only relevant if EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::csfbForVolteEnabled is true.
Deprecated: Since 20.Q1. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Time to wait for next B1 Array (three batches of B1 measurement configuration) for EN-DC.

Value -1 means B1 Array will not be restarted.
Time duration waiting for other B1 measurement reports after receiving first B1 measurement report.

This attribute is used for whether to check EN-DC setup or not.

If set to true, B1 measurement for Release with Redirect to NR can be configured regardless of EN-DC setup.
Deprecated: Since 22.Q3. Replaced by nrB1MeasAtEndcEnabled. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Enables checking the second value - RSRP or RSRQ - in A5 measurement report during HO evaluation for Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover feature.

If set to true, handover occurs only if both the RSRP_target and RSRQ_target conditions are met.

Checking options for RSRP and RSRQ in UL-heavy measurement.

If true, check both RSRP and RSRQ to trigger handover.

If false, only check RSRP or RSRQ to trigger handover according to triggerQuantity.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when license for Uplink-Traffic-Triggered Mobility is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Waiting time for UL-heavy measurement report, excluding time to trigger.

If value is 0, timer is not started.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when license for Uplink-Traffic-Triggered Mobility is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Measurement time for Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility or Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility feature.

If set to 0, timer is not started.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility or Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether NR SA B1 measurement is enabled when EN-DC is configured.

If set to true, B1 measurement for mobility to NR SA can be configured regardless of EN-DC setup.

Measurement window in which eNodeB waits for B1 measurement report with highest priority frequency.

Timer is started after receiving first NR SA B1 measurement report, if the NR frequency is not highest configured frequency priority.

Enables evaluation of value of second quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) in event B2 for NR measurement report.

If set to true, handover occurs only if both RSRP_target and RSRQ_target conditions are met.

Enables evaluation of value of second quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) in event B1 for NR measurement report.

If set to true, handover occurs only if both RSRP_target and RSRQ_target conditions are met.
Activates or deactivates B2 measurements on NR frequencies for mobility purposes.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks mobility to GUTRAN based on B2 measurements on NR frequencies.

Parameter Description:
Whether GUTRAN measurements for mobility purposes are activated.

Not applicable if feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is enabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks mobility to GUTRAN based on B2 to NR measurements.
Obsolete: Since 23.Q3. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Time period, during which EN-DC is inhibited after E-RAB release.

If -1, timer is not started.
Delay timer before LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority is attempted for UE.

Timeout for A5 measurement report ordered by LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority.

Timeout does not include ReportConfigA5InterFreqHoHigherPrio::timeToTriggerA5.

Whether NR Standalone B1 measurement is enabled.

If true, B1 measurement for mobility to NR Standalone is configured for UE in good LTE coverage.

Only applicable if license for NR Coverage-Triggered NR Session Continuity is present and feature is active.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Label for free use.
ANR performs measurement on the referenced frequency if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, ANR does not perform any measurements on this frequency.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Label for free use.
Reference to the UTRAN frequency MO, UtranFreq.

The threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency from the current serving frequency. Each UTRAN frequency may have a specific threshold. The threshold is specified as parameter Thresx,high in 3GPP TS 36.304.

The threshold used in reselection towards a lower frequency priority from a higher priority frequency. Each frequency of UTRAN may have a specific threshold. The threshold is specified as parameter Thresx,low in 3GPP TS 36.304.
The required minimum received Rx level in the UTRAN frequency used in cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304.
Used to calculate the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304) at cell reselection to a UTRAN cell.
Minimum required quality level in the cell (dB). Corresponds to parameter Qqualmin in 3GPP TS 25.304

The absolute priority of the carrier frequency used by the cell reselection procedure. Corresponds to parameter priority in 3GPP TS 36.304.

Value 0 means lowest priority. The UE behavior when the field is empty if applicable, is specified in 3GPP TS 36.304.
Dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

Parameter Description:
List of all PLMN IDs allowed for this frequency relation.

A UE that does not support any IDs included in allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency. UE support of PLMN is defined in UE Handover Restriction List.

If empty, frequency has no restrictions for PLMN.

PLMN ID contains following parts:
1. MCC (Mobile Country Code), 3 digits
2. MNC (Mobile Network Code), 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)

For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to which frequency/frequency group to make CS Fallback to.
The value -1 means the frequency is excluded.
The value 0 means the lowest priority.
The value 7 means the highest priority.

Prioritizes UTRA frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
(0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)
Indicates a frequency-specific offset to apply when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies for emergency calls among all frequencies/frequency groups related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to which frequency to make emergency call CS Fallback to.
The value -1 means the frequency is excluded.
The value 0 means the lowest priority.
The value 7 means the highest priority.
The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN FDD frequency in case of coverage triggered mobility.
The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN FDD frequency in case of CS Fallback.

Specifies the quality level threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority UTRA frequency than the current serving frequency.

Corresponds to ThreshX, HighQ in 3GPP TS 36.304
Dependencies: This parameter is included in SIB6 if the threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is included in systemInformationBlockType3.

Parameter Description:
Specifies the quality level threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a lower priority UTRA frequency than the current serving frequency.

Corresponds to ThreshX, LowQ in 3GPP TS 36.304
Dependencies: This parameter is included in SIB6 if the threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is included in systemInformationBlockType3.

Parameter Description:
Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets priority to frequency that mobility for a voice session is performed to. Valid for VoLTE and PTT.
Value -1 means frequency is excluded.
Value 0 means lowest priority.
Value 7 means highest priority.

QCI profile relation
The attribute encapsulates parameters for service specific load management for specific QCI profiles.

Specifies the policy for updating the loadBalancing attribute by the feature Best Neighbor Relations for WCDMA IRAT Offload. The policy is valid for all cell relations corresponding to this UtranFreqRelation.
This parameter specifies the maximum number of UtranCellRelations per UtranFreqRelation. The value is set by the action with name SetMaxNrUtranCellRelations.

Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to the alternative target frequency/frequency group to which  to make release with redirect when measurement or handover to selected target fails.
Value -1 means the frequency is excluded.
Value 0 means the lowest priority.
Value 7 means the highest priority.

Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies for emergency calls among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to the alternative target frequency/frequency group to which to make release with redirect when measurement or handover to selected target fails for emergency calls.
Value -1 means the frequency is excluded.
Value 0 means the lowest priority.
Value 7 means the highest priority.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2EcNo, Ratio of energy for each modulation bit to noise spectral density in the ThresholdUTRA for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2Rscp, RSCP in the ThresholdUTRA for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
Specifies whether Admission-triggered offload (ATO) is activated from the current cell towards a certain UTRAN frequency.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility and High Power UE.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.

Indicates the ARFCN applicable for a downlink UTRA carrier frequency, as defined in 3GPP TS 25.331.
Allowed ARFCN values are specified in 3GPP TS 25.101 (UTRAN FDD) and 3GPP TS 25.102 (UTRAN TDD).
The value component of the RDN.

Maximum allowed number of paging records included in one Radio Resource Control (RRC) paging message.

Allowed maximum number of UE that can be paged per paging occasion.

If cellMaxNoOfPagingRecords in EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD instance is not 0, this attribute is overridden by cellMaxNoOfPagingRecords in corresponding cell.

LTE UEs and Category M1 UEs are included. For Category M1 UEs, maximum effective number of paging records is 4 if it is set higher than or equal to 4.
Change Take Effect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.
Dependencies:
Attribute value range is limited by the cell with narrowest bandwidth:
- Cannot be larger than 1 if dlChannelBandwidth is 1400 in any EUtranCellFDD instance.
- Cannot be larger than 4 if dlChannelBandwidth is 3000 in any EUtranCellFDD instance.
- Cannot be larger than 7 if dlChannelBandwidth is 5000 in any EUtranCellFDD instance, or if channelBandwidth is 5000 in any EUtranCellTDD instance.

Parameter Description: Paging cycle (T). Used by RBS and broadcast in system information type 2. UE-specific DRX cycle overrides defaultPagingCycle if UE-specific DRX cycle is provided in S1AP paging. If extended Idle Mode DRX feature is active, paging cycle can be extended up to 262144 radio frames.
Change Take Effect: After all cells in the RBS are locked and then unlocked. Lock/unlock cells manually, immediately after changing defaultPagingCycle.
Disturbances: If cell lock/unlock is not performed immediately after changing defaultPagingCycle, the number of discarded paging messages increases, and KPI drops.
Dependencies: Parameter modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle must be equal or less than 1024 radio frames.

Parameter Description:
Used to calculate the number and position of Paging Occasions (PO) and Paging Frames (PF).

The numerical value of nB depends on the value of the defaultPagingCycle (T) and can be set to one of the following values:
4T, 2T, T, T/2, T/4, T/8, T/16, T/32.

When nB is set to T, 2T or 4T, it determines the number of POs per PF, and the PO position in PF.

When nB is set to a value smaller than T, it affects the System Frame Number of the PF, the position of PO in the PF, and also distribution of UE into groups with the same PF.

When nB is set to smaller value, amount of groups is smaller, but amount of UEs inside each groups is larger. When nB is set to a larger value, amount of groups is larger but amount of UEs inside each groups is smaller.

If categoryMAccess is enabled and nBBr is set to the default value (NOT_PRESENT) then further restrictions apply. If highestSupportedCeLevelBr = 0 then nB should be selected from the following available options (T, T/2, T/4, T/8, T/16, T/32) due to the half duplex nature of Cat-M devices. If highestSupportedCeLevelBr = 1 then nB should be selected from the following available options (T/8, T/16, T/32) due to repetitions.
Change Take Effect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.
Dependencies: nB=T4 can not be used in combination with specialSubframePattern = 5 on MO EUtranCellTDD, see 3GPP TS 36.213.

Parameter Description: The length of time a received paging is retained or queued in the RBS before it is discarded. The timer should be set to the same (or smaller) value as the paging resend timer in MME (T3413). This setting  prevents the RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after the re-sent copy is received from the MME.
Change Take Effect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q4. Replaced by pagingDiscardTimerDrx. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Number of consecutive "DefaultPagingCycles" in which paging for Earthquake and Tsunami Warning System (ETWS) Primary Notification shall be transmitted in the RBS.

Calculates number and position of POs and PFs for Bandwidth Reduced (BR) UEs.

Numerical value of nBBr depends on value of defaultPagingCycle (T) and can be set to one of the following values based on Enhanced Paging Capacity (EPC):
- If EPC is on, then set to T/8, T/16, T/32, T/64, T/128, T/256, and NOT_PRESENT.
- If EPC is off, then set to T/64, T/128, T/256, and NOT_PRESENT.

nBBr value affects the following:
- SFN of PF
- Position of PO in PF
- Distribution of UE into groups with same PF

When nBBr is set to a smaller value, amount of groups is smaller, but amount of UEs inside each group is larger.
When nBBr is set to a larger value, amount of groups is larger but amount of UEs inside each group is smaller. nBBr value needs to be always >=1 . That is, if T=128, then nBBr >= T/128, meaning that there is at least one paging group. For more information, see 3GPP TS 36.304, Evolved Universal Terrestrial Radio Access (E-UTRA); User Equipment (UE) procedures in idle mode.

When nBBr is set to NOT_PRESENT, attribute is not used. Instead, nB value is used to calculate PF and PO for CAT-M1 users.
When nBBr is set to T/8, T/16, or T/32 and CatMEnhancedPagingCapacity is operable, attribute is not used. Instead, nB with same value is used to calculate PF and PO for CAT-M1 users.
When nBBr is set to T/8, T/16, or T/32 and CatMEnhancedPagingCapacity is not operable, then default value (T/64) is used to calculate PF and PO for CAT-M1 users.

nBBr values 4T, 2T, T, T/2, and T/4 are not allowed.
Range and Values:
NOT_PRESENT
T1_64
T1_128
T1_256
T
T1_2T
T1_4T
T1_8T
T1_16T
T1_32T

Parameter Description: NB IoT paging cycle (also called T) used by RBS and broadcast in NB-SIB2. For defaultPagingCycle 128, numRepetitionsPaging must not exceed 512. For defaultPagingCycle 256, numRepetitionsPaging must not exceed 1024.
Change Take Effect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked

Parameter Description:
Used to calculate number and position of NB-IoT Paging Occasions (PO) and NB-IoT Paging Frames (PF).
When nBNbIot is set to T, it determines PO number for each PF, and PO position in PF. When nBNbIot is smaller than T, it affects SFN of PF, PO position in PF, and UE distribution into groups with same PF.
nBNbIot values of 4T and 2T are not allowed because they result in grouping issues for paging occasions.
nBNbIot values of T and T/2 are not recommended because they can result in higher paging discard rates compared to default value.
Values of 4T and 2T are converted to T/16.

The time a UE can be inactive before it is released.

86400s = 24 hours

0 is used to turn off the use of this timer. This means that a UE will not be released due to inactivity.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Attribute controls the action when there is an RLC DL Delivery failure on a DRB in a connection. The action can be set to:
- always make an UE Context release
- resume the connection if higher ARP prioritized DRBs exist to get better retainability
If there is RLC Delivery failure on SRB or on the DRB used for IMS Signaling (indicated by ServiceType in QciProfileOperatorDefined/QciProfilePredefined), the design base behavior applies. In this case, eNodeB triggers a UE Context Release regardless of the value of attribute rlcDlDeliveryFailureAction.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic if the value is not set to make a UE context release. When there is a RLC DL Delivery failure on one of several DRBs of a UE, the DRB may be marked as failed and the other DRBs are then retained. The marked DRB cannot be used after the failure until a handover or an RRC Connection Re-establishment initiated by the UE is successful.
Dependencies:
If this attribute is not set to UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE, the behavior depends on:
- ARP priority
- ServiceType attribute

Parameter Description:
Time while a Bandwidth Reduced (BR) UE can be inactive before released or suspended.

86400 s = 24 hours

Value 0 turns timer off. If so, UEs are not released or suspended because of inactivity.

Timer is triggered when UL and DL buffers are empty.

Time after which an inactive connection is released or suspended and BR UE enters idle state.

Value 0 turns timer off. If so, UEs are not released or suspended because of bufferInactivityTimerBr.

Delay timer for RAI.

Time after which an inactive connection is released or suspended and BR UE enters idle state.

Value 0 turns timer off. If so, UEs are not released or suspended because of raiReleaseDelayTimerBr.

Time for which UE that is eligible for early UE preemption can be inactive before it is released. Release happens when there is resource shortage on UE or bearer level for non-GBR E-RABs.
No UE is eligible for early UE preemption in the following cases:
- tInactivityTimer is set to the minimum of its configurable range and offset is not configured for any non-GBR QCIs.
- tInactivityTimerMin is greater than or equal to tInactivityTimer (including highest QCI offset, if used).

86400s = 24 hours.
Dependencies: Only applicable when preemption function of Differentiated Admission Control feature is enabled, that is, AdmissionControl.arpBasedPreEmptionState is ACTIVATED.
Deprecated: Since 20.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Whether inactive UE is released or performs handover when measurement report is received.

If set to 0, handover of inactive UE is always performed prior Rcs.tInactivityTimer expires.
If UE is inactive for a time shorter than or equal to parameter value, it performs handover, except when Rcs.tInactivityTimer expires, in which case it is released.
If UE is inactive for a time longer than parameter value, it is released instead of performing handover.

An array specifying the ciphering algorithms that should be allowed and their priority order. The array has a maximum length of 4 and a minimum length of 1. The algorithm in index zero has the highest priority. Each algorithm shall be written only once in the array.

An array specifying the integrity protection algorithms that should be allowed and their priority order. The array has a maximum length of 3 and a minimum length of 1. The algorithm in index zero has the highest priority. Each algorithm shall be written only once in the array.

Whether personal data protection is enabled.
When personal data protection is enabled, subscriber personal data is not logged. If protection is disabled, there are rare traffic occasions when subscriber personal data is revealed and can be logged in PM events and other short-lived on-demand troubleshooting logs.

Parameter Description:

For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

A PCI confusion exists if a source cell has relations to two neighbor cells where both neighbor cells have the same PCI and frequency. A PCI collision exists if a source cell has a relation to a neighbor cell where both the source cell and neighbor cell have the same PCI and frequency.

Parameter Description: See attribute x2RetryTimerStart.

After failed X2 setup and after X2 link break the x2retryTimer is used to control the time till next retry.

x2retryTimer is used for DNS, SCTP, X2AP retries and x2IpAddrViaS1.

After first failed setup or missing IP address from DNS, x2retryTimer = max(x2retryTimerStart,W), where W is the timeToWait received in x2SetupFail. If W is not received, W=0.

After link break, x2retryTimer = random(0,x2retryTimerStart). If the first setup after link break fails, the timer values according to the above and below paragraphs must apply as for failed initial setup.

After 2nd and following fails, if the X2 connection is being setup by operator in the S-RBS, x2retryTimer = max(x2retryTimerStart,W).

After 2nd and following fails, if the X2 connection is not being setup by operator in the S-RBS, x2retryTimer = max(min[2^(n-2)*x2retryTimerStart, x2retryTimerMaxAuto], W), where n is failure number.

Each W is only used in the first retry after it is received.

The list of whitelisted RBS IDs, Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) is not allowed to disconnect X2 for any neighbor RBS in the whitelist.

This parameter indicates if two way relations shall be setup during X2 setup and eNB configuration. The RBS creates a two-way relation for each entry in the received neighbour information that contains a relation to a source cell. Neighbour information is sent in X2 setup and eNB configuration. Neighbour information is eUtranCellRelations per source cell from the sending node.
Defines the maximum allowed time/phase deviation for time/phase synchronization of the eNodeB.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: This parameter is relevant when the parameter timeAndPhaseSynchCritical has the value true.

Parameter Description: Used to set how the licensed capacity will be distributed between the baseband processing resources

S1 Handover data forwarding can be of two types, direct and indirect. Direct forwarding requires direct connectivity between source and target eNodeB. This parameter is used to indicate if such direct connectivity exist.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible throughput degradation at S1 HO.
Dependencies: Optional Feature Data Forwarding at S1 Handover

Parameter Description:
Rand range datatype is the eight most significant bits (MSB) of the Rand used for authentication.
This attribute controls the minimum random number value that can be generated. Typically a range of random numbers is allocated to each system using this attribute.
Dependencies: minRandc < maxRandc

Parameter Description:
Rand range datatype is the eight most significant bits (MSB) of the Rand used for authentication.
This attribute controls the maximum random number value that can be generated. Typically a range of random numbers is allocated to each system using this attribute.
Dependencies: maxRandc > minRandc

Parameter Description:
Random number update interval
This attribute specifies the time interval in minutes between random number generation. When this interval expires, the eNodeB generates a new random number between MinRandc and MaxRandc.

Specifies whether the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is supported in the eNB.

Reference to an instance of AddressIPv4 or AddressIPv6 MO.

Configures IP address for S1 and X2 user plane connections unless specified by upX2IpAddressRef.
Also configures IP address for X2 EN-DC user plane connections if upEndcX2IpAddressRef and upX2IpAddressRef are not configured. upIpAddressRef can use same IP protocol version in SctpEndpoint MO. Different IP version between upIpAddressRef and SctpEndpoint causes service impact.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic. A node restart is required.

Parameter Description: Decides whether or not PWS data must be persistently stored.

When CS Fallback is requested for a UE in idle mode this parameter controls if measurements for release with redirect and handover must be performed. If the parameter is set to false a blind release with redirect is done.
Dependencies: This parameter is only relevant for features 'Measurement-Based CSFB Target Selection' and 'PSHO-based CS Fallback to WCDMA' .

Parameter Description: Max number of UTRAN/GERAN cells with system information. Can be included in an RRC connection release message triggered by CS Fallback as specified in 3GPP TS 36.331.

Maximum number of NACC elements, where one NACC element corresponds to one cell, that can be included in an RRC Connection Release 3GPP TS 36.331 message triggered by Session Continuity (bad coverage).
Dependencies: Only applicable if Redirect with System Information is active.

Parameter Description: Specifies whether or not the functionality to send NACC information, regardless of UE capability, is activated, provided that the feature Redirect with System Information is active.
Indicates that prescheduling is enabled during connection setup phase.

Supervision timer of the outgoing LTE to CDMA 1xRtt handover execution procedure.

In order to send a UE to WiFi, a throughput comparison is made between WiFi and LTE.
For comparisons made in eNodeB, a UE is admitted to WiFi if, WiFi throughput > biasThpWifiMobility * LTE throughput.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

Parameter Description:
The timeout time for receiving HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE after RBS sent HO CANCEL message to MME.
Value specifies supervision time of outgoing S1 HO Cancellation according to procedure described in 3GPP TS 36.413 section 8.4.5.

Controls DNS selection for S1 and X2 lookups. If not set, DNS server on OAM network is used.

For DU Radio Node it can be set to reference a DnsResolver, and DNS queries are resolved using referenced DnsResolver (typically using DNS server on transport network).

For Baseband Radio Node it can be set to reference a DnsClient, and DNS queries are resolved using referenced DnsClient (typically using DNS server on transport network).
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Precondition: To enable this attribute DNS servers must support EDNS0.

Parameter Description: Inactivity time value to be used to decide release of inactive UEs at handover.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Minimum MP load level at which inactive UEs are released at handover.
Used for PDSCH and PHICH sector selection in combined Cell. For each UE, all sectors received power are compared against the primary sector. Sectors that are below the threshold will be selected.
Disturbances: Changes may affect Sector Selection.

Parameter Description: Used for PUSCH sector selection in combined Cell. For each UE, all sectors received power are compared against the primary sector. Only the primary and the best sector that is below the threshold will be selected.
Disturbances: Changes may affect Sector Selection.

Parameter Description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for SIB16 Time Information Broadcast feature to function. When the limit is exceeded, the feature is deactivated.
Disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the SIB16 Time Information Broadcast due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

Parameter Description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) to function. When the limit is exceeded, the service is deactivated.
Disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

Parameter Description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) Support to function. When the limit is exceeded, the service is deactivated.
Disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) Support feature due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

Parameter Description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for features related to CDMA2000 fallback and handover to function. When the limit is exceeded, some of the functionality is deactivated.
Disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the features related to CDMA2000 due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

Parameter Description: Max allowed deviation for time and phase synchronization of eNodeB for TDD cells. If exceeded, TDD cells that use this limit are disabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.
Dependencies: timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment must be true.

Parameter Description: Set to false when the SIB16 Time Information Broadcast feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
Set to false when the Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
Set to false when the Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
Set to false when the features related to CDMA2000 are degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
If set to true, any time and phase synchronization accuracy-dependent feature is deactivated or degraded if its time and phase synchronization accuracy is not fulfilled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description: The percentile to use for the counter pmLicConnectedUsersActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicDlCapActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicUlCapActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicDlPrbCapActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicUlPrbCapActual.
Enables or disables the RRC Connection Reestablishment in source cell when there is no target neighbor cell information.
Dependencies: This attribute is only effective when feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Reestablishment is activated.

Parameter Description: Minimum required hit rate to qualify a related cell as high hit rate coverage cell by feature Cell Sleep Mode.
Used to turn on and off the function for checking existence of emergency calls.
Length of waiting time before soft-lock of cell starts to release all ongoing calls with Release with Redirect (RwR), when eNodeB internally triggers soft-lock of cell.
Length of waiting time before soft-lock of cell starts to release all ongoing calls with Release with Redirect (RwR), when operator triggers soft-lock of cell.
A policy parameter that sets the start value of the attribute mfbiSupport when an ExternalENodeBFunction is automatically created by the eNodeB.

DrxProfile ID used for TDD VOIP bearers on a mixed FDD/TDD eNodeB. The default value results in TDD using the same DrxProfile as FDD for VOIP bearers.
Configures use of autonomous gap as method of CGI measurement. If enabled, capable UEs are configured to use autonomous gap for CGI measurement to target LTE or UTRAN cell.
Dependencies: This attribute is effective only when ANR for LTE or UTRAN feature is activated.

Parameter Description: Enables or disables the UL SINR max measurements and event triggers for the UL quality. Only has effect if license for Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is not installed.

The targeted maximum allowed time between scheduling occasions of an UL bearer. A bearer that is not scheduled within the specified time is given higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. It is recommended to set the value =< than the PDB. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
Dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Dynamic UE Admission Control is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: The targeted maximum allowed time between scheduling occasions of a DL bearer. A bearer that is not scheduled within the specified time is given higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. It is recommended to set the value =< than the PDB. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
Dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Dynamic UE Admission Control is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Supervision timer of the outgoing S1/X2/intra-eNodeB handover execution procedure according to 3GPP TS 36.413 and TS 36.423.
If the feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Re-establishment is active this timer also supervises the Context Fetch procedure.
Disturbances: Low values can stop outgoing HO.

Parameter Description: Configures UL quality measure type utilized for decisions on when to configure and de-configure TTI Bundling. If setting is 'ULTRIG' uplink SINR value from 'Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility' is used for TTI Bundling.
Obsolete: Since 25.Q3. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
If the node monitors and measures delay for all S1-U termination points or not.

Delay measurements are performed and monitoring interval is 60 seconds. Processing time at responder is included in the measured delay.
If the node monitors and measures delay for all X2-U termination points or not.
Dependencies:
If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, and peer node supports delay measurements, delay measurements are performed and monitoring interval is 1 second.
If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is not activated, or peer node does not support delay measurements,
delay measurements are not performed and monitoring interval is 60 seconds.

Parameter Description: DSCP value used for outgoing GTP-U echo request packets on S1-U.
DSCP value used for outgoing GTP-U echo request packets on X2-U.
DSCP value used for outgoing GTP-U error indication messages.
S1-U failure action.

Activation/deactivation of feature Intra-Cell Handover to Additional Band.
Precondition: Requires support for the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators in the eNB.

Parameter Description: When enabled, additional frequency bands have higher priority than primary frequency band when considering whether intra-cell handover will improve secondary cell availability.
Precondition: useBandPrioritiesInSCellEval must be enabled.

Parameter Description: When enabled, secondary cell evaluation for CA aware Intra-Cell Handover to Additional Band is done according to priorities in prioritizeAdditionalBands and EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList.
Precondition: caAwareMfbiIntraCellHo must be enabled.

Parameter Description: When enabled, prioritized additional frequency band list is broadcasted in SIB1 according to priorities in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed
Precondition: Requires support for the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators in the eNB.

Parameter Description:
Local outer address used for this node.

Reference to an instance of AddressIPv4 or AddressIPv6 MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
Reference to an instance of AddressIPv4 or AddressIPv6 MO for configuring IP address for X2 user plane connections.

Also configures IP address for X2 EN-DC user plane connections if upEndcX2IpAddressRef is not configured.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

Parameter Description: Reference to an instance of SctpEndpoint. Refers to the SCTP endpoint for X2 control connections unless specified by sctpEndcX2Ref.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in Baseband Radio Node.

Parameter Description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. VlanPort instance that can be used to set up EranInterMeLinks and BbLinks. Used as default when no value is specified for ExternalENodeBFunction::eranVlanPortRef.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Immediately after the change, all EranInterMeLinks are disconnected. Node restart is required.

Parameter Description:
DSCP value used for outgoing inter-eNB CA packets on X2.
It is recommended to set this to the same value as "QCI9 - Non-GBR TCP Default Bearer", as inter-eNB CA benefits should be treated as opportunistic and not allowed to interfere with baseline LTE performance.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can also affect other X2 traffic than CA packets.

Parameter Description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the maximum deviation that is allowed for Carrier Aggregation to function. When the limit is exceeded, inter-eNB CA or eRAN CA is deactivated. Takes effect immediately.
Disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the inter-eNB CA or eRAN CA feature due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization between two eNodeBs.
Dependencies: Only effective if timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment is true.

Parameter Description:
Granted UL baseband capacity.
Available capacity of corresponding Baseband HWAC property for all enabled Baseband HW.

Max UL baseband capacity available on unlocked Baseband hardware.
Maximum limit of UL capacity that can be granted by baseband HWAC. This level sets the limit at emergency unlock.

Granted DL baseband capacity.
Available capacity of corresponding Baseband HWAC property for all enabled Baseband HW.

Max DL baseband capacity available on unlocked Baseband hardware.
Maximum limit of DL capacity that can be granted by baseband HWAC. This level sets the limit at emergency unlock.

Method to select an alternative MME when eNodeB sends back initial UE message to MME. Used when eNodeB fails to select valid MME by receiving reroute NAS request message that is defined in TS36.413 ch. 8.6.2.5.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Enables processing resource trading between PUCCH and PUSCH during uplink resource allocation.

Parameter Description: Reduced observability mode that is activated automatically due to PM memory overload.

Required amount of Baseband HWAC throughput capacity for DL to be allocated to LTE.

The setting impacts installation and distribution of HUPs on the node.
In LTE+NR mixed mode Baseband configuration, GNBDUFunction::dlBbCapacityTarget must also be considered in following cases:

- If dlBbCapacityTarget value is greater than or equal to 75 for just one RAT, the system attempts to allocate the required value to that RAT. Available excess capacity is allocated to the other RAT.
- If dlBbCapacityTarget value is greater than or equal to 75 on both RATs, an attempt to fulfill both requirements is made with priority to NR. Until requirements are met, HUPs are distributed proportionally. Afterwards, HUPs are distributed equally.
- If dlBbCapacityTarget value is undefined on both RATs (set to empty on NR and set to -1 on LTE), Baseband HWAC throughput capacity for DL is equally allocated by system to the extent allowed by HUPs, with priority to NR.

With the Instantaneous Licensing feature activated, an undefined attribute setting gives a minimum requirement of 75 Mbps.

Granted Baseband DL capacity is shown by ENodeBFunction::dlBbCapacityNet attribute.
Granted Baseband UL capacity is half of granted DL capacity and is shown by ENodeBFunction::ulBbCapacityNet attribute.

Information on installed Baseband HWACs and HUPs can be found in CapacityUsage::hupInfo.
Disturbances: Changing this parameter in LTE+NR mixed mode configuration can impact throughput limit on NR and LTE and can cause traffic degradation.

Parameter Description:
Whether functionality to support LTE MFBI for EN-DC setup and EN-DC Triggered Handover is activated.

When activated, following apply:
- LTE MFBI is considered.
- PCell band can be changed to additional band if it supports EN-DC.
- EN-DC-triggered handover can be performed to a neighbor LTE cell that supports EN-DC on the additional band.
Dependencies: Only applicable when feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is present and active in eNodeB.

Parameter Description:
Whether SRS allocation algorithm version 2 for TDD AAS is enabled.

Value must be set to true when there are more than three cells unlocked when any cell has SRS capability.
Value false increases performance slightly when there are up to three cells unlocked when any cell has SRS capability.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in TDD cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio when Basic AAS for TDD is active and EUtranCellTDD::ulSrsEnable is true.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when all EUtranCellTDD instances in the RBS are locked.

Parameter Description:
Time and phase synchronization state for NR interwork.

Set to false when features that interwork with NR are degraded due to unfulfilled requirement on time and phase synchronization accuracy (0.5 ms). Otherwise, set to true.
Only applicable when timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment is set to true.

Whether intra-band EN-DC is blocked for all overlapping bands.

If true and EndcCaPolicy = NR_PREFERRED, intra-band EN-DC is blocked for all overlapping bands, that is, overlapping bands in following combinations:
- Intra-band combinations
- Mixed intra- and inter-band combinations
This includes blocking B41-n41.

If false or EndcCaPolicy = LTE_PREFERRED, intra-band EN-DC is blocked for overlapping bands in intra-band combinations only.
As an exception, B41-n41 is not blocked.

Whether flexible duct interference detection is enabled.

Function locates and reduces interference between TDD cells with arbitrary bandwidth. Detection method uses flexible characteristic sequence.
Dependencies:
Can be set to true only when value of EUtranCellTDD::earfcn minus lowest channel number of EUtranCellTDD::freqBand minus EUtranCellTDD::ductIntFlexibleDetectionOffset can be divided by 3.

Specification: 3GPP TS 36.101.

Parameter Description:
Whether LTE Persistent PRACH Configuration feature is enabled.

If enabled, PRACH configuration index can be changed by setting prachSfn attribute.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when all EUtranCellFDD/TDD instances in the RBS are locked.

Parameter Description: Allows or restricts use of EN-DC for UEs within node.

Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
Whether EN-DC FR2 is inhibited during VoLTE.

Time period between fault detection and External Link Failure alarm notification.

If link is reestablished before timer expires, alarm is not raised.

Time period between fault detection and External Link to gNodeB Failure alarm notification.

If link is reestablished before timer expires, alarm is not raised.

Time period between fault detection and PLMN Service alarm notifications.

Following alarms are reported:
- PLMN Service Redundancy Lost
- PLMN Service Unavailable

If link is reestablished before timer expires, alarm is not raised.

Parameter allows to choose on which level PLMN Service Unavailable alarm is raised.

When set to ENODEB, PLMN Service Unavailable alarm is raised on node level.
When set to CELL, PLMN Service Unavailable alarm is raised on cell level.
S1-U redundancy mode.
Dependencies: Only relevant when upIpAddress2Ref is set.

Parameter Description:
Number of steps for UE capability enquiry procedure.

Two-step or three-step capability enquiry is used on initial connection.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Whether sleeping cell data collection mechanism is enabled.
Whether PIM cancellation automatic configuration is active.

Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
Specifies periodic repetition of NB-IoT ON duration followed by a possible period of inactivity.
Number of consecutive NPDCCH periods at the beginning of NB-IoT DRX Cycle.
Dependencies:
Value of struct member drxInactivityTimerNb0 must be greater than or equal to value of struct member onDurationTimerNb0.
Value of struct member drxInactivityTimerNb1 must be greater than or equal to value of struct member onDurationTimerNb1.
Value of struct member drxInactivityTimerNb2 must be greater than or equal to value of struct member onDurationTimerNb2.

Parameter Description:
Number of NB-IoT consecutive NPDCCH periods after subframe in timer expires.

Timer refers to HARQ RTT timer or UL HARQ RTT timer.
Dependencies:
Value of struct member drxInactivityTimerNb0 must be greater than or equal to value of struct member onDurationTimerNb0.
Value of struct member drxInactivityTimerNb1 must be greater than or equal to value of struct member onDurationTimerNb1.
Value of struct member drxInactivityTimerNb2 must be greater than or equal to value of struct member onDurationTimerNb2.

Parameter Description:
Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q2. Replaced by diffX2CauseMisconfig. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Whether Location Report is sent when PSCell is added, released or changed.

Timer used for DoNAS for NB-IoT.

Starts when S1 message which need MME response is sent to MME.
Stops when response from MME is received.

Whether 3450-3550 MHz range of band n77 is supported.

If true, only UEs that indicate capability for extendedBand-n77-r16 can access 3450-3550 MHz range of band n77.
Value must be true for 3450-3550 MHz range of band n77 in the USA.
Whether automatic PIM detection is activated.
Dependencies: Cannot be true while any EUtranCellFDD::pimDetectionEnabled attribute is true.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q1. Replaced by ENodeBFunction::pimDetectionEnabled. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Whether UEs in EN-DC are configured to provide overheating assistance information.

If true, overheating assistance configuration is sent in RRC Connection Reconfiguration message for all UEs with overheating indication capabilities.
Prohibit timer for overheating assistance information reporting (T345).
Dependencies: Only applicable when attribute endcOverheatingAssistance is set to true.

Parameter Description: Enables PS handover and SRVCC to Shared WCDMA RAN for additional 3G PLMNs in MOCN configuration.

Enables activation of MORAN on Single Baseband configuration.

Value true means that MORAN on Single Baseband (Shared LTE RAN configuration) can be activated.
Dependencies:
MORAN on Single Baseband (Shared LTE RAN configuration) is activated if moranOnSingleBbEnabled is set to TRUE and feature Shared LTE RAN and feature Multiple IP Addresses for S1 and X2 are active.

When MORAN on Single Baseband (Shared LTE RAN configuration) is activated, MORAN EUtranCellFDD and EUtranCellTDD can be created.

Parameter Description: Channel quality mode when scheduler considers channel quality.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: This parameter can take effect if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium" or "proportional_fair_high" has been selected. Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and active.

Parameter Description:
Whether preceding NR frequency of UE is excluded from mobility back to NR standalone.

Determines mobility method to be excluded.
Only applicable when UE is moved from NR due to traffic steering or offload functionalities.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
Temporary attributes are intended for temporary solutions.

Their usage may vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use may be overridden by the information in CPI Info documents. Note that a later release may use another attribute to control the functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or may remove the functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
Number of IPEC control steps after which IPEC Available PRB will be reported.
Change Take Effect: Only after CellMeasurements procedure is restarted, i.e. a request start is sent, followed by a request stop for a particular report type.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when licenses for Intelligent Power Emission Control feature and Global SCell Evaluation feature are present and features are active.
Applicable when EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::IpecGseEnabled is true and PowerBackoff::powerBackoffEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: Whether voice session mobility to NR standalone network is allowed.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to false might stop outgoing handover.
Deprecated: Since 23.Q4. Replaced by voiceMobilityToNrEnabled. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Whether relativePriorityBr attribute applies for QCIs carrying Cat-M traffic.

If true, relativePrority attribute defined for QCI carrying Cat-M traffic must be overridden with value of relativePriorityBr attribute. If false, value of relativePrority attribute is taken directly from QCI table and overriding is not possible.

Only applicable if licenses for Category M Access and Category M Dynamic Resource Sharing with LTE are present and features are active.

Whether separate en-gNodeB list for each PLMN is used for MORAN cell.

If true, dedicated Connected en-gNB List for MORAN cell is sent over S1.
Dependencies: Only applicable when ENodeBFunction::endcX2IpAddrViaS1Active is true.

Parameter Description:
Whether 3650-3980 MHz range of band n77 is supported.

If set to true, only UEs that indicate capability for extendedBand-n77-2-r17 can access 3650-3980 MHz range of band n77.
Value must be set to true for 3650-3980 MHz range of band n77 in Canada.

Enables queueing of E-RAB Setup Requests that are received during ongoing CGI Measurement procedure.

If disabled, ENodeB rejects the E-RAB Setup Request with cause Interaction-with-other-procedure, if received during ongoing CGI measurement.

PCI conflict detecting and reporting for following architectures.

- E-UTRAN,
- NR RAN,
- Both E-UTRAN and NR RAN.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for PCI Conflict Reporting is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether mobility to NR for Mission-Critical Push-to-Talk connections is disabled.

Only applicable if license for Outgoing NR IRAT Handover is present and feature is active.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
NR cell is considered to be overloaded for this time.

Cell is barred from EN-DC and handover to NR SA procedures.
If 0, timer is not started for congested cells.
Disturbances: High values can prevent EN-DC setup or Handover to NR SA.

Parameter Description:
The size limit of Source RNC to Target RNC Transparent Container IE.

Carrier Aggregation is related part of UE capabilities in S1AP HandoverRequired message is removed during SRVCC and non-SRVCC handovers to 2G or 3G when UE capabilities are larger than size limit of Source RNC to Target RNC Transparent Container IE. Value must be aligned with actual limits in 2G and 3G Core Networks.
Enables or disables mobility to GERAN or UTRAN for MC PTT connections.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
Whether extended transmission mode mixture is enabled.

When enabled, transmission mode tunability and mixture are extended for eNodeB that has cells with mixed number of TX antennas (2TX, 4TX, or 8TX).

Concerns interaction of following features:

- Dual Antenna Downlink Performance Package
- 4x2 Quad Antennal Downlink Performance Package
- 4x4 Quad Antennal Downlink Performance Package

with following features:

- Single Layer Beamforming Performance Package
- Dual Layer Beamforming Performance Package
- TM9 8x2 Octal Antenna Downlink Performance Package
- TM9 8x4 Octal Antenna Downlink Performance Package

Whether Inter-eNodeB Carrier Aggregation support for TDD as PCell is enabled.

Only applicable if license for Inter-eNodeB Carrier Aggregation is present and featue is active.

Reference to an instance of VlanPort MO.

VlanPort instances that can be used to set up EranInterMeLinks and Bblinks for PIM function. Used as default value when no value is specified for ExternalENodeBFunction::eranPimVlanPortRef.
If empty, EranInterMeLinks and Bblinks for PIM function cannot be created.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Immediately after the change, all EranInterMeLinks are disconnected. Node restart is required.

Parameter Description: Whether voice session mobility to NR standalone network is allowed.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to false might stop outgoing handover.

Parameter Description:
Number of connected Elastic RAN PIM avoidance partners.

If 6, new Elastic RAN tunnel for PIM avoidance cannot be established.
Whether automatic PIM detection is activated.

Whether security mode setup and RRC connection reconfiguration from Idle mode is skipped.

Applied before UE release when CSFB is started from RRC Idle mode, if no CSFB measurements are needed.

Whether differentiated cause value is used when EN-DC SgNB change is refused.

If true, eNodeB returns cause value no-radio-resources-available instead of target-not-allowed in X2AP message SGNB CHANGE REFUSE. This cause conversion occurs only when inter-gNodeB PSCell change is refused by eNodeB because of configuration error.

Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Percentage of UEs selected for performing security-initiated UE measurements.

If 0, LTE Security-Initiated UE Measurements feature is deactivated in eNodeB.
Threshold for Rx Branch Imbalance alarm trigger.
Threshold for Rx Diversity Lost alarm trigger.

Whether alarm handling for antenna system monitoring is enabled.

Only applicable if license for Antenna System Monitoring is present and feature is active.

Whether Multi-Node PIM Avoidance is PLMN agnostic.

If true, Multi-Node PIM Avoidance is agnostic to PLMN when selecting aggressors.
If false, Multi-Node PIM Avoidance ignores aggressors if victim has other PLMN.

Whether PWS feature is supported in Cell Sleep Mode feature and MIMO Sleep Mode feature.

If true, sleeping capacity cells can be activated by PWS feature. Then following applies when S1AP WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message is received:
- In Cell Sleep Mode feature, cell in sleep state is activated and starts broadcasting PWS alert. Activated cell is prevented from entering sleep state until PWS broadcast is over.
- In MIMO Sleep Mode feature, cell previously reconfigured from MIMO to SIMO is reconfigured to MIMO. Reconfiguration to SIMO is prevented until PWS broadcast is over.

If false, sleeping capacity cells cannot be activated by PWS feature.

Only applicable if license for Public Warning System feature is present and feature is active,
and license for Cell Sleep Mode feature, or MIMO Sleep Mode feature, or both, is present and feature is active.

Whether sleeping capacity cells are added in S1AP WRITE-REPLACE WARNING RESPONSE message.

If true, sleeping capacity cells are included in message.
If false, sleeping capacity cells are not included in message.
Value of ENodeBFunction::pwsSupportInCsmAndMsm attribute does not affect whether sleeping capacity cells are included in message.

Changing this attribute to true can result in increased PWS broadcast success ratio in statistics visible in core network.
Success ratio can increase in statistics also if ENodeBFunction::pwsSupportInCsmAndMsm is false.

Only applicable if license for Public Warning System feature is present and feature is active,
and license for Cell Sleep Mode feature, or MIMO Sleep Mode feature, or both, is present and feature is active.

Whether automatic removal of disabled E-RAN link for downlink carrier aggregation is enabled.

Only ASM-triggered E-RAN link, over which there is no manually configured SCell candidate for carrier aggregation, can be automatically removed.

ASM-triggered means automatically triggered by Automatic SCell Management feature.

Time ASM-triggered E-RAN link must be disabled before it can be removed automatically.

If 0, disabled ASM-triggered E-RAN link for downlink carrier aggregation is removed immediately.

ASM-triggered means automatically triggered by Automatic SCell Management feature.

Control of default value of eranPrioritizationDisabled for automatically created ExternalENodeBFunction instance.

If true, initial value of ExternalENodeBFunction::eranPrioritizationDisabled is set to false in ExternalENodeBFunction instance when created automatically by ANR or X2.

If false, initial value of ExternalENodeBFunction::eranPrioritizationDisabled is set to true in ExternalENodeBFunction instance when created automatically by ANR or X2.
