Specifies if outgoing uplink-triggered mobility actions are enabled or disabled in the cell.
Used when Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled. The parameter has effect if Mobility Control in Poor Coverage is enabled and mobCtrlAtPoorCovActive is set to true in the cell.
PDCCH DCI format 1A is used for SRB to increase transmission success rate and to minimize interruption time.
PDCCH DCI format 1A to increase MOS for QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT in high interference or high path loss scenarios.
PDCCH DCI format 1A for first retransmission due to DTX of SRB and serviceType VoIP or PTT.

Relative priority in initial SCell selection for cells that can be configured with UL Carrier Aggregation. Applicable where several SCells are initially configured simultaneously. Lowest value has highest priority.
Dependencies: Applicable when 3CC Carrier aggregation Extension Feature (FAJ 121 3084) is enabled and sCellSelectionMode is equal to UN_ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION or ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION.

Parameter Description: List of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to. Primary frequency band, EARFCN value of the cell, is not included. Secondary cell evaluation is done according to list order, and/or the list is broadcasted in SIB1. Highest priority band is position 0 in the list.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if ENodeBFunction::useBandPrioritiesInSCellEval or EUtranCellFDD/TDD::mfbiFreqBandIndPrio is enabled.
prioAdditionalFreqBandList only contains frequency bands from additionalFreqBandList.
prioAdditionalFreqBandList is reset to empty list if MO action changeFrequency changes frequency of EUtranCellFDD/TDD, and new additionalFreqBandList does not contain bands included in prioAdditionalFreqBandList.

Parameter Description: Defines how many dB higher than the original SR detection threshold can be used as high SR detection threshold. Used together with srProcessingLevel to reduce false SR detection.
Defines how many SRs eNodeB must receive in a row in order to process it. Used together with srDetectHighThres to reduce false SR detection.
Controls adaptive CFI to avoid using CFI=1 or CFI=1,2, when scheduling UEs that are in handover. The highest CFI value in available CFI values determined by pdcchCfiMode is not prohibited.
Dependencies: Only applicable when attribute pdcchCfiMode is set to CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_2, CFI_STATIC_3, or CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_3.

Parameter Description: Controls if link adaptation function allocates largest possible resource to last scheduled UE in the DL. Used to improve UE decoding success rate with reduced code rate.

Maximum number of physical resource blocks (PRBs) allowed on PDSCH for each UE.
Note: If the set value is larger than the system bandwidth, then the system bandwidth value will be used instead.
For PDSCH resource allocation type 0, the actual maximum number of PRBs that is allocated will be a multiple of RBGs (Resource Block Groups) that is nearest to the set value but without exceeding it.

SI message to which each SIB is mapped.
Note: SIB2 is always mapped to SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: SI validity timer. The timer is set to 3h or 24h.
Min received RSRP level in E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection for UE in enhanced coverage mode. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin_CE in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1-BR.

Min quality level (RSRQ) in cell for UE in enhanced coverage mode.

Corresponds to Qqualmin_CE in TS 36.304, sent in SIB1-BR. If 0, it is not sent and UE applies default value of negative infinity for Qqualmin_CE.
Enables Dynamic uplink resource allocation on cell level.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license UlDynamicResourceAllocation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Specifies if SINR-based UL power control can be used or not. If enabled, SNR-based closed-loop power control and SINR-based closed-loop power control can be adaptively selected.
Dependencies: Attribute only has effect if feature Differential Uplink Power Control is activated.

Parameter Description: SINR target value for SINR-based UL closed-loop power control.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: SINR target only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

Parameter Description: Threshold value for measured noise plus interference level. If measured noise plus interference is higher than interferenceThresholdSinrClpc, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
Dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

Parameter Description: Threshold of UL transmission power per PRB. If averaged UL transmission power measurement per PRB is lower than ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc over a set percentage of UL bandwidth, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
Dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

Parameter Description:
Threshold number of SCells configured by Carrier Aggregation (CA) users with this cell as PCell. When number of SCells configured for UEs connected in this PCell is higher than caPrioThreshold, following rules apply:
- For Configurable SCell Priority, all frequency carriers configured for CA are assumed to have equal priority regardless of configured values.
- For Global SCell Evaluation, all SCell relations from PCell are handled equally regardless of threshold for number of SCell UEs.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when following apply:
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to PRIORITIZED and Configurable SCell Priority is active.
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to GLOBAL_EVALUATION and Global SCell Evaluation is active.

Parameter Description: Enables or disables measurement-based Ericsson Lean Carrier Control.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license Ericsson Lean Carrier is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs that do not have a secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

Initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

Initial value for primary cell PDCCH outer loop adjustment in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have a bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have a bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.
PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

PDCCH outer loop up step size for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

PDCCH target error rate for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.
PDCCH target error rate for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

PDCCH target error rate for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.
Set to true when idle mode eDRX shall be allowed in the cell.
Long DRX cycle for ELC. Value of elcLongDrxCycle is in number of sub-frames.
Dependencies: Feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is present active.

Parameter Description:
Enable automatic configuration of tReorderingDl and tReorderingUl. Configuration is based on HARQ-interval together with an offset defined by harqOffsetDl/harqOffsetUl.tReordering >= 'Max number of HARQ' * HARQ-interval + harqOffset, where closest higher or equal allowed value is used.

This configuration is only applied to UM bearers. AM bearers will still use tReorderingUl and tReorderingDl from QciProfilePredefined or QciProfileOperatorDefined.
Offset used when tReorderingDl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingDl = 'Max number of HARQ for DL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetDl.
Offset used when tReorderingUl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingUl = 'Max number of HARQ for UL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetUl.
Enables function to automatically adapt t-PollretransmitTimer to the time it takes to complete HARQ procedure + harqOffset (UL and DL).
Enable/disable service-specific HARQ on cell level. Function must have valid license.
Maximum downlink PRB usage that scheduling stays on-hold for Low Energy Scheduler Solution.
Turns on/off Configurable DL BLER Target.
SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values go higher, more candidates are selected for Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP, but more user measurements are triggered. This impacts MP load and transport load over X2.
Dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrHys.

Parameter Description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values get bigger, gaps for triggering Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP user switching get bigger.
Dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrThr.

Parameter Description: Threshold for % of PRBs with "UL Tx power per PRB >= ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc" during measSinrClpcPeriod. Below threshold means low cell power load and then SINR based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
Dependencies: Attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc must be true.

Parameter Description: Shows the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.
Whether or not UL scheduler is enabled to force allocation of PRBs to Data-Aware, UL-Scheduling UEs last.
Number of data-aware UL-scheduling UEs that can be improved at allocation of PDCCH and PUSCH.
Whether or not UL-scheduler is enabled that uses adaptive re-transmission more frequently for data-aware UL-scheduling UEs, to reduce fragments in UL spectrum.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Threshold used to help identify data-aware UL scheduling UEs. If BSR >= bsrThreshold, UE becomes candidate UE for UL improvement.

Length of time eNodeB rejects traffic requests from non-privileged UEs when detecting high procedure latency. Used in Procedure Latency Supervision. Privileged traffic, such as High Priority Access (HPA) and Emergency, is never rejected due to high procedure latency conditions.
Whether or not SCell selection for high power UE that is not capable of CA simultaneously is enabled.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Current barring priority level based on Progressive Access Barring or PLMN-Specific Access Barring algorithms.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description:
Minimum barring factor for Load-Based Access Barring algorithm or priority level 0 for one of the following algorithms:
- Progressive Access Barring
- Progressive Barring of Special Access Classes
- PLMN-Specific Access Barring
Dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description:
Priority level 1 minimum barring factor for one of the following algorithms:
- Progressive Access Barring
- Progressive Barring of Special Access Classes
- PLMN-Specific Access Barring
Dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description:
Priority level 2 minimum barring factor for one of the following algorithms:
- Progressive Access Barring
- Progressive Barring of Special Access Classes
- PLMN-Specific Access Barring
Dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: Physical-layer cell ID.
Dependencies:
Pair of earfcndl and physicalLayerCellId attributes must be unique in RBS.
Equal to 3 x physicalLayerCellIdGroup + physicalLayerSubCellId.

Parameter Description: Priority of high power UE capability.

Threshold used in restrict SE number that enhanced adaptive Retransmission candidates, if there are too many non-adaptive retransmission candidates, only "noOfEnhAdptReTxCand" numbers SE can be the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue.
Maximum number of SEs added to the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue as candidates.
If set to -1, number of candidates is automatically decided by eNodeB.
If set to 0, no UEs added to queue and thus feature has no effect.

SI message to which each SIB is mapped.
Note: SIB2 is always mapped to SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.
Whether or not prescheduling is enabled.
SINR threshold for Elastic RAN UL CoMP user selection.
Dependencies: Must be used together with eranUlCompUserSelSinrHys.

Parameter Description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for Elastic RAN UL CoMP user selection.
Dependencies: Must be used together with eranUlCompUserSelSinrThr.

Parameter Description: References to an instance of CellResource MO.
Dependencies: CellResource MO having non empty plmnList and CellResource MO having non empty spidList shouldn't be referred together(CellResource MO having empty plmnList and empty spidList is considered as configuring spidList(non empty spidList)). Duplication of PLMN or SPID within referred CellResouce MOs is not allowed.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: LiteMcsReduction feature mode.

Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

Parameter Description: References to an instance of MeasCellGroup MO for grouping on a cell basis.
Dependencies:
MeasCellGroup with 0 groupId can not be referred.
Only MeasCellGroup having empty spidList and empty plmnList can be referred.

Parameter Description: Enables Instant Uplink Access (IUA) for a cell.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q3. Replaced by InstantUplinkAccess::iuaEnabled. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Time interval between UL short-SPS (semi-persistent scheduling) instances. Value 0 means load based selection of IUA interval.
Dependencies: In MO EUtranCellFDD, only values 0,1,2,4 are allowed. In MO EUtranCellTDD, only values 0,1,5 are allowed.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q3. Replaced by InstantUplinkAccess::iuaInterval. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Maximum percentage of UL PRBs and SEs that are used by IUA at cell level. The actual number of resources per cell depends on iuaMaxResourcePerBbm.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q3. Replaced by InstantUplinkAccess::iuaCellResourceLimit. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Maximum UL PRBs that are used by an IUA UE. The actual number of PRBs per UE depends on iuaMaxResourcePerCell.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q3. Replaced by InstantUplinkAccess::iuaUePrbLimit. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Enables PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

Parameter Description: Value of threshold to enable the PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling. PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling is triggered when the number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell is less than or equal to ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and
- attribute ns05FullBandSchedEnabled in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is true.

Parameter Description: Controls if the low band can be allocated to NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_PROHIBIT', the low band cannot be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_AVAILABLE', the low band can always be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION', the low band can only be allocated to the NS_05 UEs which are detected as not in repeater zone.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

Parameter Description: Value of threshold to detect if the NS_05 UE is in repeater zone. If the NS_05 UE's pathloss measured on low band is bigger than or equal to the value of other band plus ns05PathlossOffsetThres, the NS_05 UE is detected as in repeater zone.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and

Parameter Description: Reference to a list of MeasCellGroup MOs for grouping on UE basis. Referenced Mos include measurements on differentiated UEs into a measurement group.
Dependencies:
MeasCellGroup with 0 groupId can not be referred.
MeasCellGroup with empty spidList and empty plmnList can not be referred.
MeasCellGroup with non-empty plmnList and MeasCellGroup having non null spidList can not be referred together.
Duplication of plmn or spid within referred MeasCellGroups is not allowed.

Parameter Description:
Controls which DL subframes are unavailable for Cat-M DL due to MBMS operation.
Fewer unavailable subframes optimize Cat-M1 DL max throughput, but change of unavailable subframes can cause Cat-M1 connection drops and temporary difficulties to page certain UEs. Avoided by less dynamic setting (lower value).
0: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to MbsfnArea::commonSFAllocList and MbsfnArea::mbsfnAreaCellRelation.
1: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to MbsfnArea::commonSFAllocList and MbsfnArea::mbsfnAreaCellRelation if any MBSFN service is active in the cell, otherwise no unavailable subframes due to MBMS.
2: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to subframes blocked by active MBSFN services.

Shows valid subframes for DL BR transmissions, indicated by broadcasted SIB1-BR.
1: Corresponding subframe is valid DL BR subframe.
0: Corresponding subframe not valid DL BR subframe.
First element in the list corresponds to radio frames satisfying SFN mod 4 = 0, the next to radio frames satisfying SFN mod 4 = 1 and so on.
Each least significant bit represents subframe #0 of the corresponding SFN.
If SIB1-BR not broadcasted (Cat-M not supported in cell), list is empty.

Parameter Description:
Changes priorities of bands for Multiple Frequency Band Indicators.

If true:
Cell broadcasts freqBandIndicatorPriority in SIB1, and FreqBandIndicatorPriority=broadcasted is sent over X2 interface to neighbor eNB.
Prioritized additional frequency band list (prioAdditionalFreqBandList) is broadcasted in SIB1 and is also used for handovers (including S1 and X2 handovers) instead of additionalFreqBandList.
If UE indicates freqBandPriorityAdjustment capability (support of freqBandIndicatorPriority), primary band has the lowest priority, otherwise primary band has the highest priority.
mfbiFreqBandIndPrio is not used for handovers between Ericsson eNBs if ENodeBFunction::caAwareMfbiIntraCellHo = true.

If false:
Cell doesn't broadcast freqBandIndicatorPriority in SIB1, and FreqBandIndicatorPriority=not-broadcasted is sent over X2 interface to neighbor eNB.
additionalFreqBandList is broadcasted in SIB1 and is also used for handovers (including S1 and X2 handovers).
Primary band always has the highest priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. X2 handover and Connection Setup for MFBI capable UE can fail during a few seconds, leading to dropped calls.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is active.

Parameter Description: Number of CRS ports used for a cell that is sending CRS over air interface. -1 means undefined when a cell is not sending CRS over air interface. For example when a cell is locked or disabled.

Partially successful preallocation: nrOfPreallocatedSrRes < nrOfPaConnReservationsPerCell

Parameter Description:
Used to decide when to switch to resource-fair (RF) resource allocation strategy for UEs configured as frequency-selective (FS). Applicable when Evolved Uplink Frequency-Selective Scheduling feature is activated. Spectrum utilization gain caused by changing FS to RF is calculated for TTI with large buffer UE. If calculation result is above threshold, UL resource allocation strategy changes to RF for large buffer and not large buffer new UL transmissions configured as FS scheduled in that TTI.

Value 0 means highest switching probability. Value 99 means lowest switching probability. Value 100 means switching to RF is turned off.

Scheduling Request (SR) transmission parameter. This parameter controls the maximum number of SR transmissions on valid PUCCH resources before UE initiates a Random Access procedure. Value 4 corresponds to four transmissions, value 8 corresponds to eight transmissions and so on.

Whether Minimum Interference Scheduling feature is enabled.

If true, a random UL start position for new transmissions of resource-fair resource allocation strategy is selected in small UL PRB use case. This helps to make PRBs in whole UL spectrum more evenly used.

UL region size between each PUCCH region and band center.

Maximum size is as follows:
- 15 PRBs for 20 MHz and 15 MHz.
- 8 PRBs for 10 MHz and 5 MHz.
- 0 PRBs for 3 MHz and 1.4 MHz.
When value greater than maximum size is set, system uses maximum size.
Value 0 means there is no UL region.

Primary PLMN defined on cell.

If defined, overrides the value of ENodeBFunction::eNodeBPlmnId.
Dependencies:
Used only in context of MORAN on Single Baseband (Shared LTE RAN configuration). MORAN cell can only be created if MORAN on Single Baseband is activated.
If MORAN cell is created or unlocked and MORAN on Single Baseband is not activated, cell is disabled.
PLMN defined as cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId cannot be the same as ENodeBFunction::eNodeBPlmnId.
If cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId is defined, additionalPlmnList must be empty.
Up to two different cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId values can be defined within ENodeBFunction.
Precondition: If TheftDeterrence::thdStatus is LOCKED or LOCKED_PERMANENTLY, this value can only be changed when modified PLMN ID is part of Lock Token or Operator List.

Parameter Description:
UL HARQ transmission number threshold for Zero Interference VoLTE Operation feature.

If transmission number is greater than or equal to this threshold, a UE candidate can be put to reserved region.
When value is greater than MACConfiguration::ulMaxHARQTx value, system uses MACConfiguration::ulMaxHARQTx value.
Value 0 means feature is disabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Zero Interference VoLTE Operation is present and the feature is active.
Only applicable if
- minInterfSchedEnabled is true.
- minInterfUlRegionSize is equal to or greater than 3.

Parameter Description:
Whether SRS bandwidth for this cell is aligned with resources limitations.

Used for Uplink Frequency-Selective Scheduling feature. Aligned with frequency resource limitation, defined by following attributes:
- EUtranCellFDD::ulFrequencyAllocationProportion
- EUtranCellFDD::ulConfigurableFrequencyStart
Dependencies:
Only applicable when following options apply:
- Feature Frequency Selective Scheduling is activated, that is, ResourceAllocationStrategy is set to FREQUENCY_SELECTIVE.
- Uplink Sounding is activated.
- Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is configured.

Parameter Description: Whether enhancement of VoLTE Optimized Carrier Aggregation is enabled.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for VoLTE Optimized Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether UE capability refreshing in specific conditions is prohibited.

Only applicable when all the following conditions are fulfilled:
- establishmentCause in RRCConnectionRequest message is mo-VoiceCall-v1280.
- eNodeB has the UE capability information.
- Incoming handover is excluded.
Whether Connected Mode DRX in cell is activated for bandwidth-reduced low-complexity UEs.
Dependencies: Only applicable if drxActive is true.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of allowed bandwidth-reduced UEs in cell that are simultaneously connected to RRC.

Note: Maximum number of connected Category M1 UEs in each cell and each eNodeB is shared between LTE and Category M. Additionally, number of admitted UEs in cell is always determined with respect to eNodeB limit. For more information, for example about actual cell and eNodeB limits, see Supported Capacity and Configurations.

MO value must be set with respect to following conditions:
- Number of Category M narrowbands
- Traffic, that is amount of data to be sent and transmission periodicity
- Radio conditions, that is presence of CE level 1 Category M1 UEs, as actual limit is possible to achieve only for CE level 0 Category M1 UEs. The more CE level 1 UEs are admitted the lower admission limit is possible to achieve.

It is recommended to configure MO value to determine admission in iterative approach. This means increasing value step by step, for example from 128 to 256, or from 256 to 512. Otherwise, a sudden change to a value that is too high can deteriorate Random Access-related KPI for Category M.
It is recommended to implement this change outside busy hours, because every change of value requires cell lock and unlock, which might cause unnecessary Category M1 UE connection storm.
Dependencies: Only applicable if catm1SupportEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Measurement gap pattern used by UEs configured for EN-DC.

Value 0 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 0, with measurement gap periodicity 40 and measurement gap length 6.
Value 1 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 1, with measurement gap periodicity 80 and measurement gap length 6.
Restricts measurement gap offset selection for UEs configured for EN-DC.
Obsolete: Since 21.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Common CQI periodicity used for all UEs except Cat-M UEs.
Dependencies: Only default value, 80 ms is allowed when elcEnabled attribute is set to true.

Parameter Description: Whether AI Powered Advanced Cell Supervision mode is activated.
Recovery actions to perform when AI Powered Advanced Cell Supervision detects a sleeping cell.
Dependencies: Only applicable if aiAdvCellSupMode is NORMAL.

Parameter Description:
Measurement gap pattern used by UEs.

Value 0 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 0, with measurement gap periodicity 40 and measurement gap length 6.
Value 1 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 1, with measurement gap periodicity 80 and measurement gap length 6.

Whether alternative Scheduling Info Lists are present in SIB1 for SIB19 and higher.

If true, SIB19 and higher are mapped in SIB1 Scheduling Info List using late non-critical extensions.
If false, all SIBs including SIB19 and higher are mapped in SIB1 using legacy format of Scheduling Info List.
3GPP Rel-15.11.0 introduced late non-critical extensions as CR 4444 'Modification of SI scheduling for extended SIBs' to allow network access to non-3GPP-compatible UEs.
Whether adaptive pulling mechanism of enqueued RRC Connection Request messages is enabled.

Subframe within a radio frame where PRACH resource starts.

Value -1 means that system automatically assigns a valid value.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when prachConfigEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: PRACH Configuration Index that is used in cell.

Whether enhancement for Adjustable CRS Power feature is enabled.

Enhancement supports CRS gain 4.77 dB and 6 dB, but does not support ESS cells.

Number of preambles for Category M UEs connecting in CE level 0.

The number transmitted in SIB2 is equal to the following options:
- Sum of noOfPreamblesCeLvl0Br and noOfPreamblesCeLvl1Br if highestSupportedCeLevel is 0.
- noOfPreamblesCeLvl0Br if highestSupportedCeLevel is greater than 0.

Only applicable if licenses for Category M Access and Category M Flexible Preamble Selection are present and features are active.
Dependencies: See also dependencies of noOfCbraPreambles.

Parameter Description:
Number of preambles for Category M UEs connecting in CE level 1.

The number transmitted in SIB2 is equal to noOfPreamblesCeLvl1Br if highestSupportedCeLevel is greater than 0. Not applicable if highestSupportedCeLevel is 0.

Only applicable if licenses for Category M Access and Category M Flexible Preamble Selection are present and features are active.
Dependencies: See also dependencies of noOfCbraPreambles.

Parameter Description: Number of contention-based random access preambles transmitted in SIB2.
Dependencies:
When catm1SupportEnabled is false, following applies:

-When cfraEnable is true: noOfCbraPreambles <= 52
-When cfraEnable is false:noOfCbraPreambles <= 64

When catm1SupportEnabled is true, all following applies:

-When prachFreqSharing is false and cfraEnable is false:
noOfPreamblesCeLvl0Br + noOfPreamblesCeLvl1Br <= 8
noOfCbraPreambles =< 64

-When prachFreqSharing is false and cfraEnable is true:
noOfPreamblesCeLvl0Br + noOfPreamblesCeLvl1Br <= 8
noOfCbraPreambles <= 52

-When prachFreqSharing is true and cfraEnable is false:
noOfPreamblesCeLvl0Br + noOfPreamblesCeLvl1Br + noOfCbraPreambles <= 64

-When prachFreqSharing is true and cfraEnable is true:
noOfPreamblesCeLvl0Br + noOfPreamblesCeLvl1Br + noOfCbraPreambles <= 52

Parameter Description: Whether resource sharing is enabled in frequency domain for LTE and Category M1 preambles.
Dependencies: See dependencies of noOfCbraPreambles.

Parameter Description: Whether feature Category M Enhanced MPDCCH Capacity is enabled.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for Category M Enhanced MPDCCH Capacity is present and the feature is active.

If set to true, this feature is configured by ReportConfigA5Spifho attributes.
If set to false, this feature is configured by ReportConfigA5 attributes.

If true, optimizedPdcchMaxTargetBler is used as maximum PDCCH target BLER.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Optimized PDCCH is present and feature is active.

Cannot be set to false if diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: PDCCH congestion threshold for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellFDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description: DL PRB threshold of PDCCH congestion for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellFDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description: UL PRB threshold of PDCCH congestion for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellFDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description:
Share of DL PRBs available for scheduling Category M RRC establishment (SRB0).

Share of DL PRBs means MPDCCH and PDSCH.
If there are free resources remaining in the cell, more resources can be used by this share. However, in a congested network the additional resources can be used to fulfill other requirements. Since MPDCCH uses DL PRBs, this parameter may limit UL scheduling.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can prevent new traffic from being set up.

Parameter Description:
Share of DL PRBs available for scheduling RRC connected Category M UEs.

Share of DL PRBs means MPDCCH and PDSCH.
If there are free resources remaining in the cell, more resources can be used by this share. However, in a congested network the additional resources can be used to fulfill other requirements. Since MPDCCH uses DL PRBs, this parameter may limit UL scheduling.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Share of UL PRBs, that is PUSCH, available for scheduling RRC connected Category M UEs.

If there are free resources remaining in the cell, more resources can be used by this share. However, in a congested network the additional resources can be used to fulfill other requirements.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Number of invalid DL subframes added to previous invalid DL subframes.

Subframes can be invalidated for several reasons, not only by distributedEssInvalidSfDlBr. If percentage of valid subframes exceeds value set by attribute maxValidSubframeDlBr, system adds invalid subframes to fulfill maxValidSubframeDlBr requirement. Invalid DL subframes in attribute distributedEssInvalidSfDlBr are distributed over a 40 ms period. Distribution is optimized to reduce impact on NR from Cat-M Category M in ESS deployment. The total invalid DL subframes for Category M must not exceed 50%. The current number of total invalid DL subframes can be observed in a read only attribute validDlBrSubframes.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic and prevent traffic from being setup.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for age of earliest RLC SDU for DRB in DL, monitored by buffer-based EN-DC setup.

If value is 0, age of RLC SDUs in DL is not considered during buffer-based EN-DC setup.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Changing this attribute can decrease number of EN-DC users.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for total volume of RLC SDUs of DRB in DL, monitored by buffer-based EN-DC setup.

If value is 0, volume of RLC SDUs in DL is not considered during buffer-based EN-DC setup.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Changing this attribute can decrease number of EN-DC users.

Parameter Description:
Srxlev delta threshold in dB during relaxed monitoring.

Relaxed monitoring is switched off when attribute set to 0. Corresponds to SSearchDeltaP in 3GPP TS 36.304.

Value of dominating QCI for selecting UE sessions for throughput calculation.

UE sessions where dominating QCI matches attribute dominQciFilter are included in calculation of QCI-based throughput filtering in UL and DL.
If value equals -1, no UE session is included.

Following counters are related:
- pmMacUeThpUlMbbLowVolQciDistr
- pmMacUeThpUlMbbHighVolQciDistr
- pmUeExclThpUlRelativeQciLowVol
- pmUeExclThpUlRelativeQciHighVol
- pmUeExclThpUlShortTimeQciLowVol
- pmUeExclThpUlShortTimeQciHighVol
- pmUeThpDlMbbFilteredQciDistr
- pmUeExclThpDlQciShortDrb

Data inactivity timer for Category M1 UEs.

Timer is sent to UE only when UE supports DataInacMon capability.
Controls data inactivity operation for Category M1 UEs r14 or higher. Value 0 means that data inactivity timer is not sent for corresponding Coverage Enhancement (CE) level UEs.

If tInactivitytimerBr is equal to 0 or higher than 90, system uses value 0 for corresponding DataInactivityTimer CE level UEs.

DataInacTimerBr is started on UE, and UE releases the connection after expiration of this timer.
Whether B1 measurement with measurement gap is enabled for EN-DC capable UEs.

In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
Controls whether Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility feature is enabled.
Threshold for potential packet loss related to Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

Whether extreme good point for P0-based closed-loop power control is enabled.

Extreme good point optimization applies to P0-based closed-loop power control of Differential Uplink Power Control feautre.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when license for Differential Uplink Power Control is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether extreme bad point for P0-based closed-loop power control is enabled.

Extreme bad point optimization applies to P0-based closed-loop power control of Differential Uplink Power Control feaure.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when license for Differential Uplink Power Control is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
SINR threshold for identifying extreme bad point users.

User is identified at extreme bad point when their measured SINR is less than this threshold. For those users UL transmission power is increased, without limitation, for reaching threshold.
If set to higner value,
- More UEs are required to increase power.
- Interference to neighbor cells increases.
If set to lower value,
- Fewer UEs are required to increase power.
- Increase of interference to neighbor cells is smaller.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable when p0ClpcExBadEnabled is set to true. When p0ClpcExGoodEnabled and p0ClpcExBadEnabled are both set to true, value of p0ClpcExBadSinrThr must be smaller than value of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr.

Parameter Description:
SINR threshold for identifying extreme good point users for 16-QAM.

User is identified at extreme good point when their measured SINR is greater than this threshold. For those threshold UL transmission power is decreased for reaching threshold.
If set to higher value,
- Interference to neighbor cells is less reduced.
- Throughput of current cell is not degraded.
If set to lower value,
- Interference to neighbor cells is more reduced.
- Throughput of current cell might be degraded.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable when p0ClpcExGoodEnabled is set to true. When p0ClpcExGoodEnabled and p0ClpcExBadEnabled are both set to true, value of p0ClpcExBadSinrThr must be smaller than value of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr.

Parameter Description:
SINR offset of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr for 64-QAM-capable UEs.

Increases SINR threshold for identifying extreme good point users for 64-QAM. Used for maintaining maximum throughput for 64-QAM.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for 64-QAM Uplink is present and feature is active. Only takes effect if p0ClpcExGoodEnabled attribute is true.

Parameter Description:
SINR offset of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr for 256-QAM-capable UEs.

Increases SINR threshold for identifying extreme good point users for 256-QAM. Used for maintaining maximum throughput for 256-QAM.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for 256-QAM Uplink is present and feature is active. Only takes effect if p0ClpcExGoodEnabled attribute is true.

Parameter Description:
Whether compensation for beamforming gain of AAS full IRC receiver is applied in UE power control.

If true, UE power is compensated for full IRC beamforming gain. It allows UE to transmit at lower power level at same path loss in FDD AAS cell compared to classic LTE cell.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for Interference Rejection Combining for AAS FDD is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether load management actions are allowed on EN-DC-capable UE.

These load management actions are triggered by load balancing and offloading features.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Basic Intelligent Connectivity is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether cell is identified as PIM victim.

PIM detection can identify a cell as PIM victim if cell is affected by interference from passive intermodulation. Details on interference can be collected with PM events.

If empty, PIM detection is not active for this cell.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q1. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Whether VoLTE and PTT prescheduling is enabled.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for VoLTE Prescheduling is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether Global SCell Evaluation (GSE) is enhanced for coexistence of Intelligent Power Emission Control (IPEC) and Carrier Aggregation.

Enhancement makes GSE consider IPEC Available PRB values reported by IPEC to optimize SCell selection and re-selection.
Reports with IPEC Available PRB are sent for intra-eNB and inter-eNB cells.
For inter-eNB cells, information is exchanged via X2 message.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when licenses for Intelligent Power Emission Control feature and Global SCell Evaluation feature are present and features are active.
Applicable when PowerBackoff::powerBackoffEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
Whether differentiated maximum PDCCH target BLER is enabled.

If true, pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow and pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh are used instead of optimizedPdcchMaxTargetBler.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if licenses for Optimized PDCCH and Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation are present and features are active.

Cannot be set to true if pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is false.

For usage in subscriber group, see description of attribute SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode.

Parameter Description:
Low maximum value for PDCCH target BLER.

Used when PDCCH SINR is greater than diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerThres.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when both pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled and diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled are true.

Cannot be higher than pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh.

Cannot be lower than pdcchTargetBler or pdcchTargetBlerPCell.

For usage in subscriber group, see attribute SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode.

Parameter Description:
High maximum value for PDCCH target BLER.

Used when PDCCH SINR is lower than or equal to diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerThres.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when both pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled and diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled are true.

Cannot be lower than pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow.

For usage in subscriber group, see attribute SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode.

Parameter Description: PDCCH congestion condition measurement period.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can effect the total number of below counters: pmPdcchTargetBlerLowRatioDistr, pmPdcchTargetBlerLowRatioPcellDistr, pmPdcchTargetBlerHighRatioDistr, pmPdcchTargetBlerHighRatioPcellDistr, pmPdcchCongestDistr, pmPdcchTargetBlerDistr, pmPdcchTargetBlerPcellDistr, pmPrbAvailUtilDlDistr, pmPrbAvailUtilUlDistr.
Dependencies: Only applicable if licenses for Optimized PDCCH and Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation are present and features are active.

Parameter Description:
SINR threshold for differentiated maximum PDCCH target BLER.

If PDCCH SINR is greater than diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerThres, pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow is used as maximum PDCCH target BLER.

Otherwise pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh is used.
Dependencies: Only applicable when both pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled and diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled are true.

Parameter Description:
Defines negative offset to pZeroNominalPusch in Optimized Power Splitting for Uplink Carrier Aggregation feature enhancement.

Value 255 means Optimized Power Splitting for Uplink Carrier Aggregation feature enhancement is turned off, and other value means this feature enhancement is activated.

For uplink 64-QAM or 256-QAM, this attribute is used to define negative offset to pZeroNominalPusch, and PUSCH power offset range is changed to [-pZeroOffsetUlCa, puschPwrOffset64qam] or [-pZeroOffsetUlCa, puschPwrOffset256qam] respectively. For other modulation, there is no impact on pZeroNominalPusch.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for indicating whether subscription ratio of cell is high.

If subscription ratio is greater than or equal to this threshold, cell is considered to be in high load.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can prevent new traffic from being setup.

Parameter Description: PDCCH CCE utilization threshold for Optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellFDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for unregistering cell for inter-cell UE preemption.

Expressed in number of preemptable UEs in cell. If configured with value 0, cell is manually unregistered from inter-cell UE preemption.

Hysteresis for calculation of threshold for registering cell for inter-cell UE preemption.

Expressed in number of preemptable UEs in cell. Threshold for registering cell for inter-cell UE preemption is calculated with formula peUeToInterCellPreThrUnreg + peUeToInterCellPreHyst.

Parameter Description: Whether B1 measurement with gap is enabled for EN-DC-capable UEs.

Maximum distance from base station where random access from UE can be admitted.

Random access preambles detected out of this range are discarded.
Lowering the value reduces the service range for admitting connection setup from UE.
Value 0 means raRange does not take effect.
Dependencies:
Must be smaller than or equal to cellRange * 1000.
Must be 0 if cellRange is greater than 100 km.

Parameter Description:
Maximum random access observability range.

Timing offset of random access preamble can be correctly calculated if UE is in random access observability range.

Percentage of total number of UE context to be reserved per cell for Privileged Access.

Value 0 removes reservation of UE context per cell for Privileged Access.

It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Whether looping EN-DC protection is enabled in cell.

Looping ED-DC protection blocks failed NR frequency for EN-DC setup, when EN-DC setup is consecutively failed by RLF within short session time.

Shows when blocked NR frequency is backed off, after a certain NR frequency is blocked.

Special value 0 means infinity.
Whether RLF detected EN-DC setup failure is regarded as short SCG session.

Whether NR frequency is blocked to protect EN-DC setup based on this threshold.

Note: Consecutive failure is counted only when EN-DC setup is failed by RLF within short SCG session.
Whether to enable PDCCH congestion control parameters for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
One of PDCCH congestion control parameters, for PDCCH outer loop adjustment.

Used during PDCCH congestion and equivalent to EUtranCellFDD::pdcchOuterLoopInitialAdj which is used when there is no PDCCH congestion.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchCongCtrlParamEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
One of PDCCH congestion control parameters, for PCell PDCCH outer loop adjustment.

Used during PDCCH congestion and equivalent to EUtranCellFDD::pdcchOuterLoopInitialAdjPCell which is used when there is no PDCCH congestion.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchCongCtrlParamEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
One of PDCCH congestion control parameters, for PDCCH power boost.

Used during PDCCH congestion and equivalent to EUtranCellFDD::pdcchPowerBoostMax which is used when there is no PDCCH congestion.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect when pdcchCongCtrlParamEnabled is true.

Cannot be higher than pdcchPowerBoostMax.

Parameter Description: PDCCH target BLER adjustment step size.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: SINR threshold for Intra-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Uplink Coordinated Multi-Point Reception is present and feature is active. Must be used together with ulCompUserSelSinrHys.

Parameter Description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for Intra-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Uplink Coordinated Multi-Point Reception is present and feature is active. Must be used together with ulCompUserSelSinrThr.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of narrowbands used for MPDCCH CSS2 and PDSCH scheduled by CSS2.

CSS2 stands for Common Search Space type 2.

Only applicable if license for Category M Flexible Narrowband is present and feature is active.
Dependencies:
Must be equal to or less than noOfMpdcchUessBr.
Must be 1 if dedicatedMpdcchCss2Br is false.
If 2, dedicatedMpdcchCss2Br must be true.
Must be 1 if dlChannelBandwidth is less than or equal to 10000.

Parameter Description: Logical PIMCU ID at local eNodeB.
Logical PIMCU ID at local eNodeB in tandem environment.

Parameter Description:
Whether adjustment of interaction with MIMO Sleep Mode is enabled.

When enabled, AI Powered Advanced Cell Supervision suppresses alarms and recovery actions for sleeping cell detections while MIMO Sleep Mode is activated and takes effect.

Reference to an instance of EndcDistrProfile MO.

If empty, Optimized UE Distribution for EN-DC is not active in cell.
Control of Uplink-Traffic-Triggered Mobility feature for EN-DC-capable UEs.
Whether LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority is enabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute for more frequent A5 measurement report can affect UE battery consumption and user throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Min intensity limit of RRCConnectionRequest messages for Load-Based Access Barring for each cell.

Minimum intensity limit is number of RRCConnectionRequest messages every second multipled by 10. Default value 50 corresponds to 5 RRCConnectionRequest messages every second.
If number of RRCConnectionRequest messages for the duration of last EUtranCellFDD.lbabPeriod or EUtranCellTDD.lbabPeriod is lower than or equal to minimum intensity limit, barring probability is decreased.
If number of RRCConnectionRequest messages for the duration of last EUtranCellFDD.lbabPeriod or EUtranCellTDD.lbabPeriod is higher than minimum intensity limit, it can contribute to barring probability increase.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring feature is activated.

Parameter Description: Controls how Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility feature is enabled.

Window length of subframe.

Used for monitoring potential packet loss related to Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

High threshold for potential packet loss related to Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

When dlVolteCovMobThrLow is bigger than or equal to dlVolteCovMobThrHigh, dlVolteCovMobThrHigh does not take effect, only dlVolteCovMobThrLow is used.

Low threshold for potential packet loss related to Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

When dlVolteCovMobThrLow is bigger than or equal to dlVolteCovMobThrHigh, dlVolteCovMobThrHigh does not take effect, only dlVolteCovMobThrLow is used.

Number of silent periods of PUCCH SR for CE0 bandwidth-reduced UEs.

Value 0 means function is turned off, and sr-Prohibit-r9 IE is not encoded in message.
Value 1 corresponds to one SR period and so on.

Only applicable if license for Category M Access is present and feature is active.

Number of silent periods of PUCCH SR for CE1 bandwidth-reduced UEs.

Value 0 means function is turned off, and sr-Prohibit-r9 IE is not encoded in message.
Value 1 corresponds to one SR period and so on.

Only applicable if license for Category M Access is present and feature is active.

Whether Multi-Node PIM Avoidance is enabled.

Cell can be victim, aggressor, or both. In case of victim cell, PIM power excess measurement is reported to aggressor cell. In case of aggressor cell, downlink PRBs are blanked to avoid PIM interference.
Dependencies: If pimAvoidManualConfigEnabled is true, value can only be set to true if pimAggressorCellId and pimAggressorENodeBId are non-empty.

Parameter Description:
Multi-Node PIM Avoidance status.

If empty, cell is not performing Multi-Node PIM Avoidance.

Cell ID of victim cell performing PIM avoidance.

If empty, cell is not aggressor cell.

ENodeB ID of victim cell performing PIM avoidance.

If empty, cell is not aggressor cell.

Cell ID of aggressor cell performing PIM avoidance.

If empty, cell is not victim cell.
Dependencies: pimAggressorCellId and pimAggressorENodeBId that belong to EUtranCellFDD or ExternalEUtranCellFDD instance must exist.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if attribute pimAvoidanceControllerEnabled is false and attribute pimAvoidManualConfigEnabled is true and pimAggressorENodeBId is non-empty.

Parameter Description:
ENodeB ID of aggressor cell performing PIM avoidance.

If empty, cell is not victim cell.
Dependencies: pimAggressorENodeBId that belongs to ENodeBFunction or ExternalENodeBFunction instance must exist.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if attribute pimAvoidanceControllerEnabled is false and attribute pimAvoidManualConfigEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
Whether manual configuration of aggressor is enabled for PIM avoidance.

If sum of ENodeBFunction::noOfUsedPimAvoidEranPartners and newly required ERAN tunnel for pimAggressorENodeBId is bigger than 6, manually configured aggressor cannot be used for Multi-Node PIM Avoidance.
Precondition: Value can only be changed if attribute pimAvoidanceControllerEnabled is false.

Parameter Description:
Frequency weighted value of manually configured aggressor.

Only applicable if pimAvoidManualConfigEnabled is true.
Minimum percent of PRBs reserved for scheduling.
PIM power reference level for remaining PIM power that is acceptable for operator.
Whether periodic pause of PIM avoidance is enabled to observe the gain.

Controls if ECGI measurements can be requested prior to Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility handover.

Used only if a PCI conflict is detected and AnrFunction::pciConflictMobilityEcgiMeas is set to true.

Only applicable if license for Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility is present and feature is active.

Threshold for uplink data volume per LCG in BSR, monitored by buffer-based EN-DC setup.

If the value is 0, UL buffer-based EN-DC setup is disabled.

Buffer monitoring restarts at target cell regardless of high buffer status in source cell.

If false, buffer monitoring is initiated based on high buffer status in source node.
Whether NR measurement report is blocked or not during LTE handover.

Maximum number of PUSCH repetitions for CAT-M UE in CE mode A.

When default value takes effect, comparing with maximum value 32, performance or coverage cannot lose more than 3 dB approximately. By setting value to 32, better coverage performance can be obtained.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect coverage.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of repetitions for MPDCCH common search space type 2.

Used for RAR, Msg3 retransmission and Msg4 for Category M devices in CE Level 1.

Default value is suitable for most cases. Attribute can be set to 16 when coverage enhancement is needed. When most UEs are in good coverage, attribute can be set to 4. Larger value means more resources are occupied and better performance can be achieved, which can result in resource waste.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect coverage.

Parameter Description:
RSRP threshold used by UE to determine CE Level for selecting PRACH resource set.

If measured RSRP by UE is less than threshold, UE is in CE Level 1.

If highestSupportedCeLevelBr is set to 0 and only one CE Level is supported, value of this attribute is ignored by UE.

If threshold is set with large value, UE is very likely to be in CE Level 1. Coverage requirement is met, but this can result in resource waste. If threshold is set with small value, UE is less likely to be in CE Level 1, which can decrease coverage performance.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect coverage.

Parameter Description:
Whether decoupled PDCCH OLA and LA between uplink and downlink is enabled.

If 1, PDCCH outer loop adjustment (OLA) and PDCCH link adaptation (LA) between uplink and downlink is implemented separately.

Only applicable if license for LTE Decoupled Downlink and Uplink PDCCH Link Adaptation is present and feature is active.

Threshold for uplink and downlink DTX rate judgment.

When cell uplink is worse and difference between cell uplink DTX rate and downlink DTX rate exceeds this threshold, stop uplink Harq feedback to trigger uplink PDCCH OLA and use downlink PDCCH OLA as uplink PDCCH OLA.

Role within victim aggressor groups for PIM detection.

If empty, no role is selected for PIM detection.

Whether cell is identified as a PIM victim.

PIM detection can identify a cell as a PIM victim if cell is affected by interference from passive intermodulation.

Set to NO_PIM_DETECTED or PIM_DETECTED only if pimDetectionRole is VICTIM or VICTIM_AND_AGGRESSOR.
Maximum number of MPDCCH repetition for CE Level 0.

Number of Msg2 repetitions for Category M UE in Coverage Enhancement Level 1.

Recommended to be equal to or larger than mpdcchCss2MaxNumRepCe1Br.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect random access success rate.

Parameter Description:
Number of Msg4 repetitions for Category M UE in Coverage Enhancement Level 1.

Recommended to be equal to or larger than mpdcchCss2MaxNumRepCe1Br.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect RRC Setup success rate.

Parameter Description:
Downlink frequency bias type for internal channel.

Only applicable when dlInternalChannelBandwidth is 7500 or 8800.
Dependencies: Value must be same as ulInternalChannelFreqBias.

Parameter Description:
Uplink frequency bias type for internal channel.

Only applicable when ulInternalChannelBandwidth is 7500 or 8800.
Dependencies: Value must be same as dlInternalChannelFreqBias.

Parameter Description:
Whether release of NR leg for EN-DC-connected UE triggers LTE inter-frequency handover.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.

Whether Connection Reestablishment triggers LTE inter-frequency handover.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.

References to instances of QciProfilePredefined or QciProfileOperatorDefined MO.

List of QCIs triggering the LTE Service-Triggered Outgoing NR IRAT Mobility action.

If non-empty, only service-triggered mobility to NR frequencies is allowed.

Only applicable if license for LTE Service-Triggered Outgoing NR IRAT Mobility is present and feature is active.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. It can decrease mobility to NR frequencies and block coverage-triggered mobility to NR frequencies.

Parameter Description:
Whether detection of uplink-heavy UE for load balancing is enabled.

UEs marked as uplink-heavy are excluded from load balancing mobility.

Transmit power of PDCCH to be boosted for RA Msg2 transmissions excluding Cat-M access.

Higher value implies less CCEs available for other UE to allocate.
Lower value implies more CCEs available for other UE to allocate.

If 0, PDCCH power is not boosted for Msg2.

Only applicable when random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled. See description of pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr.

Transmit power of PDSCH to be boosted for RA Msg2 transmissions excluding Cat-M access.

Higher value implies less downlink PRBs available for other UE to allocate.
Lower value implies more downlink PRBs available for other UE to allocate.

If 0, PDSCH power is not boosted for Msg2.

Only applicable when random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled. See description of pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr.

Timing advance threshold for RA Msg2 power boost excluding Cat-M access.

Random access Msg2 power boost function is active when timing advance of UE is greater than or equal to the threshold.

It can be active only within distance defined by raRange or cellRange.
Distance from attaching UE to eNodeB is approximately Timing Advance (TA) value * 78.125 meters.
If raRange is defined (value not equal to 0), then Random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled if pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr * 78.125 is smaller than raRange value.
if raRange is undefined (value equal to 0), then Random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled if pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr * 78.125 is smaller than cellRange * 1000.

If 65535, Random access Msg2 power boost function is disabled.

Only applicable if license for LTE Flexible Power Boost for Initial Access is present and feature is active.

Whether LTE inter-frequency handover is triggered for EN-DC-connected UEs.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.

Muting start point of manually configured aggressor cell for this victim cell.

Only applicable if pimAvoidManualConfigEnabled is true.
Minimum time length for which eNodeB recommends a bit rate index to UE when bit rate increases.
Dependencies: Must be greater than or equal to EUtranCellFDD::bitRateDownRecommTimer.

Parameter Description: Minimum time length for which eNodeB recommends a bit rate index to UE when bit rate decreases.
Dependencies: Must be less than or equal to EUtranCellFDD::bitRateUpRecommTimer.

Parameter Description:
Whether enhanced VoLTE Rate Recommendation is enabled.

Only applicable if licenses for both following features are present and features are active:
- VoLTE Rate Recommendation.
- Robust Header Compression.

Whether frequency selection for UE with SPID profile is defined on SPID-specific level.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.

Power scaling mode in uplink carrier aggregation.

Value 0 means that power scaling is disabled and PRB resource is allocated conservatively.
Value 1 means that power scaling is enabled and PRB resource is allocated moderately.
Value 2 means that power scaling is enabled and PRB resource is allocated aggressively.

Only applicable if license for Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Fallback policy in uplink carrier aggregation.

Value 0 means fallback to component carrier with higher SINR.
Value 1 means fallback to component carrier with higher estimated transmission capability.
Value 2 means fallback to PCell.

Only applicable if license for Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Maximum allowed number of paging records for cell.

Allowed maximum number of UE that can be paged per paging occasion.

If not 0, overrides Paging::maxNoOfPagingRecords.

LTE UEs and Category M1 UEs are included. For Category M1 UEs, maximum effective number of paging records is 4 if it is set higher than or equal to 4.
Dependencies:
Cannot be larger than 1 if dlChannelBandwidth is 1400.
Cannot be larger than 4 if dlChannelBandwidth is 3000.
Cannot be larger than 7 if dlChannelBandwidth is 5000.

Parameter Description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Offset value for the neighbor cell. Used when UE is in connected mode. This attribute can be modified by SON functions.
Reference to an instance of EUtranCellFDD, ExternalEUtranCellFDD, EUtranCellTDD or ExternalEUtranCellTDD managed object.
Specifies if handover between the cells in this relation is allowed.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to false stops outgoing HO.

Parameter Description: Offset value applied to a specific cell in idle mode mobility state.

Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.

Whether referred cell is included in System Information.

When attribute is set to false, cell is not included in freqNeighList in SIB4 or SIB5. Also not included in excludedCellList in SIB4 or SIB5, unless included by EUtranFreqRelation::blackListEntryIdleMode attribute.

Following options are possible for coverage area of cell indicated by relation:
- Whether coverage area has approximately same coverage area (overlap) as this cell.
- Whether coverage area fully covers this cell.
- Whether coverage area is fully contained in this cell.
Value influences SCell priority in Dynamic SCell Selection for Carrier Aggregation.
Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

Parameter Description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2

Indicates the time and date when the MO was created.

Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2 and if the MO is to be deleted who triggered the deletion

This attribute indicates whether Inter-Frequency Load Balancing is ALLOWED or NOT_ALLOWED or if Inter-Frequency Offload shall be applied from the current cell to the cell indicated by the cell relation.

SCell candidate status.

The value indicates whether the cell indicated by parameter cellrelation can be used as SCell for UEs using this cell as their PCell. The SCell can be either local to the eNodeB, or on a remote eNodeB.
Change Take Effect: Changed value will take effect in relation to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection. When going from state NOT_ALLOWED to ALLOWED the SCell will not be available at re-selection for ongoing connections.

Parameter Description: Specifies if the feature Best Neighbor Relations for Intra-LTE Load Management is allowed to automatically change the loadBalancing attribute for this EUtran cell relation.

Determines if feature Overlaid Cell Detection has qualified this cell relation as an overlaid neighbor, i.e. high-hitRate, on the corresponding frequency relation.

The value "true" means the neighbor cell is encouraged to initiate load balancing towards the source cell.
The value "false" means no specific preferences exist.

Determines if the cell relation has high hitRate towards the source cell.
The attribute is automatically updated when the feature Overlaid Cell Detection is operable.

Sleep Mode Coverage Cell candidate status.

Indicates if related cell can be used as coverage cell for Cell Sleep Mode.
Indicates if related cell is a dependent capacity cell for Cell Sleep Mode support.
Indicates if related cell is a coverage cell for Cell Sleep Mode support.
DL PRB usage percentage threshold. At least one of the coverage cells must exceed this threshold to wake-up the capacity cell.
Minimum number of RRC connections needed to wake-up the capacity cell. Sent by the capacity cell.
Minimum duration for coverage cell to satisfy configured load thresholds before the capacity cell can wake-up. Used in feature Cell Sleep Mode.

Priority of neighbor cell whose CRS Assistance Information is sent to UE. For values between 1 and 100, the smaller the value, the higher the neighbor cell is prioritized for selection. Value 0 means the CRS Assistance Information of this neighbor cell is not sent.
Note: This attribute is valid only for FDD cells.

Mobility status information for EUTRAN cell relation. When struct member mobilityStatus.available is set to false, no HO is performed on EUTRAN cell relation. Reason why HO is not allowed on EUTRAN cell relation is shown on mobilityStatus.reason.
Handover statistics status information. Each value corresponds to the status of the handover statistics.

Whether a cell can serve as ESCell.

Only applicable for external SCells.

Following settings are required for value ENABLED_ERAN:
- Elastic RAN feature is active in both local and remote node.
- PCell and SCell are unlocked.
- ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState is ENABLED.
- Connection between two Baseband units is enabled.
- eRanCaProtVerActive is the same on both eNodeBs.
- sCellCandidate is set to ALLOWED.

Following settings are required for value ENABLED_IENB:
- Inter-eNodeB Carrier Aggregation feature is active in both local and remote node.
- PCell and SCell are unlocked.
- ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState is ENABLED.
- Connection between two Baseband units is enabled.
- interEnbCaProtVerActive is the same on both eNodeBs.
- sCellCandidate is set to ALLOWED.

ENABLED
NOT_APPLICABLE

PCELL_DISABLED
ESCELL_DISABLED
MAX_PARTNERS_ON_REMOTE_ENB

Depends on feature license and success of tunnels in the following options:
- TermPointToLbm for IeNodeB-CA feature only
- TermPointToENB::interEnbSwCompatibilityState
- ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState
Deprecated: Since 21.Q2. Replaced by sCellCaConfigurationAvail. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Whether or not AMO function is allowed. Used to turn off AMO function on cell relation level.
Describes AMO function enabling state. RBS system sets the value.
Dependencies: Depends on the operator configuration of AmoFunction::amoAllowedInterVendor, EUtranFreqRelation::amoAllowed, EUtranCellRelation::amoAllowed and the type of cell relation.

Parameter Description:
Priority for selecting an SCell within a frequency carrier.

SCell with highest priority is selected during initial blind SCell selection.

Value 0 is lowest priority.
If -1, cell is excluded from blind SCell selection.

If EUtranCellRelation MO instance is created automatically by Automated Neighbor Relations feature or X2 messages, initial sCellPriority value is assigned based on whether cell relation is from local node, remote co-sited or remote non co-sited node:
sCellPriority is set to value of EUtranFreqRelation::sCellPriorityLocal if cell relation is from local node.
sCellPriority is set to value of EUtranFreqRelation::sCellPriorityExtCoSited if cell relation is from remote co-sited node.
sCellPriority is set to value of EUtranFreqRelation::sCellPriorityExtNonCoSited if cell relation is from remote non co-sited node.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when Configurable SCell Priority is active with following apply:
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to PRIORITIZED.
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to GLOBAL_EVALUATION.

Parameter Description: Indicates whether a shutting down cell can be chosen as SCell or not.
Obsolete: Since 24.Q1. Deprecated: Since 17.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Whether external cell is allowed to be used as cooperating cell candidates for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP.
Whether external cell belongs to external UL Comp Group for each serving cell.
Dependencies:
Depends on feature license and success of UL CoMP tunnels in TermPointToLbm, which is decided by the values of TermPointToENB::interEnbUlCompSwCompatibility and ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellStateInterEnbUlComp (or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellStateInterEnbUlComp) and EUtranCellRelation::ieNBUlCompCoopCellAllowed.
Also depends on remote cell configuration, following conditions must be compatible with serving cell.
- Same Frame Structure and Duplex mode
- Same DL&UL EARFCN and UL Bandwidth for FDD
- Same DL EARFCN, Bandwidth, Subframe Assignment for TDD

Parameter Description:
Whether external cell belongs to Elastic RAN external Uplink Coordinated Multi-Point Reception Group for each serving cell.

Value is set to ENABLED if all of the following options apply:
- ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState is ENABLED.
- The following configurations are the same for remote and serving cell:
-- Frame structure and duplex mode.
-- Applicable for EUtranCellFDD: earfcndl, earfcnul, dlChannelBandwidth and ulChannelBandwidth.
-- Applicable for EUtranCellTDD: earfcn, channelBandwidth and subframeAssignment.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for Elastic RAN Uplink Coordinated Multi-Point Reception is present and the feature is active. Otherwise value is DISABLED.

Parameter Description: Whether external cell is allowed to be used as cooperating cell candidates for Elastic RAN UL CoMP.
Specifies if CAT-M Connected Mode Mobility between the cells in this relation is allowed.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to false stops outgoing HO for CAT-M UE.

Parameter Description: Cell Individual Offset for QCI1 and QCIs with serviceType PTT. Used when UE with QCI1 or QCI with serviceType PTT bearer is in connected mode. Can be modified by SON functions.
Coverage area of cell indicated by relation, compared to this cell. Coverage area is approximately the same (overlap), it fully covers this cell, or it is fully contained in this cell for CAT-M UE.

Controlled by Automatic SCell Management feature.

Applicable only if following apply:
- sCellCandidate is set to AUTO.
- For cells of type indicated by EUtranFreqRelation::asmSCellDetection attribute.

Whether the cell is restricted to DL-only if configured as an SCell.

Based on value asmStatus is set to ALLOWED or ONLY_ALLOWED_FOR_DL.
Change Take Effect: Next Automatic SCell Management update cycle.

Parameter Description:
Availability of indicated cell to serve as SCell candidate.

Applicable to both local and external cells.

Following settings are required for value ENABLED_ERAN:
- Elastic RAN feature is active in both local and remote node.
- PCell and SCell are unlocked.
- ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState is ENABLED.
- Connection between two Baseband units is enabled.
- TermPointToENB::eRanCaProtVerActive is the same on both eNodeBs.
- sCellCandidate is set to ALLOWED, or sCellCandidate is set to AUTO and asmStatus is set to value other than NOT_ALLOWED.

Following settings are required for value ENABLED_IENB:
- Inter-eNodeB Carrier Aggregation feature is active in both local and remote node.
- PCell and SCell are unlocked.
- ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState is ENABLED.
- Connection between two Baseband units is enabled.
- TermPointToENB::interEnbCaProtVerActive is the same on both eNodeBs.
- sCellCandidate is set to ALLOWED, or sCellCandidate is set to AUTO and asmStatus is set to value other than NOT_ALLOWED.

Following settings are required for value ENABLED_LOCAL:
- PCell and SCell are unlocked.
- EUtranCellFDD::operationalState or EUtranCellTDD::operationalState is ENABLED.
- sCellCandidate is set to ALLOWED, or sCellCandidate is set to AUTO and asmStatus is set to ALLOWED or ONLY_ALLOWED_FOR_DL.

Depends on feature license and success of tunnels in the following attributes:
- TermPointToLbm (for Inter-eNodeB Carrier Aggregation feature only)
- TermPointToENB::interEnbSwCompatibilityState
- ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState.
