Parameter Description:
Whether related cell must be selected as handover target cell in PCI conflict cases.

Used for manual selection of cell relations for handovers in PCI conflicts when CGI report is not available.

Takes effect only if related cell is involved in PCI conflict.

If false, related cell is not selected as a handover target cell, if there is another handover candidate cell with same PCI and on same frequency with this parameter set to true.
If true, related cell is always selected as a handover target cell, if there are other handover candidate cells with same PCI and on same frequency.

There can be only one EUtranCellRelation instance on given EUtranFreqRelation instance pointing to neighbor cells with same PCI, with EUtranCellRelation::pciConflictPreferredCellMan value true.
Dependencies: There can be only one EUtranCellRelation instance on given EUtranFreqRelation instance pointing to neighbor cells with same PCI, with EUtranCellRelation::pciConflictPreferredCellMan value true.

Parameter Description:
Whether related cell must be selected as handover target cell in PCI conflict cases.

Used for automatic selection of cell relations for handovers in PCI conflicts when CGI report is not available.

Takes effect only if neighbor cell is involved in PCI conflict. If automatic selection of cell relations for handovers in PCI conflicts is enabled, this attribute overrides value of EUtranCellRelation::pciConflictPreferredCellMan.

If false, related cell is not selected as a handover target cell, if there is another handover candidate cell with same PCI and on same frequency with this parameter set to true.
If true, related cell is always selected as a handover target cell, if there are other handover candidate cells with same PCI and on same frequency.

There can be only one EUtranCellRelation instance on given EUtranFreqRelation instance pointing to neighbor cells with same PCI, with EUtranCellRelation::pciConflictPreferredCellAuto value true.

Whether ANR function is allowed to bar this relation from mobility.

Relation can be excluded from barring only due to bad handover success ratio. Barring due to not supported PLMN on target cell is not affected by this attribute.Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Label for free use.
Refers to the EUTRAN frequency MO, EUtranFrequency.

The required minimum received Reference Symbol Received Power
(RSRP) level in the (E-UTRA) frequency for cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB3 or SIB5, depending on whether the related frequency is intra- or inter-frequency.

Calculates the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304), at cell reselection to an E-UTRAN Cell. Corresponds to parameter PEMAX in 3GPP TS 36.101.
Value 1000 means the parameter is not sent in the system information block.
The cell reselection timer TreselectionRAT for E-UTRA. Value in seconds.

The attribute t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in high mobility state. Corresponds to the parameter Speed dependent ScalingFactor for TreselectionEUTRAN for medium high state in 3GPP TS 36.304.
Value mapping:
25 = 0.25
50 = 0.5
75 = 0.75
100 = 1.0

The attribute t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in medium mobility state. Corresponds to the parameter Speed dependent ScalingFactor for TreselectionEUTRAN for medium mobility state in 3GPP TS 36.304.
Value mapping:
25 = 0.25
50 = 0.5
75 = 0.75
100 = 1.0

Absolute priority of carrier frequency used by cell reselection procedure. Corresponds to parameter priority in 3GPP TS 36.304, Evolved Universal Terrestrial Radio Access (E-UTRA); User Equipment (UE) procedures in idle mode.

Value 0 means lowest priority. UE behavior when no value is entered is specified in 3GPP TS 36.304.
Value -1 means frequency is excluded from SIB5 and IdleModeMobilityControlInfo.
Dependencies:
Value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, that is, equal priorities between RATs are not supported.
Value -1 cannot be assigned if this EUtranFreqRelation MO is associated with frequency equal to parent cell frequency.

Parameter Description: The threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards the higher priority frequency X from the current serving frequency. Each frequency of E-UTRAN can have a specific threshold. Refer to the parameter Thresx,high in 3GPP TS 36.304.

The threshold used in reselection towards frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency. Each frequency of E-UTRAN can have a specific threshold. Corresponds to parameter Thresx,low in 3GPP TS 36.304.

The maximum allowed measurement bandwidth on a carrier frequency.
Note: The values indicate the number of resource blocks and correspond to the channel bandwidth 1,4MHz, 3MHz, 5MHz, 10MHz, 15MHz, 20MHz respectively specified in 3GPP TS 36.104.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Frequency specific offset for E-UTRAN frequencies used in connected mode. In idle mode,  the negative value of this offset is used.
Specification: 3GPP TS 36.331
Indicates if all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1.  When set to TRUE, the UE expects that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.

Lists all Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) IDs allowed for this frequency relation.

A UE that does not support a PLMN included in allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency according to the UE Handover Restriction List.

No values in allowedPlmnList imply that the frequency has no restrictions for PLMN.

The PLMN identity consists of the following parts:
1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits
2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)

For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Prioritizes EUTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
(0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)
The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to this EUTRA frequency.
MO is created by operator or X2.

Indicates the time and date when the MO was created.

Parameter Description:
Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified.
Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

Parameter "ThreshX, HighQ" in TS 36.304.

For the EUtranFreqRelation that points to the intra frequency EUtranFrequency MO, the attribute is invalid, that is, this attribute does not affect SIB3.
Dependencies: The field is mandatory present if the Struct Member threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is used in systemInformationBlockType3.

Parameter Description:
Parameter "ThreshX, LowQ" in TS 36.304.

For the EUtranFreqRelation that points to the intra frequency EUtranFrequency MO, the attribute is invalid, that is, this attribute does not affect SIB3.
Dependencies: The field is mandatory present if the Struct Member threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is used in systemInformationBlockType3.

Parameter Description:
Parameter "Qqualmin" in TS 36.304.

Value 0 means that it is not sent and UE applies in such case the (default) value of negative infinity for Qqualmin. Sent in SIB3 or SIB5.

Provides to the UE information related to MBSFN and TDD UL/DL configuration of neighbor cells.

For TDD, the values DIFF_MBSFN_SUBFRAMES, SAME_MBSFN_SUBFRAMES and NO_MBSFN_SUBFRAMES indicates same UL/DL allocation in neighboring cells compared to the serving cell.

The value is included in SIB3, SIB5 and MeasObjectEUTRA.

Prioritizes EUTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets priority to frequency that mobility for a voice session is performed to. Valid for VoLTE and PTT.
Value -1 means frequency is excluded.
Value 0 means lowest priority.
Value 7 means highest priority.
Specifies a list of PCI that are exclude-listed in EUTRAN measurements.
The type of event based measurements on other LTE frequencies.
Encapsulates parameters for service specific load management for a certain QCI profile.
Specifies exclude-listed cells in SIB4 and SIB5.

Specifies the policy for updating the loadBalancing attribute by the feature Best Neighbor Relations for Intra-LTE Load Management. The policy is valid for all cell relations corresponding to this EUtranFreqRelation.
ANR performs measurement on the referenced frequency if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, ANR does not perform any measurements on this frequency.
Minimum target cell load (subscription ratio) taken into account by source cell when it determines amount of load balancing action to cell that uses this carrier frequency.
Parameter used to specify whether or not CA triggered redirection is activated from the current cell towards a certain frequency.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

Parameter Description:
Prioritizes EUTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell. Sets the priority to which frequency to perform mobility for a bearer with specific ARP Priority Level when the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover is activated.
The value -1 means the frequency is excluded.
The value 0 means the lowest priority.
The value 7 means the highest priority.
Specific PCI reserved by operator for Femto Cell. It is the initial physical cell ID of Non-planned PCI. If value equals 1000, Non-planned PCI is not configured for this frequency relation.
Dependencies: This attribute has a dependency to nonPlannedPhysCellIdRange.

Parameter Description: PCI range for the Non-planned PCI.
Dependencies: If nonPlannedPhysCellId != 1000, nonPlannedPhysCellId + nonPlannedPhysCellIdRange <= 504

Parameter Description: Cell Individual Offset value for the Non-planned PCI, CSG or Hybrid CSG neighbor cell. Used when UE is in connected mode.
Target eNodeB Identity type for the Non-planned PCI neighbor cell. Attribute is used to encode the message Handover Required when it is defined in TS36.413 ch. 9.1.5.1, S1AP parameter Global eNB ID.
The neighbor relations candidate list.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold2Rsrp, RSRP threshold2 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold2Rsrq, RSRQ threshold2 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
Specifies whether Admission-triggered offload (ATO) is activated from the current cell towards a certain EUTRAN frequency.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description: Cell sleep mode performs measurement on the referenced frequency for coverage cell discovery if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, cell sleep mode does not perform any measurements on this frequency.
The type of event based measurements used for inter-frequency LTE measurements when the measurements are uplink triggered.
PCI for the closed access mode CSG cell. It is the start physical cell ID in the SIB4. If value is equal to 1000, it means that csg-PhysCellIdRange IE is not presented in SIB4.
Dependencies: If csgPhysCellId != 1000, csgPhysCellId + csgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

Parameter Description: The range of PCI for the closed access mode CSG cell. The information is broadcasted in SIB4.
Dependencies: If csgPhysCellId != 1000, csgPhysCellId + csgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

Parameter Description: PCI for the Hybrid CSG cell. It is the start physical cell ID of Hybrid CSG cell. If value is equal to 1000, it means that Hybrid CSG cell is not supported for this frequency relation.
Dependencies: If hybridCsgPhysCellId != 1000, hybridCsgPhysCellId + hybridCsgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

Parameter Description: The range of PCI for the Hybrid CSG cell.
Dependencies: If hybridCsgPhysCellId != 1000, hybridCsgPhysCellId + hybridCsgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

Parameter Description: Target eNodeB ID type for the CSG and Hybrid CSG neighbor cell. Attribute is used to encode the message Handover Required when it is defined in TS36.413 ch. 9.1.5.1, S1AP parameter Global eNB ID.
Whether or not AMO function is allowed. Used to turn off AMO function on frequency relation level.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event A5, used for Inter-frequency load balancing.
Prioritizes EUTRAN frequency carriers from which to pick SCells for carrier aggregation. 0 means lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded from SCell selection.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when Configurable SCell Priority is active with following apply:
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to PRIORITIZED.
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to GLOBAL_EVALUATION.

Parameter Description: In conjunction with caPrioThreshold the value sets a threshold for the number of SCells on this frequency carrier that can be configured using prioritized SCell selection. A normalized value is applied. When frequency carriers have same priority, SCells are selected on the carrier with the lowest proportional SCell utilization.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when Configurable SCell Priority is active with following apply:
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to PRIORITIZED.
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to GLOBAL_EVALUATION.

Parameter Description: The cell reselection timer TreselectionEUTRA_CE for E-UTRA.

Min received RSRP level in E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection for UE in enhanced coverage mode. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin_CE in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1-BR. This attribute is broadcast in SIB3 or SIB5. Depends on whether related frequency is intra- or inter-frequency.

Min quality level (RSRQ) in cell for UE in enhanced coverage mode.
Corresponds to Qqualmin_CE in TS 36.304. Sent in SIB3 or SIB5. Depends on whether related frequency is intra- or inter-frequency. If 0, it is not sent and UE applies default value of negative infinity for Qqualmin_CE.
Whether or not UE capability monitoring for the coverage frequency on capacity cell is enabled.

Length of time that sleep criteria monitors UE capability for coverage frequency. Only valid if attribute csmUeCapMonitorEnabled is set to true. Value 0 means that sleep criteria checks connected UEs.
If true, MDT measures referenced frequency. Otherwise, MDT does not perform any MDT measurements on this frequency. This attribute is only applicable for MDT reportingTrigger set to PERIODICAL.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold, RSRP/RSRQ threshold1 and threshold2 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility and high power UE.
Enables cellIndividualOffsetEUtranQci1 on frequency relation level. Valid for QCI1 and QCIs with serviceType PTT.
E-UTRAN frequency priority among frequencies related to cell for CAT-M UEs in connected mode. Value 0 means lowest priority, value -1 means frequency is excluded.

E-UTRAN frequency priority among frequencies related to cell for UEs in connected mode. Priority of frequency to perform mobility to for a voice session. Value -1 means frequency is excluded, value 0 means lowest priority, value 7 means highest priority.
Preferred transfer of CAT-M UE in connected mode to this E-UTRA frequency. Value 0 means Release with redirect, value 1 means Handover.
Frequency-relation specific offset adjustment for absolute offset a3OffsetRsrp for event A3, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
Frequency-relation specific offset adjustment for absolute offset a3OffsetRsrq for event A3, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

Parameter Description:
Whether cells on this relation are configured as offloading SCells for Carrier Aggregation.

This attribute can be used to restrict offloading from PCell towards SCells enabled for offloading on EutranFrequency level.
Dependencies: Only applicable when CarrierAggregationFunction::caOffloadingMode equals ENABLED_SELECTED_SCELLS and EUtranFrequency::caOffloadingEnabled equals true for object referred by eutranFrequencyRef.

Parameter Description:
Relative priority of E-UTRAN frequencies used by enhanced Capability-Aware Idle Mode Control feature.

If endcAwareImc is MODE_1, EN-DC capable frequencies are ranked based on this value.
If endcAwareImc is MODE_2, EN-DC capable frequencies are ranked based on this value when number of NR bands for two or more LTE frequencies is the same.

Value 0 means lowest priority.
Value 7 means highest priority.
Value -1 means frequency is considered as EN-DC non-capable frequency from the IMMCI for enhanced Capability-Aware Idle Mode Control feature.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for Capability-Aware Idle Mode Control feature is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
All PLMN IDs allowed for all non-planned PCI cells configured on this frequency relation.

A UE that does not support, according to UE Handover Restriction List, a PLMN included in nonPlannedPciAllowedPlmnList does not start CGI measurement for reported cell.

If empty, non-planned PCI cells configured on this frequency have no restrictions for PLMN.
Reference to an instance of EUtraFreqRelProfileSet MO.

Whether LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority is allowed.

Only applicable when configuring event A5 measurement.

If false, frequency is not to be measured.

Default sCellPriority of co-sited external SCell candidates within a frequency carrier.
Default sCellPriority of non co-sited external SCell candidates within a frequency carrier.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.

ARFCN applicable for a downlink E-UTRA carrier frequency, as defined in 3GPP TS 36.104 for specified E-UTRA bands. For TDD this also indicates the ARFCN for uplink. Values that can be used depend on national operator specific frequency allocation as well as supported frequency band(s) of the equipment in the eNodeB. Must match EUtranFrequencyId.

A list of additional frequency bands the frequency belongs to. The list is automatically set by the eNB. The list does not include the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the frequency (primary frequency band). These additional frequency bands are broadcasted to the UEs in SystemInformationBlockType5 in case the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell.

A list of frequency bands to be excluded from the list of additional frequency bands in the additionalFreqBandList MOM attribute. The list shall not include the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the frequency (primary frequency band). These frequency bands are excluded from the list of broadcasted additional frequency bands in SystemInformationBlockType5 in case the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell.
Dependencies: List can contain only frequency bands from EUtranFrequency::additionalFreqBandList, which are not present in EUtranFrequency::prioAdditionalFreqBandList.

Parameter Description: The primary frequency band the frequency belongs to according to its defined EARFCN.

Prioritized list of additional frequency bands the frequency belongs to. Relevant for external cells only. Bands are listed in decreasing priority order. Primary frequency band, which is the band of EARFCN value of the cell, is not included.

prioAdditionalFreqBandList and additionalFreqBandList are used for populating ExternalEUtranCellFDD/TDD::additionalFreqBandList, before eNodeB has received additional frequency band information from neighbor eNodeB. ExternalEUtranCellFDD/TDD::additionalFreqBandList contains bands from prioAdditionalFreqBandList, followed by other bands from additionalFreqBandList, except bands listed in excludeAdditionalFreqBandList.
Dependencies: List can contain only frequency bands from EUtranFrequency::additionalFreqBandList, which are not present in EUtranFrequency::excludeAdditionalFreqBandList.

Parameter Description: A value of freqBandIndicatorPriority set in external EUtran cells defined on this frequency. This value is used when eNodeB not received value from the neighbor eNodeB.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if Multi Frequency Band Indicators is active.

Dependencies: In 3GPP rel9, the possiblity to add 16 additional CDMA2000 cells on the same frequency, was added. The additional CDMA2000 cells are controled by the parameter includeInSystemInformationRel9.

The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Label for free use.

The CDMA frequency band in which the HRPD or 1xRTT carrier is located

The UNDEFINED_VALUE can never be used - either at create or modify of an MO.

Parameter Description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Label for free use.
Reference to the Cdma2000 frequency band MO, Cdma2000FreqBand.

The threshold used in reselection towards a high priority CDMA2000 HRPD band class, expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 db.

If sNonServingCell > threshXHighHrpd, reselection is considered towards the band class with higher priority. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdmaHrpd.

sNonServingCell is the RX-level value of a neighboring cell.

The threshold used in reselection towards a low priority CDMA2000 HRPD band class expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 db.

If sServingCell < threshServingLow and sNeighbor > threshXLow (see corresponding attribute), reselection towards this lower prioritized band class is considered. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdmaHrpd.

sServingCell is the RX level value of the serving cell and sNeighborCell is the RX level value of a neighbor frequency.
Absolute priority of the RAT (0 means: lowest priority).
Dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

Parameter Description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Label for free use.

The assignment of uplink and downlink subframes for the TDD frame structure (called UL/DL configuration in 3GPP TS 36.211). All TDD cells in the same DU or Baseband, or same frequency band, or specific frequency band combinations where one frequency band overlaps with another (e.g. Band 38 and Band 41) must have the same uplink and downlink subframe assignment.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description: The special subframe pattern configuration for Downlink Part of Time Slot (DwPTS), Guard Period (GP), and Uplink Part of Time Slot (UpPTS). All TDD cells in the same frequency band, or specific frequency band combinations where one frequency band overlaps with another (e.g. Band 38 and Band 41) must have the same special subframe pattern configuration.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.
Dependencies:
specialSubframePattern = 5 can not be used in combination with nB=T4 on MO Paging, see 3GPP TS 36.213.
The round trip time at the cellRange together with switching time must be less than the time available in special subframe.

Parameter Description: The channel bandwidth in the cell.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.
Dependencies: Cannot be 5000 if cellMaxNoOfPagingRecords or Paging.maxNoOfPagingRecords is larger than 7.

Parameter Description:
The E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number (EARFCN) for the TDD cell. The mapping from EARFCN to physical frequency is for E-UTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. The values depend on national, operator specific frequency allocation, as well as from the supported frequency band(s) of the equipment in the RBS.

Use MO action changeFrequency for changing the frequency after that cell is initially setup. See description of changeFrequency, on how change takes effect and disturbances.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.
Dependencies:
Pair of earfcn and physicalLayerCellId attributes must be unique in RBS.
Attribute physicalLayerCellId is equal to 3 x physicalLayerCellIdGroup + physicalLayerSubCellId.

Parameter Description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

The frame start offset of the cell. All TDD cells in the same frequency band, or specific frequency band combinations where one frequency band overlaps with another (e.g. Band 38 and Band 41) must have the same frame start offset.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description:
The number of Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) resources available on the PUCCH channel.
For TDD Subframe Assignment 1 the recommended value is 64.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description:
The number of Scheduling Request (SR) resources available on the PUCCH channel.
For TDD Subframe Assignment 1 the recommended value is 64.
Disturbances: Cell runs new set-up procedure. All cell-connected UEs are released and connected again.

Parameter Description: Maximum distance from base station where connection to UE can be setup and maintained.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.
Dependencies:
Round-trip time at cellRange together with switching time must be less than time available in special subframe.
Value * 1000 must be greater than or equal to raRange.

Parameter Description:
Defines the Transmission Mode (e.g. Transmit Diversity and Closed-Loop Spatial Multiplexing) that shall be used for the UEs that are connected to the cell.
See 3GPP TS 36.213 table 7.1-5 for a definition of Transmission Mode.
Range and Values:
TRANSMISSION_MODE_2
TRANSMISSION_MODE_3
TRANSMISSION_MODE_4
TRANSMISSION_MODE_7
TRANSMISSION_MODE_8
TRANSMISSION_MODE_9
Dependencies: If mbsfnSubframesForTm9 enabled, TM9-capable UE is reconfigured.

Common SR periodicity, used for all UEs.
Dependencies: For 1.4 MHz: Only valid inputs are 10 and 20.

Parameter Description: The number of channel selection PUCCH resource sets (CS sets) to reserve in each cell for secondary cell HARQ feedback. To conserve PUCCH resource, this attribute can be set to 0 if the cell is not used as PCell for Carrier Aggregation.
This attribute specifies configuration type of CSI-RS (Channel State Information Reference Signal) for TDD 8Tx.
Enables multiplexing as DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode for TDD UEs not configured for carrier aggregation.
Enables PUCCH format3 as DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode for TDD UEs not configured for carrier aggregation.
Dependencies: Applicable only when attribute noOfPucchFormat3PrbPairs > 0.

Parameter Description:
Controls number of non-carrier aggregation TDD UEs configured with PUCCH format3 as DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode.

Note: PUCCH Format3 resources can be shared with CA users. Then attribute value depends on maximum number of carrier aggregation users that are configured with PUCCH Format3 resources.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q1. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Number of PUCCH Format 3 PRB pairs.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect when either of the following conditions is satisfied:
3CC Carrier aggregation Extension Feature (FAJ 121 3084) is enabled, or nonCaAnModeF3Enable is true.

Parameter Description: Indicates if the cell is operated in unlicensed spectrum with downlink only and no uplink.
Disturbances: Changes can affect traffic.

Parameter Description: Indicates if the cell is operated with downlink only and with no uplink.
Upper percentage threshold for PUCCH format 3 resource collision rate. Limits number of TDD non-carrier aggregation UEs configured with PUCCH format 3 as HARQ feedback mode.
Upper threshold for number of active DL users. Limits number of TDD non-carrier aggregation UEs configured with multiplexing as HARQ feedback mode.
Index of max allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of TDD cell.
Range and Values:
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX0
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX1
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX2
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX3
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX4
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX5
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX6
TIME_PHASE_MAX_DEVIATION_TDD_IDX7
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.
Dependencies: ENodeBFunction::timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment must be true.

Parameter Description: Enables uplink multiuser MIMO at cell level. The value corresponds to the maximum number of co-scheduled layers that is allowed. Only single user MIMO is allowed when the value is zero.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if the cell is operating with an AAS radio.

Parameter Description: Enables downlink multiuser MIMO at cell level. The value corresponds to the maximum allowed number of co-scheduled layers. Only single user MIMO is allowed when the value is zero.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if the cell is operating with an AAS radio.

Parameter Description: Enables dynamic switching between TM7 and TM3.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if radio equipment supports AAS functionality.

Parameter Description: Enables dynamic switching between TM8 and TM3.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if radio equipment supports AAS functionality.

Parameter Description: Reference to an instance of ExternalGUtranCell. If set, indicated GUTRAN cell must have coverage over this cell.
CBRS cell. If cell is externally supervised and operated with authorized channel by a spectrum access system.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in Baseband Radio Node.

Parameter Description:
UTC time to determine when to stop transmitting on assigned spectrum. After it expires or is set to "", cell becomes disabled. Initial value is "".

Value represents international standard for date and time representation (ISO 8601). String format is YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[.S+]Z.

Controls allocation of PRACH to upper or lower part of band.

For example, it can be used for avoiding interfered part of band.
0: Allocate PRACH from lower part of band.
1: Allocate PRACH from upper part of band.
Number of Format 1 PUCCH PRB pairs for each subframe to be configured in each cell.
Disturbances: Setting lower value can cause loss in traffic.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if attribute ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is set to 1.

Parameter Description: Number of Format 2 PUCCH PRB pairs for each subframe to be configured in each cell.
Disturbances: Setting lower value can cause lower periodic CQI reporting from UEs.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if attribute ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is set to 1.

Parameter Description:
Number of PUCCH SR users supported when Flexible Uplink Processing is enabled.

Value depends on ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled.

If ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is 0, noOfPucchSrUsersCalc is not applicable.

If ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is 1, noOfPucchSrUsersCalc is based on value of noOfPucchFormat1PrbPairsPerFrameConf.

If ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is 2, value of noOfPucchSrUsersCalc is same as value of noOfPucchSrUsers.

Number of PUCCH CQI users supported when Flexible Uplink Processing is enabled.

Value depends on ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled.

If ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is 0, noOfPucchCqiUsersCalc is not applicable.

If ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is 1, noOfPucchCqiUsersCalc is based on value of noOfPucchFormat2PrbPairsPerFrameConf.

If ulPhyProcResTradingEnabled is 2, value of noOfPucchCqiUsersCalc is same as value of noOfPucchCqiUsers.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Configuration type of 8-port CSI-RS (Channel State Information Reference Signal).
Dependencies: Only takes effect in TDD cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio when Basic AAS for TDD is active.

Parameter Description: Whether TM9 is allowed on cell level.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in TDD cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio when Basic AAS for TDD is active.

Parameter Description: Whether dynamic switching is enabled between TM9 and TM3.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in TDD secondary cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio, when Basic AAS for TDD is active.

Parameter Description: Tuning of Atmospheric Duct Interference Reduction.
Operation mode for Atmospheric Duct Interference Reduction.
Dependencies:
To set values LOCATION and REDUCTION when channelBandwidth is 5000 or 15000, ENodeBFunction::ductIntFlexibleDetectionEnabled must be true.
Value REDUCTION cannot be set when Paging::nB is T4.

Parameter Description:
Instantaneous status of special subframe pattern configuration.

Equals the instantaneous value of parameter specialSubframePattern in SystemInformationBlockType1. Same as specialSubframePattern at cell setup, possible to change in case of Atmospheric Duct Interference Reduction.

Instantaneous status of time domain slope detection.

Value true indicates that the slope character of duct interference is detected.
If true and value of ductIntOpMode is LOCATION or REDUCTION, characteristic sequence transmission is automatically triggered.
Dependencies: Only relevant when ductIntOpMode is not DISABLED.

Parameter Description:
Instantaneous status of characteristic sequence detection.
Value true indicates that the characteristic sequence is detected.
If true, characteristic sequence transmission is automatically triggered.
Dependencies: Only relevant when ductIntOpMode is LOCATION or REDUCTION.

Parameter Description:
Instantaneous status of duct interference reduction.
Value true indicates that interference reduction is triggered.
If true, PDSCH is stopped on TDD special subframe.
Dependencies: Only relevant when ductIntOpMode is REDUCTION.

Parameter Description: Refers to an instance of AirIfLoadProfile. Assigns a AirIfLoadProfile to a cell.
The state of the feature Air Interface Load Generator. Indicates if it is running or stopped.
For each System Information Block (SIB), indicates when the SIB content is changed, if system information change notification is broadcast prior to broadcast of updated system information.

The System Information (SI) message to which each System Information Block (SIB) is mapped.

Note: SIB2 is always mapped to the SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.
The modification period, expressed in number of radio frames = modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle. See MO Paging for information about defaultPagingCycle.
Dependencies: modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle must be equal or less than 1024 radio frames. See MO Paging for information about defaultPagingCycle.

Parameter Description: The periodicity of System Information (SI) messages. If a System Information Block (SIB) is not mapped to a SI message, the SI message is not transmitted.

Length of the System Information (SI) window within which each SI message is transmitted. Applies to all SI messages.

Note:  An SI window of 1 ms may be configured only when a maximum of 5 SI messages is configured for broadcast by attribute mappingInfo, to avoid collision with SIB1 transmission in subframe #5.
Dependencies: siWindowLength must be 10 ms or above in case PWS SI messages are broadcasted.

Parameter Description: The required minimum received Reference Symbol Received Power (RSRP) level in the E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1.

Number of attempts for handover to a cell better than the serving cell, before handover is attempted to the next best cell. If there is no next best cell in the UE report, handover to the best cell is attempted repeatedly.
Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards UTRAN.
Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards GERAN.

Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards CDMA2000. This is controlled by the licensing MO Cdma2000SessionContinuity. The SIB8 distribution and information are also controlled by other licenses.
Contains a list of managed object instances that reserves this managed object instance.
Dependencies: The managed object cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

Parameter Description: Contains cell re-selection information common for intra-frequency, inter-frequency and/ or inter-RAT cell re-selection.
Specifies if uplink interference management is enabled or disabled.
Time for which randomly selected start frequency is valid before new start frequency is allocated. If set to 0, start frequency is randomly selected once, but never updated.
Dependencies: Only applicable if ulInterferenceManagementActive is true.

Parameter Description:
Array with all active Local Measurements on this MO.
Up to 10 measurements can be active.
Indicates if the cell is barred and should not be accessible to random UEs.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to BARRED blocks all traffic in the cell.

Parameter Description: Specifies if the downlink interference management is enabled or disabled.
Time for which randomly selected start frequency is valid before new start frequency is allocated. If set to 0, start frequency is randomly selected once, but never updated.
Dependencies: Only applicable id dlInterferenceManagementActive is true.

Parameter Description:
Limits UE uplink transmission power in the serving cell and calculates the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304) for cell selection.
The attribute is broadcast in SIB1.

Value 1000 means the parameter is not included in system information.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: The nominal component of the UE transmit power for Physical Uplink Control Channel (PUCCH).
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description: The nominal component of the UE transmit power for Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.
Dependencies:
Changing the value of pZeroNominalPusch, might have impact on the setting of puschPwrOffset64Qam.
See puschPwrOffset64Qam for how that attribute depends on pZeroNominalPusch.

Parameter Description:
Refers to an instance of QciTable and assigns a QciTable to a cell. The QciTable defines Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) to use in the cell.

Refers to the QciTable instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, QciTable=default
Dependencies: It is assumed that the QciTable MO has been created.

Parameter Description:
Number of subframes for each radio frame where PRACH is allocated. PRACH configuration is broadcasted as part of system information.

Value mapping:
5 = 0.5 (One every second radio frame)
10 = 1
20 = 2
30 = 3
50 = 5
100 = 10

Whether RACH preamble repetition is used for preamble sequence generation and detection. When set to false, preamble format is 0 (no repetition). When set to true, preamble format is 2 (with repetition). Preamble format is broadcasted as part of system information.

The first root sequence number for Random Access Channel (RACH) preamble generation. RACH root sequence is broadcast as a part of system information distribution and used for preamble detection.
See definition for logical root sequence number in 3GPP TS 36.211.

If feature Automated Rach Root Sequence Allocation is not activated a parameter change triggers automatic cell lock/unlock.
If feature Automated Rach Root Sequence Allocation is activated the parameter is changed without the need to lock/unlock the cell.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.
Range and Values:
IN_TEST
FAILED
POWER_OFF
OFF_LINE
OFF_DUTY
DEPENDENCY
DEGRADED
NOT_INSTALLED
LOG_FULL
DEPENDENCY_LOCKED
DEPENDENCY_FAILED
DEPENDENCY_SHUTTINGDOWN
DEPENDENCY_RECOVERY
DEPENDENCY_HOLDING

Parameter Description: The operational state.  This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.
The administrative state.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED or SHUTTINGDOWN causes loss of traffic. Changing this attribute can cause all unlocked NBIoT cells to change administrativeState to LOCKED and then UNLOCKED. This happens when one of the following thresholds is crossed: 18 EUTRAN cells + 1 NBIoT cell or 9 NBIoT cells.

Parameter Description:
RBS internal ID attribute for EUtranCell. Must be unique in the RBS. Together with the Node ID and Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) this is a universally unique cell ID.

Range 0-255.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Physical layer cell ID group.

Physical layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical layer cell ID groups. Each group contains 3 unique subidentities.
Used with physicalLayerSubCellId to calculate physical layer cell ID.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description:
Subidentity within the physical layer cell ID group.

Physical layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical layer cell ID groups. Each group contains 3 unique subidentities.
Used with physicalLayerCellIdGroup to calculate physical layer cell ID.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.
Tracking Area Code for the EUtran Cell.
Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

Parameter Description: Indicates if the DRX function in the cell is activated.
Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1.

NS_01
NS_03

Parameter Description: Intended type of CDMA2000 system time to broadcast in SIB8, if applicable.
The actual type of CDMA2000 system time that is broadcast in SIB8.

Number of resource blocks outside each Physical Uplink Control Channel (PUCCH) region that are available for scheduling Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).

Note: Both the value of this attribute and the amount of resources allocated for PUCCH impacts where the resource allocation of the PRACH starts.
The offset applied to the signaled Qrxlevmin. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevminoffset in 3GPP TS 36.304. Value 1000 means it is not sent and the UE sets Qrxlevminoffset=0dB.
Estimated E2E RTT used by AQM.
Indicates if the feature OTDOA Support in SUPL Environment is ACTIVATED  or DEACTIVATED in the cell.

The Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) index value for the cell defines the periodicity of the PRS occasions and the PRS subframe offset, as defined in 3GPP TS 36.211. The value -1 (default) means that this parameter will not be used for setting the PRS period and prsSubframeOffset. Instead the parameter prsPeriod shall be used to directly set the PRS period while prsSubframeOffset will be set by the system to guarantee non collision with SIB1.
The number of consecutive downlink sub-frames with positioning reference signals as defined in 3GPP TS 36.211. Values define 1, 2, 4, or 6 consecutive sub-frames.

The degree of latitude of the transmitter antenna position.
In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell):
   For indoor system, antenna of any sector.
   For outdoor system,antenna of macro sector.

The degree of longitude of the transmitter antenna position.
In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell):
   For indoor system, antenna of any sector.
   For outdoor system,antenna of macro sector.

Transmitter antenna altitude (meters). Use +/- values to denote height/depth.
In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell):
For indoor system, antenna of any sector.
For outdoor system, antenna of macro sector.

Semi-major axis of uncertainty. The uncertainty (r) is derived from the uncertainty code (k) by:

r = 10 * ((1.1^k) - 1).

Semi-minor axis of uncertainty. The uncertainty (r) is derived from the uncertainty code (k) by:

r = 10 * ((1.1^k) - 1).

Orientation of the major axis of uncertainty, in degrees clockwise from north.  Orientation value (N) is derived by the formula:

N <= X < (N + 1)

where X is the orientation in degrees (0 - 180).
The uncertainty altitude (h) expressed in meters is derived from the uncertainty altitude (k) by h = 45*((1.025)^k - 1).
Percentage of confidence that the target device is within the ellipsoid defined by the three axes of uncertainty: semi-major, semi-minor, and altitude.

The decimal part of the GPS time for the most recent occurrence of System Frame Number (SFN)=0 in the cell.

Unit: 2^(-32) second
Indicates if the primary PLMN ID in the cell is reserved for operator use. The primary PLMN ID is reserved if this attribute is set to true.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block traffic in the cell.
Dependencies: When cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId is defined, primaryPlmnReserved refers to cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId. Otherwise, it refers to ENodeBFunction::eNodeBPlmnId.

Parameter Description: For the list of PLMN IDs in the cell, indicates if they are reserved for operator use. The list must have the same number of entries as additonalPlmnList. The PLMN ID appearing in additionalPlmnList[x] is reserved when additionalPlmnListReserved[x] is set to true.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: The length of this list must be the same as the list in addtionalPlmnList.

Parameter Description:
Lists additional PLMN IDs supported in cell.

List can include up to five PLMNs that must be same in all EUtranCells in same Tracking Area (TA).
One TA can contain up to six PLMN identifiers.
If not set at MO creation, then attribute is automatically set to a list of five elements, each representing a dummy PLMN identity.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
If ENodeBFunction::allowMocnCellLevelCommonTac is true, different values of additionalPlmnList can be set for each cell belonging to the same TA.
If EUtranCellTDD::cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId is defined, additionalPlmnList must be empty.
Precondition: If TheftDeterrence::thdStatus is LOCKED or LOCKED_PERMANENTLY, this value can only be changed when all modified PLMN IDs are part of Lock Token or Operator List.

Parameter Description: Lists the PLMN IDs served by at least one MME. The PLMN ID is defined in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId in the parent ENodeBFunction. PLMN IDs from additionalPlmnList also appear in this list. The list may include up to 6 PLMNs.
The integer part of the GPS time for the most recent occurrence of SFN=0 in the cell.

The period of Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) occasions. Valid periods include 160 ms, 320 ms, 640 ms and 1280 ms.

prsPeriod is used to calculate the prsConfigIndex to avoid PRS sub-frame collisions with SIB1 sub-frames.

Says whether a blind Handover from this cell can be initiated when a UE reports bad coverage, or not. Note that even if the value is True, the eNB will only initiate a blind handover if it finds a suitable cell.

Start frequency offset for resource allocation when downlink interference management is disabled.

Expressed as percentage of configured bandwidth. Controls number of PRBs not scheduling PDSCH on low edge of channel.
Dependencies: dlInterferenceManagementActive shall be disabled before this parameter takes effect.

Parameter Description:
Start frequency offset for resource allocation when uplink interference management is disabled.

Expressed as percentage of configured bandwidth. Controls number of PRBs not scheduling PUSCH on low edge of channel.
Dependencies: ulInterferenceManagementActive shall be disabled before this parameter takes effect.

Parameter Description: Specifies the amount of frequency resources that is allocated in DL expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Specifies the amount of frequency resources that is allocated in UL expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.

Models the manageable characteristics for the cell polygon used for UE positioning. Each polygon corner is described by a latitude and longitude pair. Each polygon corner is represented with one position in the sequence. The other configured polygon corners follow in sequence. There must at least be three corners configured in a polygon when the function is active/used. The points shall be connected in the order that they are given. The last point is connected to the first point.

This parameter holds the resulting prsConfigIndex value. If prsPeriod is used by the operator then prsConfigIndexMapped will be set by the system. If prsConfigIndex is used by the operator then prsConfigIndexMapped will be a copy of the entered value.

Models the cell coverage area used for UE positioning. The cell coverage area is defined by the cell bearing, cell opening angle and cell radius.

This attribute has no operational impact.

Specifies the minimum required quality level (RSRQ) in the cell in dB.

Corresponds to Qqualmin in TS 36.304, sent in SIB1. Value 0 means that it is not sent and UE applies in such case the (default) value of negative infinity for Qqualmin.
Dependencies: The field is mandatory present if the Struct Member threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is used in systemInformationBlockType3.

Parameter Description:
The offset applied to the signaled qQualMin.

Corresponds to Qqualminoffset in TS 36.304.

Value 0 means that it is not sent in SIB1 and UE applies in such case the (default) value of 0 dB for Qqualminoffset.
Dependencies: If the value of qQualMin is set to 0 the parameter qQualMinOffset will not be broadcasted.

Parameter Description:
Controls CFI used for control region.

CfiMode maps to CFI as described under enumerations. For downlink bandwidth of 1400 kHz, values of CFI = 1, 2, and 3 map to 2, 3, and 4 control region symbols respectively. For other bandwidths, CFI maps directly to number of control region symbols.

In MBSFN subframes, number of control region symbols can never exceed 2, regardless of pdcchCfiMode setting.
Range and Values:
CFI_STATIC_BY_BW
CFI_STATIC_1
CFI_STATIC_2
CFI_STATIC_3
CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_2
CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_3
Dependencies: pdcchCfiMode cannot equal CFI_STATIC_1 while dlChannelBandwidth = 1400, 3000, or 5000 kHz since there would be insufficient CCEs to transmit a PDCCH for common channel messages such as SIB1 or SI. Certain values of pdcchCfiMode that allow high CFI values may be disallowed when the combination of attributes pdcchCfiMode, dlChannelBandwidth, noOfPucchCqiUsers, and noOfPucchSrUsers require too many corresponding PUCCH HARQ-ARQ resources.

Parameter Description: Controls whether sounding shall be enabled or not for the functionality that supports sounding.
Indicates if End-user bitrate shaping functionality is activated in this cell.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for End-user bitrate shaping is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Normalized subscription capacity of the cell. The value represents the total capacity of the cell used for traffic load balancing purposes.
Disturbances: Low values reduce cell capacity.

Parameter Description:
Specifies the threshold that the signal strength of the serving cell must be below for cell reselection towards a lower priority Inter-Frequency or Inter-RAT frequency.
Corresponds to ThreshServingLowP in TS 36.304.

A PCI confusion exists if a source cell has relations to two neighbor cells where both neighbor cells have the same PCI and frequency. A PCI collision exists if a source cell has a relation to a neighbor cell where both the source cell and neighbor cell have the same PCI and frequency.
Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the operator or if the MO has been modified by the PCI conflict detection application.
Indicates the CGI of the other cell that is involved in the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL".

Indicates time and date when MO was last modified.
Value has no impact on functionality. Format is not restricted.
Recommended format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.

This parameter controls if Contention Free Random Access (CFRA, known as non-contention based random access in 3GPP term) shall be enabled or not. When enabled, a portion of random access preambles should be allocated for CFRA and CFRA can be used for incoming HO and PDCCH ordered uplink re-sync.

Specifies presence of the following IEs:
- ac-BarringInfo
- ssac-BarringForMMTEL-Voice-r9
- ssac-BarringForMMTEL-Video-r9
- ac-BarringForCSFB-r10
- ac-BarringSkipForMMTELVoice-r12
- ac-BarringSkipForMMTELVideo-r12
- ac-BarringSkipForSMS-r12 in SIB2
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Access class barring parameters for mobile originating signaling.
Information broadcasted in SIB2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block mobile originating signaling call.

Parameter Description:
Access class barring parameters for mobile originating calls.
Information broadcasted in SIB2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block mobile originating data calls.

Parameter Description: Specifies presence of Information Element ssac-BarringForMMTEL-Voice-r9 in SIB2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block VoLTE calls in the cell.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by AcBarringPresence.acBarringForMmtelVoicePresence in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::acBarringPresence. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Specifies presence of Information Element ssac-BarringForMMTEL-Video-r9 in SIB2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block video calls in the cell.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by AcBarringPresence.acBarringForMmtelVideoPresence in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::acBarringPresence. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Service specific access class barring parameters for MMTEL voice originating calls.
Information broadcasted in SIB2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block VoLTE calls in the cell.

Parameter Description:
Service specific access class barring parameters for MMTEL video originating calls.
Information broadcasted in SIB2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block video calls in the cell.

Parameter Description: Access class barring for  Emergency, which corresponds to access class 10.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block emergency calls.
Dependencies: When acBarringPrescence.acBarringForEmergencySpecAcPres is AUTO, ac-BarringForEmergency value in SIB2 is overridden automatically by Progressive Barring of Special Access Classes algorithm.

Parameter Description: Indicates the CGI of the cell that detected the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the corresponding attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL". The first cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the first cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict. The second cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the second cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict.
A cell that supports  broadcast of warning messages can belong to one to 15 Emergency Areas, identified by an Emergency Area Id, set by the operator.  Value -1 means identity not set.
Shows the DU or Baseband on which baseband processing for the cell is located
Indicates if the feature High Speed UE is activated in the cell

Indicates the sensitivity of the Advanced Cell Supervision function. A higher value will make ACS detect a sleeping cell faster, but with higher risk for false detection. A lower value will make ACS detect a sleeping cell slower, but with lower risk for false detection.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Controls which recovery actions to be performed when ACS detects a sleeping cell.
The operational cycle of the handover optimization function.
The minimal number of handovers required by the handover optimization function before adjusting  handover parameters.
Specifies if the feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is enabled or disabled in the cell.

Specifies if SDM (Spatial Division Multiplexing) for CombinedCell configuration is activated or not. If SDM is activated, it is possible to multiplex multiple Ues in different sectors in the same time and same frequency resource.
Disturbances: Change can affect traffic

Parameter Description: Reference to a list of instances of SectorCarrier MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for eNodeB
The value applies for offload towards UTRAN target cells. The eNodeB attempts to offload traffic from the source cell corresponding to the subscription ratio above the threshold.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Reference to an ExternalCdma20001xRttCell

Access class barring parameters for mobile originating CSFB calls.
The information is broadcasted in SIB2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Temporary attributes are intended for temporary solutions, and their usage may vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use may be overridden by the information in CPI Info documents. Note that a later release may use another attribute to control the functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or may remove the functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
Deprecated: Since 20.Q1. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Temporary attributes are intended for temporary solutions, and their usage may vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use may be overridden by the information in CPI Info documents. Note that a later release may use another attribute to control the functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or may remove the functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

The active MBMS Service Area Identity. The content of this attribute is either empty or has the value of the attribute MbsfnArea::serviceAreaId for one or more MbsfnArea MOs. Purpose of this attribute is to support OSS SNAD functionality. This attribute is mirrored by OSS to ExternalEUtranCellFDD/TDD.
Dependencies:
A (configured) MbsfnArea::serviceAreaId becomes Active ServiceAreaId if:
- the MBMS Multicarrier feature is activated
- the cell has an unreserved MBSFNAreaCellRelation to an UNLOCKED MBSFNArea
- time and phase synchronization accuracy fulfills requirements for LTE Broadcast

Parameter Description:
Maximum power boost applied to UE-specific PDCCHs that require more CCEs than the maximum available CCE aggregation level. If UE-specific PDCCHs  require equal or less, an automatic power boost algorithm is applied. Attribute pdcchPowerBoostMax does not affect those PDCCHs.
If set to 0, there is no PDCCH power boost of the maximum CCE aggregation level. PDCCH coverage is not increased but the feature still optimizes the PDCCH power setting for PDCCHs that require equal or less CCEs than the maximum CCE aggregation level. This still allows for higher PDCCH capacity.
Dependencies: Cannot be lower than pdcchPowerBoostMaxCong.

Parameter Description: The pathloss compensation factor for power control of the Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Cell is locked and unlocked automatically.

Parameter Description: This attribute is a threshold for eNodeB. The value applies for offload towards EUTRAN target cells. The eNodeB attempts to offload traffic from the source cell to Inter-Frequency LTE neighbors corresponding to the subscription ratio above the threshold.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: This attribute is a threshold for eNodeB. The value applies in the target cell for incoming offload. The eNodeB accepts incoming offload traffic in the target cell as long as the subscription ratio is below the threshold.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: This attribute indicates the offload subscription capacity associated with the EUTRAN target cell. The value is used to moderate the offload rate to the EUTRAN target cell.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: A list of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to, not including the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the cell (primary frequency band). The list is automatically set by the eNB. These additional frequency bands are broadcasted to the UEs in SystemInformationBlockType1 in case the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell.
The primary frequency band the cell belongs to according to its defined EARFCN.
The absolute threshold value for adjusted handover failure rate required to adjust handover parameters.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

Parameter Description: The permillage threshold value for adjusted handover failure rate required to adjust handover parameters.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

Parameter Description:
DL power of Cell-specific Reference Signal (CRS) related to PDSCH type A resource elements.

If crsGain is + 3 dB, CRS power is 3 dB higher than that of a PDSCH type A resource element.

When adjustCrsPowerEnhEnabled = false, settings crsGain = 4.77 dB and 6 dB are mapped to 3 dB. When adjustCrsPowerEnhEnabled = true, crsGain = 4.77 dB and 6 dB are supported. For ESS cells, settings crsGain = 4.77 dB and 6 dB are always mapped to 3 dB.

PDSCH type A resource elements are located in symbols that do not contain CRS.

See readOnly attribute pa for actual p-a value.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if noOfCrsPorts is 2 or 4. With one port, crsGain is mapped to 0 dB.

Parameter Description: Parameter that contains the automatically estimated cell capacity value. The value 0 indicates that no estimated value exists.
Minimum value for the estimated cell capacity.
Dependencies: cellCapMinCellSubCap < cellCapMaxCellSubCap

Parameter Description: Maximum value for the estimated cell capacity.
Dependencies: cellCapMinCellSubCap < cellCapMaxCellSubCap

Parameter Description: A list of network signaling values, where each value corresponds to the frequency band on the same position in additionalFreqBandList. Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1 when the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell. The content of this list is based on spectrumEmissionReqMapping. This list will be broadcasted in SIB2 as multiBandInfoList.
Range and Values:
NS_01
NS_03
NS_04
NS_05
NS_06
NS_07
NS_08
NS_09
NS_10
NS_11
NS_12
NS_13
NS_14
NS_15
NS_16
NS_17
NS_18
NS_19
NS_20
NS_21
NS_22
NS_23
NS_24
NS_25
NS_26
NS_27
NS_28
NS_29
NS_30
NS_31
NS_32
NS_35

Parameter Description: A list which maps frequency bands to network signaling values specifying additional spectrum emissions, as described by 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. A band which is not explicitly mapped to a network signaling value by this list, will use the value NS_01. This list is used to generate the value of additionalSpectrumEmissionValues.

The expected max number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell. Will be used at unlock of the cell to distribute cells to different cores in Digital Units and Baseband Units with a multicore Main Processor. A value of -1 indicates that measuredMaxNoOfUsersInCell will be used to control the cell distribution.

Peak number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode measured in the cell. This attribute will be updated during operation of the eNB and used at unlock of the cell to distribute cells to different cores in Digital Units and Baseband Units with a multicore Main Processor. If attribute expectedMaxNoOfUsersInCell is changed from -1 to zero or higher, attribute measuredMaxNoOfUsersInCell will be reset to zero and not used to control the cell distribution.

GINR back-off parameter for PDCCH link adaptation. Applies to all UEs when the feature Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation is disabled. In FDD, if the licenses for both Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation and Carrier Aggregation are enabled, this parameter applies to secondary cell PDCCH for UEs capable of carrier aggregation. In TDD, if the license for Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation is enabled, this parameter applies to:
- UEs configured with carrier aggregation, and
- UEs configured with HARQ-ACK PUCCH format 3 or HARQ-ACK multiplexing.
The number of bytes that is assumed to be in the UE buffer when an SR is received through PUCCH.
Indicates the upper limit value of cellIndividualOffsetEUtran range that the SON function is allowed to adjust.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

Parameter Description: Indicates the lower limit value of cellIndividualOffsetEUtran range that the SON function is allowed to adjust.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

Parameter Description: Specifies the trigger used in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.
Determines if the OTDOA functionality should be considered in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.
Indicates if release with redirection is allowed in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.

ARP Priority Level list used in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.
The first instance in the list is for ARP Priority Level 0, second for 1, and so on. Value "false" means the UE with this bearer is not intended to be moved to other frequency.
How fast the Access Class Barring probability is increased, that is how fast acBarringFactor in SIB2 is decreased when the cell load is increased.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: Specifies how access class barring IE for each traffic class is present in SIB2 and priority level assigned to it.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Time period to measure RRC Connection Reject Ratio against threshold lbabThreshRejectRateHigh.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: Time period to measure RRC Connection Reject Ratio against threshold lbabThreshRejectRateLow.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: RRC Connection Reject Ratio threshold above which Load-Based Access Barring increases access class barring probability or Progressive Access Barring, or PLMN-Specific Access Barring proceeds to higher priority.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: RRC Connection Reject Ratio threshold below which Load-Based Access Barring decreases access class barring probability or Progressive Access Barring, or PLMN-Specific Access Barring recedes to lower priority.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: How fast the Access Class Barring probability is decreased, that is how fast acBarringFactor in SIB2 is increased when the cell load is decreased.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: Minimum time for how often the acBarringFactor in SIB2 can be changed.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: Current barring factor based on LBAB algorithm or PAB algorithm.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

Parameter Description: Used for selecting whether the PRS transmission must use antenna switching or pre-coder switching.

Used for selecting the different power boosting alternatives for PRS transmissions. If set to 0, a default table based on the number of PBCH antennas and transmission scheme is shown. If set to 1, 2, or 3, it results in a power boosting of 0 dB, 3 dB, or 6 dB respectively.

Used for selecting the length of the PRS muting pattern. Setting the pattern length to 1 results in deactivation of PRS muting. The muting pattern is set to "1111111111111" in this case. Other recommended muting pattern lengths are: 2, 4, 8, and 16 bits.
Used for storing the calculated muting pattern for the cell. This parameter cannot be manually set.
Initial preamble power value in dBm, according to 3GPP specification 36.331 and 36.321.
Number of bytes assumed to be in UE buffer when SR is received through PRACH or PUCCH when Msg5 is expected to be scheduled for the UE.

Assumed TX power value of UE for transmission of Msg3. Msg3 can be used for estimating maximum value of initial pathloss when UE access the network. To set UE maximum output power according to the highest UE Power Class in the network (see 3GPP TS 36.101) use the following values of assumedUePowerMsg3:
230 for 23 dBm
260 for 26 dBm
310 for 31 dBm
When set to 1000, Msg3 pathloss estimation turns off.

Specifies the action performed when a S1AP:E-RAB SETUP REQUEST arrives and both the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover is active and the conditions for the bearer request are fulfilled.
Dependencies: This attribute only takes effect when attribute servOrPrioTriggeredIFHo has value 'QCI'.

Parameter Description:
DL power of PDSCH type B resource elements related to PDSCH type A resource elements.

Values pdschTypeBGain = (0,1,2,3) define gains (5/4,1,3/4,1/2), corresponding to multi-antenna scenario specified in 3GPP TS 36.213.

Example: If pdschTypeBGain is set to 3 (gain = 1/2), power of PDSCH type B resource elements is a factor 1/2 of the power of the PDSCH type A resource elements.

PDSDH type A resource elements are located in symbols that do not contain Cell-specific Reference Signals (CRS). PDSCH type B resource elements are located in symbols that contain CRS.

When adjustCrsPowerEnhEnabled = false, pdschTypeBGain = 0 (gain = 5/4) is not allowed if crsGain = 1.77,3.0, 4.77,6.0 dB. This combination causes overallocation of DL mean radio power and attribute pdschTypeBGain is mapped to 1 (gain = 1).

See readOnly attribute pb for actual p-b value.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if noOfCrsPorts is 2 or 4. With one port, power of resource elements for PDSCH type A and B is equal.

Specifies whether or not the function to set the serving frequency as sticky carrier is active in the current cell.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of physical resource blocks allowed on PUSCH for each UE.
Dependencies: This parameter only takes effect if the feature PUCCH Overdimensioning is activated.

Parameter Description: Dummy CDMA frequency band in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 information element that can be used to force registration each time the UE moves across LTE and CDMA 1xRTT networks. This can be achieved by setting both this parameter to a dummy band class that is not used in the native CDMA 1xRTT network and by setting the powerUpReg flag to TRUE in SIB-8. Parameter Description:
Controls if RRC connection establishments with cause Mobile Terminating Access is prioritized and not load regulated in folllowing:
- DU Connection Intensity Control
- Baseband Connection Intensity Control
- Dynamic Load Control.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. If set to true, RRC connection establishments with cause Mobile Terminating Access are not load regulated in the DU or Baseband Connection Intensity Control and in the Dynamic Load Control. This increases the risk for running into overload scenarios.

Parameter Description: UL BLER target to be used for VoLTE or PTT UEs. Used for all UL transmissions for UEs that have QCI1 or a QCI with serviceType PTT bearer configured. If a UE does not have QCI1 or a QCI with serviceType PTT bearer configured, normal UL BLER target is used.
A timer used for supervision and control of uplink synchronization. Special value: 0 means infinity.

Write protection that prevents feature Automated Cell Capacity Estimation from changing the value on parameters cellCapMinCellSubCap and cellCapMaxCellSubCap.

If set to true, feature Automated Cell Capacity Estimation cannot reset cellCapMinCellSubCap and cellCapMaxCellSubCap at cell unlock.
If set to false, feature Automated Cell Capacity Estimation can change cellCapMinCellSubCap and cellCapMaxCellSubCap at cell unlock.

PRB usage for PUCCH format 1 for each frame.

Based on PUCCH Scheduling Request, CFI and Carrier Aggregation user configuration. Not applicable for DL-only cells.

Value 65535 means not applicable.

PRB usage for PUCCH format 2 for each frame.

Based on PUCCH CQI user configuration. Not applicable for DL-only cells.

Value 65535 means not applicable.

PRB usage for PUCCH format 3 for each frame.

Based on HARQ ACK or NACK when Carrier Aggregation with more than two Component Carriers (2CC) is used. Not applicable for DL-only cells.

Value 65535 means not applicable.

The fraction of non-qualified UEs at UE selection for throughput aware load balancing. In case throughput aware UE selection is enabled, this parameter sets a target size for the fraction of UE to be disqualified for load balancing due to insufficient relative gain when moving UE from source to target cell.
Special value 0 means that the throughput aware UE selection for this cell is disabled.

The minimum threshold for the relative gain at throughput aware load balancing. A negative value may allow for some throughput loss for the individual UE, if the load balancing criteria requires so. Higher values may increase the fraction of non-qualified UEs at UE selection for throughput aware load balancing and may cause the load balancing to stall.
Special value -100 means the lower boundary for the threshold is disabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Whether primary PLMN ID is suppressed for some alarms when primary PLMN is not available in cell.

These alarms are PLMN Service Degraded and PLMN Service Unavailable alarm.

For PLMN Service Unavailable alarm, suppression of PLMN means its PLMN ID is not included in the alarm.

For PLMN Service Degraded alarm, suppression of PLMN means the alarm is not raised for it.

Primary PLMN ID is suppressed if this attribute is set to true.

If configured PLMN ID is not a served PLMN ID, then alarm is suppressed independent of configured settings.

When plmnServiceAlarmLevel is set to ENODEB, a PLMN is suppressed for PLMN Service Unavailable alarm if PLMN is suppressed in at least one cell.

Whether list of PLMN IDs in cell is suppressed for some alarms when PLMN is not available in cell.

These alarms are PLMN Service Degraded and PLMN Service Unavailable alarm.

For PLMN Service Unavailable alarm, suppression of PLMN means its PLMN ID is not included in the alarm.

For PLMN Service Degraded alarm, suppression of PLMN means alarm is not raised for it.

PLMN ID appearing in additionalPlmnList[x] is suppressed when additionalPlmnAlarmSupprList[x] is true.

If configured PLMN ID is not a served PLMN ID, then alarm is suppressed independent of configured settings.

When plmnServiceAlarmLevel is set to ENODEB, a PLMN is suppressed for PLMN Service Unavailable alarm if PLMN is suppressed in at least one cell.
Dependencies: The length of this list must be the same as the list in addtionalPlmnList.
