Parameter Description: Reference to an IdleModePrioAtRelease MO. Assigns an IdleModePrioAtRelease to a cell.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description: Controls the LCGs that are included in pmMacUeThpVolUl, pmMacUeThpTimeUl, and pmMacUeThpUlDistr. To include the n:th LCG, set includeLcgInMacUeThp[n]=true.
Indicates whether or not access attempts for MMTEL voice from UEs are to skip Access Class Barring functionality.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block VoLTE calls.

Parameter Description: Indicates whether or not access attempts for MMTEL video from UEs are to skip Access Class Barring functionality.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block Video calls.

Parameter Description: Indicates whether or not access attempts for SMS over SGs or SMS over IP from UEs are to skip Access Class Barring functionality.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can block sms.

Parameter Description:
Power offset to the target-received PUSCH Power Spectral Density (PSD) for 64-QAM-capable UEs. Used to control the received SINR target.
It is used to enable maximum throughput for 64QAM, which in some configurations is not possible otherwise, see dependencies.
Disturbances: Changes can affect traffic.
Dependencies:
Only relevant if the license for 64-QAM Uplink is present and the
feature is active.
For 2Rx, pZeroNominalPusch + puschPwrOffset64qam needs to be -100 dBm or higher to achieve maximum throughput.
puschPwrOffset64Qam should be set to 0 when both UL 64QAM and UL MU-MIMO are enabled in eNB.

Parameter Description: Enables UL 64-QAM at cell level.
Dependencies:
Only relevant if the license for UL 64-QAM is present and the
feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Highest allowed UL radio resource use ratio for admission of a non-privileged UE.

Applies to each UL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control feature. Resource use is checked against this threshold for one of the following options:
- All new RRC connections
- Reestablished RRC connections
- Incoming handovers
- Resumed RRC connections
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can affect the following:
- Number of RRC-connected users
- Cell throughput
- Number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests
- Rejected non-privileged RRC connection reestablishment requests
- Rejected non-privileged incoming handover requests
- Rejected non-privileged RRC connection resume requests
Dependencies:
ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr >= ulDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr.
ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr <= ulDynUeAdmCtrlPaOverloadThr.

Parameter Description:
Highest allowed UL radio resource use ratio for admission of a non-privileged UE.

Applies to each UL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control feature. Resource use is checked against this threshold for one of the following options:

- Incoming handovers

Disturbances:

dlDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr <= dlDynUeAdmCtrlPaOverloadThr.

Parameter Description:

Resource use is checked against this threshold for one of the following options:

- Resumed RRC connections
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can affect the following:

- Rejected non-privileged incoming handover requests
- Rejected non-privileged RRC connection resume requests
Dependencies: cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr >= cceDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr

Parameter Description:
Highest allowed UL radio resource use ratio for admission of a new non-privileged UE.

Applies to each UL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control feature. Resource use is checked against this threshold for all new RRC connections and RRC connection resumes.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can affect the following:
- Number of RRC-connected users
- Cell throughput
- Number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests
- Number of RRC connection resume requests
Dependencies: ulDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr =< ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr

Highest allowed DL radio resource use ratio for admission of a new non-privileged UE.

Parameter Description:
Highest allowed radio resource use ratio of control channel element for admission of a new non-privileged UE.

Dependencies: cceDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr =< cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr

Parameter Description: Time constant of the exponential-weighted moving average filter applied to the radio resource utilization ratios considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can affect following:
- Number of RRC-connected users.
- Cell throughput and number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests.
- Rejected non-privileged RRC connection reestablishment requests and rejected non-privileged incoming handover requests.
- If active, Enhanced Dynamic UE Admission Control for Privileged Access feature can affect the number of rejected Privileged Access (PA) RRC connection requests, PA RRC connection reestablishment requests, and PA incoming handover requests.

Parameter Description: Enable Dynamic UE Admission Control at cell level.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can affect the following:
- the number of RRC-connected users
- cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests
- rejected non-privileged RRC connection re-establishment requests and rejected
  non-privileged incoming handover requests.
Dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Dynamic UE Admission Control is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Determines whether a bearer that fulfills the criteria for the feature Service- or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover is set up, or rejected in UE .
Enables additional spectrum emission requirements for CA according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4A-1.
Range and Values:
CA_NS_01
CA_NS_02
CA_NS_03
CA_NS_04
CA_NS_05
CA_NS_06
CA_NS_07
CA_NS_08
CA_NS_31

Parameter Description: Enables Ericsson Lean Carrier functionality in the cell.
Dependencies: Only relevant if licence for ELC is present and feature is active. When set to true, commonCqiPeriodicity attribute must be set to default value, 80 ms.

Parameter Description: Normalized downlink cell capacity available for use by carrier aggregation. The value is used to calculate the aggregated capacity of a UE:s possible aggregation possibilities, for example by the CA Aware IFLB feature.

Scaling factor for the estimated cell subscription capacity. Can be used to reduce the traffic load balancing attraction of the cell. Used if traffic handling capacity of the cell is constrained by circumstances the ACCE feature is unable to capture. An example of such a circumstance is at limited UL capacity in a TDD cell.

When the attribute is value is set to 0, the corresponding cell uses the value cellSubscriptionCapacity as the Cell Subscription Capacity value for the cell. This bypasses the automatically estimated Cell Subscription Capacity value for the cell.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Indicates a maximum handover backoff time. The value is applied to inhibit further handover attempts to a EUTRAN target cell that rejects incoming handover for soft-lock of cell.

If set to true, AILG is automatically restarted when:
- cell disabled followed by cell enabled, for example at node start or restart.
Turns feature Configurable UL BLER Target on and off.
Enables operator configuration of the RTP timeout value at the eNodeB at a cell level that corresponds to the RTP timeout value get set at the IMS layer.
Enable or disable 256 QAM support in DL.
Indication if 256 QAM in DL is supported in the cell.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of UEs with Clustered PUSCH allocations allowed in a TTI.
Multiplication factor applied to the 3GPP-defined Maximum Power Reduction values for Clustered PUSCH. Low settings imply high usage of Clustered PUSCH, high settings imply the opposite.
Enable or disable the UE-Assisted Adaptive DRX feature.
Enable or disable the UE-Assisted Signaling Reduction feature.
Decides if a bearer handled by the feature Service or Priority Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover (SPIFHO) is set up at Initial Context Setup even when attribute servOrPrioIFHoSetupBearer is false.
Dependencies: The value of this attribute is only considered when the value of servOrPrioIFHoSetupBearer=false.

Parameter Description: Threshold in terms of number of remaining SR resources available for the cell. Below this threshold, allocTimerPucchFormat1 for allocation of an additional PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is triggered. Occurs if  feature Dynamic PUCCH  is activated. Value 0 means the dynamic PUCCH allocation/deallocation operation for this cell is disabled.
Dependencies:
If Scheduling Request resources limitation pool for privileged access connections is activated in eNodeB, threshold for allocation of an additional PUCCH format 1 PRB pair by dynamic PUCCH must be higher than number of resources in limitation pool.
(allocThrPucchFormat1 > AdmissionControl::limitSrNonPa)

Parameter Description: A guard time. After this time, a PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is allocated if threshold allocThrPucchFormat1 is still passed.

Threshold in terms of number of remaining SR resources available for the cell. Above this threshold, deallocTimerPucchFormat1 for deallocation of a PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is triggered. Occurs if  feature Dynamic PUCCH  is activated.
A guard time. After this time, a PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is deallocated if threshold deallocThrPucchFormat1 is still passed.
Offset value that controls the maximum allowed difference between pZeroNominalPusch and the received power below pZeroNominalPusch in the primary sector when UL CoMP is used.

Threshold for when UE is considered to be Out Of Coverage (OOC). If the number of OOC trigger events is greater than or equal to the threshold, the UE is in the OOC state; if the number of OOC trigger events is less than the threshold, the UE is not in the OOC state.
Maximum number of consecutive OOC easing events that leave the OOC state when UE is in OOC state for a long time.
Number of bytes for BSR at eNodeB when UE is in OOC state, and OOC spare grant scheduling is applied.
Repetition rate of UL sparse grants that are eNodeB-triggered to Out Of Coverage (OOC) UEs.
Enables feature UL Scheduling Control for Out Of Coverage (OOC) UEs.
Reference to an instance of ResourcePartitionGroup MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Specifies if outgoing uplink-triggered mobility actions are enabled or disabled in the cell.
Used when Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled. The parameter has effect if Mobility Control in Poor Coverage is enabled and mobCtrlAtPoorCovActive is set to true in the cell.
PDCCH DCI format 1A is used for SRB to increase transmission success rate and to minimize interruption time.
PDCCH DCI format 1A to increase MOS for QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT in high interference or high path loss scenarios.
PDCCH DCI format 1A for first retransmission due to DTX of SRB and serviceType VoIP or PTT.

Relative priority in initial SCell selection for cells that can be configured with UL Carrier Aggregation. Applicable where several SCells are initially configured simultaneously. Lowest value has highest priority.
Dependencies: Applicable when 3CC Carrier aggregation Extension Feature (FAJ 121 3084) is enabled and sCellSelectionMode is equal to UN_ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION or ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION.

Parameter Description: List of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to. Primary frequency band, EARFCN value of the cell, is not included. Secondary cell evaluation is done according to list order, and/or the list is broadcasted in SIB1. Highest priority band is position 0 in the list.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if ENodeBFunction::useBandPrioritiesInSCellEval or EUtranCellFDD/TDD::mfbiFreqBandIndPrio is enabled.
prioAdditionalFreqBandList only contains frequency bands from additionalFreqBandList.
prioAdditionalFreqBandList is reset to empty list if MO action changeFrequency changes frequency of EUtranCellFDD/TDD, and new additionalFreqBandList does not contain bands included in prioAdditionalFreqBandList.

Parameter Description: Defines how many dB higher than the original SR detection threshold can be used as high SR detection threshold. Used together with srProcessingLevel to reduce false SR detection.
Defines how many SRs eNodeB must receive in a row in order to process it. Used together with srDetectHighThres to reduce false SR detection.
Controls adaptive CFI to avoid using CFI=1 or CFI=1,2, when scheduling UEs that are in handover. The highest CFI value in available CFI values determined by pdcchCfiMode is not prohibited.
Dependencies: Only applicable when attribute pdcchCfiMode is set to CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_2, CFI_STATIC_3, or CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_3.

Parameter Description: Controls if link adaptation function allocates largest possible resource to last scheduled UE in the DL. Used to improve UE decoding success rate with reduced code rate.

Maximum number of physical resource blocks (PRBs) allowed on PDSCH for each UE.
Note: If the set value is larger than the system bandwidth, then the system bandwidth value will be used instead.
For PDSCH resource allocation type 0, the actual maximum number of PRBs that is allocated will be a multiple of RBGs (Resource Block Groups) that is nearest to the set value but without exceeding it.

SI message to which each SIB is mapped.
Note: SIB2 is always mapped to SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: SI validity timer. The timer is set to 3h or 24h.
Min received RSRP level in E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection for UE in enhanced coverage mode. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin_CE in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1-BR.

Min quality level (RSRQ) in cell for UE in enhanced coverage mode.

Corresponds to Qqualmin_CE in TS 36.304, sent in SIB1-BR. If 0, it is not sent and UE applies default value of negative infinity for Qqualmin_CE.
Enables Dynamic uplink resource allocation on cell level.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license UlDynamicResourceAllocation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Specifies if SINR-based UL power control can be used or not. If enabled, SNR-based closed-loop power control and SINR-based closed-loop power control can be adaptively selected.
Dependencies: Attribute only has effect if feature Differential Uplink Power Control is activated.

Parameter Description: SINR target value for SINR-based UL closed-loop power control.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: SINR target only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

Parameter Description: Threshold value for measured noise plus interference level. If measured noise plus interference is higher than interferenceThresholdSinrClpc, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
Dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

Parameter Description: Threshold of UL transmission power per PRB. If averaged UL transmission power measurement per PRB is lower than ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc over a set percentage of UL bandwidth, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
Dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

Parameter Description:
Threshold number of SCells configured by Carrier Aggregation (CA) users with this cell as PCell. When number of SCells configured for UEs connected in this PCell is higher than caPrioThreshold, following rules apply:
- For Configurable SCell Priority, all frequency carriers configured for CA are assumed to have equal priority regardless of configured values.
- For Global SCell Evaluation, all SCell relations from PCell are handled equally regardless of threshold for number of SCell UEs.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when following apply:
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to PRIORITIZED and Configurable SCell Priority is active.
- dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to GLOBAL_EVALUATION and Global SCell Evaluation is active.

Parameter Description: Enables or disables measurement-based Ericsson Lean Carrier Control.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license Ericsson Lean Carrier is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs that do not have a secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

Initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

Initial value for primary cell PDCCH outer loop adjustment in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have a bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have a bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.
PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

PDCCH outer loop up step size for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

PDCCH target error rate for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.
PDCCH target error rate for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

PDCCH target error rate for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.
Set to true when idle mode eDRX shall be allowed in the cell.
Long DRX cycle for ELC. Value of elcLongDrxCycle is in number of sub-frames.
Dependencies: Feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is present active.

Parameter Description:
Enable automatic configuration of tReorderingDl and tReorderingUl. Configuration is based on HARQ-interval together with an offset defined by harqOffsetDl/harqOffsetUl.tReordering >= 'Max number of HARQ' * HARQ-interval + harqOffset, where closest higher or equal allowed value is used.

This configuration is only applied to UM bearers. AM bearers will still use tReorderingUl and tReorderingDl from QciProfilePredefined or QciProfileOperatorDefined.
Offset used when tReorderingDl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingDl = 'Max number of HARQ for DL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetDl.
Offset used when tReorderingUl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingUl = 'Max number of HARQ for UL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetUl.
Enables function to automatically adapt t-PollretransmitTimer to the time it takes to complete HARQ procedure + harqOffset (UL and DL).
Enable/disable service-specific HARQ on cell level. Function must have valid license.
Maximum downlink PRB usage that scheduling stays on-hold for Low Energy Scheduler Solution.
Turns on/off Configurable DL BLER Target.
SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values go higher, more candidates are selected for Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP, but more user measurements are triggered. This impacts MP load and transport load over X2.
Dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrHys.

Parameter Description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values get bigger, gaps for triggering Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP user switching get bigger.
Dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrThr.

Parameter Description: Threshold for % of PRBs with "UL Tx power per PRB >= ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc" during measSinrClpcPeriod. Below threshold means low cell power load and then SINR based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
Dependencies: Attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc must be true.

Parameter Description: Shows the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.

Whether or not UL-scheduler is enabled that uses adaptive re-transmission more frequently for data-aware UL-scheduling UEs, to reduce fragments in UL spectrum.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Threshold used to help identify data-aware UL scheduling UEs. If BSR >= bsrThreshold, UE becomes candidate UE for UL improvement.

Length of time eNodeB rejects traffic requests from non-privileged UEs when detecting high procedure latency. Used in Procedure Latency Supervision. Privileged traffic, such as High Priority Access (HPA) and Emergency, is never rejected due to high procedure latency conditions.
Whether or not SCell selection for high power UE that is not capable of CA simultaneously is enabled.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Enables PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

Parameter Description: Value of threshold to enable the PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling. PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling is triggered when the number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell is less than or equal to ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and
- attribute ns05FullBandSchedEnabled in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is true.

Parameter Description: Controls if the low band can be allocated to NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_PROHIBIT', the low band cannot be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_AVAILABLE', the low band can always be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION', the low band can only be allocated to the NS_05 UEs which are detected as not in repeater zone.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

Parameter Description: Value of threshold to detect if the NS_05 UE is in repeater zone. If the NS_05 UE's pathloss measured on low band is bigger than or equal to the value of other band plus ns05PathlossOffsetThres, the NS_05 UE is detected as in repeater zone.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect if:
- license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and
- attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and
- attribute ns05LowBandSchedMode is ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION.

Hysteresis of SINR threshold for triggering a switch to high power UE.
Time-to-trigger value for UL measurement in switching between High Power UE to Carrier Aggregation.

The attribute in broadcast in SIB1 as multiBandInfoList-v10j0. A list of additionalPmax and additionalSpectrumEmission values. If E-UTRAN includes multiBandInfoList-v10j0, it includes the same number of entries, and listed in the same order, as in multiBandInfoList.

A list which maps frequency bands to additional Pmax value, and additional spectrum emissions as described by 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. This list is used to generate the value of additionalMultipleNSPmax.
Disturbances: Changing the pMax value for additional band can cause loss of traffic. additionalPMax in MultipleNSPmaxReqMapping structure indicates the pMax value.

Parameter Description:
Initial ratio for downlink output power to start power ramp up.
Value 100 indicates full cell coverage.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Power ramp up rate per second for downlink output power to reach full cell coverage.
Normal or Large Window Size for PUSCH filter channel estimation for normal CP.

If enabled, prioritized additional frequency band list is broadcast in SIB1 according to priorities set in EUtranCellFDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList or in EUtranCellTDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList. The priorities must be valid.

If disabled, EUtranCellFDD::additionalFreqBandList or EUtranCellTDD::additionalFreqBandList is used.
Deprecated: Since 18.Q4. Replaced by mfbiFreqBandIndPrio. Planned to be removed.
Precondition: eNodeB must support Multiple Frequency Band Indicators feature.

Parameter Description: Reference to a list of MeasCellGroup MOs for grouping on UE basis. Referenced Mos include measurements on differentiated UEs into a measurement group.
Dependencies:
MeasCellGroup with 0 groupId can not be referred.
MeasCellGroup with empty spidList and empty plmnList can not be referred.
MeasCellGroup with non-empty plmnList and MeasCellGroup having non null spidList can not be referred together.
Duplication of plmn or spid within referred MeasCellGroups is not allowed.

Parameter Description:
Controls which DL subframes are unavailable for Cat-M DL due to MBMS operation.
Fewer unavailable subframes optimize Cat-M1 DL max throughput, but change of unavailable subframes can cause Cat-M1 connection drops and temporary difficulties to page certain UEs. Avoided by less dynamic setting (lower value).
0: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to MbsfnArea::commonSFAllocList and MbsfnArea::mbsfnAreaCellRelation.
1: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to MbsfnArea::commonSFAllocList and MbsfnArea::mbsfnAreaCellRelation if any MBSFN service is active in the cell, otherwise no unavailable subframes due to MBMS.
2: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to subframes blocked by active MBSFN services.

Shows valid subframes for DL BR transmissions, indicated by broadcasted SIB1-BR.
1: Corresponding subframe is valid DL BR subframe.
0: Corresponding subframe not valid DL BR subframe.
First element in the list corresponds to radio frames satisfying SFN mod 4 = 0, the next to radio frames satisfying SFN mod 4 = 1 and so on.
Each least significant bit represents subframe #0 of the corresponding SFN.
If SIB1-BR not broadcasted (Cat-M not supported in cell), list is empty.

Reference to an instance of PtmCellProfile that contains configuration for the cell.
If not set, PTM is disabled on the cell.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
Changes priorities of bands for Multiple Frequency Band Indicators.

If true:
Cell broadcasts freqBandIndicatorPriority in SIB1, and FreqBandIndicatorPriority=broadcasted is sent over X2 interface to neighbor eNB.
Prioritized additional frequency band list (prioAdditionalFreqBandList) is broadcasted in SIB1 and is also used for handovers (including S1 and X2 handovers) instead of additionalFreqBandList.
If UE indicates freqBandPriorityAdjustment capability (support of freqBandIndicatorPriority), primary band has the lowest priority, otherwise primary band has the highest priority.
mfbiFreqBandIndPrio is not used for handovers between Ericsson eNBs if ENodeBFunction::caAwareMfbiIntraCellHo = true.

If false:
Cell doesn't broadcast freqBandIndicatorPriority in SIB1, and FreqBandIndicatorPriority=not-broadcasted is sent over X2 interface to neighbor eNB.
additionalFreqBandList is broadcasted in SIB1 and is also used for handovers (including S1 and X2 handovers).
Primary band always has the highest priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. X2 handover and Connection Setup for MFBI capable UE can fail during a few seconds, leading to dropped calls.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is active.

Parameter Description: Number of CRS ports used for a cell that is sending CRS over air interface. -1 means undefined when a cell is not sending CRS over air interface. For example when a cell is locked or disabled.
Defines PDCP volume threshold for counter pmUeThpDlMbbFilteredDistr. UE session with PDCP volume less than this threshold is filtered out.
Deprecated: Since 21.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Defines DRB transport time threshold for counter pmUeThpDlMbbFilteredDistr. UE session with DRB transport time less than this threshold is filtered out.
Deprecated: Since 21.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Whether release-with-redirect in critical zone is allowed.

Only allowed to:
-EUtran frequency when EUtranFreqRelation::mobilityAction attribute is configured as HANDOVER.
-GUtran frequency when GUtranFreqRelation::mobilityAction attribute is configured as HANDOVER.

Only applicable if license for Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is present and feature is active.

Whether release-with-redirect in search zone is allowed.

Only allowed to:
-EUtran frequency when EUtranFreqRelation::mobilityAction attribute is configured as HANDOVER.
-GUtran frequency when GUtranFreqRelation::mobilityAction attribute is configured as HANDOVER.

Only applicable if license for Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is present and feature is active.
High and low MSR thresholds for Load-Based CA SCell Handling.
Dependencies: Only used when Load-Based CA SCell Handling is active and loadBasedCaEnabled=1.

Parameter Description: Enables Load-Based CA SCell Handling.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for Load-Based CA SCell Handling is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Number of successfully preallocated Scheduling Request resources at cell setup.

Undefined value: -1
Dependencies:
Relation to AdmissionControl::nrOfPaConnReservationsPerCell.
Successful preallocation: nrOfPreallocatedSrRes = nrOfPaConnReservationsPerCell
Partially successful preallocation: nrOfPreallocatedSrRes < nrOfPaConnReservationsPerCell
Failed preallocation: nrOfPreallocatedSrRes = 0
No preallocation attempt (default): nrOfPreallocatedSrRes = -1

Parameter Description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Initial ratio for downlink output power to start power ramp up.
Value 100 indicates full cell coverage.
Time alignment timer, used for supervision and control of uplink synchronization for Bandwidth reduced UEs. Special Value 0 means infinity.
Deprecated: Since 21.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: High load indication that affects Carrier Aggregation (CA) traffic (SCell).
Dependencies: Only used when loadBasedCaEnabled=true.

Parameter Description:
Used to decide when to switch to resource-fair (RF) resource allocation strategy for UEs configured as frequency-selective (FS). Applicable when Evolved Uplink Frequency-Selective Scheduling feature is activated. Spectrum utilization gain caused by changing FS to RF is calculated for TTI with large buffer UE. If calculation result is above threshold, UL resource allocation strategy changes to RF for large buffer and not large buffer new UL transmissions configured as FS scheduled in that TTI.

Value 0 means highest switching probability. Value 99 means lowest switching probability. Value 100 means switching to RF is turned off.

Scheduling Request (SR) transmission parameter. This parameter controls the maximum number of SR transmissions on valid PUCCH resources before UE initiates a Random Access procedure. Value 4 corresponds to four transmissions, value 8 corresponds to eight transmissions and so on.
Contains cell reselection information common for cell reselection towards NR.
Enables Inter-Frequency Load Balancing (IFLB) during access class barring.
Enables uplink 256-QAM at cell level.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for uplink 256 QAM is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Power offset to target-received PUSCH Power Spectral Density (PSD) for 256-QAM-capable UEs. Controls received SINR target.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for uplink 256 QAM is present and feature is active.
Precondition: ul256qamEnabled is set to true.

Parameter Description: Resource coordination to use with neighboring NRCells.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description:
Whether detection of uplink-heavy UE is enabled.

Only applicable if license for at least one of following features is present and feature is active:
- Uplink-Traffic-Triggered Mobility
- Data-Aware Carrier Aggregation Configuration
Enables skip uplink padding on dynamic grants for prescheduling UEs.
Enables skip uplink padding on dynamic grants for all UEs.
Enables prioritization of mobile originating voice RRC connection requests in Dynamic UE Admission Control.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if feature Optimization VoLTE Access at High Load is active.

Parameter Description: Activates or deactivates ASGH based BLER target. When set to true, BLER target for a subscriber group is configured through SubscriberGroupProfile::ulHarqBlerTarget and SubscriberGroupProfile::dlHarqBlerTarget.
Dependencies: When set to true, SubscriberGroupProfile::ulHarqBlerTarget and SubscriberGroupProfile::dlHarqBlerTarget override BLER related attributes in EUtranCellFDD and EUtranCellTDD for UEs in that subscriber group.

Parameter Description: Whether Flexible Channel Bandwidth with CRS Control Channel Blocking is activated in cell.
Whether power boosting for non-blocked PRBs is activated.
Dependencies: Only relevant if dlCchAndRefSigBlockActive is set to true.

Parameter Description:
Coefficient used to select candidate target cells for uplink-heavy handover.

If following condition is fulfilled, neighbor cell can be a candidate:
uplink capacity of neighbor cell > (1 + ulCellCapCoeff) x uplink capacity of source cell.

Disturbances: Setting this attribute to 1 may cause higher throughput for Elastic RAN.

Deprecated: Since 20.Q1. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Whether Reduced Connection Setup Time feature is enabled using enhanced initial prescheduling.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for Reduced Connection Setup Time is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Configuration of Coverage-Triggered Mobility at Setup feature.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for Coverage-Triggered Mobility at Setup is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: E-UTRAN frequency with aggregated hit rate value greater than this threshold is considered suitable for Load-Based Distribution at Release prioritization.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: Only applicable when Evolved Load-Based Distribution at Release is enabled and LoadBalancingFunction.coverageAwareLbdar is true.

Controls initial DL HOM mode and switching between HOM mode and Legacy mode. In case of Carrier Aggregation, value setting in PCell is also used by SCells and ESCells.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if license for Instant Downlink 256-QAM Activation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of RLC retransmissions in DL for RRCConnectionRelease message.

Stopping and indicating to RRC if RLC threshold is reached. Value -1 means not used.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Optimized RRC Connection Release Control is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Time lapsed before new poll is requested.

Request is sent if no status report arrives for sequence number. Sequence number is contained in DL RLC data PDU that contains RRCConnectionRelease message in which poll bit is set. Value -1 means not used.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Optimized RRC Connection Release Control is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description: Ratio of t300 timer value that specifies the maximum time a cell can queue RRC connection. Maximum time in queue = rrcQueueT300Ratio * t300. If set to 0, cell does not queue RRC Connection Requests.
Whether automatic configuration of upperLayerIndication is enabled.

Whether upperLayerIndication is set for PLMNs configured in cell.

First indication in upperLayerAutoConfIndList refers to ENodeBFunction::eNodeBPlmnId or EUtranCellTDD::cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId if configured.
Indication in upperLayerAutoConfIndList[x+1] refers to PLMN ID in additionalPlmnList[x].

This attribute is referenced in broadcasting upperLayerIndication in SIB2.

Whether Dynamic UE Admission Control takes into account dynamic PTT MSR reservations.

Valid if Enhanced PTT Admission Control and Dynamic UE Admission Control features are enabled.

Highest allowed CCE radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a PA UE.

Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, reestablished, or incoming handover RRC connections.
Benefit of this threshold is expected in configurations where high number of PA users is perceived.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause rejection of Privileged Access RRC connection requests, Privileged Access RRC connection re-establishment requests and Privileged Access incoming handover requests.
Dependencies:
cceDynUeAdmCtrlPaOverloadThr >= cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr.

Only applicable when Enhanced Dynamic UE Admission Control for Privileged Access feature is enabled.

Parameter Description:
Highest allowed DL radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a PA UE.

Applies to each DL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, reestablished, or incoming handover RRC connections.
Benefit of this threshold is expected in configurations where high number of PA users is perceived.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause rejection of Privileged Access RRC connection requests, Privileged Access RRC connection re-establishment requests and Privileged Access incoming handover requests.
Dependencies:
dlDynUeAdmCtrlPaOverloadThr >= dlDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr.

Only applicable when Enhanced Dynamic UE Admission Control for Privileged Access feature is enabled.

Parameter Description:
Highest allowed UL radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a PA UE.

Applies to each UL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, reestablished, or incoming handover RRC connections.
Benefit of this threshold is expected in configurations where high number of PA users is perceived.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause rejection of Privileged Access RRC connection requests, Privileged Access RRC connection re-establishment requests and Privileged Access incoming handover requests.
Dependencies:
ulDynUeAdmCtrlPaOverloadThr >= ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr.

Only applicable when Enhanced Dynamic UE Admission Control for Privileged Access feature is enabled.

Parameter Description: Maximum number of HARQ transmissions for Msg3.

Whether Minimum Interference Scheduling feature is enabled.

If true, a random UL start position for new transmissions of resource-fair resource allocation strategy is selected in small UL PRB use case. This helps to make PRBs in whole UL spectrum more evenly used.

UL region size between each PUCCH region and band center.

Maximum size is as follows:
- 15 PRBs for 20 MHz and 15 MHz.
- 8 PRBs for 10 MHz and 5 MHz.
- 0 PRBs for 3 MHz and 1.4 MHz.
When value greater than maximum size is set, system uses maximum size.
Value 0 means there is no UL region.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if minInterfSchedEnabled is true.

Primary PLMN defined on cell.

If defined, overrides the value of ENodeBFunction::eNodeBPlmnId.
Dependencies:
Used only in context of MORAN on Single Baseband (Shared LTE RAN configuration). MORAN cell can only be created if MORAN on Single Baseband is activated.
If MORAN cell is created or unlocked and MORAN on Single Baseband is not activated, cell is disabled.
PLMN defined as cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId cannot be the same as ENodeBFunction::eNodeBPlmnId.
If cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId is defined, additionalPlmnList must be empty.
Up to two different cellDefinedPrimaryPlmnId values can be defined within ENodeBFunction.
Precondition: If TheftDeterrence::thdStatus is LOCKED or LOCKED_PERMANENTLY, this value can only be changed when modified PLMN ID is part of Lock Token or Operator List.

Parameter Description:
UL HARQ transmission number threshold for Zero Interference VoLTE Operation feature.

If transmission number is greater than or equal to this threshold, a UE candidate can be put to reserved region.
When value is greater than MACConfiguration::ulMaxHARQTx value, system uses MACConfiguration::ulMaxHARQTx value.
Value 0 means feature is disabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Zero Interference VoLTE Operation is present and the feature is active.
Only applicable if
- minInterfSchedEnabled is true.
- minInterfUlRegionSize is equal to or greater than 3.

Parameter Description:
Whether SRS bandwidth for this cell is aligned with resources limitations.

Used for Uplink Frequency-Selective Scheduling feature. Aligned with the resource limitation, defined by following attributes:
- EUtranCellTDD::ulFrequencyAllocationProportion
- EUtranCellTDD::ulConfigurableFrequencyStart
Dependencies:
Only applicable when following options apply:
- Feature Frequency Selective Scheduling is activated, that is, ResourceAllocationStrategy is set to FREQUENCY_SELECTIVE.
- Uplink Sounding is activated.
- Flexible Channel Bandwidth feature is configured.

Parameter Description: Whether enhancement of VoLTE Optimized Carrier Aggregation is enabled.
Dependencies: Only relevant if license for VoLTE Optimized Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether UE capability refreshing in specific conditions is prohibited.

Only applicable when all the following conditions are fulfilled:
- establishmentCause in RRCConnectionRequest message is mo-VoiceCall-v1280.
- eNodeB has the UE capability information.
- Incoming handover is excluded.
Controls MU pairable transmission mode for LTE TDD AAS downlink MU-MIMO.

CBRS cell priority.

Cell priority is used by Domain Coordinator in channel allocation algorithm and other algorithms together with customized policies defined by operator. It allows control over CBRS cell function, for example influencing channel grant type assigned to cell and its recovery time.
Rank of CBRS cell in priority group.
Preferred bandwidth for CBRS cell.
SRS bandwidth for AAS TDD cells.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in TDD cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio when Basic AAS for TDD is active and EUtranCellTDD::ulSrsEnable is true.

Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Measurement gap pattern used by UEs configured for EN-DC.

Value 0 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 0, with measurement gap periodicity 40 and measurement gap length 6.
Value 1 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 1, with measurement gap periodicity 80 and measurement gap length 6.
Restricts measurement gap offset selection for UEs configured for EN-DC.
Obsolete: Since 21.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Common CQI periodicity used for all UEs except Cat-M UEs.
Dependencies: Only default value, 80 ms is allowed when elcEnabled attribute is set to true.

Parameter Description: Whether AI Powered Advanced Cell Supervision mode is activated.
Recovery actions to perform when AI Powered Advanced Cell Supervision detects a sleeping cell.
Dependencies: Only applicable if aiAdvCellSupMode is NORMAL.

Parameter Description:
Measurement gap pattern used by UEs.

Value 0 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 0, with measurement gap periodicity 40 and measurement gap length 6.
Value 1 corresponds to measurement gap pattern 1, with measurement gap periodicity 80 and measurement gap length 6.

Whether alternative Scheduling Info Lists are present in SIB1 for SIB19 and higher.

If true, SIB19 and higher are mapped in SIB1 Scheduling Info List using late non-critical extensions.
If false, all SIBs including SIB19 and higher are mapped in SIB1 using legacy format of Scheduling Info List.
3GPP Rel-15.11.0 introduced late non-critical extensions as CR 4444 'Modification of SI scheduling for extended SIBs' to allow network access to non-3GPP-compatible UEs.
Whether adaptive pulling mechanism of enqueued RRC Connection Request messages is enabled.
Preferred offset option for Carrier Aggregation Transformation for CBRS cell.

Subframe within a radio frame where PRACH resource starts.

Value -1 means that system automatically assigns a valid value.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect when prachConfigEnabled is true.

When subframeAssignment is set to 2, values 3 and 8 cannot be used because these are DL subframes.

Parameter Description: PRACH Configuration Index that is used in cell.

Whether enhancement for Adjustable CRS Power feature is enabled.

Enhancement supports CRS gain 4.77 dB and 6 dB, but does not support ESS cells.
Actual p-a value sent to UE in RRC messages.
Range and Values:
DB_MINUS_6
DB_MINUS_4_DOT_77
DB_MINUS_3
DB_MINUS_1_DOT_77
DB_0
DB_1
DB_2
DB_3

Parameter Description: Whether PIM-Detection in DU feature is activated for this cell.
Deprecated: Since 22.Q2. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Whether dedicated A5 report settings for Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover feature are enabled.

If set to true, this feature is configured by ReportConfigA5Spifho attributes.
If set to false, this feature is configured by ReportConfigA5 attributes.
Whether UE TX antenna selection is enabled for antenna selection-capable UEs.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when license for Basic AAS for TDD is present and feature is active.
Only takes effect in TDD cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio.

Parameter Description:
Whether PDCCH flexible BLER is enabled for optimized PDCCH.

If true, optimizedPdcchMaxTargetBler is used as maximum PDCCH target BLER.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Optimized PDCCH is present and feature is active.

Cannot be set to false if diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: PDCCH congestion threshold for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellTDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description: DL PRB threshold of PDCCH congestion for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellTDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description: UL PRB threshold of PDCCH congestion for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellTDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description: Maximum PDCCH target BLER for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true and diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled is false.

Cannot be lower than pdcchTargetBler.

For usage in subscriber group, see description of attribute SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode.

Parameter Description: Whether DL SCell carrier aggregation traffic is offloaded at high load in DL MU-MIMO in TDD AAS.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when license for Multi-User MIMO Downlink Layers Extension is present and feature is activated, and attribute dlMaxMuMimoLayers is greater than 0.

Parameter Description:
Whether eNodeB supports eCall over IMS.

Support is indicated in SIB1.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for feature NG eCall Support for Emergency Calls is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Lowest allowed paging priority which is not rejected by Dynamic UE Admission Control.

Applicable only for RRC Connection Request with Establishment Cause mt-Access.
Applicable only if MSR value reaches cceDynUeAdmCtrlRedDiffThr, dlDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr or ulDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr.
Range and Values:
OFF
PRIO_LEVEL_1
PRIO_LEVEL_2
PRIO_LEVEL_3
PRIO_LEVEL_4
PRIO_LEVEL_5
PRIO_LEVEL_6
PRIO_LEVEL_7
PRIO_LEVEL_8
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Prioritized Mobile Terminating Access at High Load is present and feature is active.
Value of pagingPriorityDiffThr must be greater than or equal to pagingPriorityOverloadThr.

Parameter Description:
Lowest allowed paging priority which is not rejected by Dynamic UE Admission Control.

Applicable only for RRC Connection Request with Establishment Cause mt-Access.
Applicable only if MSR value reaches cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr, dlDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr or ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for age of earliest RLC SDU for DRB in DL, monitored by buffer-based EN-DC setup.

If value is 0, age of RLC SDUs in DL is not considered during buffer-based EN-DC setup.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Changing this attribute can decrease number of EN-DC users.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for total volume of RLC SDUs of DRB in DL, monitored by buffer-based EN-DC setup.

If value is 0, volume of RLC SDUs in DL is not considered during buffer-based EN-DC setup.
Disturbances:
Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Changing this attribute can decrease number of EN-DC users.

Parameter Description: Whether TM8 is allowed on TDD AAS SCell.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when license for Basic AAS for TDD is present and feature is active.
Only takes effect in TDD secondary cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio.

Parameter Description:
Whether 2RX TM9 can be overridden to TM8 on TDD AAS SCell.

Only applicable when tm8SCellAllowed is set to true.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when license for Basic AAS for TDD is present and feature is active.
Only takes effect in TDD secondary cell using TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio.

Parameter Description:
Value of dominating QCI for selecting UE sessions for throughput calculation.

UE sessions where dominating QCI matches attribute dominQciFilter are included in calculation of QCI-based throughput filtering in UL and DL.
If value equals -1, no UE session is included.

Following counters are related:
- pmMacUeThpUlMbbLowVolQciDistr
- pmMacUeThpUlMbbHighVolQciDistr
- pmUeExclThpUlRelativeQciLowVol
- pmUeExclThpUlRelativeQciHighVol
- pmUeExclThpUlShortTimeQciLowVol
- pmUeExclThpUlShortTimeQciHighVol
- pmUeThpDlMbbFilteredQciDistr
- pmUeExclThpDlQciShortDrb
Whether B1 measurement with measurement gap is enabled for EN-DC capable UEs.
Deprecated: Since 23.Q1. Replaced by EUtranCellTDD::endcB1MeasGapConfig. Planned to be removed.
