Characteristic information value used to generate cell-level characteristic sequences.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if ENodeBFunction::ductIntCharInfoScheme is set to CELL_SPECIFIC.
Cannot be set to -1 when ENodeBFunction::ductIntCharInfoScheme is set to CELL_SPECIFIC.

Parameter Description: Controls whether Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility feature is enabled.
Threshold for potential packet loss related to Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

Whether extreme good point for P0-based closed-loop power control is enabled.

Extreme good point optimization applies to P0-based closed-loop power control of Differential Uplink Power Control feautre.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when license for Differential Uplink Power Control is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Whether extreme bad point for P0-based closed-loop power control is enabled.

Extreme bad point optimization applies to P0-based closed-loop power control of Differential Uplink Power Control feaure.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when license for Differential Uplink Power Control is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
SINR threshold for identifying extreme bad point users.

User is identified at extreme bad point when their measured SINR is less than this threshold. For those users UL transmission power is increased, without limitation, for reaching threshold.
If set to higner value,
- More UEs are required to increase power.
- Interference to neighbor cells increases.
If set to lower value,
- Fewer UEs are required to increase power.
- Increase of interference to neighbor cells is smaller.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable when p0ClpcExBadEnabled is set to true. When p0ClpcExGoodEnabled and p0ClpcExBadEnabled are both set to true, value of p0ClpcExBadSinrThr must be smaller than value of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr.

Parameter Description:
SINR threshold for identifying extreme good point users for 16-QAM.

User is identified at extreme good point when their measured SINR is greater than this threshold. For those threshold UL transmission power is decreased for reaching threshold.
If set to higher value,
- Interference to neighbor cells is less reduced.
- Throughput of current cell is not degraded.
If set to lower value,
- Interference to neighbor cells is more reduced.
- Throughput of current cell might be degraded.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable when p0ClpcExGoodEnabled is set to true. When p0ClpcExGoodEnabled and p0ClpcExBadEnabled are both set to true, value of p0ClpcExBadSinrThr must be smaller than value of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr.

Parameter Description:
SINR offset of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr for 64-QAM-capable UEs.

Increases SINR threshold for identifying extreme good point users for 64-QAM. Used for maintaining maximum throughput for 64-QAM.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for 64-QAM Uplink is present and feature is active. Only takes effect if p0ClpcExGoodEnabled attribute is true.

Parameter Description:
SINR offset of p0ClpcExGoodSinrThr for 256-QAM-capable UEs.

Increases SINR threshold for identifying extreme good point users for 256-QAM. Used for maintaining maximum throughput for 256-QAM.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UL SINR distribution and UL throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for 256-QAM Uplink is present and feature is active. Only takes effect if p0ClpcExGoodEnabled attribute is true.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of layers for DMRS-Based Downlink Multi-User MIMO feature.

Value corresponds to maximum number of co-scheduled layers. Value 0 means that DMRS-Based Downlink Multi-User MIMO feature is not enabled.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for DMRS-Based Downlink Multi-User MIMO is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
SINR threshold for DMRS based downlink MU-MIMO user selection.

Candidates below this threshold are filtered out from the DMRS MU-MIMO candidate list.
Whether AI-powered SRS allocation is enabled in TDD AAS.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when license for LTE AI Powered SRS Allocation for Downlink Multi-User MIMO is present and feature is active.
Only takes effect in TDD cell that uses TDD-enabled AAS-capable radio when EUtranCellTDD::ulSrsEnable is true.
Obsolete: Since 24.Q1. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Whether load management actions are allowed on EN-DC-capable UE.

These load management actions are triggered by load balancing and offloading features.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Basic Intelligent Connectivity is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Whether VoLTE and PTT prescheduling is enabled.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for VoLTE Prescheduling is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Offset for flexible duct interference detection.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when ENodeBFunction::ductIntFlexibleDetectionEnabled is true.

ENodeBFunction::ductIntFlexibleDetectionEnabled can be set to true only when value of EUtranCellTDD::earfcn minus lowest channel number of EUtranCellTDD::freqBand minus EUtranCellTDD::ductIntFlexibleDetectionOffset can be divided by 3.

Specification: 3GPP TS 36.101.

Parameter Description:
Whether Global SCell Evaluation (GSE) is enhanced for coexistence of Intelligent Power Emission Control (IPEC) and Carrier Aggregation.

Enhancement makes GSE to consider IPEC Available PRB values reported by IPEC to optimize SCell selection and re-selection.
Reports with IPEC Available PRB are sent for intra-eNB and inter-eNB cells.
For inter-eNB cells, information is exchanged via X2 message.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when licenses for Intelligent Power Emission Control feature and Global SCell Evaluation feature are present and features are active.
Applicable when PowerBackoff::powerBackoffEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
Whether differentiated maximum PDCCH target BLER is enabled.

If true, pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow and pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh are used instead of optimizedPdcchMaxTargetBler.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if licenses for Optimized PDCCH and Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation are present and features are active.

Cannot be set to true if pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is false.

For usage in subscriber group, see description of attribute SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode.

Parameter Description:
Low maximum value for PDCCH target BLER.

Used when PDCCH SINR is greater than diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerThres.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when both pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled and diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled are true.

Cannot be higher than pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh.

Cannot be lower than pdcchTargetBler.

For usage in subscriber group, see attribute SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode.

Parameter Description:
High maximum value for PDCCH target BLER.

Used when PDCCH SINR is lower than or equal to diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerThres.
Dependencies:
Only applicable when both pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled and diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled are true.

Cannot be lower than pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow.

For usage in subscriber group, see attribute SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode.

Parameter Description: PDCCH congestion condition measurement period.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can effect the total number of below counters: pmPdcchTargetBlerLowRatioDistr, pmPdcchTargetBlerHighRatioDistr, pmPdcchCongestDistr, pmPdcchTargetBlerDistr, pmPrbAvailUtilDlDistr, pmPrbAvailUtilUlDistr.
Dependencies: Only applicable if licenses for Optimized PDCCH and Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation are present and features are active.

Parameter Description:
SINR threshold for differentiated maximum PDCCH target BLER.

If PDCCH SINR is greater than diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerThres, pdcchMaxTargetBlerLow is used as maximum PDCCH target BLER.

Otherwise pdcchMaxTargetBlerHigh is used.
Dependencies: Only applicable when both pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled and diffPdcchMaxTargetBlerEnabled are true.

Parameter Description: Whether dual-layer MU MIMO is enabled to UEs without antenna switch.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Dual-Layer Downlink Multi-User MIMO is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Defines negative offset to pZeroNominalPusch in Optimized Power Splitting for Uplink Carrier Aggregation feature enhancement.

Value 255 means Optimized Power Splitting for Uplink Carrier Aggregation feature enhancement is turned off, and other value means this feature enhancement is activated.

For uplink 64-QAM or 256-QAM, this attribute is used to define negative offset to pZeroNominalPusch, and PUSCH power offset range is changed to [-pZeroOffsetUlCa, puschPwrOffset64qam] or [-pZeroOffsetUlCa, puschPwrOffset256qam] respectively. For other modulation, there is no impact on pZeroNominalPusch.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for indicating whether subscription ratio of cell is high.

If subscription ratio is greater than or equal to this threshold, cell is considered to be in high load.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can prevent new traffic from being setup.

Parameter Description: PDCCH CCE utilization threshold for Optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when EUtranCellTDD::pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true or SubscriberGroupProfile::pdcchFlexibleBlerMode is ENABLED.

Parameter Description:
Threshold for unregistering cell for inter-cell UE preemption.

Expressed in number of preemptable UEs in cell. If configured with value 0, cell is manually unregistered from inter-cell UE preemption.

Hysteresis for calculation of threshold for registering cell for inter-cell UE preemption.

Expressed in number of preemptable UEs in cell. Threshold for registering cell for inter-cell UE preemption is calculated with formula peUeToInterCellPreThrUnreg + peUeToInterCellPreHyst.
Whether B1 measurement with gap is enabled for EN-DC-capable UEs.
Whether TM8-based MU-MIMO is enabled on TDD AAS SCell.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for DMRS-Based Downlink Multi-User MIMO is present and feature is active.
Only takes effect if dlMaxDmrsMuMimoLayers is greater than 0, tm8SCellAllowed is true, and caOffloadDlSCellTddAas is false.

Parameter Description:
Maximum distance from base station where random access from UE can be admitted.

Random access preambles detected out of this range are discarded.
Lowering the value reduces the service range for admitting connection setup from UE.
Value 0 means raRange does not take effect.
Dependencies: Must be smaller than or equal to cellRange * 1000.

Parameter Description:
Maximum random access observability range.

Timing offset of random access preamble can be correctly calculated if UE is in random access observability range.

Percentage of total number of UE context to be reserved per cell for Privileged Access.

Value 0 removes reservation of UE context per cell for Privileged Access.

Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Whether looping EN-DC protection is enabled in cell.

Looping ED-DC protection blocks failed NR frequency for EN-DC setup, when EN-DC setup is consecutively failed by RLF within short session time.

Shows when blocked NR frequency is backed off, after a certain NR frequency is blocked.

Special value 0 means infinity.
Whether RLF detected EN-DC setup failure is regarded as short SCG session.

Whether NR frequency is blocked to protect EN-DC setup based on this threshold.

Note: Consecutive failure is counted only when EN-DC setup is failed by RLF within short SCG session.
Whether to enable PDCCH congestion control parameters for optimized PDCCH.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
One of PDCCH congestion control parameters, for PDCCH outer loop adjustment.

Used during PDCCH congestion and equivalent to EUtranCellTDD::pdcchOuterLoopInitialAdj which is used when there is no PDCCH congestion.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchCongCtrlParamEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
One of PDCCH congestion control parameters, for PCell PDCCH outer loop adjustment.

Used during PDCCH congestion and equivalent to EUtranCellTDD::pdcchOuterLoopInitialAdjPCell which is used when there is no PDCCH congestion.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchCongCtrlParamEnabled is true.

Parameter Description:
One of PDCCH congestion control parameters, for PDCCH power boost.

Used during PDCCH congestion and equivalent to EUtranCellTDD::pdcchPowerBoostMax which is used when there is no PDCCH congestion.
Dependencies:
Only takes effect when pdcchCongCtrlParamEnabled is true.

Cannot be higher than pdcchPowerBoostMax.

Parameter Description: PDCCH target BLER adjustment step size.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when pdcchFlexibleBlerEnabled is true.

Parameter Description: SINR threshold for Intra-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Uplink Coordinated Multi-Point Reception is present and feature is active. Must be used together with ulCompUserSelSinrHys.

Parameter Description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for Intra-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
Dependencies: Only applicable when license for Uplink Coordinated Multi-Point Reception is present and feature is active. Must be used together with ulCompUserSelSinrThr.

Parameter Description: Whether downlink SRS MU-MIMO strict pairing is enabled.

Whether downlink SRS MU-MIMO link adaptation enhancement is enabled.

The enhancement takes inter-layer interference into consideration.

Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
Deprecated: Since 25.Q2. Replaced by interFreqHoHigherPrioSpid. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Whether adjustment of interaction with MIMO Sleep Mode is enabled.

When enabled, AI Powered Advanced Cell Supervision suppresses alarms and recovery actions for sleeping cell detections while MIMO Sleep Mode is activated and takes effect.

Reference to an instance of EndcDistrProfile MO.

If empty, Optimized UE Distribution for EN-DC is not active in cell.

Active symbol positions where duct interference reduction is suppressed.

Defines a range of OFDM symbols starting from first symbol of Uplink Part of Time Slot (UpPTS). For symbols in those positions, detected duct interference characteristic sequences are ignored for reduction operation.
Dependencies: Only relevant if ductIntOpMode is REDUCTION.

Parameter Description:
CRS muting mode in Downlink Part of Time Slot (DwPTS) PDSCH region of special subframe.

Only supports TDD uplink-downlink configuration 2, specified in 3GPP TS 36.211.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if license for Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.
Only applicable if subframeAssignment is 2.
Only relevant if ductIntOpMode is REDUCTION.

Parameter Description: Control of Uplink-Traffic-Triggered Mobility feature for EN-DC-capable UEs.
Whether LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority is enabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute for more frequent A5 measurement report can affect UE battery consumption and user throughput.
Dependencies: Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority is present and the feature is active.

Parameter Description:
Min intensity limit of RRCConnectionRequest messages for Load-Based Access Barring for each cell.

Minimum intensity limit is number of RRCConnectionRequest messages every second multipled by 10. Default value 50 corresponds to 5 RRCConnectionRequest messages every second.
If number of RRCConnectionRequest messages for the duration of last EUtranCellFDD.lbabPeriod or EUtranCellTDD.lbabPeriod is lower than or equal to minimum intensity limit, barring probability is decreased.
If number of RRCConnectionRequest messages for the duration of last EUtranCellFDD.lbabPeriod or EUtranCellTDD.lbabPeriod is higher than minimum intensity limit, it can contribute to barring probability increase.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring feature is activated.

Parameter Description: Controls how Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility feature is enabled.

Window length of subframe.

Used for monitoring potential packet loss related to Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

High threshold for potential packet loss related to Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

When dlVolteCovMobThrLow is bigger than or equal to dlVolteCovMobThrHigh, dlVolteCovMobThrHigh does not take effect, only dlVolteCovMobThrLow is used.

Low threshold for potential packet loss related to Downlink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility.

When dlVolteCovMobThrLow is bigger than or equal to dlVolteCovMobThrHigh, dlVolteCovMobThrHigh does not take effect, only dlVolteCovMobThrLow is used.

AI-powered SRS allocation strategy in TDD AAS.

Only applicable when license for LTE AI Powered SRS Allocation for Downlink Multi-User MIMO is present and feature is active.
Dependencies: If EVENT_TRIGGER or RECURRENT, ulSrsEnable must be true.

Parameter Description:
Controls if ECGI measurements can be requested prior to Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility handover.

Used only if a PCI conflict is detected and AnrFunction::pciConflictMobilityEcgiMeas is set to true.

Only applicable if license for Uplink-Triggered VoLTE Mobility is present and feature is active.

Threshold for uplink data volume per LCG in BSR, monitored by buffer-based EN-DC setup.

If the value is 0, UL buffer-based EN-DC setup is disabled.

Buffer monitoring restarts at target cell regardless of high buffer status in source cell.

If false, buffer monitoring is initiated based on high buffer status in source node.
Whether NR measurement report is blocked or not during LTE handover.

Whether decoupled PDCCH OLA and LA between uplink and downlink is enabled.

If 1, PDCCH outer loop adjustment (OLA) and PDCCH link adaptation (LA) between uplink and downlink is implemented separately.

Only applicable if license for LTE Decoupled Downlink and Uplink PDCCH Link Adaptation is present and feature is active.

Threshold for uplink and downlink DTX rate judgment.

When cell uplink is worse and difference between cell uplink DTX rate and downlink DTX rate exceeds this threshold, stop uplink Harq feedback to trigger uplink PDCCH OLA and use downlink PDCCH OLA as uplink PDCCH OLA.

Whether release of NR leg for EN-DC-connected UE triggers LTE inter-frequency handover.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.

Whether Connection Reestablishment triggers LTE inter-frequency handover.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.

References to instances of QciProfilePredefined or QciProfileOperatorDefined MO.

List of QCIs triggering the LTE Service-Triggered Outgoing NR IRAT Mobility action.

If non-empty, only service-triggered mobility to NR frequencies is allowed.

Only applicable if license for LTE Service-Triggered Outgoing NR IRAT Mobility is present and feature is active.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. It can decrease mobility to NR frequencies and block coverage-triggered mobility to NR frequencies.

Parameter Description:
Whether detection of uplink-heavy UE for load balancing is enabled.

UEs marked as uplink-heavy are excluded from load balancing mobility.

Transmit power of PDCCH to be boosted for RA Msg2 transmissions excluding Cat-M access.

Higher value implies less CCEs available for other UE to allocate.
Lower value implies more CCEs available for other UE to allocate.

If 0, PDCCH power is not boosted for Msg2.

Only applicable when random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled. See description of pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr.

Transmit power of PDSCH to be boosted for RA Msg2 transmissions excluding Cat-M access.

Higher value implies less downlink PRBs available for other UE to allocate.
Lower value implies more downlink PRBs available for other UE to allocate.

If 0, PDSCH power is not boosted for Msg2.

Only applicable when random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled. See description of pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr.

Timing advance threshold for RA Msg2 power boost excluding Cat-M access.

Random access Msg2 power boost function is active when timing advance of UE is greater than or equal to the threshold.

It can be active only within distance defined by raRange or cellRange.
Distance from attaching UE to eNodeB is approximately Timing Advance (TA) value * 78.125 meters.
If raRange is defined (value not equal to 0), then Random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled if pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr * 78.125 is smaller than raRange value.
if raRange is undefined (value equal to 0), then Random access Msg2 power boost function is enabled if pwrBoostRaMsg2TaThr * 78.125 is smaller than cellRange * 1000.

If 65535, Random access Msg2 power boost function is disabled.

Only applicable if license for LTE Flexible Power Boost for Initial Access is present and feature is active.

Whether LTE inter-frequency handover is triggered for EN-DC-connected UEs.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.
Minimum time length for which eNodeB recommends a bit rate index to UE when bit rate increases.
Dependencies: Must be greater than or equal to EUtranCellTDD::bitRateDownRecommTimer.

Parameter Description: Minimum time length for which eNodeB recommends a bit rate index to UE when bit rate decreases.
Dependencies: Must be less than or equal to EUtranCellTDD::bitRateUpRecommTimer.

Parameter Description:
Whether enhanced VoLTE Rate Recommendation is enabled.

Only applicable if licenses for both following features are present and features are active:
- VoLTE Rate Recommendation.
- Robust Header Compression.

Whether frequency selection for UE with SPID profile is defined on SPID-specific level.

Only applicable if license for LTE Inter-Frequency Handover to Higher Priority feature is present and feature is active.

Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions.

Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Power scaling mode in uplink carrier aggregation.

Value 0 means that power scaling is disabled and PRB resource is allocated conservatively.
Value 1 means that power scaling is enabled and PRB resource is allocated moderately.
Value 2 means that power scaling is enabled and PRB resource is allocated aggressively.

Only applicable if license for Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Fallback policy in uplink carrier aggregation.

Value 0 means fallback to component carrier with higher SINR.
Value 1 means fallback to component carrier with higher estimated transmission capability.
Value 2 means fallback to PCell.

Only applicable if license for Uplink Carrier Aggregation is present and feature is active.

Maximum allowed number of paging records for cell.

Allowed maximum number of UE that can be paged per paging occasion.

If not 0, overrides Paging::maxNoOfPagingRecords.
Dependencies: Cannot be larger than 7 if channelBandwidth is 5000.

Parameter Description: The downlink channel bandwidth in a cell that is served by a neighboring RBS. In TDD mode, the uplink bandwidth is equal to the downlink bandwidth. The attribute is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure. The value 0 means there is no valid value available.
Refers to the EUTRAN frequency MO, EUtranFrequency. Cannot be changed as long as this MO is referred to by a EUtranCellRelation MO.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
RBS internal ID attribute for the ExternalEUtranCellTDD. Must be unique in the RBS. Together with the Node ID and PLMN ID this is a globally unique eUTRAN Cell ID (ECGI).
The physical-layer cell identity group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.
The physical-layer cell identity group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.
Lists the EUtranCellRelation managed object instances that reserve this managed object instance.
Dependencies: The managed object cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

Parameter Description: Identifies a Tracking Area Code (TAC) of an external cell.
Label for free use.

Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.
The ID of the EUtranCellTDD that this MO represents for automatically created ExternalEUtranCellTDD managed objects.

Lists the PLMN IDs in the external E-UTRAN cell. The list may include up to 6 PLMN IDs. The list tracks the activePlmnList in the corresponding instance of EUtranCellFDD/TDD in another RBS. It is configured by ANR when ANR feature creates the MO and then set to the PLMN Id from the CGI report. The list is updated via X2 or OSS-RC, or manually.
Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2

Indicates the time and date when the MO was created.
Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2 and if the MO is to be deleted who triggered the deletion
Range and Values:
ANR_MODIFICATION
X2_MODIFICATION
OPERATOR_MODIFICATION
ANR_DELETE
X2_DELETE
OPERATOR_DELETE
NOT_MODIFIED
MRO_MODIFICATION
PCI_MODIFICATION
MLB_MODIFICATION
RACH_OPT_MODIFICATION
LM_MODIFICATION

Parameter Description:
Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified.
Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

A PCI confusion exists if a source cell has relations to two neighbor cells where both neighbor cells have the same PCI and frequency. A PCI collision exists if a source cell has a relation to a neighbor cell where both the source cell and neighbor cell have the same PCI and frequency.
Indicates the CGI of the other cell that is involved in the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL".

Indicates the CGI of the cell that detected the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the corresponding attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL". The first cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the first cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict. The second cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the second cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict.

The active MBMS Service Area Identity of an external cell.
This attribute indicates the offload subscription capacity associated with the EUTRAN target cell. The value is used to moderate the offload rate to the EUTRAN target cell.

A list of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to, not including the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the cell (primary frequency band). The list is automatically set by the eNB.
The primary frequency band the cell belongs to according to its defined EARFCN. This frequency band indicator is broadcasted to the UEs in SystemInformationBlockType1.

The assignment of uplink and downlink subframes for the TDD frame structure (called UL/DL configuration in 3GPP TS 36.211). The parameter is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure.
Undefined value: -1
Reflects whether the indicated cell is currently able to serve as an SCell. The remote cell must be operState ENABLED and adminState UNLOCKED.
Dependencies: Depends on X2 connection being operational and software compatibility.

Parameter Description: Whether indicated cell can serve as external cell for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP.
Dependencies: X2 connection must be operational and software compatible. Remote cell must be operState ENABLED and adminState UNLOCKED.

Parameter Description: Shows the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.
Physical-layer cell ID.
Dependencies: Equal to 3 x physicalLayerCellIdGroup + physicalLayerSubCellId.

Parameter Description:
The special subframe pattern configuration for Downlink Part of Time Slot (DwPTS), Guard Period (GP), and Uplink Part of Time Slot (UpPTS) (used to control special subframe in 3GPP TS 36.211). The parameter is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure.
Undefined value: -1
Whether indicated cell can serve as external cell for Elastic RAN UL CoMP.
Dependencies: X2 connection must be operational and software compatible. Remote cell must be operState ENABLED and adminState UNLOCKED.
Deprecated: Since 20.Q2. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Indicates if external cell supports additional frequency band priority. Used during handover procedure.

Undefined value: UNDEFINED_VALUE
Dependencies: Only takes effect if MFBI is active.

Parameter Description: High load indication that affects Carrier Aggregation (CA) traffic (SCell).
Dependencies: Only used when EUtranCellFDD / EUtranCellTDD::loadBasedCaEnabled=true.

Parameter Description: Whether PLMN IDs on ExternalEUtranCellTDD MO are verified. Verification method is by X2 Setup or by CGI.
PLMN ID allowed to use EN-DC. If empty, EN-DC is not allowed in external E-UTRAN cell. List is automatically set when information is received over X2.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of managed object instances that reserves this managed object instance.
Dependencies: The MO may not be deleted if it is reserved.

Parameter Description: Label for free use
The value component of the (Relative Distinguished Name) RDN

Minimal load level associated with downlink Physical Resource Block (PRB) use.

Parameter Description: Contains the attributes required to configure a traffic model pattern to  use for filling the Physical Resource Blocks (PRBs).

The pattern for generated artificial load changes periodically after each  ailgChangePeriod. The period applies to both PDSCH and PDCCH artificial load.
Within each period the same load pattern in terms of positions of PDSCH PRBs and/or PDCCH CCEs within the available bandwidth is used.

Minimum load level for PDCCH in terms of utilization of the available Control Channel Elements (CCE). If the PDCCH load from real UE is below this level, lower priority artificial load is generated to reach this minimum load level.

The value "0" means that no minimum load level is defined.
Decides the type of load to be generated by means of different combinations of PDSCH load, Beam Forming (BF) and PDCCH load.
Range and Values:
PDSCH_NO_BF
PDSCH_BF_TYPE1
PDSCH_NO_BF_AND_PDCCH
PDSCH_BF_TYPE1_AND_PDCCH
PDSCH_BF_TYPE2
PDSCH_BF_TYPE2_AND_PDCCH
PDCCH_ONLY

This parameter together with a5Threshold1Rsrp specifies "The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold1 value for eventA5." . The eNodeB interprets Allocation Retention Priority (ARP) levels, received from the Core Network, between 1 and paArpOverride (inclusive) as Privileged Access.

Dependencies: Must be equal to or larger than values of paArpOverrideHpa and paArpOverrideEc.

Parameter Description:
Activates or deactivates the Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) based pre-emption function.
The value of the attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the Differentiated Admission Control feature.

Activates or deactivates the Resource Reservation for Privileged Access.

Not applicable for Enhanced UE Preemption for Privileged Access.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can impact accessibility at high load.

Unit: 0.001
Deprecated: Since 19.Q3. Replaced by ulNonPaGbrTn. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Sets wanted downlink resource use ratio of MBMS-GBR bearers on transport network. Given parameter value specifies MBMS-GBR part of total bandwidth. Parameter is used by Admission Control to balance GBR, MBMS-GBR, and non-GBR use of resources. Downlink transport network bandwidth for LTE needs to be configured into AdmissionControl::dlTransNwBandwidth.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in DU Radio Node.

Parameter Description: Sets the resource reservation used for ARP based differentiation. The value of this attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the Differentiated Admission Control feature.

Sets the highest allowed downlink radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a GBR radio bearer. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, re-established or incoming handover GBR bearer requests.
Dependencies: dlAdmOverloadThr>=dlAdmDifferentiationThr

Parameter Description: Sets the highest allowed uplink radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a GBR radio bearer. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, re-established or incoming handover GBR bearer requests.
Dependencies: ulAdmOverloadThr>=ulAdmDifferentiationThr

Parameter Description:
If both Dynamic GBR Admission Control and Differentiated Admission Control are licensed and activated:

Sets the highest allowed downlink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers with lower ARP priority in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.

If Dynamic GBR Admission Control is licensed and activated but Differentiated Admission Control is not licensed or not activated:

Sets the highest allowed downlink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.
Dependencies: dlAdmDifferentiationThr<=dlAdmOverloadThr

Parameter Description:
If both Dynamic GBR Admission Control and Differentiated Admission Control are licensed and activated:

Sets the highest allowed uplink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers with lower ARP priority in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.

If Dynamic GBR Admission Control is licensed and activated but Differentiated Admission Control is not licensed or not activated:

Sets the highest allowed uplink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.
Dependencies: ulAdmDifferentiationThr<=ulAdmOverloadThr

Parameter Description: Highest allowed fraction of non-privileged RRC connections that might be admitted without ARP based differentiation. When fraction of RRC connected users versus available capacity exceeds this threshold, only RRC connections that setup bearers with high ARP priority are admitted. Other RRC connections may only be admitted if preemption is possible. The fraction is given with respect to the maximum capacity after privileged access resource reservation has been subtracted.

Highest allowed fraction of radio bearers not reserved for privileged access connections that might be admitted without ARP based differentiation. When fraction of active radio bearers versus available capacity exceeds this threshold, only bearer requests with high ARP priority are admitted. Other bearer requests may only be admitted if preemption is possible. The fraction is given with respect to the maximum capacity after privileged access resource reservation has been subtracted.
Number of privileged access connections to be reserved per cell.
Dependencies:
Applicable only if resourceReservationForPAState is set to ACTIVATED.
nrOfPaConnReservationsPerCell >= nrOfPaConnHpaReservPerCell.

Parameter Description: Number of Radio Bearers to be reserved per privileged access connection. This includes SRB1, SRB2 and DRBs.
Dependencies: Applicable only if resourceReservationForPAState is set to ACTIVATED.
Deprecated: Since 23.Q4. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Lowest QCI priority (highest numerical value) for DRBs included into monitoring of radio resources considered in GBR bearer admission control.
For any value of this parameter, bearer admission control also takes into account resource usage from non-DRB traffic with higher priority than DRBs, e.g. Signaling Radio Bearers. If this parameter is set to 0, only the resource usage for traffic with priority higher than DRBs is monitored.

Enables filtering profiles for additional level of Differentiated Admission Control on eNodeB level.
When enabled, parameters in MO DiffAdmCtrlFilteringProfile take effect.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Parameter Description: Number of PA Signaling Radio Bearers that can be allocated in preventive preemption pool.
Dependencies: If feature Privileged Access Admission Balancing is activated, only PA Signaling Radio Bearers setup with establishment cause High Priority Access can be allocated in preventive preemption pool.

Parameter Description: Indicates if Scheduling Request (SR) resources preallocation for privileged access connections is activated in eNodeB.
Number of Scheduling Request resources in limitation pool for privileged access connections per cell.
Dependencies:
Threshold for allocation of an additional PUCCH format 1 PRB pair by dynamic PUCCH must be higher than number of resources in limitation pool.
(EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::allocThrPucchFormat1 > limitSrNonPa)

Parameter Description: Number of High Priority Access connections to be reserved for each cell.
Dependencies:
Can be used by Enhanced UE Preemption for Privileged Access regardless of resourceReservationForPAState. For other cases, applicable only if resourceReservationForPAState is set to ACTIVATED.
nrOfPaConnHpaReservPerCell <= nrOfPaConnReservationsPerCell.

Parameter Description:
The eNodeB interprets Allocation Retention Priority (ARP) Levels, received from Core Network, between 1 and paArpOverrideHpa (inclusive) as High Priority Access if paArpOverrideEc is -1.

If 0, High Priority Access ARP override is disabled if paArpOverrideEc is -1.
If paArpOverrideEc is not -1, paArpOverrideHpa is not used to identify High Priority Access. Instead, ARP levels, received from Core Network, between 1 and paArpOverride, excluding value of paArpOverrideEc, are interpreted as High Priority Access.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can impact High Priority Access accessibility at high load.
Dependencies: Must be equal to or lower than value of paArpOverride.

Parameter Description: Sets wanted downlink resource utilization ratio of Non-PA GBR bearers, for example for Mobile Broadband users, on transport network. Value specifies threshold in per mille for accumulated GBR values of all admitted Non-PA GBR bearers. Used by Admission Control to balance PA and non-PA GBR use of resources. Downlink transport network bandwidth for LTE must be configured into dlTransNwBandwidth.

Sets wanted uplink resource utilization ratio of Non-PA GBR bearers, for example for Mobile Broadband users, on transport network. Value specifies threshold in per mille for accumulated GBR values of all admitted Non-PA GBR bearers. Used by Admission Control to balance PA and non-PA GBR use of resources. Uplink transport network bandwidth for LTE must be configured into ulTransNwBandwidth.

Inactivity time when UE is eligible for early UE preemption before release. Release occurs when there is resource shortage on UE or bearer level for non-GBR E-RABs.
UE is not eligible for early UE preemption if value is greater than or equal to tInactivityTimer, including highest QCI offset if used.

86400 s = 24 hours.

Parameter Description:
Enables the rejection of PA GBR bearer requests above the overload threshold.

Parameter is valid only if Enhanced PTT admission Control, Differentiated Admission Control and Dynamic GBR Admission Control are activated.
Time value per cell defining recalculation periods for inter-cell UE preemption.

The eNodeB interprets Allocation Retention Priority equal to paArpOverrideEc as Emergency Call.

With this attribute, it is possible to configure a higher priority (lower value) for Allocation Retention Priority (ARP) of Emergency Call than ARP of High Priority Access.

If -1, paArpOverrideEc is not used to identify Emergency Call. Instead, ARP levels, received from Core Network, between paArpOverrideHpa (exclusive) and paArpOverride are interpreted as Emergency Call.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can impact accessibility at high load.
Dependencies: Must be equal to or lower than value of paArpOverride.

Label for free use.
Reference to the UTRAN frequency MO, UtranFrequency.

CellReselectionPriority concerns the absolute priority of the concerned carrier frequency, as used by the cell reselection procedure. Corresponds with parameter "priority" in TS 36.304.

Value 0 means lowest priority. The UE behaviour for the case the field is absent, if applicable, is specified in TS 36.304.
Dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

Parameter Description: This specifies the threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards the higher priority frequency X than current serving frequency. Each frequency of UTRAN might have a specific threshold. Parameter "Threshx,high" in TS 36.304

This specifies the threshold used in reselection towards frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency. Each frequency of UTRAN might have a specific threshold. Parameter "Threshx,low" in TS 36.304.
Parameter Qrxlevmin, see TS 25.304. Specifies the minimum required Rx level in the cell expressed in dBm.
The maximum allowed transmission power on the (uplink) carrier frequency, see TS 25.304.

List of all Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) IDs allowed for this frequency relation.

A UE that does not support one of the IDs included in the allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency, according to the UE Handover Restriction List.

No values in allowedPlmnList imply that the frequency has no restrictions for PLMN.

The PLMN ID contains the following parts:
1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits
2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)

For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

Prioritizes UTRA frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
(0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)

Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to which frequency/frequency group to make CS Fallback to.
The value -1 means the frequency is excluded.
The value 0 means the lowest priority.
The value 7 means the highest priority.

Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies for emergency calls among all frequencies/frequency groups related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to which frequency to make emergency call CS Fallback to.
The value -1 means the frequency is excluded.
The value 0 means the lowest priority.
The value 7 means the highest priority.
Indicates a frequency-specific offset to apply when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.
The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN TDD frequency in case of coverage triggered mobility.
The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN TDD frequency in case of CS Fallback mobility.
ANR performs measurement on the referenced frequency if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, ANR does not perform any measurements on this frequency.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

The mchSchedulingPeriod in the MO class PmchMch must be
smaller than or equal to mcchModificationPeriod.
Precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

Parameter Description: Indicates the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) applicable for the subframes indicated by the field sf-AllocInfo and for the first subframe of each MCH scheduling period (which may contain the MCH scheduling information provided by MAC). Precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

Parameter Description: Specifies the period during which resources corresponding with field commonSFAlloc are divided between the (P)MCH that are configured for this MBSFN area. The subframe allocation patterns, as defined by commonSFAlloc, repeat continuously during this period. Value 4 corresponds to 4 radio frames, 8 corresponds to 8 radio frames and so on.
Dependencies:
The mchSchedulingPeriod in the MO class PmchMch must be
a multiple of commonSFAllocPeriod.
Precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

Must not be changed when MbsfnArea is unlocked.

If Autoconfiguration of LTE Broadcast Subframes is used, new values are set by system every time subframe allocation changes for (P)MCH. If value is -1, no subframe is allocated.

Specifies the value for parameter I-MCS in TS 36.213, Table 7.1.7.1-1, which defines the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) applicable for the subframes of this (P)MCH as indicated by the field commonSF-Alloc. The MCS does however neither apply to the subframes that may carry MCCH i.e. the subframes indicated by the field sf-AllocInfo within SystemInformationBlockType13 nor for the first subframe of each MCH scheduling period (which may contain the MCH scheduling information provided by MAC).

MCH scheduling period. Used to provide MCH scheduling information at applicable lower layers (MAC). Value 8 sets 8 radio frames, 16 sets 16 radio frames and so on.
Values 512 and 1024 cannot be used.
Dependencies:
mchSchedulingPeriod must be:
- a multiple of commonSFAllocPeriod in MO class MbsfnArea.
- smaller than or equal to mcchRepetitionPeriod in MO class MbsfnArea.

synchPeriodLength in MO class Mbms must be a multiple of mchSchedulingPeriod * 10 ms.

Parameter Description: Offset to obtain the Hysteresis for inter-frequency A3 measurement for trigger quantity RSRQ. hysteresisA3Rsrq = hysteresisA3 + hysteresisA3RsrqOffset
Dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

Parameter Description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold value for events A1Search and A2Search.
If Multi-Layer Service Triggered Mobility feature is enabled QCI offsets in QciProfilePredefined configuration is overridden by this feature QCI configuration.

The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold value for events A1Search and A2Search.
If Multi-Layer Service Triggered Mobility feature is enabled QCI offsets in QciProfilePredefined configuration is overridden by this feature QCI configuration.
The hysteresis value for RSRP in events A1Search and A2Search measurements.
The hysteresis value for RSRQ in events A1Search and A2Search measurements.
Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A1Search. If timeToTriggerA1SearchRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.
Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Search. If timeToTriggerA2SearchRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.
The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold value for event A2Critical.
The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold value for event A2Critical.
The hysteresis value for RSRP in event A2Critical measurement.
The hysteresis value for RSRQ in event A2Critical measurement.

Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Critical. If timeToTriggerA2CriticalRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.
Parameters for adding QCI profile specific offsets to threshold values for events A1Search and A2Search used for mobility decisions. Applicable if Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility is active.
Offset for threshold a1a2SearchThresholdRsrp to configure RSRP threshold value for events A2OuterSearch.

Offset for threshold a1a2SearchThresholdRsrq to configure RSRQ threshold value for events A2OuterSearch. Note: RSRQ thresholds are configured in 0.5dB steps according to 3GPP TS36.331. Use multiples of 5 for this attribute. Other values are rounded down to the closest lower multiple of 5.
Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A1Search with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.
Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Critical with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.
Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Search with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.

Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2OuterSearch. If timeToTriggerA2OutSearchRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.
Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2OuterSearch with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.
Hysteresis value for RSRP in events A2OuterSearch measurements.
Hysteresis value for RSRQ in events A2OuterSearch measurements.
QCI1 offset (used also for QCIs with serviceType PTT or MC_SIGNALING) on cell level for threshold a2CriticalThresholdRsrp and RSRP threshold value for events A2Critical.

QCI1 offset (used also for QCIs with serviceType PTT or MC_SIGNALING) on cell level for threshold a2CriticalThresholdRsrq and RSRQ threshold value for events A2Critical.

RSRQ thresholds are configured in 0.5 dB steps according to 3GPP TS36.331. Use multiples of 5 for this attribute. Other values are rounded down to closest lower multiple of 5.
Inhibit type of A2Search Report configuration.

Disturbances: Change can affect traffic

Parameter Description: Reference to an instance of SectorEquipmentFunction MO.
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Number of antennas that SectorCarrier uses for UL transmission.
If SectorCarriers have different number of RX antennas, set it to number of RX antennas SectorCarrier uses.
If set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of RX antennas are deactivated, SectorCarrier uses two RX branches.
If set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of RX antennas are activated, SectorCarrier uses maximum number of RX antennas defined by operable features.
Set to zero for sectors equipped with AAS capable radio units. System decides optimal number of receive branches to use.
Dependencies: Dependent on optional features and configured radio that enable using multiple Rx antennas.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description:
Number of antennas SectorCarrier uses for DL transmission.
If SectorCarriers have different number of TX antennas in the node, set to the number of TX antennas SectorCarrier uses.
If set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of TX antennas are deactivated, SectorCarrier uses one TX branch.
If set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of TX antennas are activated, SectorCarrier uses maximum number of TX antennas defined by operable features.
Set to zero for sectors equipped with AAS capable radio units. System decides optimal number of transmit branches to use.
Dependencies: Dependent on optional features and configured radio that enable using multiple Tx antennas.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description:
Number of used receive antennas.

Maximum number is determined by noOfRxAntennas.
Value 0 indicates that no Rx antennas are used.
Value -1 means undefined.

Number of used transmit antennas.

Maximum number is determined by noOfTxAntennas.
Value -1 means undefined.

Maximum possible power at the antenna reference point, for all downlink channels in all TX branches used simultaneously in the SectorCarrier.

-1 is used as an undefined value.

Note: Setting SectorCarrier::configuredMaxTxPower has an impact on this attribute. See Radio Network Configuration user guide 11/1553-HSC 105 50/1.
Note: Setting RfBranch::dlAttenuation has an impact on this attribute.

If true, the Positioning Reference Signal is sent from this sector carrier.
1: For indoor antennas at the same location, if the sector carriers are isolated, set prsEnabled to true for all sector carriers. Transmission of PDSCH on the PRS subframe is not scheduled.
2: For combined macro and pico sector carriers, set prsEnabled to true for the macro sector only. The other sector or sectors have prsEnabled = false. However, transmission of PDSCH is still not scheduled on the same subframe to prevent undesirable interferences.
Note: To reclaim PRS subframe for PDSCH transmission, OTDOA Supl license state must be set to DISABLED.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description: Contains references to RF branches or MultCastAntenna branches whose RF ports are to be used for RX carrier allocations for this particular SectorCarrier. This is used only for deterministic carrier allocation. Values are taken into consideration if noOfRxAntennas > 0. If no reference is specified, carrier allocation is based on RF branch MOM list (default behavior).
Dependencies:
If non-empty, number of references must be equal to noOfRxAntennas.
List must contain only RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch MO instances, but not both.
All references in both rfBranchTxRef and rfBranchRxRef must refer to either RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch MO instances.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description: Contains references to RF branches or MultCastAntenna branches whose RF ports are to be used for TX carrier allocations for this particular SectorCarrier. This is used only for deterministic carrier allocation. Values are taken into consideration if noOfTxAntennas > 0. If no reference is specified, carrier allocation is based on TF branch MOM list (default behavior).
Dependencies:
If non-empty, number of references must be equal to noOfTxAntennas.
List must contain only RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch MO instances, but not both.
All references in both rfBranchTxRef and rfBranchRxRef must refer to either RfBranch or MulticastAntennaBranch MO instances.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description: Forced additional value for Timing Advance Command in Random Access Response according to 3GPP TS 36.213.
Number of muted Tx antennas related to MIMO Sleep Mode feature.
A desired radio transmit operating mode, which is tailored to achieve good throughput performance for a given highest modulation in downlink.
Deprecated: Since 20.Q1. Replaced by radioTransmitPerfMode. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Maximum output power to be used in a SectorCarrier. The output power is evenly distributed over antenna connectors used for TX transmission allocated for the SectorCarrier.

To prevent the cell from transmitting, it must be locked.

Parameter Description:
Whether or not sector carrier is virtual sector, modelled by MO SectorCarrier.
Sector carriers can have different sector carrier shapes by using custom channel beamforming weights, so called "virtual sector".
Virtual sector cannot carrier aggregate with other virtual sectors in same sector.
Dependencies: If true, then virtualComChBeamfrmWtsAmplitude must be valid.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description: Array of eight amplitudes for common channel beamforming weights of virtual sector. One of eight amplitudes must be non-zero for beamforming weights to take effect. Actual value = Set value / 100.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description: Array of eight phases for common channel beamforming weights of virtual sector.
Precondition: Value can only be changed when cell has administrativeState LOCKED, operationalState DISABLED, and availabilityStatus OFFLINE.

Parameter Description:
Digitally-controlled tilt through beamforming.

Positive value gives downwards tilt and negative value gives upwards tilt.

Only MACRO, MACRO_2LOBE, MACRO_NARROW and MACRO_WIDE sector shapes are affected. Select a value supported by installed radio equipment. Refer to CPI for installed radio equipment for supported values.

If empty, or unsupported for the configuration, the system selects a value within the supported range.

Attribute usedDigitalTilt shows digital tilt in use.
Dependencies: Only takes effect for AAS radios with digital tilt functionality.

Parameter Description:
Antenna calibration configuration mode for TDD AAS DL.

0: Guard-period based antenna calibration. DL antenna calibration windows in TDD guard period.

1: Puncturing antenna calibration. DL antenna calibration windows in TDD DL subframes.
Baseband samples are punctured in antenna calibration windows.

antCalModeTddAasDl takes effect only if the radio equipment in the referenced sector supports multiple configuration modes. Refer to CPI for installed radio equipment.

PIM threshold level, relative to the 20W CW. Determines whether to perform PIM mitigative actions on associated sector carrier.

When set to zero and optional feature PIM Mitigation is enabled, PIM Mitigation is deactivated or not performed for carrier branches in this SectorCarrier.
When changed to a non-zero value and optional feature PIM Mitigation is enabled, PIM Mitigation is performed for carrier branches in this SectorCarrier reporting a PIM level equal to, or exceeding the threshold.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause degradation of DL throughput.
Dependencies: Only takes effect if license for PIM Mitigation is present and feature is active.

Parameter Description: Presence indication in SIB8 of Information Element acBarring1xRttMoData

MSC identity in CDMA 1xRTT network
If this 1xRTT cell is referred by EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD, this identifier will be used by eNodeB for tunneling of 1xRTT signaling messages towards this MSC. It has to be configured for LTE CSFB to 1xRTT features since it is used to fill a field in S1AP message sent to MME.

System unique identifier (15bits)
This attribute is used along with the NID as a pair to control when the UE should register or reregister with the CDMA2000 1xRTT network. SID=0 is reserved. It is broadcast on SIB8.
It is also used with CellId, SectorNumber and NID for the 1xRTT cell global identity.

Network unique identifier (16 bits) within a system used along with the SID as a pair to control when the UE should register or reregister with the CDMA2000 1xRTT network.
NID=0 and NID=65535 are reserved.

Cell identifier
If a 1xRTT cell is referred by EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD, this cell/sector attribute in conjunction with marketId and switchNumber shall be used to set the IE CDMA2000 Sector ID in Uplink S1 CDMA2000 tunneling message.

Access Barring parameters for CDMA2000 1xRTT capable UE originating signaling
The information is broadcast in SIB8. This is controlled by the licensing MO CsfbTo1xRtt and acBarring1xRttForMoDataPresent

Information for preregistration to 1xRTT system
The information is broadcast in SIB8. This information, together with the information in mobilityParams1xRttMoData, must be used to build IE in RRC messages: CSFBParametersResponseCDMA2000 and HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest.
This is controlled by the licensing MO CsfbTo1xRtt.

Information for registration/reregistration to 1xRTT system
The information, together with the information in csfbRegParams1xRttMoData, is used to build the IE in RRC messages: CSFBParametersResponseCDMA2000 and HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest.
This is controlled by the licensing MO CsfbTo1xRtt.
Label for free use
Describes the SRVCC capability of the external cell.
Reference to the CDMA2000 frequency band MO, Cdma2000FreqBand
Value component of the RDN
Absolute priority of the RAT (0 means: lowest priority)

Threshold used in reselection towards a high priority CDMA2000 1xRTT band class, expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 dB

If sNonServingCell > threshXHigh1xRtt, reselection is considered towards the band class with higher priority. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdma1xRtt.

sNonServingCell is the RX-level value of a neighboring cell.

Threshold used in reselection towards a low priority CDMA2000 1xRTT band class expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 db.

If sServingCell < threshServingLow and sNeighbor > threshXLow (see corresponding attribute), reselection towards this lower prioritized band class is considered. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdma1xRtt.

sServingCell is the RX level value of the serving cell and sNeighborCell is the RX level value of a neighbor frequency.
Label for free use
Reference to the Cdma2000Freq MO
Value component of the RDN

CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB frequency priority.
This attribute prioritizes CDMA2000 1xRTT frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to which frequency/frequency group to make CS Fallback.
The value 0 means the lowest priority.
The value 7 means the highest priority.

CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency priority for emergency calls
This attribute prioritizes CDMA2000 1xRTT frequencies for emergency calls among all frequencies/frequency groups related to the cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets the priority to which frequency to make emergency call CS Fallback.
The value 0 means the lowest priority.
The value 7 means the highest priority.
Label for free use
Frequency-specific offset to apply when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting

Prioritizes CDMA 1xRtt frequencies among all frequencies related to cell for UEs in connected mode.
Sets priority value for frequency to which mobility action for a voice session is performed. Valid for VoLTE and PTT.
Value -1 means frequency is excluded.
Value 0 means lowest priority.
Value 7 means highest priority.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2Cdma20001xRtt, Signal quality in the thresholdCDMA2000 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.
Reference to an ExternalCdma20001xRttCell
Value component of the RDN

CDMA2000 cell inclusion in system information.
This attribute indicates whether the CDMA2000 cell is included in System Information.
When the value is set to false, the CDMA2000 cell is not included in SIB8.
A maximum of 16 CDMA2000 cells can be included per frequency.
A maximum of 32 CDMA2000 cells can be included in SIB8.
Dependencies: Restriction: The referred cell shall only set one of the attributes (includeInSystemInformation or includeInSystemInformationRel9) to true.

Parameter Description:
CDMA2000 cell inclusion in Release 9 part of system information.
This attribute indicates whether the CDMA2000 cell is included in the Release 9 part of System Information.
When the value is set to false, the CDMA2000 cell is not included in the Release 9 part of SIB8.
A release 8 relation of the same frequency is required for the CDMA2000 cell to be included in the Release 9 part of SIB8.
A total maximum of 40 1xRTT CDMA2000 cells (release 8 and 9 combined) can be included in SIB8.
Dependencies:
Restriction: The referred cell shall only set one of the attributes (includeInSystemInformation or includeInSystemInformationRel9) to true.
Dependencies: In 3GPP rel9, the possibility to add 16 additional CDMA2000 cells on the same frequency, was added. The additional CDMA2000 cells are controlled by the parameter includeInSystemInformationRel9.

The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

The value configures the number of SCell connections which can be in use for carrier aggregation. A secondary cell (SCell) costs in memory the same as a primary cell (PCell) for each UE. It is preferred to avoid limiting SCell connections with caUsageLimit, and use caPreemptionThreshold instead.

Configures resource consumption margin in percentage. This stops configuring new SCells when there is total resource usage on a DU or Basedband.

Total number of connected UEs + total number of configured SCells > Maximum RRC Connected Users * (100 - caPreemptionThreshold ) / 100

Maximum of RRC Connected Users is a DU or Baseband hardware capacity limit which can be found in CPI LTE Supported Capacity and Configurations.

One or more SCells can be activated if minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues of UE is higher than sCellActDeactDataThres.

When deciding the activation of one SCell, minimum time needed to transmit all bits is calculated as the number of bits in all priority queues, divided by the number of bits that can be transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells prior to activation decision. This is computed as though the UE is given all resources in those cells. If the condition for activating one SCell is satisfied, a second SCell is also considered for activation but the minimum time needed to transmit all bits is now calculated by considering the added capacity of the first new SCell that is already considered for activation.

For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms, but for TDD UL/DL subframe configuration 1, there are 6 DL subframes in 10ms, and for UL/DL subframe configuration 2, there are 8 DL subframes in 10ms.

"-1" means the data-triggered activation condition is always satisfied even with no data in the buffer, and also that the data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied.
Dependencies: sCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= sCellActDeactDataThres when sCellActDeactDataThres is not equal to -1

Parameter Description:
If the minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues of a UE is less than or equal to sCellActDeactDataThres minus sCellActDeactDataThresHyst, then deactivation of one component carrier is considered.

Minimum time needed to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by the number of bits that can be transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells after deactivation decision. This is computed as though the UE is given all resources in those cells.

For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms, but for TDD UL/DL subframe configuration 1, there are 6 DL subframes in 10ms, and for UL/DL subframe configuration 2, there are 8 DL subframes in 10ms.

If sCellActDeactDataThres is set to "-1", the data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied and the value of sCellActDeactDataThresHyst is ignored.
Dependencies: sCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= sCellActDeactDataThres when sCellActDeactDataThres is not equal to -1

Parameter Description: No data is scheduled on SCell if wideband SINR is lower than sCellScheduleSinrThres. If SINR remains below threshold, SCell is deactivated when sCellDeactOutOfCoverageTimer expired.

Controls the length of time that elapses until a UE is considered once again for SCell configuration after the eNB was not able to configure this UE with a suitable Scell.

"-1" means wait forever.

Changed value may take effect related to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection.
Disturbances: Extreme settings can turn off CA for the eNB.

Parameter Description:
Controls time eNodeB waits after reception of an A2 measurement report until SCell is deconfigured. If an A6 measurement report is received on an allowed SCell candidate before timer expires, an SCell swap is performed.
Value -1 means wait forever.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.

Parameter Description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

Controls the length of time that elapses until a UE is reconsidered for additional SCell configuration after the eNB was unable to configure this UE with more than one SCell.

"-1" means wait forever.

Changed value can take effect related to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection.

Used to adjust factor of CC rate for CA UEs, which is used in scheduler's proportional fairness algorithm. A smaller value gives CA UE a greater advantage over non-CA UE.
Value 0 sets rate as 0 and this is for testing purpose only; values 1 - 4 set the rate as fraction of the cell rate in increased order; value 5 sets cell based rate; values 6 - 9 set the rate as cell rate plus rate influence from other CCs in increased order; value 10 sets the rate as aggregated rate of all CCs .

Cell selection priority between FDD and TDD SCell candidates for initial selection of SCells. This priority has precedence over all other priorities in Dynamic SCell Selection. Applicable only if Dynamic SCell Selection is active. If Configurable SCell Priority or Global SCell Evaluation is active, this attribute has no impact.
Change Take Effect: At the next initial SCell selection during the ongoing connection

Parameter Description:
When set to true, SCell candidate with MO attribute EUtranCellFDD::isDlOnly set to true is given priority in initial SCell selection.

Priority is applied after priority set by fddTddSCellPriority.
Change Take Effect: At the next initial SCell selection during the ongoing connection

Parameter Description: If the minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues in UL of a UE is higher than sCellActDeactUlDataThresh, activation of one or more secondary cells is considered.
Dependencies: sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst =< sCellActDeactUlDataThresh

Parameter Description: If minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues in UL of a UE is less than sCellActDeactUlDataThresh minus sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst, deactivation of one CC is considered.
Dependencies: sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst =< sCellActDeactUlDataThresh

Parameter Description: Enables CA when VoIP (or PTT) and enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation on FDD PCell are both active. Not used for TDD PCells.
Change Take Effect: At the next initial SCell selection during the ongoing connection
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Carrier Aggregation FAJ 121 3046 and Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation FAJ 121 3051 are active, and a VoIP or PTT bearer exists for a UE.

Parameter Description:
Selects behavior of selecting SCell candidates beyond first candidate.
Warning: There is a risk when using UN_ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION since UE does not send A1 measurement report for coverage confirmation.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Dynamic SCell Selection for Carrier Aggregation and 3CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension are active.

Parameter Description:
If minimum time to transmit all bits is higher than laaSCellActDeactDataThres, activation of one or more secondary cells is considered.

Minimum time to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells. Computed as if UE has all resources in those cells.

For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms, but for TDD UL/DL subframe configuration 1, there are 6 DL subframes in 10ms, and for UL/DL subframe configuration 2, there are 8 DL subframes in 10ms.

Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
Dependencies: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= laaSCellActDeactDataThres
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by UnlicensedAccessFunction::laaSCellActDeactDataThres. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
If minimum time to transmit all bits is less than laaSCellActDeactDataThres minus laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst, then deactivation of one component carrier is considered.

Minimum time to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells after deactivation decision. Computed as if UE has all resources in those cells.

For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms.

Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
Dependencies: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= laaSCellActDeactDataThres
Deprecated: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by UnlicensedAccessFunction::laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
Activation/deactivation prohibit timer. No new activation/deactivation of an LAA SCell is allowed while this timer is running.

Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q1. Replaced by laaSCellActProhibitTimer and laaSCellDeactProhibitTimer. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
No data is scheduled on LAA SCell if wideband SINR is lower than laaSCellScheduleSinrThres. If SINR stays below threshold, LAA SCell eventually becomes deactivated.

Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
Deprecated: Since 17.Q1. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Activation prohibit timer. No new SCell activation is allowed while this timer is running.
Deactivation prohibit timer. No new SCell deactivation is allowed while this timer is running.

SCell is deactivated if:
- wideband DL SINR remains below sCellScheduleSinrThres, or
- no Channel State Information is received by the eNB
for a duration of sCellDeactOutOfCoverageTimer.

Deactivation can be deferred, for example by sCellDeactProhibitTimer.

"-1" means the SCell is not deactivated due to the SINR condition.

One SCell is deactivated if minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues of a UE is less than or equal to sCellActDeactDataThres minus sCellActDeactDataThresHyst for a duration of sCellDeactDelayTimer.
Dependencies: sCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= sCellActDeactDataThres

Parameter Description: Method used to select SCell candidates.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Dynamic SCell Selection for Carrier Aggregation and Configurable SCell Priority features, Global SCell Evaluation feature, or both are active.

Parameter Description: The SINR margin for secondary cell (sCell) PDCCH outer loop.

Used to enable enhanced selection of four layer MIMO and carrier aggregation. Secondary cell is not added if effective bandwidth is reduced. If effective bandwidth is not changed, tie-breaking rule is governed by fourLayerMimoPreferred. Effective bandwidth includes the number of DL PRBs and DL MIMO layer capability of the UE in all serving cells.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Dynamic SCell Selection is active.

Parameter Description: Whether or not SCell is added when there is no change in effective bandwidth. Applies when enhanced selection of four layer MIMO and carrier aggregation is enabled. If set to true, SCell is not added, otherwise SCell is added.
Dependencies: Only takes effect when Dynamic SCell Selection is active.

Parameter Description: LAA activation prohibit timer. No new LAA SCell activation is allowed while this timer is running.

Parameter Description: LAA deactivation prohibit timer. No new LAA SCell deactivation is allowed while this timer is running.

Parameter Description:
Amount of weight given to the UL effective bandwidth (of band combinations) in the effective bandwidth evaluation function of Global SCell Evaluation feature.
If set to 0, effective bandwidth evaluation function does not consider UL effective bandwidth and is fully determined by DL effective bandwidth.
If set to 100, effective bandwidth evaluation function does not consider DL effective bandwidth and is fully determined by UL effective bandwidth.
If set to -1, CarrierAggregationFunction::caPreference applies.
Change Take Effect: New connection or next SCell configuration.
Dependencies: Only active when Global SCell Evaluation is active.

Parameter Description: A target minimum ratio of UL to DL effective BW, beyond which further SCells with no UL component will not be considered.
Change Take Effect: Takes effect on next SCell reconfiguration
Dependencies: Only active if Configurable SCell Priority or Automatic SCell Priority is enabled.
Deprecated: Since 19.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

Dependencies: Only applicable when dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to GLOBAL_EVALUATION.

Parameter Description: Expected DL throughput gain of having four layers compared with two. For used SCell evaluation in Global SCell Evaluation.
