Parameter Description: The hardware version of the Antenna Near Unit.

Type of Iuant-compliant Antenna Line Device (ALD).

Takes following values after conversion from hexadecimal to decimal:

- 1 indicates single-antenna RET device.
- 2 indicates tower-mounted amplifier.
- 17 indicates multi-antenna RET device.
- 35 indicates ASD.
- 37 indicates GLS device.
- 49 indicates RAE device.
- 64 indicates AISG3.0 Single-primary ALD.
- 65 indicates AISG3.0 Multi-primary ALD.

For more information, see following documentation:
- Section 4.7 of 3GPP TS 25.462
- Section 7.1 of AISG ES-RAE
- AISG ES-ASD
- AISG ES-GLS
- aisg.org.uk

3GPP TS 25.462 defines device types by providing hexadecimal codes. Code must be converted to decimal. 
If multi-antenna RET device is indicated as 0x11 in 3GPP TS 25.462, decimal equivalent, 17 must be used.

The unique ID reported by the physical antenna near unit.
The first two characters of the ID are the vendor code.
The value is extracted from the response message sent by the antenna near unit during connection establishment.
3GPP TS 25.462 specifies the procedure in detail.

It is used to support advanced antenna system configurations, such as cascaded RETs. Leave empty when the units are not cascaded.

The value stated is a subset of the uniqueID(concatenation of the vendor code and the antenna near unit serial number) 
which must contain enough significant characters/digits to be unique among the antenna near units (with iuantDeviceType single antenna RET or multiple antenna RET) connected to the RfPort. 
See also 3GPP 25.462.

Some vendors use specific modifications of the serial number on the device label to define the unique ID. 
Contact the vendor of the antenna near unit (RET) to obtain the mapping between the serial number taken from the label and the unique ID.

Selects between co-polarized and cross-polarized beamforming antenna port mapping.
Valid both for pre-defined antenna weights and custom antenna weights configured by customComChBeamfrmWtsAmplitude and customComChBeamfrmWtsPhase.

CROSS_POLARIZED is always used for NR.
Disturbances: Changed coverage may affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
Array of eight amplitudes for custom common channel beamforming weights.

Only first two are valid for 2T2R radio units. Only first four are valid for 4T4R radio units. At least one of the eight, four, or two valid amplitudes have to be non-zero for custom beamforming weights to take effect.
Weight amplitudes must be sorted according to the following sequence:
Amplitudes for one polarization in a left to right order facing front of antenna unit, followed by amplitudes for the other polarization in a left to right order facing front of antenna unit.
Disturbances: Changed coverage may affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
Array of eight phases for custom common channel beamforming weights.

Only first two are valid for 2T2R radio units. Only first four are valid for 4T4R radio units. Weight phases must be sorted in the same order as weight amplitudes.
Disturbances: Changed coverage may affect traffic.

Parameter Description:
The maximum antenna elevation including the installed tilt and the tilt applied by the Remote Electrical Tilt (RET).
described by the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the horizontal plane. It is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt. It sets a limitation on total tilt which is given by:

TotalTilt = AntennaUnit.mechanicaAntennalTilt + RetSubunit.electricalTilt

NOTE: If the antenna has no RET installed, this value does not account for the inclination that the antenna beam might have by default, with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis.

The minimum antenna elevation including the installed tilt and the tilt applied by the Remote Electrical Tilt (RET) described by the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the horizontal plane.
It is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt. The limitation on total tilt is found by the following equation:

TotalTilt = AntennaUnit.mechanicaAntennalTilt + RetSubunit.electricalTilt

NOTE: If the antenna has no RET installed, the total tilt value does not necessarily account for the inclination that the antenna beam might have by default, with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis.
Reference to the RET subunit controlling the tilt of this antenna subunit.

Total antenna elevation including the installed tilt and the tilt applied by the Remote Electrical Tilt (RET).
Total tilt is defined as the inclination of the maximum of the antenna main beam with respect to the horizontal plane.
Tilt is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, and negative indicates uptilt, found by the following equation:

totalTilt = AntennaUnit.mechanicaAntennalTilt+RetSubunit.electricalTilt

NOTE: If the antenna has no RET installed, this value does not account for the inclination that the antenna beam may have by default, with respect to the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis.

Uplink attenuation of the cross-connect cable.
The sequence contains 40 entries and each entry represents one 5-MHz interval.
The first entry represents the attenuation value of the lowest frequency interval in the operating band, and so on.
The number of intervals depends on the operating band.
For information on the different operating bands, refer to 3GPP TS 36.104.
The value range for each entry is -500 to -2, -1, 0-500 (-50 to 50 dB). Unused entries are set to -1.

Uplink delay of the cross-connect cable.
The sequence contains 40 entries and each entry represents one 5-MHz interval. The first entry represents the delay value of the lowest frequency interval in the operating band, and so on.
The number of intervals used depends on the operating band.
For information on the different operating bands, refer to 3GPP TS 36.104.
The value range for each entry is 0-800000 (0-800000 ns). Unused entries are set to -1.
NOTE: The range supported by individual radio units may be smaller and must be considered when configuring the antenna system.

Number of required  dot groups wanted and branches in each dot group of parent FRU representing IRU. 
Values must be set starting with dot group 1, in ascending and consecutive order. Number of elements with non-zero value represents the number of required dot groups wanted. 
If all elements have value 0, no dot group is configured and this attribute has no effect.
If IRU has no dot grouping capability, this attribute must have value 0, otherwise IRU cannot function correctly and alarm is raised.
Number of dot groups can be 1, 2, or 4, which means the following configuration options can be selected:
1. Setting value for noOfBranchesInGrp1 while leaving other elements 0.
2. Setting values for noOfBranchesInGrp1 and noOfBranchesInGrp2 while leaving other elements 0.
3. Setting values for all elements. 
Sum of branch numbers of all dot groups must not exceed 16. For example {4,4,4,8} is not allowed because 4 + 4 + 4 + 8 > 16. Takes effect: Next unlock of parent FieldReplaceableUnit MO.
Precondition: Value can only be set when parent FieldReplaceableUnit MO has administrativeState LOCKED.
Change Take Effect: Next unlock of parent FieldReplaceableUnit MO.

Parameter Description: Internal identifier for the RfPort to ease error traceability.
The operational state.
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.

VSWR supervision status.
Indicates if supervision of Voltage Standing Wave Ratio (VSWR) is enabled for the branch of this port on the Radio Unit.
VSWR supervision is possible on a TX branch only.

VSWR supervision sensitivity.

High values enable detection of low-reflected power (high return loss). Low values require high-reflected power (low return loss) to cause alarms.

VSWR = (1+10^(-RL/20))/(1-10^(-RL/20))

Where RL is Return Loss

If -1, radio chooses default return loss threshold.

For default return loss threshold and relation between sensitivity and return loss refer to either VSWR Antenna Supervision feature or Return Loss Antenna Supervision feature. Refer to Return Loss Antenna Supervision feature for list of supported radios.

The administrative state.
When set to LOCKED, the RfPort might still be used and RF power might still be transmitted, but any corresponding alarms cease.
If set to SHUTTINGDOWN, the state will immediately be brought to LOCKED.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

Refers to an instance of a retSubUnit from which this antenna near unit is controlled and supplied with power.

Fixed antenna tilt of installation, defined as inclination of antenna element axis with respect to vertical plane.
A signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, negative indicates uptilt.

Maximum antenna elevation including installed tilt and tilt applied by Remote Electrical Tilt (RET).
Described by inclination of antenna main beam maximum with respect to horizontal plane. A signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, negative indicates uptilt.
Sets a limitation on total tilt which is given by following formula:

TotalTilt = Transceiver.mechanicalAntennaTilt + RetSubunit.electricalTilt

If RET not installed, this value does not account for inclination that antenna beam can have by default, with respect to orthogonal direction to antenna element axis.

Minimum antenna elevation including installed tilt and tilt applied by Remote Electrical Tilt (RET). Described by inclination of antenna main beam maximum with respect to horizontal plane. A signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, negative indicates uptilt.
Limitation on total tilt is found by following equation:

TotalTilt = Transceiver.mechanicalAntennaTilt + RetSubunit.electricalTilt

If RET not installed, total tilt value does not necessarily account for inclination the antenna beam can have by default, with respect to orthogonal direction to antenna element axis.

Total antenna elevation including installed tilt and tilt applied by Remote Electrical Tilt (RET).
Total tilt is defined as inclination of antenna main beam maximum with respect to horizontal plane.
Tilt is a signed value. Positive indicates downtilt, negative indicates uptilt. Can be found by following equation:

TotalTilt = Transceiver.mechanicalAntennaTilt + RetSubunit.electricalTilt

If RET not installed, this value does not account for inclination that antenna beam can have by default, with respect to orthogonal direction to antenna element axis.
Indicates if the active antenna system is installed behind a passive antenna system as interleaved.
Dependencies: Only takes effect in AAS radio equipment supporting configurable embedded array antenna module.

The total measured battery backup current. When the batteries are charging, the current is positive. When the batteries are discharging, the current is negative.
Undefined value: -9999 indicates no contact with battery interfacing unit such as a BFU or BPA unit.

The offset for the disconnect temperature below which the battery will be reconnected. Applies to both main and priority loads. The battery is reconnected when batteryTemperature < batteryDisconnectedTemp - batteryDisconnectTempCeaseOffset.
The date when the batteries in the battery backup of the RBS were installed and taken into service. Format: YYYYMMDD.
Dependencies: The date must not be a future date. Changing this attribute will cause the system to restart battery capacity test calculations and recalculate attribute referenceBatteryCapacity.
Deprecated: Since 18A. Replaced by installationDate in MO BatteryUnit. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
The current temperature reported by the battery temperature sensor installed on the battery.
Undefined value represented by nil, indicates no contact with BFU, BFU has no battery or BFU has no temperature sensor.

State whether a battery test is running or not.

Possible values:
- true: A battery test cycle has been started
- false: Either the battery test is disabled or there is not any ongoing battery test.
The type of battery to which the installed battery conforms. The type is related to the capabilities of the battery.

Parameter Description:
The measured battery voltage. It is equal to the attribute systemVoltage, PowerdDistribution MO, when the battery is connected.
0 means the battery is disconnected. 
Undefined value represented by nil, indicates no contact with the battery interfacing unit, such as a BFU or a BPA unit.
The time in boost charge. Value zero (0) means that boost charging is disabled.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED

Parameter Description: Defines the trigger voltage for boost charge. When the trigger voltage is surpassed during discharge, the consecutive charging is boost charging.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: Maximum allowed battery current during charging. The maximum battery current is limited if the maximum current supported by the BFU is lower than this defined value.

The type of battery charging used. If charging is user-defined, the charging algorithm and parameters must be specified. If chargingMode = AUTOMATIC, the following attributes are not used:
 floatChargeVoltage

Parameter Description: The number of days between equalize charging. The cycle is reset at restart.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: The time in equalize charge. Value zero (0) means that equalize charging is disabled. To enable equalize charging, the value must be set to a number other than zero (0).
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: The charge voltage used at boost charging and equalize charging.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.
Deprecated: Deprecated since 16A, replaced by ElevatedChargeVoltage

Parameter Description: Defines the period following disconnection after which the battery is reconnected. Used in intermittent charging.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: Defines the minimum battery voltage level allowed for a disconnected battery. When minimum level is reached, the battery is reconnected. Used in intermittent charging.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: Defines the time until the batteries are disconnected (during this time the batteries are connected). Value zero (0) means that intermittent charging is not enabled.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: The minimum requirement for backup time for the installed batteries when conducting a battery backup time test. An alarm is raised if measured backup time is shorter than minimumBackupTime.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if sharedBattery is set to true.

Parameter Description: The minimum value for the State-of-Health of the battery backup system. An alarm is raised if stateOfHealth value for the battery backup system is lower than minimumStateOfHealth value.
Dependencies: The attribute is only relevant if sharedBattery is set to false.

Parameter Description: Date of next scheduled periodic battery test. Format: "YYYYMMDD".
Dependencies: The value is undefined if testMode has the value DISABLED.

Parameter Description: Nominal temperature for temperature compensated charging.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description:
The initial nominal battery capacity. The value is extracted from intelligent batteries as a sum of all installed batteries nominal capacity. For batteries that cannot communicate, the value is calculated at the first battery capacity test. If  the capacity value becomes significantly higher at a succeeding battery capacity test, the value is replaced with the highest value.

Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been retrieved.
Dependencies: The value is either the sum of all battery units initial nominal capacity or the result of the first conducted battery capacity test of the battery system. A battery capacity test can only be executed if the attribute sharedBattery = false.

Parameter Description: Indicates if the RBS shares a battery with another RBS or other power consumer on the site. The setting of this attributes has a great impact on the system behavior.
Dependencies: If sharedBattery is set to True a backup time test will be used as battery test. A battery capacity test cannot be executed if shared batteries are used.

Parameter Description: The maximum voltage allowed for temperature compensated charging.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: The minimum voltage allowed for temperature compensated charging.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description:
A compensation factor that expresses the amount of voltage changes caused by temperature. Used in temperature compensated charging. Higher temperature gives a lower charging voltage. Fixed battery charging is achieved by assigning this attribute the value zero.
Example: The default value -96 = -0.096 V per 1 degree Celsius, gives that a 10 degree temperature increase changes the voltage from e.g. -50.000 V to -49.040 V.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

Parameter Description: The mode of the battery test.
Disturbances: Depending on values of other BatteryBackup attributes, changing this attribute can start a battery test which can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: The following attributes are only relevant if testMode is set to CONFIGURED: testStartDay, testStartTime, testStartMonths and minimumStateOfHealth.

Parameter Description: The day of month for periodic battery tests.
Dependencies: The attribute is relevant only when testMode has the value CONFIGURED. Combination of testStartDay and testStartMonths must be a valid date.

Parameter Description: The months in which periodic battery tests are performed. A battery test is performed in the months listed in the parameter. A month may be listed only once in the parameter.
Range and Values:
JANUARY
FEBRUARY
MARCH
APRIL
JUNE
JULY
AUGUST
MAY
SEPTEMBER
OCTOBER
NOVEMBER
DECEMBER
Dependencies: The attribute is only relevant if attribute testMode has the value CONFIGURED.

Parameter Description: The time of day to start periodic battery tests. Format: HH:MM, 24-hour format.
Dependencies: The attribute is only relevant if testMode has the value CONFIGURED.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Voltage at which BFU must disconnect main load. Main load is disconnected when value of systemVoltage is below mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect.
For example, default value -460 = -46.0 V means that main load is disconnected if systemVoltage is -45.9 V.
During deprecation period, setting of mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect is converted and mirrored to BatteryBackup.mainLoadDisconnectLevel.
Dependencies:
priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect - mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect >= 0.2 V. 
mainLoadUnderVoltageDisconnect > systemUndervoltageAlarmLevel
Deprecated: Since 18A. Replaced by mainLoadDisconnectLevel on MO BatteryBackup. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
The voltage at which the Battery Fuse Unit (BFU) must disconnect the Priority Load. The primary load is disconnected when systemVoltage is below priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect.
Example: The default value -450 = -45.0 V, gives that the priority load is disconnected if systemVoltage is e.g. -44.9 V.
During deprecation period, a setting of the priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect is converted and mirrored to attribute batteryDisconnectLevel of MO BatteryBackup.
Disturbances: When running on batteries, changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
Dependencies: priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect - mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect >= 0.2 V
Deprecated: Since 18A. Replaced by batteryDisconnectLevel on MO BatteryBackup. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description:
The offset for the disconnected voltage above which the Battery Fuse Unit (BFU) reconnects the load. Applies to both main and priority load.
The main load is reconnected when system voltage is above (mainLoadUndervoltageDisconect - undervoltageDisconnectCeaseOffset).
systemVoltage = batteryVoltage when the system is running on battery supply.
Example: The default values gives a main load undervoltage reconnection at -460  70 = -530 (-53.0 V DC), the load is reconnected if systemVoltage is e.g. -53.1 V.

Note: 
the batteries are reconnected when systemVoltage is above (mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnected -underVoltageDisconnectCeaseOffset) and batteryVoltage is above -39.0V.
systemVoltage is an attribute in MO PowerSupply.
batteryVoltage is an attribute in MO BatteryBackup.
Deprecated: Since 18A. Planned to be removed.

CRL grace period timer.

Specifies the length of  grace period before a revokation of a software signing certificate takes effect.
The grace period starts when system is upgraded and new UP contains an updated certificate revocation list in which an installed certificate is revoked.

The grace period allows the operator to revert system to an older UP where the revocation has not occurred.

When the grace period expires, it will no longer be possible to revert to any older UP signed using the expired certificate. Both those Upgrade packages and the associated backups will be removed automatically.
Precondition: Cannot be changed during ongoing grace period.

Parameter Description:
Time error of PTP path at node interface.

If PTP network has full timing support, this attribute must contain maximum absolute time error generated by chain of boundary, transparent clocks and asymmetry of worst-case path from grandmaster to node. This corresponds to network limit at reference point C according to G.8271.1 without time error introduced by grandmaster. Latter part is taken from BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO attribute parentDS.grandmasterClockAccuracy. Maximum absolute time error is theoretical sum of worst-case of each component.

As alternative, attribute can be used to set worst-case measured time error of path from grandmaster to node.

If BoundaryOrdinaryClock MOs are reserved by AssistingReference MO, this attribute is ignored.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

VlanPort MO, to which this encapsulation refers, must be referenced by MO type InterfaceIPv4, InterfaceIPv6, or Bridge.
If maintenanceAssociationType is set to PRIMARY_VID this attribute must refer to VlanPort MO, where attribute isTagged must be set to true.

Parameter Description: Which defects raise CfmFault alarm.
The value component of the RDN.

MA name.

If maintenanceAssociationType is PRIMARY_VID, this attribute is not used. Primary VID, defined by underlying VlanPort MO, is used to identify CFM messages.

Maximum length of maintenanceDomainName + maximum length of maintenanceAssociationName is 44 octets.
Dependencies:
If maintenanceAssociationType is set to PRIMARY_VID this attribute must be empty.
If maintenanceDomainType is set to NO_NAME this attribute must be at most 45 characters.
If maintenanceDomainType is set to DNS_BASED or STRING, combined length of maintenanceAssociationName and maintenanceDomainName must be at most 44 chars.
If maintenanceDomainType is set to MAC, combined length of maintenanceAssociationName and maintenanceDomainName must be at most 44 characters, where maintenanceDomainName has 8 characters.
If maintenanceAssociationType is set to STRING this attribute length must be more than 0 characters.
If maintenanceAssociationType is set to INTEGER this attribute must be integer within range 0-65535.

Parameter Description:
Type and format of maintenanceAssociationName.

If this attribute is set to PRIMARY_VID, encapsulation must refer to a VlanPort MO, where isTagged attribute must be set to true.

MD level.

Specifies nesting relationship between maintenance domains.

For each value of this attribute, only one EthernetOamLocalMep MO can be configured for each MO type VlanPort, EthernetPort, or LagPort, that is referred by encapsulation attribute.
Dependencies: All EthernetOamLocalMep MOs with same encapsulation that refers to MO type VlanPort, EthernetPort or LagPort MO, must have unique maintenanceDomainLevel.

Parameter Description: MD name.
Dependencies:
If maintenanceDomainType is set to NO_NAME this attribute must be empty.
If maintenanceAssociationType is set to PRIMARY_VID or INTEGER this attribute must be at most 42 characters.
If maintenanceDomainType is set to DNS_BASED or STRING, combined length of maintenanceAssociationName and maintenanceDomainName must be at most 44 chars.
If maintenanceDomainType is set to MAC, combined length of maintenanceAssociationName and maintenanceDomainName must be at most 44 characters, where maintenanceDomainName has 8 characters.
If maintenanceDomainType is set to STRING or DNS_BASED  this attribute length must be more than 0 characters.
If maintenanceDomainType is set to MAC  this attribute must have format 11:22:33:44:55:66.1234.

Parameter Description: Type and format of maintenanceDomainName.

Indication of current defects.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Reference to FieldReplaceableUnit MO that represents external unit to primary core.
The value component of the RDN.

The action of the ACL entry. 

The value can be either PERMIT or DENY.

When a packet matches the filters in this entry, the action is executed. 
When the attribute has the value DENY, the packet is dropped silently. When the attribute has the value PERMIT, the packet is accepted.

Destination IP Address filter. 

The value is a list of IPv4 subnets: Value/prefix-length. 

The ACL entry matches if any address in the list matches.

If the value list is empty, any IP address matches this entry.

Source IP Address filter.

The value is a list of IPv4 subnets: Value/prefix-length. 

The ACL entry matches if any address in the list matches.

If the value list is empty, any IP address matches this entry.

DSCP field filter.

The value is a list of DSCP values: Ranges [dd..dd] or single-values [dd], where dd represents an integer in {0..63}. 

The ACL entry matches if any DSCP value in the list matches.

If the value list is empty, any DSCP value will match this entry.

Fragment type filter. 

The value is a fragment type. 

If the value is empty, state-less handling of fragments is performed.
Range and Values:
NOTFRAGMENTED
FRAGFIRST
FRAGLAST
FRAGMENT
INITIAL
NONINITIAL

Parameter Description:
ICMP type filter.

The ACL entry matches if any element in the list matches. 

If the value list is empty, any ICMP types match this entry.
Dependencies: It can be non-empty only if ipProtocol contains one single-value element, equal to ICMP (1).

Parameter Description:
Protocol number filter.

The value is a list of ranges [ddd..ddd] or single-values [ddd], where ddd represents an integer in the range {0..255}. 

The ACL entry matches if any protocol number in the list matches. 

If the value list is empty, any protocol number matches this entry.

Transport layer destination port filter (UDP, TCP or SCTP only).

The value is a list of port numbers: Ranges [ddddd..ddddd] or single values [ddddd], where ddddd represents an integer in the range {0..65535}.

This attribute can be non-empty only if the protocol is non-empty and if it contains elements that are single values equal to UDP (17), TCP (6), or SCTP (132).
 
The ACL entry matches if any port number in the list matches.

If the value list is empty, any port number matches this entry.

Transport layer source port filter (UDP, TCP or SCTP only).

The value is a list of port numbers: Ranges [ddddd..ddddd] or single values [ddddd], where ddddd represents an integer in the range {0..65535}. 

This attribute can be non-empty only if the protocol is non-empty and if it contains elements that are single values equal to UDP (17), TCP (6), or SCTP (132)

The ACL entry matches if any port number in the list matches.

If the value list is empty, any port number matches this entry.
Priority of this ACL entry relative to the other entries in the list.
Dependencies: The attribute values of the AclEntryIpv4 instances must be unique within the same AclIpv4 MO.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.
The value component of the RDN.

Specifies whether implicit rules are added to permit NDP and MLD protocol packets.
 
If this attribute is set to true, packets with the following ICMP types are permitted:
- 130 (Multicast Listener Query)
- 131 (Multicast Listener Report v1)
- 132 (Multicast Listener Done)
- 133 (Router Solicitation)
- 134 (Router Advertisement)
- 135 (Neighbor Solicitation)
- 136 (Neighbor Advertisement)
- 137 (Redirect)
- 143 (Multicast Listener Report v2)
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.

If certificate based authentication is used, attribute refers to NodeCredential MO including IPsec node certificate to be used in IKE SA negotiation.

If credential and trustCategory not specified, pre-shared key-based authentication is used. Referring Ikev2Session MO must have pre-shared keys installed.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
Either both credential and trustCategory must be set or neither of them.
Must refer to existing NodeCredential MO.

Parameter Description:
Max time  to detect that IKE SA is down.

If node detects that IKE SA is down, alarm is raised. Node tries continually re-establish IKE SA.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: DSCP value that node uses when transmitting IKE messages.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description:
Lifetime for IKE SA.

Node initiates re-keying according to soft lifetime in order to complete process before lifetime expires.
Soft lifetime is calculated as (0.8+0.1*R)*ikeSaLifetime, where R is random factor between 0 and 1.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description:
IKEv2 fragmentation functionality.

IKEv2 fragmentation is only applicable if both peers enable fragmentation.

If false, fragmentation is disabled.
If true, fragmentation is enabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Ordered list of IKE proposals, used for IKE SA negotiation.

Each proposal contains set of cryptographic algorithms that can be used for IKE SA.

If not set, node generates proposal based on all node-supported algorithms.

First proposal in list has highest priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Reference to TrustCategory MO containing list of trusted certificates used in IKE SA negotiation.
Referred TrustCategory MO must contain CA certificates for both peer node and this node.

Must be set if certificate based authentication is used.
If credential and trustCategory not set, pre-shared key based authentication is used. Referring Ikev2Session MO must have pre-shared keys installed.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
Either both credential and trustCategory must be set or neither of them.
Must refer to existing TrustCategory MO.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.

Lifetime for negotiated Child SAs.
In order for node to complete the rekeying process before lifetime expires, node starts new rekeying according to soft lifetime. Soft lifetime is calculated as (0.8+0.1*R)*childSaLifetime, where R is random factor between 0 and 1.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description:
Ordered list of Child SA proposals.

Each proposal contains set of cryptographic algorithms applicable for the Child SA.

If attribute is not set, system generates proposals based on node-supported algorithms.
Neither NULL encryption algorithm nor AES-GMAC integrity algorithms are included in this case.

First proposal in list has highest priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Enables Perfect Forward Secrecy.

By default, PFS is disabled and is not used for any Child SA pair rekeying or establishment of new Child SA pairs.

If PFS is enabled, node requires PFS for any Child SA pair rekeying or establishment of new Child SA pairs.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbance.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.
Reference to Ikev2PolicyProfile MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

IKE ID must be identical to subjectAltName or subject field in certificate.
If certificate based authentication is used, node sends IKE ID to security gateway identical to subjectAltName in used certificate.
If more than one IPsec VPN connection is setup from node to same security gateway, node can be forced to send different IKE IDs on two IKE SAs.
Certain security gateway configurations can reject multiple IKE SAs with same IKE ID.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description:
The operational state.

Disabled if no IKE SA or first Child SA pair is established.
Label for free use.
Enable or disable anti-replay protection.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Reference to IpsecProposalProfile MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description:
Local traffic selector to be used for Child SA negotiation.

If localTrafficSelector is not specified, all virtual inner addresses of relevant IP version in inner Router will be used as local traffic selectors in Child SA negotiation.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If set, localTrafficSelector and remoteTrafficSelector must have same address family.
If parent IpsecTunnel MO is referenced by both InterfaceIPv4 MO and InterfaceIPv6 MO, localTrafficSelector must be set.
Combination of remoteTrafficSelector and locaTrafficSelector must be unique for each IpsecPolicy MO, and must not be overlapping, within one IpsecTunnel MO.
If set for one IpsecPolicy MO, it must be set for all IpsecPolicy MOs within IpsecTunnel MO.
If there is AddressIPv4 MO with configurationMode IKE in Router MO, attribute must not be set for IpsecPolicy MO where IpsecTunnel MO is encapsulated by InterfaceIPv4 MO. Same applies to corresponding IPv6 case.

Parameter Description:
Ordered list of traffic selectors to be used for Child SA negotiation.

If remoteTrafficSelector is not specified, any IP address is possible.

First in list has highest priority.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If set, localTrafficSelector and remoteTrafficSelector must have same address family.
Combination of remoteTrafficSelector and locaTrafficSelector must be unique for each IpsecPolicy MO, and must not be overlapping, within one IpsecTunnel MO.
If localTrafficSelector is same for different IpsecPolicy MOs, at least one remoteTrafficSelector must be set for each IpsecPolicy MO.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Valid reference is of MO type AddressIPv4 or AddressIPv6.

Must not refer to child of InterfaceIPv4 MO or InterfaceIPv6 MO encapsulating IpsecTunnel MO.

The operational state.

Attribute operationalState is disabled if associated Ikev2Session MO is disabled.

Remote outer address of IPsec VPN connection.

Valid reference is of MO type PeerIPv4 or PeerIPv6.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
Local and remote addresses must have same address family and belong to same routing domain. They must be contained under same Router MO.
This attribute and remoteAddressSecondary addresses must have same address family.
This attribute and remoteAddressSecondary cannot be same.
Combination of local and remote outer addresses must be unique for each IpsecTunnel MO.

Parameter Description:
Secondary remote outer address of IPsec VPN connection.

Configure if IPsec active-standby redundancy is to be used. Only one reference can be configured.
In this case PeerIPv4 MO or PeerIPv6 MO in remoteAddress represents primary security gateway.
PeerIPv4 MO or PeerIPv6 MO in remoteAddressSecondary represents secondary security gateway.

Valid reference is of MO type PeerIPv4 or PeerIPv6.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
Local and remote addresses must have same address family and belong to same routing domain. They must be contained under same Router MO.
This attribute and remoteAddress addresses must have same address family.
Maximum one remoteAddressSecondary is allowed.
Must not refer to same PeerIPv4 or PeerIPv6 MO as attribute remoteAddress.
If this attribute is configured, address attribute on PeerIPv4 or PeerIPv6 MOs for both remoteAddress and remoteAddressSecondary must be IP address.
Combination of local and remote outer addresses must be unique for each IpsecTunnel MO.

The administrative state.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: Administrative operating mode of Ethernet port. Used when auto-negotiation is enabled or disabled.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
MASTER and SLAVE options are only valid for external electrical interface ports.
Configuration of invalid attributes can result in non-operational port.

When configuring 1G_FULL or 10G_FULL on external electrical interfaces:
- if MASTER or SLAVE is not specified and autoNegEnable=true, master or slave mode is auto-negotiated,
- if MASTER or SLAVE is not specified and autoNegEnable=false, master or slave mode is set to SLAVE.

ANY can be used by auto-negotiation to negotiate:
- interface rate,
- master or slave settings,
- Forward Error Correction (FEC) mode.
ANY can only be set if attribute autoNegEnable is set to true.
Using ANY will not set rates of:
- 10G,
- 25G,
- 50G,
- 100G.

If 25G_AUTO_FEC, autoNegEnable attribute must not be set to false.
Must be set to ANY if underlying encapsulation is RiPort MO.

Parameter Description:
Whether auto-negotiation of operating mode is enabled or disabled for this Ethernet port.

If true, auto-negotiation is enabled.
If false, auto-negotiation is disabled.
If true, 1Gbps Ethernet over twisted-pair cable can be used with RJ45 connector.
If admOperatingMode is 25G_AUTO_FEC, this attribute must not be set to false.
If admOperatingMode is 10G_FULL, this attribute must not be set to true.

Can only support:
- Ethernet over twisted-pair cable with RJ45 connector.
- 1Gbps over twinaxial copper or fiber-optical cable with SFP connector.

Cannot be set to false if underlying encapsulation is RiPort MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Cannot be configured if underlying encapsulation is EthernetPort MO, that encapsulates RiPort MO.
Cannot be configured if underlying encapsulation is RiPort MO.

Parameter Description:
Tagged or untagged traffic on port.

If set to true, tagged frames are accepted and sent.

If set to false, untagged frames are accepted and sent.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If set to false, untagged frames are accepted and sent.
Must be set to true if ENodeBFunction MO or ExternalENodeBFunction MO reserves this port.
Cannot be set to false if underlying encapsulation is EthernetPort MO, that encapsulates by TnPort MO for IDL connector.
Cannot be set to false if underlying encapsulation is EthernetPort MO, that encapsulates RiPort MO.

Parameter Description: Enables port low latency switching.
Obsolete: Since 2024-01-10. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.

Ingress classifies which VlanPort MO traffic will be going into, when being received on EthernetPort MO.

Egress indicates VLAN ID in VLAN tag of packets being transmitted out of EthernetPort MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies: Must be configured to value 10 if underlying encapsulation is EthernetPort MO, that encapsulates RiPort MO.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Configured IPv4 address.

IPv4 decimal address + "/" + prefix length <0-32>.

Configuration with prefix length /31 is supported according to RFC 3021, using 31-bit prefixes on IPv4 Point-to-Point links.

AddressIPv4 MOs that are children of same InterfaceIPv4 MO must either have identical prefix or different and non-overlapping prefix.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If loopback is set, or if encapsulation refers to IpsecTunnel MO, for parent InterfaceIPv4 MO, prefix length must be 32.
If parent InterfaceIPv4 MO has encapsulation towards physical network via LagPort MO or Bridge MO, there is no support for prefix length 31.
If subnet mask equals 31, encapsulation of parent InterfaceIPv4 MO must refer to EthernetPort MO or VlanPort MO.
If configurationMode is MANUAL, this attribute must be set.
If configurationMode is DHCP or IKE, this attribute must not be set.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Whether IP address is configured manually, or retrieved from network using either DHCP or IKEv2 configuration payload.

If MANUAL, address is manually configured.
If DHCP, address and default routes are retrieved from DHCP server.
If IKE, address is retrieved from security gateway using IKEv2 configuration payload in IKE negotiation.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If DHCP, encapsulation of parent InterfaceIPv4 MO must refer to MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, LagPort or Bridge.
If DHCP, no other AddressIPv4 MO with configurationMode DHCP must exist within same Router MO.
If DHCP, bfdProfile attribute in parent InterfaceIPv4 MO must not be set.
If IKE, encapsulation of parent InterfaceIPv4 MO must refer to IpsecTunnel MO.
If IKE, only one AddressIPv4 MO must exist within same Router MO.
If IKE, parent InterfaceIPv4 MO must not refer to IpsecTunnel MO referred by InterfaceIPv6 MO.
Must be MANUAL or IKE, if there is RouteTableIPv4Static MO in Router MO.
Must be MANUAL, if DhcpRelayIPv4 MO or AbisIP MO refer to this MO.
Must be MANUAL, if there is Ospfv2 MO in Router MO.
Must be MANUAL, if loopback attribute in parent InterfaceIPv4 MO is set.
Must be MANUAL, if parent InterfaceIPv4 MO has more than one child AddressIPv4 MO.

Parameter Description:
Specifies DHCP client identifier to be used when dhcpClientIdentifierType is set to MANUAL.

Arbitrary client identifier string, ASCII encoding. Empty string not allowed.

Example: eNodeB47
Dependencies:
If configurationMode is DHCP and dhcpClientIdentifierType is MANUAL, this attribute must be set.
If configurationMode is DHCP and dhcpClientIdentifierType has any other value than MANUAL, this attribute must not be set.
If configurationMode is MANUAL or IKE, or if dhcpClientIdentifierType is AUTOMATIC, this attribute must not be set.

Parameter Description:
Specifies whether dhcpClientIdentifier is configured manually, automatically generated or not used at all.

DHCP client identifier is unique identifier assigned to each client on network that DHCP server uses to identify node interface and to connect it with its address binding.
This identifier must be unique for all clients in administrative domain of DHCP server.
Dependencies: Only applicable if configurationMode is DHCP.

Parameter Description: Selection of primary or secondary IP address.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies: Must be set to true for exactly one of AddressIPv4 MOs that are children of specific InterfaceIPv4 MO.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Used IP address as IPv4 decimal address + "/" + prefix length <0-32>.

If configurationMode is MANUAL, this attribute has same content as address attribute.
If configurationMode is DHCP or IKE, retrieved address is shown in this attribute.
Label for free use.

Reference to AclIpv4 MO applied in egress direction.

If attribute is empty, no ACL filtering will take place in egress direction.
When ACL entries are configured, ACL entry must be added for default action, otherwise non-matching packets will be silently discarded.
Dependencies:
Attribute can only be set if encapsulation refers MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.
Referred AclIpv4 MO must belong to same Router MO, and must have at least one AclEntryIpv4 MO as child.

Parameter Description:
Reference to AclIpv4 MO applied in ingress direction.

If attribute is empty, no ACL filtering will take place in ingress direction.
When ACL entries are configured, ACL entry must be added for default action, otherwise non-matching packets will be silently discarded.
Dependencies:
Attribute can only be set if encapsulation refers MO types EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.
Referred AclIpv4 MO must belong to same Router MO, and must have at least one AclEntryIpv4 MO as child.

Parameter Description:
Average time that entry remains in ARP cache.

Entry is dynamically learned IP address and its corresponding MAC address.
Entry is then either refreshed, if entry is still needed, or removed, if entry is not needed any more.
Dependencies: Attribute is only relevant if encapsulation refers MO type EthernetPort a VlanPort, or a Bridge.

Parameter Description:
The availability status.
It contains details about operationalState.
Range and Values:
IN_TEST
FAILED
POWER_OFF
OFF_LINE
OFF_DUTY
DEPENDENCY
DEGRADED
NOT_INSTALLED
LOG_FULL
DEPENDENCY_LOCKED
DEPENDENCY_FAILED
DEPENDENCY_SHUTTINGDOWN

Parameter Description: Reference to BfdProfile MO containing BFD parameters used for BFD sessions from this interface.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If bfdStaticRoutes is set to ENABLED, this attribute must be set.
If configurationMode in AddressIPv4 MO is set to DHCP, this attribute must not be set.
Referred BfdProfile MO must belong to Transport MO or same Router MO.
If loopback is set, this attribute must not be set.

Parameter Description:
Enables or disables BFD monitoring of static route and PBR nexthops on this interface.

This attribute works in conjunction with bfdProfile.
To enable BFD monitoring for this interface, bfdStaticRoutes must be set to ENABLED and bfdProfile must be set.
If BFD monitoring is enabled, all static routing nexthops on subnets of this IP interface are monitored, unless explicitly disabled on PeerIPv4 MO or NextHop MO.
BFD monitoring of static routes for a specific peer can be enabled on PeerIPv4 MO even if this attribute is DISABLED.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If attribute is set to ENABLED, bfdProfile must be set.
Attribute can only be ENABLED if encapsulation refers MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.

Parameter Description:
DSCP to PCP map used for marking DSCP tagged packets with PCP value.
Packets are marked either host originated or routed into QoS domain.

If empty, DSCP values are mapped to PCP values according to following:

pcp0 = 0
pcp1   (empty)
pcp2 = 10,12,14
pcp3 = 18,20,22
pcp4 = 8,16,26,28
pcp5 = 34,36,38,46
pcp6 = 32,40,48
pcp7 = 51,54
Dependencies:
Attribute can only be set if encapsulation refers MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.
DSCP to PCP map is not relevant if loopback is set, or encapsulation refers to IpsecTunnel MO.

Parameter Description: Reference to underlying encapsulation, which can be MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, Bridge, IpsecTunnel or LagPort.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
One of encapsulation or loopback must be set, but not both at same time.
Only one InterfaceIPv4 MO can refer to same MO.
Cannot refer to EthernetPort MO referred by VlanPort MO.
Cannot refer to VlanPort MO referred by Bridge MO.
Referred IpsecTunnel MO must belong to same Router MO.
If InterfaceIPv4 MO and InterfaceIPv6 MO refer to same MO in encapsulation, they must belong to same Router MO.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, none of aclIngress, aclEgress, egressQosMarking, or routingPolicyIngress can be set.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, bfdStaticRoutes must be DISABLED.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, configurationMode for child AddressIPv4 MO must not be DHCP.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, the only relevant configuration attributes are mtu and routesHoldDownTimer.
If attribute does not refer to MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, LagPort or Bridge, maximum one AddressIPv4 MO can be configured for this MO.

Parameter Description:
DSCP to DSCP map used for remarking ingress DSCP tagged packets.

Empty string means no re-marking is done.
Attribute used to fix specific issues within QoS domain and should most often be empty.

It can refer to DscpDscpMap MO.
Dependencies: Attribute is only relevant if encapsulation refers MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Whether IP packets with supported IP options are dropped or not.

If set to false, IP packets with supported IP options are allowed.
If set to true, IP packets with IP options are dropped.
Dependencies: Not applicable if encapsulation refers to IpsecTunnel MO.

Parameter Description: Specifies if interface is IP loopback interface.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
One of encapsulation or loopback must be set, but not both at same time.
If set, none of aclIngress, aclEgress, egressQosMarking or routingPolicyIngress can be set.
If set, bfdStaticRoutes must be DISABLED.
If set, configurationMode for child AddressIPv4 MO must be MANUAL.
If set, only relevant other configuration attribute is trackedInterface.
If set, bfdProfile must not be set.
If set, ipOptionsDisabled must be FALSE.

Parameter Description:
Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU).
Real MTU is minimum of this configured value and MTU given by encapsulation.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If InterfaceIPv4 MO and InterfaceIPv6 MO refer to same MO in encapsulation, they must have same MTU value.
This attribute is not relevant if loopback is set.

Parameter Description: The operational state.
PCP value for ARP packets using this interface.
Dependencies: Attribute is only applicable if encapsulation refers MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Hold-down timer used for static and dynamic routes that use this interface.

If attribute is set, hold-down timer starts when conditions for static route is available and fulfilled.
When hold-down timer expires, route is available.

OSPFv2 uses this attribute to delay neighbour discovery on this interface (that is, until interface is deemed reliably up) until routesHoldDownTimer has expired, counting from time that underlying L2 interface transitioned to operational state of ENABLED.

If attribute is empty, there is no hold-down timer for routes and existing route over this interface is available without additional delay.

Attribute must not be set in case there is no alternative route.

This attribute does not affect the operational state of the interface.
Dependencies:
If InterfaceIPv4 MO and InterfaceIPv6 MO refer to same MO in encapsulation, they must have same routesHoldDownTimer value.
Attribute is not relevant if loopback is set.

Parameter Description:
Reference to a RoutingPolicyIPv4 MO to be used for Policy Based Routing in ingress direction.

If attribute is set, Policy Based Routing of incoming packets is enabled.
Dependencies:
Referred RoutingPolicyIPv4 MO must belong to same Router MO, and must have at least one RoutingRuleIpv4 MO as child.
Attribute can only be set if encapsulation refers MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.

Parameter Description: If set for loopback interface, operationalState and availabilityStatus from referred tunnel interface is inherited.
Dependencies:
Only relevant if attribute loopback is set.
Can only refer to InterfaceIPv4 MO within same Router MO that has IpsecTunnel MO as encapsulation reference.

Parameter Description: Defines whether DSCP field of ingress datagrams shall be trusted or not.
Deprecated: Since 16.2.8 (16-01-25). Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.

Configured IPv6 address.
IPv6 address + "/" + prefix length<0-128>.

AddressIPv6 MOs that are children of same InterfaceIPv6 MO must either have identical prefix or different and non-overlapping prefixes.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If loopback attribute in parent InterfaceIPv6 MO is set, or if encapsulation refers to IpsecTunnel MO, prefix length must be 128.
If configurationMode is MANUAL, this attribute must be set.
If configurationMode is other than MANUAL, this attribute must not be set.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Whether IP address is configured manually, or retrieved from network using IKEv2 configuration payload or IPv6 autoconfiguration.

If MANUAL, address is manually configured.
If IKE, address is retrieved from security gateway using IKEv2 configuration payload in IKE negotiation.
If AUTO, AUTO_NO_DHCPV6, or AUTO_DHCPV6, address and default routes are retrieved from network using IPv6 autoconfiguration.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
Must be MANUAL, if loopback attribute in parent InterfaceIPv6 MO is set.
Must be MANUAL, if there is RaTransmitter MO in parent InterfaceIPv6 MO.
Must be MANUAL or IKE, if there is RouteTableIPv6Static MO in Router MO.
Must be MANUAL or IKE, if encapsulation attribute in InterfaceIPv6 MO refers to IpsecTunnel MO.
Must be MANUAL if parent InterfaceIPv6 MO has more than one child AddressIPv6 MO.
If IKE, encapsulation of parent InterfaceIPv6 MO must refer to IpsecTunnel MO.
If IKE, only one AddressIPv6 MO must exist within same Router MO.
If IKE, parent InterfaceIPv6 MO must not refer to IpsecTunnel MO referred by InterfaceIPv4 MO.
If AUTO, AUTO_NO_DHCPV6 or AUTO_DHCPV6, encapsulation of parent InterfaceIPv6 MO must refer to MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, LagPort, or Bridge.
If AUTO, AUTO_NO_DHCPV6 or AUTO_DHCPV6, no other AddressIPv6 MO with configurationMode AUTO, AUTO_NO_DHCPV6 or AUTO_DHCPV6 must exist within same Router MO.
If AUTO, AUTO_NO_DHCPV6 or AUTO_DHCPV6, bfdProfile attribute in parent InterfaceIPv6 MO must not be set.

Parameter Description: DHCP Unique Identifier (DUID).
Dependencies: Only applicable if configurationMode is AUTO or AUTO_DHCPV6.

Parameter Description:
Whether DUID is based on link-layer address and time (DUID_LLT), or on serial number using vendor specific option (DUID_EN or DUID_EN_SERIAL_NUMBER ).

DUID is assigned to each DHCPv6 client and server. Used by DHCPv6 server to identify clients for selection of configuration parameters.
Must be unique globally across all DHCPv6 clients and servers.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
Only applicable if configurationMode is AUTO or AUTO_DHCPV6.
DUID_EN_SERIAL_NUMBER can only be set in max one MO instance in node.

Parameter Description:
Selection of primary or secondary IP address.

Must be set to true for exactly one of AddressIPv6 MOs that are children of specific InterfaceIPv6 MO.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Used IP address.

If configurationMode is MANUAL, this attribute has same content as address attribute.
If configurationMode is other than MANUAL, retrieved address is shown in this attribute.
Label for free use.

Reference to AclIpv6 MO applied in egress direction.

If this attribute is empty, no ACL filtering will take place in egress direction.

Dependencies:
This attribute can only be set if encapsulation refers to EthernetPort MO, VlanPort MO, or Bridge MO.
The referred AclIpv6 MO must belong to same Router MO, and must have at least one AclEntryIpv6 MO as child.

Parameter Description:
Reference to AclIpv6 MO applied in ingress direction.

This attribute can only be set if encapsulation refers to EthernetPort MO, VlanPort MO, or Bridge MO.

Parameter Description: Reference to BfdProfile MO containing BFD parameters used for BFD sessions from this interface.

Dependencies:
If bfdStaticRoutes is set to ENABLED, this attribute must be set.
If configurationMode in AddressIPv6 MO is set to AUTO, AUTO_NO_DHCPV6 or AUTO_DHCPV6, this attribute must not be set.
Referred BfdProfile MO must belong to Transport MO or same Router MO.
If loopback is set, this attribute must not be set.

Parameter Description:
Enables or disables BFD monitoring of static route nexthops on this interface.

This attribute works in conjunction with bfdProfile.
To enable BFD monitoring for this interface, bfdStaticRoutes must be set to ENABLED and bfdProfile must be set.
If BFD monitoring is enabled, all static routing nexthops on subnets of this IP interface are monitored, unless explicitly disabled on PeerIPv6 MO or NextHop MO.
BFD monitoring of static routes for a specific peer can be enabled on PeerIPv6 MO even if this attribute is DISABLED.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
If this attribute is set to ENABLED, bfdProfile must be set.
This attribute can only be ENABLED if encapsulation refers to EthernetPort MO, VlanPort MO or Bridge MO.

Parameter Description:
Whether UDP datagrams with checksum zero are accepted for processing by higher layers.

Valid for UDP datagrams containing GTP-U messages, received on this interface.
Other kinds of UDP datagrams with checksum zero are always dropped.
Set to true increases vulnerability and risk of data corruption.
Only to be set to true if network conditions, such as peer nodes lack proper support for UDP checksum calculation.

Only supported for RAN Compute Group 4 and 5.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.
Deprecated: Since 24.Q2. Planned to be removed.

Parameter Description: Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value for Neighbor Discovery Protocol (NDP).
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if encapsulation refers to EthernetPort MO, VlanPort MO, or Bridge MO.

Parameter Description:
DSCP to PCP map used for marking DSCP tagged packets with PCP value. Packets marked are either host originated or routed into QoS domain.

If empty, DSCP values are mapped to PCP values according to following:

pcp0 = 0
pcp1   (empty)
pcp2 = 10,12,14
pcp3 = 18,20,22
pcp4 = 8,16,26,28
pcp5 = 34,36,38,46
pcp6 = 32,40,48
pcp7 = 51,54
Dependencies:
Attribute can only be set if encapsulation refers to MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, or Bridge.
DSCP to PCP map is not relevant if loopback is set or encapsulation is IpsecTunnel MO.

Parameter Description: Reference to underlying encapsulation, which can be MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, Bridge, IpsecTunnel or LagPort.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.
Dependencies:
One of encapsulation or loopback must be set, but not both at same time.
Only one InterfaceIPv6 MO can refer to same MO.
Cannot refer to EthernetPort MO referred by VlanPort MO.
Cannot refer to VlanPort MO referred by Bridge MO.
Referred IpsecTunnel MO must belong to same Router MO.
If InterfaceIPv4 MO and InterfaceIPv6 MO refer to same MO in encapsulation, they must belong to same Router MO.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, none of aclIngress, aclEgress or egressQosMarking can be set.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, bfdStaticRoutes must be DISABLED.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, configurationMode for child AddressIPv6 MO must not be AUTO, AUTO_NO_DHCPV6 or AUTO_DHCPV6.
If attribute refers to IpsecTunnel MO, the only relevant configuration attributes are mtu and routesHoldDownTimer.
If attribute does not refer to MO type EthernetPort, VlanPort, LagPort or Bridge, maximum one AddressIPv6 MO can be configured for this MO.

Parameter Description:
DSCP to DSCP map used for remarking ingress DSCP tagged packets.

Empty string means no re-marking is done.
This attribute is used to fix specific issues within QoS domain and should most often be empty.

It can refer to DscpDscpMap MO.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if encapsulation refers to EthernetPort MO, VlanPort MO, or Bridge MO.

Parameter Description: Value component of the RDN.
Specifies if interface is IP Loopback Interface.

If set, none of aclIngress, aclEgress or egressQosMarking can be set.

Parameter Description:
Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU).

This attribute is not relevant if loopback is set.

Parameter Description:
Timeout value for neighbor entry.

Configures how long remote IPv6 node is considered reachable after reachability confirmation event has occurred.
Value of zero means that entries are never cleared from cache.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if encapsulation refers to EthernetPort MO, VlanPort MO, or Bridge MO.

Parameter Description: Interval between retransmitted neighbor solicitation messages on interface.
Dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if encapsulation refers to EthernetPort MO, VlanPort MO, or Bridge MO.

Parameter Description: The operational state.
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

Hold-down timer used for static routes that use this interface.

If attribute is set, hold-down timer starts when conditions for static route is available and fulfilled.
When hold-down timer expires, route is available.

If attribute is empty, there is no hold-down timer for routes and existing route over this interface is available without additional delay.

Attribute must not be set in case there is no alternative route.

This attribute does not affect operational state of interface.
Dependencies:
If InterfaceIPv4 and InterfaceIPv6 refer to same MO in encapsulation, they must have same routesHoldDownTimer value.
This attribute is not relevant if loopback is set.

Parameter Description: If set for loopback interface, operationalState and availabilityStatus from referred tunnel interface is inherited.
Dependencies:
Only relevant if attribute loopback is set.
Can only refer to InterfaceIPv6 MO within same Router MO that has IpsecTunnel MO as encapsulation reference.

Parameter Description: Label for free use.

1 bit managed address autoconfiguration flag.

If false, address autoconfiguration is not available via DHCPv6.
If true, address autoconfiguration is available via DHCPv6.
If true, otherConfig is redundant and can be ignored because DHCPv6 will return all available configuration information.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: Maximum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from interface.

Minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from interface.

If MaxRtrAdvInterval >= 9 seconds, its value is 0.33 * MaxRtrAdvInterval, otherwise value is 0.75 * MaxRtrAdvInterval.

1-bit other configuration flag.

If true, other configuration information, excluding address, is available via DHCPv6.
If false, other configuration information is not available via DHCPv6.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.
Whether or not router sends periodic Router Advertisements and responds to Router Solicitations.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

The value component of the RDN.
Label for free use.

IPv6 default hop limit.

Default value inserted into hop limit field of IPv6 header of datagrams, originated from all Router MOs, whenever hop limit value is not supplied by transport layer protocol.

Changed value takes effect on existing GPRS Tunneling Protocol paths and UDP sessions after node restart.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute too low might cause total loss of traffic or loss of connectivity to the node.

Parameter Description: Number of seconds between PMTU probing.

Parameter Description: The value component of the RDN.

Specifies network type of this interface.

For some settings, this attribute changes OSPF behavior of electing designated router, sending of database descriptions, and content of LSAs.

Enables passive mode on this interface.

If this attribute is set to true, this interface does not participate in OSPF, and does not send routing updates or establish adjacencies while interface is still advertised to other routers.

Router dead interval specifies time after which neighbor is declared as unavailable, if no hello packet is received during this interval.

This value is advertised in hello packets from router and must be multiple of helloInterval. Same value must be set on all interfaces in network.
Dependencies: routerDeadInterval must be greater than helloInterval.

Parameter Description:
Router priority used on this interface.

This priority used to determine OSPF Designated Router (DR) for the network this interface is on. If two routers attempt to become the DR, router with higher router priority becomes DR. If router priority is same for two routers, router with higher router ID takes precedence. Only routers with nonzero router priority values are eligible to become designated or backup designated router.

Parameter Description:

Adjust route-calculation timers using exponential back-off delays. This attribute, together with maxHoldTime, configures minimum and maximum delay time between receipt of topology change and calculation of SPF.
The value component of the RDN.

Specifies the reference bandwidth used by for automatic interface cost calculation indicated by the attribute operCost in class Interface.

This calculation divides the reference bandwidth by the interface bandwidth. If adminCost is set in class Interface then no automatic cost calculation is done and the administratively set cost is used for that interface.

Specified the value for the router ID to be used as a fixed ID for the OSPFv2 instance.

If the OSPFv2 router ID is not configured, OSPF chooses the lowest loopback interface address. If there are no loopback interfaces then the lowest interface address is used. When reset to empty OSPFv2 reverts to automatic router ID assignment. The OSPFv2 router process is automatically restarted when the router ID is changed.
Change Take Effect: The OSPFv2 process is restarted. All OSPFv2 routes are removed from the routing table and traffic is impacted until OSPFv2 has converged.

The value component of the RDN.

The averaging weight factor used by the RED drop mechanism.

The weight factor is used when calculating the average queue length and it is represented as the parameter n in the following formula:

average_queue_length = old_average_queue_length * (1 - 2^-n) + current_queue_length * 2^-n, where 2^-n means: 2 raised to the power of n.

The averaging weight factor controls the sensitivity to bursts and rapid changes in the current queue length. Setting the averaging weight factor too high causes the average queue length to respond too slowly to changes in the current queue size, thus not reacting to congestion. Setting the averaging weight factor too low causes the average queue length to respond too fast to changes in the actual queue size, thus overreacting to bursts and dropping packets unnecessarily.

Guideline: The egress bandwidth and the average packet size should influence the choice of this attribute value.

The maximum threshold for RED.

When the average queue length is above the minimum threshold, RED starts dropping packets. The rate of packet drop increases linearly as the average queue length increases until the average queue length reaches the maximum threshold.

When the average queue length is above the maximum threshold, all packets are dropped.

The minimum threshold for RED.

When the average queue length is above the minimum threshold, RED starts dropping packets. The rate of packet drop increases linearly as the average queue length increases until the average queue length reaches the maximum threshold.

When the average queue length is above the maximum threshold, all packets are dropped.
Dependencies: minThreshold should be less than or equal to maxThreshold.

Parameter Description:
Enables/disables BFD monitoring of static routes with this peer as netxthop.

If set to ENABLED, BFD monitoring is enabled for static routes where address of NextHop MO is equal to address of this PeerIPv4 MO.
If bfdProfile is set on this MO, BFD session uses parameters configured in referred BfdProfile MO.
If bfdProfile is not set on this MO, BFD session uses parameters configured in BfdProfile MO referred from InterfaceIPv4 MO bfdProfile attribute.
If bfdProfile is not set on this MO and neither InterfaceIPv4 MO, BFD monitoring is not enabled.

If set to DISABLED, BFD monitoring is disabled for static routes where address of NextHop MO is equal to address of this PeerIPv4 MO. This overrides bfdStaticRoutes attribute on InterfaceIPv4 MO.

If not set, BFD monitoring can still be enabled towards this peer by setting bfdStaticRoutes attribute to ENABLED on InterfaceIPv4 MO. bfdProfile on this PeerIPv4 MO is in this case not used.

If BFD monitoring is enabled, all static routes with this peer as nexthop are monitored, unless explicitly disabled per NextHop MO.

BFD monitoring of PBR nexthops is not controlled by this attribute.
If this attribute is set to ENABLED (that is BFD monitoring for static routes is enabled for this peer) and bfdProfile is set in this PeerIPv4 MO, BfdProfile MO referred from this PeerIPv4 MO is used also for PBR nexthops.
Disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

Parameter Description: Defines the operational state.
Current number of BCHs (Broadcast CHannels) in the cell. The BCH is a fixed rate point to multi point downlink channel, used to convey system information in the whole coverage area of the cell.
Current number of PCCPCHs (Primary Common Control Physical CHannel) in the cell. This downlink physical channel carries the transport channel BCH.

Current number of PCPICHs (Primary Common Pilot CHannel) in the cell. This is a fixed rate downlink physical channel that carries a predefined symbol sequence. PCPICH is used as phase reference for other downlink physical channels. No transport channel is carried on PCPICH.

Current number of PSCHs (Primary Synchronization CHannel) in the cell. This is a downlink physical channel used to find the scrambling code of the cell. The PSCH transmits the Primary Synchronization Code, which is the same for every cell in the system and known by each UE. It is sent simultaneously with the transmission on the SSCH. No transport channel is carried on PSCH.

Current number of SCPICHs (Secondary Common Pilot CHannel) in the cell. This is a fixed rate downlink physical channel that carries a predefined symbol sequence. SCPICH is used as phase reference for other downlink physical channels on a second antenna branch in certain MIMO configurations. No transport channel is carried on SCPICH.

Current number of SSCHs (Secondary Synchronization CHannel) in the cell. This is a downlink physical channel used to find the scrambling code of the cell. SSCH transmits a sequence of 15 codes, simultaneously with transmission on the PSCH. By identifying the sequence the UE can derive the primary scrambling code of the cell. No transport channel is carried on SSCH.
The value component of the RDN.
Total number of Communication Contexts allocated in the Node B.

This is a sequence of 16 weight factors associated with the 16 Scheduling Priority Indicators (SPIs). The weight factors represent the relative bandwidth between users assigned to the different scheduling priorities. The special value 0xFFFE (65534) is used to represent infinity. When eulSchedulingWeight is set to infinity, users with higher SPI values have absolute priority over those with lower SPI.

Parameter Description: Determines required amount of data in MC PQ data buffer. Used to re-activate secondary serving HS-DSCH cell for UE in MC mode when it is deactivated. If multiple MC-PQs belong to same UE any data buffer can contain required amount of data to perform re-activation.

Parameter Description: Parameter determining the required time of empty multi-carrier (MC) priority queue (PQ) data buffer in order to deactivating the secondary serving HS-DSCH cell for a UE in MC mode. In the case of multiple MC-PQs belonging to the same UE all data buffers should be empty during the required time to perform the deactivation.

Parameter Description: E-HICH (for serving and non serving) have fixed power relative CPICH power. Parameter Description: Offset to be used in E-HICH power.

The uplink interference contribution from other cells is estimated in the load estimator, but is never allowed to go below the value of this parameter. The unit is load factor, that is, interference power from other cells divided by total interference power.

Maximum number of serving EUL users allowed per cell.

Alarm Licensed Capacity Exceeded is given if:

         administrativeState=UNLOCKED and
         maxNumEulUsers higher than the upper limit and
         Emergency Unlock is not activated
Where upper limit is: 
         License key value if Licensed capacity 'Number of EUL users' is enabled (see licenseState in MO CapacityState) or 
         default value (maximum 4 EUL users) if license key is disabled.

During Emergency Unlock, maximum 128 EUL users are allowed in each cell.
Change Take Effect: Increase takes effect immediately. Decrease takes gradual effect; existing users are allowed to terminate normally until the new limit is reached. No new users are allowed until below limit.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of HSDPA users allowed per cell.

Alarm Licensed Capacity Exceeded is given if:

         administrativeState=UNLOCKED and
         maxNumHsdpaUsers higher than the upper limit and
         Emergency Unlock is not activated
Where upper limit is: 
         License key value if Licensed capacity 'Number of HSDPA Users per cell' is enabled (see licenseState in MO CapacityState) or 
         default value (maximum 16 HSDPA users) if license key is disabled.

During Emergency Unlock, maximum 128 HSDPA users are allowed in each cell.
Change Take Effect: Increase takes effect immediately. Decrease takes gradual effect; existing users are allowed to terminate normally until the new limit is reached. No new users are allowed until below limit.

Parameter Description:
Maximum number of HS-PDSCH codes allowed per cell.

Alarm Licensed Capacity Exceeded is given if:

         administrativeState=UNLOCKED and
         maxNumHsPdschCodes higher than the upper limit and
         Emergency Unlock is not activated
Where upper limit is: 
         License key value if Licensed capacity 'Number of HSDPA Codes per cell' is enabled (see licenseState in MO CapacityState) or 
         default value (maximum 5 HS-PDSCH codes) if license key is disabled.

During Emergency Unlock, maximum 15 HS-PDSCH codes are allowed in each cell.
Change Take Effect: Increase takes effect immediately. Decrease takes effect gracefully (if more codes than the new limit are setup by RNC, the new limit will not apply until the RNC has reconfigured the physical shared channel so that less codes than the new limit are used).

Parameter Description:
Activation delay time for secondary UL carrier in serving Node B. 

This delay ensures that RNC and UE have time to measure secondary carrier before secondary UL carrier activation in serving Node B. This will mitigate interference to neighboring cells from secondary carrier in heterogeneous network case. Delay applies to all EUL Multi-Carrier users with their primary serving E-DCH cell in this cell.

Set to 20 (1000 ms) for cells that act as primary E-DCH cell, when neighboring cell on corresponding secondary carrier exists, and no corresponding neighboring cell on primary carrier is available. Otherwise, set to 0.

Parameter Description:
Locks the noise floor level for RoT calculation to the given value, when set. The locked level is shown by the attribute eulLockedNoiseFloor.

Attribute is empty -> The noise floor level is not locked.
Value = -1 -> The noise floor level is locked to current level.

If the cell is setup, the value -1 locks the noise floor to the current estimated noise floor level.
If the cell is not setup, the value -1 locks the noise floor to the value given by eulThermalLevelPrior at next cell setup.

The level used for the locked noise floor will be lost at next cell deletion.
